ed in Europe (06:19)  \n    - This structure covers different time zones and allows team members to cover vacations or workload spikes without service disruption  \n    - Igor brings broad content experience, enhancing strategic input for the account  \n    - Baylee emphasized the benefit of having multiple points of contact for consistent account support (06:40)  \n    - This setup aims to improve client satisfaction through reliable availability\n\n## **Next Steps and Follow-Up Commitments**\n\nClear follow-up actions focus on pricing adjustment and competitive positioning.\n\n- Baylee will investigate competitive pricing models and consult with Justin to formulate a revised offer for Gil (05:34)  \n    - Gil will attempt to provide names of competitors for benchmarking via Slack to support this effort (07:22)  \n    - A follow-up meeting is planned within one to two weeks to review the pricing proposal and discuss continuation (05:34)  \n    - This timeline ensures swift response to market pressures and signals commitment to maintaining the partnership  \n    - Transparent communication around costs and service scope will help realign expectations and secure future collaboration","outline":null,"keywords":["podcast production","pricing strategy","AI podcast tools","Riverside software","content strategy","download statistics"],"overview":"- **Podcast Success:** Over 10,000 downloads in 30 days show strong audience engagement and interest in current themes.  \n- **Competitive Pricing Pressure:** Offers around $500 for four episodes prompt urgent review of pricing strategy to avoid client churn.  \n- **Competitors Spotlighted:** Riverside offers similar services at lower prices, highlighting the need for competitive adjustments.  \n- **Account Management Improvements:** A dual-point contact model enhances continuity and client satisfaction with diverse team availability.  \n- **Next Steps Outlined:** Baylee to explore competitive pricing; follow-up meeting in one to two weeks to discuss proposals.  \n- **Benchmarking Support:** Gil will share competitor names via Slack to assist in formulating a revised pricing strategy.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nConnect with Justin to discuss pricing adjustments and more competitive service offerings (03:23)\nFollow up with Gil in the next one to two weeks to review progress on pricing and service options (05:34)\nCoordinate with Igor to manage Gil’s account collaboratively and ensure coverage across time zones (06:37)\nCollect competitor names and pricing details from Gil via Slack for benchmarking (07:31)\n\n**Gil**\nLocate and share competitor podcast production pricing info with Baylee via Slack (07:31)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"d7749253-a1fc-4d3c-b401-2ef0d449779f","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
