WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '52b3ee0f-cbad-4031-a387-79ecb54874fb',
    '2026-01-30 16:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KFNT5BJFME7FKPRE4D4XKCNX',
    'AQI // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"bwillans","Colin Costigan","Guille Santana"}'::text[],
    1232,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89786281993?pwd=li2lwrSFpmITXPKEdOBBgaXPwh8ONO.1',
    '{"id":"01KFNT5BJFME7FKPRE4D4XKCNX","title":"AQI // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Data Integrity and Contact Management**\n\nThe team confirmed a significant cleanup of contact data, reducing duplicates and improving accuracy across systems.\n\n- **Salesforce contact lists for WIMS and Aquarius dropped from 17,000 to 3,500 after deduplication** (03:16)  \n    - Colin explained the drop was due to multiple duplicate records tied to legacy systems.  \n    - Barb noted this matched her experience with Salesforce showing repeated entries causing scoring confusion.  \n    - This cleanup improves marketing contact quality, reducing wasted outreach and improving targeting precision.  \n    - The inconsistent product naming in Deskpro (e.g., \"WIMS Rio,\" \"Rio,\" \"WIMS Classic\") was flagged for cleanup to avoid segmentation errors.  \n\n- **Lead scoring is currently in testing but may require a custom module for greater control and override ability** (07:20)  \n    - Colin suggested building a custom lead scoring property to replace HubSpot''s native system for better granularity.  \n    - Barb shared manual scoring efforts revealed gaps in reflecting true engagement for leads, highlighting the need to preserve historical activity.  \n    - The legacy integration issues cause confusing and conflicting scoring data, as discussed by Colin and Barb.  \n    - Syncing approach prioritizes Salesforce updates pushing to HubSpot, ensuring Salesforce is the system of record for contacts.  \n\n## **Marketing Automation and Webinar Management**\n\nWebinar content has been successfully transitioned to on-demand format with minor website updates required.\n\n- **Both Salesforce and HubSpot are fully synced, enabling automatic contact updates and interaction tracking** (11:36)  \n    - Guille confirmed the contact sync is stable, supporting seamless marketing and sales workflows.  \n    - Barb updated the webinar page slug from \"upcoming\" to \"on demand\" to reflect the new webinar format, fixing visibility issues.  \n    - Redirects from old URLs to new ones are handled automatically, avoiding broken links or loss of traffic.  \n    - Two-factor authentication issues on WordPress are being addressed to improve independent content management access.  \n\n- **Lead submission data showed multiple duplications from a single rep, requiring manual review** (14:03)  \n    - Barb identified 14 leads from one rep with many duplicated entries but varying comments, indicating possible data quality challenges.  \n    - Colin and Barb agreed to review and clean this data to ensure accurate lead counts and reporting.  \n\n## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Strategy Development**\n\nThe team is preparing to launch targeted ABM campaigns leveraging personalized automated content to drive demos and engagement.\n\n- **Colin introduced an ABM offer concept with personalized competitive intelligence reports to attract prospects** (16:14)  \n    - The offer collects minimal vital data points (e.g., website, role, competitors) to avoid overwhelming prospects.  \n    - Reports generated include executive summaries, competitor comparisons, and action recommendations, delivered within 45 seconds.  \n    - The output is branded to Aquarius Informatics and designed to guide prospects toward scheduling demo calls.  \n    - This approach leverages recent AI advances to quickly produce high-value, personalized marketing assets.  \n\n- **Barb plans initial meetings with key contacts Eric and Safia to align on ABM rollout before involving the wider team** (17:20)  \n    - The goal is to familiarize stakeholders with ABM concepts and finalize offer details before a broader campaign kickoff.  \n    - A collaborative brainstorming session is scheduled for next week, with a possible ABM launch targeted for the following Friday.  \n    - This phased approach supports better buy-in and ensures readiness before full execution.  \n\n## **Process Improvements and System Integration**\n\nThe team is addressing legacy system complexity and improving workflow transparency for marketing and sales alignment.\n\n- **Legacy marketing and CRM systems have created a ''Frankenstein'' environment with overlapping scores and data inconsistencies** (09:28)  \n    - Colin and Barb acknowledged the complexity built up over 10 years of integrations, causing duplicate records and conflicting lead scores.  \n    - The plan to build a custom lead scoring module is a key step to regain clarity and reduce confusion for sales reps.  \n    - Syncing updates from Salesforce to HubSpot ensures data consistency and reduces manual reconciliation efforts.  \n    - Cleaning product naming conventions in Deskpro is critical to maintain segmentation integrity and streamline reporting.  \n\n- **Operational improvements include enabling public access to Salesforce reports for self-service adjustments** (03:58)  \n    - Barb will adjust original Salesforce reports as needed and coordinate with Kyle for building classic lists.  \n    - This shift empowers marketing to manage data quality without overburdening technical teams.  \n    - Continuous cleanup and standardization efforts are planned to improve data hygiene and support future automation.  \n\n## **Timelines and Next Steps**\n\nClear deadlines and ownership were assigned to maintain momentum on key initiatives.\n\n- **Lead scoring refinement and custom module development are planned for Q2, with priority on granular control** (07:40)  \n    - Barb will coordinate with Colin and Demir to finalize workflows and custom properties.  \n    - This timeline aligns with planned resource leveling to support expanded marketing efforts.  \n\n- **ABM ideation and offer development will progress asynchronously with scheduled meetings next week** (16:14)  \n    - Barb will hold initial kickoff meetings with Eric and Safia to confirm ABM readiness.  \n    - The broader team will join for brainstorming and campaign planning the week after to target a launch by the following Friday.  \n\n- **Data cleanup tasks such as duplicate lead reviews and product naming standardization are ongoing with shared ownership** (14:27)  \n    - Barb and Colin will collaborate on validating lead submissions and cleaning inconsistent naming conventions.  \n    - Kyle is involved in list building and ensuring Deskpro data integrity.  \n\nThis coordinated effort addresses data quality, marketing automation, and strategic growth through ABM with clear timelines and ownership.","outline":null,"keywords":["Data Deduplication","Lead Scoring","Salesforce HubSpot Sync","Account-Based Marketing","Webinar On-Demand","Competitive Intelligence Report"],"overview":"- **Contact Data Cleanup:** Salesforce contact lists reduced from 17,000 to 3,500, improving accuracy and targeting.  \n- **Lead Scoring Development:** Custom module planned for Q2 to enhance lead scoring precision and integrate with Salesforce.  \n- **Webinar Transition:** On-demand webinars launched with synced systems for seamless contact updates and interaction tracking.  \n- **ABM Campaign Plans:** Personalized competitive reports to attract leads; initial stakeholder meetings scheduled for alignment.  \n- **Process Improvements:** Legacy system issues are being addressed to ensure better data quality and streamlined workflows.  \n- **Ongoing Data Cleanup:** Continuous review of duplicate leads and product naming standardization to maintain accurate reporting.","action_items":"\n**Barb Willans**\nAdjust original Salesforce reports to build and share updated Wims Classic contact list, confirming data cleanliness (03:54)\nReview “hack” campaign lead duplicates, verify distinct leads, and report findings to the team (14:27)\nMeet with Eric and Safia for ABM kickoff to familiarize them with the approach and gather initial insights (16:20)\nProvide updates and follow up on ABM ideation via email or next meetings (17:45)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nSupport Barb and team in building custom lead scoring module with workflows allowing overrides and granular control (07:20)\nAssist in cleanup and standardization advice regarding inconsistent product brand naming to improve data integrity (04:38)\nShare examples and walkthroughs of ABM automated offer tools and competitive intelligence report functionality to guide upcoming Wims and Aquarius campaigns (16:14)\nCoordinate internally and with Barb asynchronously on ABM ideation and offer development, aiming for readiness by next Friday (16:20)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nMonitor and troubleshoot 2FA issues restricting form and WordPress access, escalating if necessary (12:03)\nVerify hack campaign lead discrepancies and coordinate with Barb on lead duplicates clean-up (14:03)\n"},"duration":20.530000686645508,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"bwillans"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Guille Santana"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Banks, when I. I drove in last night, I''m like, holy.","index":0,"end_time":2.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, it''s.","index":1,"end_time":3.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2.96,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s a lot.","index":2,"end_time":4.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.6,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"How much did you guys get?","index":3,"end_time":5.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.32,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We got 13 inches.","index":4,"end_time":6.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A lot.","index":5,"end_time":8.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.92,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":6,"end_time":9.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":7,"end_time":9.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.44,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, we haven''t had that much in like 10 years, I think.","index":8,"end_time":12.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, wow.","index":9,"end_time":13.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.04,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, we got more than that here.","index":10,"end_time":15.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.8,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But just judging by the snow.","index":11,"end_time":18.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.24,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Banks and my sister, who had to shovel it all week.","index":12,"end_time":20.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.04,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But.","index":13,"end_time":21.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":20.92,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":14,"end_time":22.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.68,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And it''s still, like, it''s just really cold.","index":15,"end_time":24.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I like the cold.","index":16,"end_time":25.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":24.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But.","index":17,"end_time":25.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.04,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":18,"end_time":26.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.93,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Woke up to minus 24.","index":19,"end_time":27.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":26.21,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":20,"end_time":30.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":29.93,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"No, thank you.","index":21,"end_time":31.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":30.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, thank you on that.","index":22,"end_time":32.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":31.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Barb, before we get started, I have some stuff I want to show you.","index":23,"end_time":35.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":32.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sure.","index":24,"end_time":36.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.01,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Oh.","index":25,"end_time":39.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":38.97,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So Marley just turned one on Wednesday, so we got our set of golf clubs.","index":26,"end_time":46.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is her eating some food and looking to share.","index":27,"end_time":50.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, she''s so cute.","index":28,"end_time":53.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":51.86,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Playing in her first big snow.","index":29,"end_time":56.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She love it.","index":30,"end_time":57.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":56.58,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Oh, she walks.","index":31,"end_time":61.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.38,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"She walks, she walks.","index":32,"end_time":63.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":61.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s got five teeth now.","index":33,"end_time":64.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s talking up a storm.","index":34,"end_time":67.299,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, my.","index":35,"end_time":69.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.14,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s her at her actual.","index":36,"end_time":70.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, her princess dress.","index":37,"end_time":72.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":70.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s so cute.","index":38,"end_time":74.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72.98,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We stole the right baby out of the hospital.","index":39,"end_time":76.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":75.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":40,"end_time":77.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.82,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Look at that face.","index":41,"end_time":78.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":77.86,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Oh, she''s adorable.","index":42,"end_time":82.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":80.85,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"She''s really cute.","index":43,"end_time":83.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":82.61,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":44,"end_time":84.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We have her.","index":45,"end_time":84.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":84.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Her one year appointment today, so.","index":46,"end_time":86.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Dad.","index":47,"end_time":87.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":87.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Dad''s not excited.","index":48,"end_time":88.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s gonna have to get some shots.","index":49,"end_time":89.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":88.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m probably gonna cry more than she is.","index":50,"end_time":91.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":89.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably.","index":51,"end_time":91.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":91.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":52,"end_time":92.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":91.73,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":53,"end_time":93.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.53,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I was asked my mom, when did I walk?","index":54,"end_time":96.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":94.69,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And she goes, oh, you didn''t even bother till you were like 15 months old.","index":55,"end_time":99.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":96.53,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"People just brought you stuff.","index":56,"end_time":100.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.69,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You''re the laziest baby ever.","index":57,"end_time":103.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":101.57,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s such a spectrum for people like, they.","index":58,"end_time":106.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think it''s really a concern until like, 18 months if they''re not.","index":59,"end_time":110.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Yeah.","index":60,"end_time":111.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":110.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":61,"end_time":112.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.03,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"My parents are medical people.","index":62,"end_time":114.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":113.07,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They didn''t care.","index":63,"end_time":115.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":114.59,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They''re just like, I don''t know.","index":64,"end_time":116.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.23,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You seem to be moving your limbs.","index":65,"end_time":118.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":116.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":66,"end_time":118.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right.","index":67,"end_time":120.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":120.43,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Sorry it took Derailleur''s, but I figured.","index":68,"end_time":122.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":120.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, thank you.","index":69,"end_time":123.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":122.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s a great start.","index":70,"end_time":123.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":123.19,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":71,"end_time":124.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":123.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right.","index":72,"end_time":125.669,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":125.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yay.","index":73,"end_time":126.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":125.669,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s.","index":74,"end_time":126.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":126.15,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Let''s get rolling.","index":75,"end_time":127.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":126.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yay, superstar.","index":76,"end_time":129.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yay.","index":77,"end_time":129.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":129.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yes.","index":78,"end_time":130.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":130.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I know, Barb.","index":79,"end_time":131.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":130.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s.","index":80,"end_time":131.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":131.47,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"She''s putting me to shame.","index":81,"end_time":132.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s like, so much faster.","index":82,"end_time":133.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":132.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You are quick.","index":83,"end_time":135.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":134.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Alrighty, the agenda for today, we''re going over the questions that you sent over this morning.","index":84,"end_time":145.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":139.36,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":85,"end_time":146.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":146.32,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Talking about the salesforce sync on demand webinars and the account executive workflow.","index":86,"end_time":153.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":147.12,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":87,"end_time":154.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So you asked us when the contact list for Wims and Aquarius were moved into HubSpot.","index":88,"end_time":164.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":157.12,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"You notice we lost about 50% of the original count.","index":89,"end_time":168.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":164.49,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And if.","index":90,"end_time":170.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":169.93,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And why was that like if that was bad email data?","index":91,"end_time":174.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":171.13,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Colleen, correct me if I''m wrong, but these were duplicates, right?","index":92,"end_time":178.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":175.45,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":93,"end_time":179.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m pulling up the table now.","index":94,"end_time":181.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Barb.","index":95,"end_time":182.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":181.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we exported all of those lists and it was about like 17,000 records.","index":96,"end_time":187.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":182.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then when I pulled them into one list just by their email address and, and hit dedupe, it dropped to like 3,500.","index":97,"end_time":194.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":187.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that''s.","index":98,"end_time":197,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":196,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You know what, that''s good to know that.","index":99,"end_time":198.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":100,"end_time":199.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":198.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it, it.","index":101,"end_time":200.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":199.28,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That tracks for every time I go into Salesforce, there''s three of the same person and trying to find the marketo scoring.","index":102,"end_time":207.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":200.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It was a nightmare.","index":103,"end_time":208.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":207.4,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that''s what happened there.","index":104,"end_time":210.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":208.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":105,"end_time":211.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":211.28,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Total makes sense.","index":106,"end_time":212.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":211.76,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Cool.","index":107,"end_time":213.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":213.04,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":108,"end_time":215.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":215.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so then your question was 0 to 90% opportunity contacts.","index":109,"end_time":220.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":110,"end_time":220.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it was all just from those reports.","index":111,"end_time":221.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we do want to expand, I mean, you guys have the room on the marketing contact side.","index":112,"end_time":225.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":221.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":113,"end_time":226.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.59,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":114,"end_time":227.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then whatever.","index":115,"end_time":228.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you need us to build the Wims Classic list or if Kyle''s just going to build it and share it with us, then totally.","index":116,"end_time":233.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":117,"end_time":234.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Do you want me to go into the original Salesforce reports and I can just.","index":118,"end_time":237.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.55,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I can adjust them?","index":119,"end_time":238.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":237.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, they''re public now, so.","index":120,"end_time":240.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":238.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, whatever.","index":121,"end_time":241.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll do that.","index":122,"end_time":243.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''ll do that.","index":123,"end_time":244.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":243.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Let you know if I have any trouble.","index":124,"end_time":245.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":244.55,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I shouldn''t.","index":125,"end_time":246.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then the Classic list is coming from Deskpro.","index":126,"end_time":249.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It seems to be like a carefully held secret.","index":127,"end_time":253.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":250.64,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I don''t know why, but yeah, one note there is.","index":128,"end_time":257.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":253.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We called it out last week or the week before, but there.","index":129,"end_time":260.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":258.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It just seems like inconsistent the way that product is mentioned, like the product brand column.","index":130,"end_time":266.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":261.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s like WIMS Rio and then there''s just Rio and then there''s WIMS Classic and some of them have spaces, some of them don''t.","index":131,"end_time":272.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":267.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we just.","index":132,"end_time":273.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Our recommendation is to clean that up and standardize it.","index":133,"end_time":275.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":273.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I don''t want to break your guys structure over there.","index":134,"end_time":278.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":135,"end_time":279.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.88,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, Kyle did mention that.","index":136,"end_time":281.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.6,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"He said it''s.","index":137,"end_time":283.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s a bit of a.","index":138,"end_time":284.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.4,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Bit of a Frankenstein in there, so.","index":139,"end_time":286.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.8,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":140,"end_time":287.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":286.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":141,"end_time":288.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":287.6,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":142,"end_time":288.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.48,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right.","index":143,"end_time":289.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then going through lead scoring, so were you.","index":144,"end_time":292.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":289.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think in your email.","index":145,"end_time":293.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Remind me.","index":146,"end_time":294.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve been back to back for a couple hours.","index":147,"end_time":295.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Me and Gay both have.","index":148,"end_time":296.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sure.","index":149,"end_time":296.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":296.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I know we built out the lead scoring and it''s pretty much like in testing right now to see how it''s interacting, but I think you mentioned that you were maybe working on something else.","index":150,"end_time":305.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":297.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll just share it with you.","index":151,"end_time":307.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Nothing to do right now.","index":152,"end_time":308.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.58,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"The BDRs have what they need, so I''m not concerned about it.","index":153,"end_time":311.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":308.3,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s.","index":154,"end_time":312.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.94,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"There''s two things, so.","index":155,"end_time":314.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":312.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":156,"end_time":315.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":315.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you drop your screen share so Barb can.","index":157,"end_time":317.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":315.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":158,"end_time":317.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":317.38,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Great.","index":159,"end_time":318.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.34,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":160,"end_time":319.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.7,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":161,"end_time":319.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.38,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":162,"end_time":320.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, So can you see my spreadsheet here?","index":163,"end_time":337.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yes.","index":164,"end_time":338.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":337.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":165,"end_time":338.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So what I did and this was for this just one example, I knew for January we weren''t there yet.","index":166,"end_time":344.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":339.23,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And that''s fine.","index":167,"end_time":344.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":344.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like it was a good exercise for me to go through.","index":168,"end_time":346.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":344.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But what I did is I took the scoring wheel that we gave to you.","index":169,"end_time":350.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And for example, this is January 15th, so I pulled everything from Zoom.","index":170,"end_time":355.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I had originally used constant contact to send emails out from.","index":171,"end_time":361.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Then I went into.","index":172,"end_time":362.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.37,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Well, and also people came in from LinkedIn and then so all of this was quite manual.","index":173,"end_time":368.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":362.49,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then, you know, you set up the HubSpot forms on the website, et cetera.","index":174,"end_time":371.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.33,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":175,"end_time":371.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.65,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we kind of have this mash of origins from where, where these people came from.","index":176,"end_time":377.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.85,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And because the scoring wasn''t ready and it just was never going to be ready at that point I went into Salesforce and I checked through all their duplicates and I, I didn''t spend that much time on their, their Salesforce score, but I looked up what they were and then our scoring.","index":177,"end_time":393.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.37,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So they opened two emails, the job title, the industry.","index":178,"end_time":396.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.14,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I guess what I''m trying to get at that this person is now an mql.","index":179,"end_time":400.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s not reflecting that anywhere.","index":180,"end_time":402.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":401.22,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And once we''re done the scoring and it starts to populate maybe in a few weeks and we''re happy with it, is there a way for me to go in?","index":181,"end_time":410.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.94,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Can I override it in HubSpot or just put like a line item into Salesforce?","index":182,"end_time":416.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.34,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I just don''t want to lose this stuff.","index":183,"end_time":418.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":416.74,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But.","index":184,"end_time":418.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.46,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, so.","index":185,"end_time":420.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":418.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So a few things here.","index":186,"end_time":421.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one, like in column M, the activities, I imagine were before the like email opens and things like that, before we set up the lead scoring.","index":187,"end_time":430.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Two, I''m thinking we may want to just develop like a custom lead score module instead of the HubSpot native one.","index":188,"end_time":438.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":189,"end_time":439.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I think we''re just gonna have more granular control over that.","index":190,"end_time":443.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then that way we would be able to just override it.","index":191,"end_time":446.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, well, we''ll.","index":192,"end_time":448.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.6,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, we can leave that for now.","index":193,"end_time":450,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":448.76,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We got a lot to do.","index":194,"end_time":451.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And.","index":195,"end_time":451.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.4,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I did speak with TRISTAN and for Q2, well, well, we''re gonna level you up and then for Q2 you''ll have more to work with.","index":196,"end_time":459.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.68,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I think that, that.","index":197,"end_time":460.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.2,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, but I think we can work on this pretty quickly.","index":198,"end_time":462.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":460.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":199,"end_time":463.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":463.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve actually already kind of talked about this internally.","index":200,"end_time":465.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":463.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You, me and Demir think we just go with using workflows in a custom property for this.","index":201,"end_time":470.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":202,"end_time":472.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":471.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But they''re.","index":203,"end_time":473.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":473.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They''re working through this.","index":204,"end_time":474.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":473.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, they''re, you know, they''re.","index":205,"end_time":476.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":474.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They''re.","index":206,"end_time":476.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":476.47,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We got quite good stuff out of this.","index":207,"end_time":479.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":476.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":208,"end_time":479.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":479.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I did the second and third one, and that one is that.","index":209,"end_time":483.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":480.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then there''s something.","index":210,"end_time":485.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.07,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"There was one other thing.","index":211,"end_time":487.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":485.07,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So here''s an example of a lead.","index":212,"end_time":493.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":491.03,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"He''s, you know, I''m just working through the digital twin one from the other day.","index":213,"end_time":499.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":493.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So just going through it and I see, you know, there was a lot of activity here for him.","index":214,"end_time":504.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":499.22,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But, you know, going back, like, as you''re adding the lead, scoring, like, it.","index":215,"end_time":511.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.78,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Are we resetting everything to zero and then building it back up?","index":216,"end_time":515.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":511.26,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, I''m just.","index":217,"end_time":516.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.54,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So his score, you know, I''m looking at this this morning and I see that his score is 10.","index":218,"end_time":521.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":517.34,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":219,"end_time":523.589,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.189,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''ll get him to 100 because he''s been quite active.","index":220,"end_time":525.629,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.589,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But that''s all coming from HubSpot.","index":221,"end_time":527.589,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.629,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, it''s not.","index":222,"end_time":529.549,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":528.469,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I just wonder, like, this is going to be a thing the past, Right?","index":223,"end_time":535.109,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":529.549,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yes.","index":224,"end_time":535.829,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":535.349,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I don''t know what the heck that is.","index":225,"end_time":538.389,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.709,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s not.","index":226,"end_time":540.469,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":539.029,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I, like, I don''t know where this is even coming from.","index":227,"end_time":544.549,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.869,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I have to imagine that it''s coming from duplicative actions between, like, Marketo and Salesforce and just legacy integrations.","index":228,"end_time":552.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":545.589,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":229,"end_time":554.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":553.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, that was my only.","index":230,"end_time":555.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":554.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I mean, one of them is literally.","index":231,"end_time":556.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":555.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, never mind.","index":232,"end_time":556.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s a recycle campaign.","index":233,"end_time":557.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That makes sense.","index":234,"end_time":558.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":557.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but there''s engagement score and lead score, and then there''s another score that you guys also have, like a fit score.","index":235,"end_time":563.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":558.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I have to imagine there''s some legacy things that are just not computing correctly here.","index":236,"end_time":568.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":563.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":237,"end_time":569.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.55,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I mean, Kyle, they do their best, but again, this is again Frankensteined over.","index":238,"end_time":574.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":239,"end_time":575.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":574.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ten years.","index":240,"end_time":576.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":241,"end_time":576.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":576.11,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And so at some point.","index":242,"end_time":578.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":576.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":243,"end_time":578.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":578.19,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Anyway, I just wanted to ask, so.","index":244,"end_time":580.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":578.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":245,"end_time":581.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":580.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":246,"end_time":581.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":581.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And one thing to note here too, is the way that we set it up is that Salesforce, like, contacts created in Salesforce, we''re doing like a.","index":247,"end_time":588.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":581.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A HubSpot first sync over.","index":248,"end_time":589.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":588.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":249,"end_time":590.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":589.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, it''s not like Salesforce is then working everything back.","index":250,"end_time":594.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":590.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, anytime something is created, it''s more of an anytime something is updated, that information is then synced back to HubSpot.","index":251,"end_time":599.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":594.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":252,"end_time":600.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":599.87,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That sounds great.","index":253,"end_time":601.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":601.16,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And yeah, I think those were the two biggest things for me.","index":254,"end_time":604.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So thanks for the explanation.","index":255,"end_time":606.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.72,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Of course.","index":256,"end_time":606.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":606.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":257,"end_time":607.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.24,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":258,"end_time":609.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":609,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And Eric McQueen is with the Seminole Tribe of Florida.","index":259,"end_time":613.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":609.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":260,"end_time":614.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":613.8,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Nice.","index":261,"end_time":615.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":614.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":262,"end_time":616.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.88,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Jealous.","index":263,"end_time":616.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Florida sounds nice right now.","index":264,"end_time":618.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I gotta be honest with you.","index":265,"end_time":621.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":618.36,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Been there many times.","index":266,"end_time":623.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":622.84,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"If I never go back, it''ll be too soon.","index":267,"end_time":626.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623.84,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m okay with it.","index":268,"end_time":628.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":627.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m okay with it.","index":269,"end_time":630.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.29,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"What part of Florida, Barb, I''ve been to?","index":270,"end_time":633.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":630.33,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Well, everything from Daytona beach to Orlando to Miami to Fisher Island.","index":271,"end_time":638.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All over the place.","index":272,"end_time":640.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":639.13,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":273,"end_time":641.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":640.41,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":274,"end_time":641.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I did the spring break and then, you know, Orlando seems to be a big conference place.","index":275,"end_time":650.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.81,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Been there many times.","index":276,"end_time":651.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":650.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Hate it.","index":277,"end_time":652.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":652.01,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"There were some other places.","index":278,"end_time":655.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":653.85,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Orlando Airport is also insane.","index":279,"end_time":658.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":656.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s insanity.","index":280,"end_time":659.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":658.47,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Not as bad as Atlanta, but insane.","index":281,"end_time":661.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":659.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, Atlanta was nice.","index":282,"end_time":663.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":661.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, Miami was really nice.","index":283,"end_time":665.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":663.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Miami.","index":284,"end_time":666.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ve been there a few times as well, but I just.","index":285,"end_time":669.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s like Vegas if I never need to.","index":286,"end_time":671.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.31,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, we only go.","index":287,"end_time":673.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We go once a year because my father in law lives in south of Naples.","index":288,"end_time":677.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like basically Marco Island.","index":289,"end_time":678.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":677.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":290,"end_time":679.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So it''s a.","index":291,"end_time":680.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":679.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s like a just remote neighborhood he lives in.","index":292,"end_time":682.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":680.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We really don''t even leave the house.","index":293,"end_time":683.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can see why.","index":294,"end_time":687.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.05,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right.","index":295,"end_time":690.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":689.93,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Da.","index":296,"end_time":690.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":690.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry for th