"Don''t worry about it.","index":368,"end_time":900.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.23,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"If you just saw eight.","index":369,"end_time":901.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I think it''s like I just started to look through the forms themselves and see if they were different.","index":370,"end_time":907.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":901.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"If they were different locations, if.","index":371,"end_time":910.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":907.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"If it was different system.","index":372,"end_time":912.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.63,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, I. I couldn''t see it off the top of my head.","index":373,"end_time":915.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":912.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I''ll go through these this afternoon.","index":374,"end_time":917.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Don''t worry about it.","index":375,"end_time":918.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":917.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then I''ll let you know if they''re different.","index":376,"end_time":920.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.31,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But it looks like he just kept putting in the same lead.","index":377,"end_time":923.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":920.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Brad Kingsmore.","index":378,"end_time":924.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":923.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":379,"end_time":926.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.78,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Brad.","index":380,"end_time":926.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":926.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"2, 3, 4, 5, 6.","index":381,"end_time":928.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":926.82,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Wow.","index":382,"end_time":929.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.22,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":383,"end_time":930.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":930.34,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So, Brad.","index":384,"end_time":932.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":931.46,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So seven leads, one of them valid.","index":385,"end_time":937.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933.86,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, let''s dig through that, and if we need to update anything, just let us know.","index":386,"end_time":941.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":938.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":387,"end_time":942.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":941.7,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"14 minus 6 would be 8.","index":388,"end_time":943.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":942.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I think we''re good.","index":389,"end_time":944.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":943.94,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right.","index":390,"end_time":947.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":947.23,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I think that was it.","index":391,"end_time":949.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":948.03,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Did we get figured out the names that you.","index":392,"end_time":952.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":950.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That we were talking about on that workflow?","index":393,"end_time":954.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":952.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":394,"end_time":955.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":955.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"There was, like, one that.","index":395,"end_time":956.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":955.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":396,"end_time":956.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":956.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ended in en versus an okay.","index":397,"end_time":958.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":956.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":398,"end_time":959.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":958.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Joan was Jonathan.","index":399,"end_time":960.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":959.07,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":400,"end_time":961.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":961.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":401,"end_time":962.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":961.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":402,"end_time":963.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.59,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Cool.","index":403,"end_time":964.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":964.11,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":404,"end_time":965.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":964.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s it, guys.","index":405,"end_time":965.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.11,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank you for everything as usual, and have a wonderful weekend.","index":406,"end_time":968.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Stay.","index":407,"end_time":968.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":968.55,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Stay warm.","index":408,"end_time":970.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":969.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Where you''re cold and cold warrior warm you as well.","index":409,"end_time":974.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":970.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Barb and I want to.","index":410,"end_time":975.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":974.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And maybe we can do some of this async, but I really want to hop into like the ABM ideation.","index":411,"end_time":980.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":975.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":412,"end_time":980.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":980.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I want to start thinking through some offers that we can put together, you know, for running one for wims and one for Aquarius.","index":413,"end_time":987.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":980.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve been building some really, really cool stuff through automations and offers where we can have like, personalized branded output documents.","index":414,"end_time":999.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":988.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A lot of what we do are like, I think it would be probably in your.","index":415,"end_time":1003.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1000.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your case, like an analysis of their current setup and what it would look like if they worked with Aquarius or aquatic informatics overall.","index":416,"end_time":1011.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1003.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Love that.","index":417,"end_time":1012.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1011.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":418,"end_time":1013.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1012.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So think on that.","index":419,"end_time":1014.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1013.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Think on what data we would need to collect.","index":420,"end_time":1016.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1014.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, is it like the water millions per gallon, something like that?","index":421,"end_time":1022.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1016.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know what data would be vital to.","index":422,"end_time":1025.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1023.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To collect.","index":423,"end_time":1026.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1025.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Collect there.","index":424,"end_time":1027.049,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1026.489,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Try to think of like maybe five.","index":425,"end_time":1028.849,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1027.289,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We don''t want to overwhelm the prospect.","index":426,"end_time":1030.569,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1028.849,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we can give them like a document that''s an analysis on the back end, branded to aqi, pushes them towards a demo call, all sorts of things.","index":427,"end_time":1039.849,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.449,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Love that.","index":428,"end_time":1041.169,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1040.569,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":429,"end_time":1041.489,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1041.169,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I meet with the two of them next week, Eric and Safia.","index":430,"end_time":1047.449,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1041.489,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we''re just doing a kickoff to get more familiar, like get them familiar with.","index":431,"end_time":1052.259,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1047.609,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"With abm and then we''ll probably have you guys the week after.","index":432,"end_time":1055.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1052.65,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So maybe we''ll hijack this meeting and make it an ABM meeting.","index":433,"end_time":1059.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1055.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":434,"end_time":1061.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1059.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Just do the update by email would be fine.","index":435,"end_time":1063.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1061.49,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Probably by then.","index":436,"end_time":1064.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1063.85,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":437,"end_time":1065.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1065.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wanted to just show you an example if you do have a minute.","index":438,"end_time":1069.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1066.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sure.","index":439,"end_time":1069.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1069.05,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":440,"end_time":1069.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1069.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right, so here''s one that we''re actually building for a campaign we''re setting up for one of our agencies.","index":441,"end_time":1090.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1085.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we acquired Ideometry almost a year ago.","index":442,"end_time":1094.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1092.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":443,"end_time":1095.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1094.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''re doing a ABM campaign.","index":444,"end_time":1097.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1095.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is a landing page for an offer that''s a competitive intelligence report.","index":445,"end_time":1101.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1097.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is a little bit too many fields.","index":446,"end_time":1104.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1101.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, we''re kind of playing around with what we can do here.","index":447,"end_time":1106.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1104.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But basically they enter their website name, email, what role, where they really fall in as a solution category.","index":448,"end_time":1113.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1106.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if they have like a target vertical and then they can add as many competitors as they want and just give a quick, like, here''s what we do and here''s why we''re different.","index":449,"end_time":1121.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1113.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They generate it.","index":450,"end_time":1122.609,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1121.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Within minutes, they get a fully customized report that is a competitive analysis.","index":451,"end_time":1127.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1122.609,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So executive summary overview, key findings about them and their competitors, priority actions they should take from a marketing standpoint, a comparison dashboard between them and their competitors, domain authority lookups, funding comparisons, auditing, all of their social media.","index":452,"end_time":1144.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1127.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like, this is what we built as an offer because this is what our clients would be interested in, but this is the type of stuff that we can do pretty quickly with how AI has changed so drastically recently.","index":453,"end_time":1156.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1145.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":454,"end_time":1157.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1157.1,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Great.","index":455,"end_time":1157.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1157.38,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, that''s terrific.","index":456,"end_time":1159.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1158.2,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, thanks for that.","index":457,"end_time":1160.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.8,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, it goes through like all of their tech stack.","index":458,"end_time":1165.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1163.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s great.","index":459,"end_time":1166.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1166.28,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I mean, this thing loads in like 45 seconds, gives a quick win, strategic, long term wins.","index":460,"end_time":1175.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1167.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They can just filter between all this.","index":461,"end_time":1177.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1175.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They can download this as a PDF, jump to sections, copy a link and share it with another team member and then schedule a call.","index":462,"end_time":1184.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1177.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sounds terrific.","index":463,"end_time":1186.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1184.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, great.","index":464,"end_time":1187.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1186.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":465,"end_time":1188.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1187.81,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I love it.","index":466,"end_time":1189.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1189.09,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re gonna walk through just a little bit of brainstorming next week, and then I think maybe the week after we''ll, we''ll be ready for the abm, maybe even next Friday, you know, that''d be awesome.","index":467,"end_time":1199.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1189.69,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, let me, let me talk to them and I just want to talk to the two of them first and.","index":468,"end_time":1203.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1199.57,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s it.","index":469,"end_time":1205.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1204.29,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":470,"end_time":1206.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1205.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":471,"end_time":1206.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1206.13,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you very much.","index":472,"end_time":1208.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1206.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have a great weekend.","index":473,"end_time":1209.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1208.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys too.","index":474,"end_time":1209.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1209.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":475,"end_time":1210.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1209.93,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Bye.","index":476,"end_time":1211.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1210.93,"speaker_name":"bwillans"}],"dateString":"2026-01-30T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89786281993?pwd=li2lwrSFpmITXPKEdOBBgaXPwh8ONO.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,barb.willans@aquaticinformatics.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","barb.willans@aquaticinformatics.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFNT5BJFME7FKPRE4D4XKCNX","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Explained 50% drop in contact count as duplicate records during Salesforce to HubSpot migration.","Confirmed HubSpot and Salesforce sync is fully operational with live contact updates.","Proposed custom lead scoring module for better control and override options.","Identified inconsistent product naming in Deskpro data; team recommends standardization.","Initiated planning for ABM campaigns with proposed offer structures and data requirements."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I think we may want to just develop like a custom lead score module instead of the HubSpot native one.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"The BDRs have what they need, so I''m not concerned about it.","speaker":"bwillans"},{"quote":"HubSpot and Salesforce are fully connected. The contacts are syncing automatically between both systems.","speaker":"Guille Santana"}],"topics":["delivery","lead_scoring","crm","abm"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-30T18:25:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Data Integrity and Contact Management**\n\nThe team confirmed a significant cleanup of contact data, reducing duplicates and improving accuracy across systems.\n\n- **Salesforce contact lists for WIMS and Aquarius dropped from 17,000 to 3,500 after deduplication** (03:16)  \n    - Colin explained the drop was due to multiple duplicate records tied to legacy systems.  \n    - Barb noted this matched her experience with Salesforce showing repeated entries causing scoring confusion.  \n    - This cleanup improves marketing contact quality, reducing wasted outreach and improving targeting precision.  \n    - The inconsistent product naming in Deskpro (e.g., \"WIMS Rio,\" \"Rio,\" \"WIMS Classic\") was flagged for cleanup to avoid segmentation errors.  \n\n- **Lead scoring is currently in testing but may require a custom module for greater control and override ability** (07:20)  \n    - Colin suggested building a custom lead scoring property to replace HubSpot''s native system for better granularity.  \n    - Barb shared manual scoring efforts revealed gaps in reflecting true engagement for leads, highlighting the need to preserve historical activity.  \n    - The legacy integration issues cause confusing and conflicting scoring data, as discussed by Colin and Barb.  \n    - Syncing approach prioritizes Salesforce updates pushing to HubSpot, ensuring Salesforce is the system of record for contacts.  \n\n## **Marketing Automation and Webinar Management**\n\nWebinar content has been successfully transitioned to on-demand format with minor website updates required.\n\n- **Both Salesforce and HubSpot are fully synced, enabling automatic contact updates and interaction tracking** (11:36)  \n    - Guille confirmed the contact sync is stable, supporting seamless marketing and sales workflows.  \n    - Barb updated the webinar page slug from \"upcoming\" to \"on demand\" to reflect the new webinar format, fixing visibility issues.  \n    - Redirects from old URLs to new ones are handled automatically, avoiding broken links or loss of traffic.  \n    - Two-factor authentication issues on WordPress are being addressed to improve independent content management access.  \n\n- **Lead submission data showed multiple duplications from a single rep, requiring manual review** (14:03)  \n    - Barb identified 14 leads from one rep with many duplicated entries but varying comments, indicating possible data quality challenges.  \n    - Colin and Barb agreed to review and clean this data to ensure accurate lead counts and reporting.  \n\n## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Strategy Development**\n\nThe team is preparing to launch targeted ABM campaigns leveraging personalized automated content to drive demos and engagement.\n\n- **Colin introduced an ABM offer concept with personalized competitive intelligence reports to attract prospects** (16:14)  \n    - The offer collects minimal vital data points (e.g., website, role, competitors) to avoid overwhelming prospects.  \n    - Reports generated include executive summaries, competitor comparisons, and action recommendations, delivered within 45 seconds.  \n    - The output is branded to Aquarius Informatics and designed to guide prospects toward scheduling demo calls.  \n    - This approach leverages recent AI advances to quickly produce high-value, personalized marketing assets.  \n\n- **Barb plans initial meetings with key contacts Eric and Safia to align on ABM rollout before involving the wider team** (17:20)  \n    - The goal is to familiarize stakeholders with ABM concepts and finalize offer details before a broader campaign kickoff.  \n    - A collaborative brainstorming session is scheduled for next week, with a possible ABM launch targeted for the following Friday.  \n    - This phased approach supports better buy-in and ensures readiness before full execution.  \n\n## **Process Improvements and System Integration**\n\nThe team is addressing legacy system complexity and improving workflow transparency for marketing and sales alignment.\n\n- **Legacy marketing and CRM systems have created a ''Frankenstein'' environment with overlapping scores and data inconsistencies** (09:28)  \n    - Colin and Barb acknowledged the complexity built up over 10 years of integrations, causing duplicate records and conflicting lead scores.  \n    - The plan to build a custom lead scoring module is a key step to regain clarity and reduce confusion for sales reps.  \n    - Syncing updates from Salesforce to HubSpot ensures data consistency and reduces manual reconciliation efforts.  \n    - Cleaning product naming conventions in Deskpro is critical to maintain segmentation integrity and streamline reporting.  \n\n- **Operational improvements include enabling public access to Salesforce reports for self-service adjustments** (03:58)  \n    - Barb will adjust original Salesforce reports as needed and coordinate with Kyle for building classic lists.  \n    - This shift empowers marketing to manage data quality without overburdening technical teams.  \n    - Continuous cleanup and standardization efforts are planned to improve data hygiene and support future automation.  \n\n## **Timelines and Next Steps**\n\nClear deadlines and ownership were assigned to maintain momentum on key initiatives.\n\n- **Lead scoring refinement and custom module development are planned for Q2, with priority on granular control** (07:40)  \n    - Barb will coordinate with Colin and Demir to finalize workflows and custom properties.  \n    - This timeline aligns with planned resource leveling to support expanded marketing efforts.  \n\n- **ABM ideation and offer development will progress asynchronously with scheduled meetings next week** (16:14)  \n    - Barb will hold initial kickoff meetings with Eric and Safia to confirm ABM readiness.  \n    - The broader team will join for brainstorming and campaign planning the week after to target a launch by the following Friday.  \n\n- **Data cleanup tasks such as duplicate lead reviews and product naming standardization are ongoing with shared ownership** (14:27)  \n    - Barb and Colin will collaborate on validating lead submissions and cleaning inconsistent naming conventions.  \n    - Kyle is involved in list building and ensuring Deskpro data integrity.  \n\nThis coordinated effort addresses data quality, marketing automation, and strategic growth through ABM with clear timelines and ownership.","outline":null,"keywords":["Data Deduplication","Lead Scoring","Salesforce HubSpot Sync","Account-Based Marketing","Webinar On-Demand","Competitive Intelligence Report"],"overview":"- **Contact Data Cleanup:** Salesforce contact lists reduced from 17,000 to 3,500, improving accuracy and targeting.  \n- **Lead Scoring Development:** Custom module planned for Q2 to enhance lead scoring precision and integrate with Salesforce.  \n- **Webinar Transition:** On-demand webinars launched with synced systems for seamless contact updates and interaction tracking.  \n- **ABM Campaign Plans:** Personalized competitive reports to attract leads; initial stakeholder meetings scheduled for alignment.  \n- **Process Improvements:** Legacy system issues are being addressed to ensure better data quality and streamlined workflows.  \n- **Ongoing Data Cleanup:** Continuous review of duplicate leads and product naming standardization to maintain accurate reporting.","action_items":"\n**Barb Willans**\nAdjust original Salesforce reports to build and share updated Wims Classic contact list, confirming data cleanliness (03:54)\nReview “hack” campaign lead duplicates, verify distinct leads, and report findings to the team (14:27)\nMeet with Eric and Safia for ABM kickoff to familiarize them with the approach and gather initial insights (16:20)\nProvide updates and follow up on ABM ideation via email or next meetings (17:45)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nSupport Barb and team in building custom lead scoring module with workflows allowing overrides and granular control (07:20)\nAssist in cleanup and standardization advice regarding inconsistent product brand naming to improve data integrity (04:38)\nShare examples and walkthroughs of ABM automated offer tools and competitive intelligence report functionality to guide upcoming Wims and Aquarius campaigns (16:14)\nCoordinate internally and with Barb asynchronously on ABM ideation and offer development, aiming for readiness by next Friday (16:20)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nMonitor and troubleshoot 2FA issues restricting form and WordPress access, escalating if necessary (12:03)\nVerify hack campaign lead discrepancies and coordinate with Barb on lead duplicates clean-up (14:03)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"224a5a98-23e4-4317-9770-ee1327a1a45b","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
