  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: AQI // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
  '## **Data Integrity and Contact Management**

The team confirmed a significant cleanup of contact data, reducing duplicates and improving accuracy across systems.

- **Salesforce contact lists for WIMS and Aquarius dropped from 17,000 to 3,500 after deduplication** (03:16)  
    - Colin explained the drop was due to multiple duplicate records tied to legacy systems.  
    - Barb noted this matched her experience with Salesforce showing repeated entries causing scoring confusion.  
    - This cleanup improves marketing contact quality, reducing wasted outreach and improving targeting precision.  
    - The inconsistent product naming in Deskpro (e.g., "WIMS Rio," "Rio," "WIMS Classic") was flagged for cleanup to avoid segmentation errors.  

- **Lead scoring is currently in testing but may require a custom module for greater control and override ability** (07:20)  
    - Colin suggested building a custom lead scoring property to replace HubSpot''s native system for better granularity.  
    - Barb shared manual scoring efforts revealed gaps in reflecting true engagement for leads, highlighting the need to preserve historical activity.  
    - The legacy integration issues cause confusing and conflicting scoring data, as discussed by Colin and Barb.  
    - Syncing approach prioritizes Salesforce updates pushing to HubSpot, ensuring Salesforce is the system of record for contacts.  

## **Marketing Automation and Webinar Management**

Webinar content has been successfully transitioned to on-demand format with minor website updates required.

- **Both Salesforce and HubSpot are fully synced, enabling automatic contact updates and interaction tracking** (11:36)  
    - Guille confirmed the contact sync is stable, supporting seamless marketing and sales workflows.  
    - Barb updated the webinar page slug from "upcoming" to "on demand" to reflect the new webinar format, fixing visibility issues.  
    - Redirects from old URLs to new ones are handled automatically, avoiding broken links or loss of traffic.  
    - Two-factor authentication issues on WordPress are being addressed to improve independent content management access.  

- **Lead submission data showed multiple duplications from a single rep, requiring manual review** (14:03)  
    - Barb identified 14 leads from one rep with many duplicated entries but varying comments, indicating possible data quality challenges.  
    - Colin and Barb agreed to review and clean this data to ensure accurate lead counts and reporting.  

## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Strategy Development**

The team is preparing to launch targeted ABM campaigns leveraging personalized automated content to drive demos and engagement.

- **Colin introduced an ABM offer concept with personalized competitive intelligence reports to attract prospects** (16:14)  
    - The offer collects minimal vital data points (e.g., website, role, competitors) to avoid overwhelming prospects.  
    - Reports generated include executive summaries, competitor comparisons, and action recommendations, delivered within 45 seconds.  
    - The output is branded to Aquarius Informatics and designed to guide prospects toward scheduling demo calls.  
    - This approach leverages recent AI advances to quickly produce high-value, personalized marketing assets.  

- **Barb plans initial meetings with key contacts Eric and Safia to align on ABM rollout before involving the wider team** (17:20)  
    - The goal is to familiarize stakeholders with ABM concepts and finalize offer details before a broader campaign kickoff.  
    - A collaborative brainstorming session is scheduled for next week, with a possible ABM launch targeted for the following Friday.  
    - This phased approach supports better buy-in and ensures readiness before full execution.  

## **Process Improvements and System Integration**

The team is addressing legacy system complexity and improving workflow transparency for marketing and sales alignment.

- **Legacy marketing and CRM systems have created a ''Frankenstein'' environment with overlapping scores and data inconsistencies** (09:28)  
    - Colin and Barb acknowledged the complexity built up over 10 years of integrations, causing duplicate records and conflicting lead scores.  
    - The plan to build a custom lead scoring module is a key step to regain clarity and reduce confusion for sales reps.  
    - Syncing updates from Salesforce to HubSpot ensures data consistency and reduces manual reconciliation efforts.  
    - Cleaning product naming conventions in Deskpro is critical to maintain segmentation integrity and streamline reporting.  

- **Operational improvements include enabling public access to Salesforce reports for self-service adjustments** (03:58)  
    - Barb will adjust original Salesforce reports as needed and coordinate with Kyle for building classic lists.  
    - This shift empowers marketing to manage data quality without overburdening technical teams.  
    - Continuous cleanup and standardization efforts are planned to improve data hygiene and support future automation.  

## **Timelines and Next Steps**

Clear deadlines and ownership were assigned to maintain momentum on key initiatives.

- **Lead scoring refinement and custom module development are planned for Q2, with priority on granular control** (07:40)  
    - Barb will coordinate with Colin and Demir to finalize workflows and custom properties.  
    - This timeline aligns with planned resource leveling to support expanded marketing efforts.  

- **ABM ideation and offer development will progress asynchronously with scheduled meetings next week** (16:14)  
    - Barb will hold initial kickoff meetings with Eric and Safia to confirm ABM readiness.  
    - The broader team will join for brainstorming and campaign planning the week after to target a launch by the following Friday.  

- **Data cleanup tasks such as duplicate lead reviews and product naming standardization are ongoing with shared ownership** (14:27)  
    - Barb and Colin will collaborate on validating lead submissions and cleaning inconsistent naming conventions.  
    - Kyle is involved in list building and ensuring Deskpro data integrity.  

This coordinated effort addresses data quality, marketing automation, and strategic growth through ABM with clear timelines and ownership.',
  '2026-01-30 16:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Adjust original Salesforce reports to build and share updated Wims Classic contact list, confirming data cleanliness (03:54)","completed":false},{"text":"Review “hack” campaign lead duplicates, verify distinct leads, and report findings to the team (14:27)","completed":false},{"text":"Meet with Eric and Safia for ABM kickoff to familiarize them with the approach and gather initial insights (16:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide updates and follow up on ABM ideation via email or next meetings (17:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Support Barb and team in building custom lead scoring module with workflows allowing overrides and granular control (07:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Assist in cleanup and standardization advice regarding inconsistent product brand naming to improve data integrity (04:38)","completed":false},{"text":"Share examples and walkthroughs of ABM automated offer tools and competitive intelligence report functionality to guide upcoming Wims and Aquarius campaigns (16:14)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate internally and with Barb asynchronously on ABM ideation and offer development, aiming for readiness by next Friday (16:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor and troubleshoot 2FA issues restricting form and WordPress access, escalating if necessary (12:03)","completed":false},{"text":"Verify hack campaign lead discrepancies and coordinate with Barb on lead duplicates clean-up (14:03)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

