    2276,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82807622497?pwd=1oWxQKkVvrj4tRTln1UgER5pencHWv.1',
    '{"id":"01KFNT5BJ8VMJ6CWHEB58RM6H7","title":"Ponce Bank // MiD: HubSpot Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **HubSpot and Salesforce Integration**\n\nThe team clarified the synchronization strategy and data flow between **HubSpot** and **Salesforce** to ensure seamless lead and contact management (18:00).\n\n- **Gabriel Bencosme** presented a detailed data flow diagram explaining that **Salesforce stores objects like person and business**, while **Mulesoft handles data transfer between systems**.\n    - Leads in Salesforce get converted to opportunities and removed, so the focus is on syncing opportunities and lifecycle stages to HubSpot contacts.\n    - The integration avoids duplications by flagging contacts created in HubSpot with backend fields and using flexible APIs for record checks.\n    - Gabriel emphasized the need for automation in Salesforce to assign branches and notify bankers to prevent duplicate contact creation.\n    - **Colin Costigan** confirmed lifecycle stages in HubSpot replace the need for a separate lead object, aligning marketing and sales data flows.\n- The team agreed to finalize the list of Salesforce fields to sync based on contacts and relationships, with **Christina** and **Betty** reviewing and approving the fields (09:08).\n    - This includes handling separate Salesforce objects for contacts and relationships while ensuring HubSpot’s association capabilities maintain data integrity.\n- **Betty Campiz** highlighted the risk of manual duplicate creation and suggested creating a dashboard view for bankers showing HubSpot-originated marketing opportunities to guide sales behavior (27:05).\n    - Gabriel confirmed this would be supported by flagging contacts and automating branch assignments and notifications in Salesforce.\n- Sync frequency was confirmed to be mainly **real-time per object**, with batch uploads as needed, following Gabriel’s design (16:54).\n    - This allows flexible, adaptive syncing tuned to business needs.\n\n## **User Permissions and Account Access**\n\nResolving access issues in **HubSpot** was identified as a critical next step to enable full user capabilities (04:25).\n\n- Colin explained only **Christina**, the super admin, can update Gabriel’s permissions to allow viewing and editing contacts in HubSpot.\n    - Once Gabriel and team have super admin access, they can fully manage contacts and properties.\n- Currently, Gabriel sees **zero contacts** on the HubSpot interface, but via API calls, **53 contacts** began populating after a hard refresh (07:08).\n- Victor committed to following up with Christina and Betty to finalize the property list and permissions update, targeting quick resolution (09:08).\n- Ashley noted that aligning on Gabriel’s planned data structure before build commencement is important for efficiency and accuracy (10:29).\n\n## **Product and Data Property Strategy**\n\nThe project is using a **placeholder set of 300 properties** in HubSpot to preserve data during early imports, with plans to refine and reduce this list based on internal review (07:29).\n\n- Gabriel confirmed about **60 properties** have been selected for active use in data exchanges between Salesforce and HubSpot.\n- Christina and Betty are reviewing which Salesforce fields from contacts and relationships should be synced, impacting what Gabriel builds into the API.\n- Ashley clarified if fields exist on the relationship object in Salesforce, a new query is needed to import them into HubSpot, setting expectations for upcoming data work (14:23).\n- Victor and Colin emphasized the need to finalize the property list promptly to avoid delays in integration and content build.\n\n## **Website Content and Timeline**\n\nThe website content build is progressing well, targeting a **February 17th** deadline for initial content delivery to senior management (33:38).\n\n- Ashley reported **five or six pages** are built, with designers making changes requested by Christina, expecting updates by **Monday** (34:44).\n- Colin confirmed the homepage design sets the tone for other pages, making content replacement easier once the design is locked.\n- Victor plans to push the initial content to Christina for departmental review to stay on schedule (35:21).\n- The team acknowledged that any delay in content delivery shifts the entire project timeline (34:09).\n\n## **Advertising and Account Issues**\n\nThere is a current issue with **Google Ads account suspension**, impacting campaign management and requiring alternative approaches (35:27).\n\n- Colin shared that Google has blocked his account and is not accepting further appeals.\n- Victor was advised to submit an appeal using drafted text provided by Colin, leveraging his company email for better credibility (36:03).\n- Colin guided Victor through navigating Google Ads interface to submit the appeal properly.\n- The team is exploring options to resolve the blockage and maintain advertising efforts.\n\n## **Process and Next Steps Coordination**\n\nThe meeting reinforced the importance of coordination among **Christina**, **Betty**, and the technical team to finalize permissions, property lists, and integration details (09:08).\n\n- Victor is assigned to follow up on outstanding approvals and permissions with Christina and Betty.\n- Gabriel plans to collaborate with Ashley and Betty to define which parts of the process require automation versus manual user actions.\n- Colin offered support for any sales process needs that arise from integration adjustments.\n- Gabriel will share the detailed process diagram with Victor and Colin for reference and ongoing updates (31:41).","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot Integration","Salesforce Sync","Data Permissions","Opportunity Management","Duplicate Avoidance","Website Content Deadline"],"overview":"- **HubSpot and Salesforce Integration:** Sync strategy and data flow detailed for seamless lead management using Mulesoft and Salesforce.  \n- **Field Syncing Agreement:** Final list of Salesforce fields for syncing to be reviewed and approved, ensuring data integrity in HubSpot.  \n- **User Permissions Update:** Critical access issues to be resolved, enabling full user capabilities for managing contacts in HubSpot.  \n- **Property Strategy:** Placeholder set of 300 properties planned, refining down to 60 active properties for effective data exchange.  \n- **Content Delivery Timeline:** Website content build targeted for February 17th, with progress and design updates to keep project on schedule.  \n- **Google Ads Issue:** Current account suspension poses challenges; team is working on appeals and alternative solutions for advertising efforts.","action_items":"\n**Gabriel Bencosme**\nShare the detailed integration sync process diagram and documentation with the team and upload it to SharePoint for collaborative updates (31:46)\nCoordinate with Ashley and Betty to clarify user processes that need automation and finalize data sync workflows on Salesforce and HubSpot sides (29:45)\nAdjust integration design to incorporate opportunity syncing nuances discussed, including duplicate checks and lifecycle stage updates (20:29)\nNotify team of any technical or design changes based on current meeting discussions regarding Salesforce-HubSpot data flow (31:57)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nFollow up with Christina to finalize and confirm the list of Salesforce Contact and Relationship fields that will be passed to HubSpot (08:48)\nAdd Gabe’s process diagrams and documents to the project SharePoint and ensure visibility to all stakeholders (31:46)\nCoordinate with department heads and manage content deadlines aiming for February 17 delivery to ensure website progress (34:09)\nSubmit appeal for Google Ads account reinstatement using provided text and company email to improve chances (36:27)\n\n**Christina Zanca**\nAccept HubSpot super admin invitation and update Gabe and Victor’s permissions to allow full access (04:25)\nReview and finalize the list of necessary properties from Salesforce Contact and Relationship objects for data syncing to HubSpot (08:48)\n\n**Ashley Taska**\nCollaborate with Gabe and Betty to review and approve the integration design and data sync processes before proceeding with further development (10:29)\nContinue website design revisions as per Christina’s feedback; expedite content creation to meet Feb 17 deadline (34:44)\n\n**Betty Campiz**\nAssist Ashley and Victor in finalizing field selections and provide feedback on Salesforce-HubSpot sync requirements related to sales and banking team workflows (21:10)\nWork with Gabe and Ashley on defining banker user automation and dashboard reporting to minimize duplicates and support sales processes (26:59)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nProvide ongoing support and consulting to resolve HubSpot admin permission issues and advise on API usage and sync configurations (04:25)\nAssist Victor with Google Ads account issues through appeal drafting and communication guidance (36:01)\nCoordinate with team to adjust integration flows as needed and prepare support documentation (29:44)\n"},"duration":37.939998626708984,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"victor garcia"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"id":5,"name":"bettycampiz"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Good morning Colin, how are you?","index":0,"end_time":239.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.65,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Hey Gabe, how''s it going?","index":1,"end_time":241.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m all right, can''t complain.","index":2,"end_time":243.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.85,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s Friday, right?","index":3,"end_time":245.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, at least.","index":4,"end_time":247.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.25,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"At least it''s Friday.","index":5,"end_time":250.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":249.29,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That''s it.","index":6,"end_time":251.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":250.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, good morning Kyla.","index":7,"end_time":256.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":255.78,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Hey Victor.","index":8,"end_time":258.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ashley might be running a few minutes late so we can start without her just in.","index":9,"end_time":262.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.82,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Just to let you know.","index":10,"end_time":264.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.86,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay, sweet.","index":11,"end_time":266.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":265.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll.","index":12,"end_time":268.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":267.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll go through kind of where we''re at on the project plan but the biggest thing is Gabe, for the email you sent over worked with HubSpot support but since Christina is the only super.","index":13,"end_time":275.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":268.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Admin on the account, she has to change your permissions.","index":14,"end_time":278.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":15,"end_time":279.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":278.66,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So I sent that over via email.","index":16,"end_time":280.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":279.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Today Victor, I think you probably saw that.","index":17,"end_time":282.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, if Christina can do that.","index":18,"end_time":285.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":284.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or if she has any questions, just let us know.","index":19,"end_time":287.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But unfortunately we can''t make any changes.","index":20,"end_time":289.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":287.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I definitely can''t make any changes either.","index":21,"end_time":292.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":289.93,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Wish I got.","index":22,"end_time":292.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":292.09,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good question Colin.","index":23,"end_time":294.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.97,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Is there a reason why I cannot see any of the contacts that you guys imported?","index":24,"end_time":297.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.33,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Like I can''t see any contacts at all on the HubSpot.","index":25,"end_time":300.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.85,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Like if I call it via the private app API then I''m able to get them but if I wanted to go into the platform it''s login myself.","index":26,"end_time":311.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":302.09,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And look at the do a share screen.","index":27,"end_time":314.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hold up.","index":28,"end_time":317.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":316.66,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Let me see.","index":29,"end_time":317.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.38,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Let me pull up because my.","index":30,"end_time":319.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.94,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Hold up, you might find this.","index":31,"end_time":322.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.42,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I have a million tabs open.","index":32,"end_time":325.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.74,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Just give me a second.","index":33,"end_time":326.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.94,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"You and every other coder and marketer.","index":34,"end_time":329.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":327.78,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":35,"end_time":332.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.18,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Let me.","index":36,"end_time":337.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":336.66,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I don''t know how to share in.","index":37,"end_time":338.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":337.26,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"In.","index":38,"end_time":339.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":338.74,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"There''s a share button at the bottom.","index":39,"end_time":341.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":340.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With like a green arrow.","index":40,"end_time":342.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I see it.","index":41,"end_time":344.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":344.03,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m just joking.","index":42,"end_time":345.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":344.71,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I get it confused with teams.","index":43,"end_time":347.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.35,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"What can you guys see?","index":44,"end_time":348.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.95,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Is it a.","index":45,"end_time":349.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":348.95,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Pretty sure I see like two monitors or two main windows.","index":46,"end_time":354.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":350.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have a really wide monitor?","index":47,"end_time":356.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":354.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I have an ultra wide monitor and so.","index":48,"end_time":360.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.75,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It would make me jealous.","index":49,"end_time":363.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":362.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gabe, you know it makes your life a lot easier when you have to deal with some of this stuff.","index":50,"end_time":369.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.95,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, okay, so yeah interesting that it''s not showing you.","index":51,"end_time":375.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I''m pretty sure you could see it but I think if I share just.","index":52,"end_time":380,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.84,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah I can see it.","index":53,"end_time":381,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":380,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I see zero contacts count on the.","index":54,"end_time":382.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":381.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On the left side which is strange because your permissions are set to be able to view that.","index":55,"end_time":386.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":382.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I cannot see like a single contact or create contacts as well.","index":56,"end_time":390.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.4,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I mean I don''t need to since we already you guys already imported but once I get access to like make being able to make changes then I want to be able to see that reflected properly in.","index":57,"end_time":400.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":390.56,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, so.","index":58,"end_time":401.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think that''ll also get fixed with.","index":59,"end_time":403.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":401.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Once her Sena makes you guys a super admin, you''ll be able to do anything in the account.","index":60,"end_time":406.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":403.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, don''t make me a super admin.","index":61,"end_time":410.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.19,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I like to break things sometimes.","index":62,"end_time":411.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.51,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Oh, here, actually, I just found a trigger.","index":63,"end_time":416.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":414.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":64,"end_time":422.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this one, it is letting me update.","index":65,"end_time":424.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":66,"end_time":425.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":424.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you do a hard refresh?","index":67,"end_time":426.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":425.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":68,"end_time":428.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428.08,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I think something is getting populated because Now I''m seeing 53 contacts, even though I don''t see names or anything like that yet, so.","index":69,"end_time":445.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":437.76,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So maybe give it a few seconds.","index":70,"end_time":448.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.85,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":71,"end_time":449.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":449.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":72,"end_time":449.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":449.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sometimes it just takes a few minutes on HubSpot said, but we did create.","index":73,"end_time":453.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":449.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we''re.","index":74,"end_time":455.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":454.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys are still working through, like, the masking and everything like that.","index":75,"end_time":458.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":455.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the time being, we created about 300 properties as placeholders just so we don''t lose any data and then we can go through and just do a cleanup that.","index":76,"end_time":466.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":458.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''s the easiest process here.","index":77,"end_time":468.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":466.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":78,"end_time":469.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.89,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":79,"end_time":470.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":469.77,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I did see a bunch of fields that were added because I was trying to look at some of the properties that are.","index":80,"end_time":476.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.09,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That I want to test with at least so I could start building more or less the JSON payload or the JSON structure.","index":81,"end_time":483.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":477.13,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And so I did see a lot.","index":82,"end_time":485.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.81,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"All of them didn''t panic, though.","index":83,"end_time":487.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":485.37,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I know that they''re still in the system, so I know we already have a few ones that are about 60 that we selected that are we going to use to be sending over back and forth.","index":84,"end_time":498.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":487.41,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I guess so.","index":85,"end_time":499.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":498.85,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Is that still going to remain the case, Colin?","index":86,"end_time":503.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":501.12,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":87,"end_time":504.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":503.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":88,"end_time":504.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.24,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"No problem.","index":89,"end_time":505.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.8,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"As far as I know.","index":90,"end_time":506.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":505.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that it''s more working through the.","index":91,"end_time":508.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":506.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like between you and Christina and Betty.","index":92,"end_time":511.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":508.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, determining what we shouldn''t pass or what we should pass.","index":93,"end_time":514.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":511.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":94,"end_time":516.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.84,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Well, I haven''t really received anything.","index":95,"end_time":520,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":516.96,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Any more updates from Christina.","index":96,"end_time":521.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.24,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I think they''re still working through that as well.","index":97,"end_time":523.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.72,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":98,"end_time":524.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":99,"end_time":524.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":524.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Victor, do you have any timeline on that?","index":100,"end_time":526.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":524.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is specifically.","index":101,"end_time":528.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.23,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m sorry.","index":102,"end_time":529.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.99,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Just like they were still.","index":103,"end_time":531.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":529.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know Christina went through the list pretty quickly after our last meeting and.","index":104,"end_time":534.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":531.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Determined like, we don''t need to pull this over.","index":105,"end_time":536.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We.","index":106,"end_time":537.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":536.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do need to pull this over.","index":107,"end_time":538.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":537.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just like, when that list is finalized.","index":108,"end_time":540.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":538.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know.","index":109,"end_time":540.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":540.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think Betty was taking a look at it as well.","index":110,"end_time":542.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":111,"end_time":542.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":542.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I sent that list over on Wednesday, so I''m just waiting on her to give me her word on that.","index":112,"end_time":548.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":542.91,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":113,"end_time":548.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":548.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I''ll leave that as a.","index":114,"end_time":550.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":548.79,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"As an action item to follow up on.","index":115,"end_time":552.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":550.31,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":116,"end_time":553.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":553.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, I mean, that''s pretty much all from our side.","index":117,"end_time":557.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":554.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So once Christina updates your Guys access.","index":118,"end_time":560.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":557.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then you''ll be in a good spot.","index":119,"end_time":561.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":560.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, and perfect timing.","index":120,"end_time":562.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":561.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ashley''s joining.","index":121,"end_time":563.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":562.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know Christina mentioned she has some questions as well.","index":122,"end_time":565.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":563.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I also have a few things before.","index":123,"end_time":568.569,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":567.05,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"After we speak on this part.","index":124,"end_time":571.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":568.81,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":125,"end_time":571.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":571.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Morning, ashley.","index":126,"end_time":576.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":576.01,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Sorry I haven''t missed anything yet.","index":127,"end_time":586.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":584.58,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Okay.","index":128,"end_time":588.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":587.38,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Not much.","index":129,"end_time":590.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":590.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing, Ashley?","index":130,"end_time":591.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":590.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Doing well.","index":131,"end_time":593.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":592.26,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":132,"end_time":593.819,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":593.3,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":133,"end_time":594.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":593.819,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":134,"end_time":596.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":596.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To catch you up, we went through.","index":135,"end_time":598.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":596.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Christina just has to accept her invite and then update your guys permissions to super admin.","index":136,"end_time":602.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":598.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So then you can see everything.","index":137,"end_time":604.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":603.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that is pretty much where we''re at.","index":138,"end_time":608.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":606.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Victor''s going to follow up.","index":139,"end_time":609.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":608.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And just get confirmation on the timeline of when Betty and Christina will have that list finalized of the.","index":140,"end_time":614.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":609.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of the properties we want to pass over.","index":141,"end_time":616.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":614.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":142,"end_time":618.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":617.93,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And I don''t know if Gabriel shared that he put something together that he wants to show to the team.","index":143,"end_time":626.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":619.13,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Like.","index":144,"end_time":626.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":626.17,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I haven''t done it yet.","index":145,"end_time":629.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I mean, I was thinking that Christina was going to join.","index":146,"end_time":631.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.97,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m not sure if anybody else is.","index":147,"end_time":633.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":631.97,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"No, no.","index":148,"end_time":636.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":636.5,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Not.","index":149,"end_time":636.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":636.78,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Not that you have to do it now, but if just make mention of it because this like aligning on what he put together will be very beneficial to how he proceeds with his build.","index":150,"end_time":647.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":636.94,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So we just want to review it with.","index":151,"end_time":649.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":647.54,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"With everyone before he starts in there.","index":152,"end_time":652.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":649.5,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So if we have some time to.","index":153,"end_time":654.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":652.86,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"To go through that.","index":154,"end_time":655.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":654.74,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":155,"end_time":656.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":656.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, pretty much where we''re at is I know that Christina mentioned you had some questions that you wanted to go through and then.","index":156,"end_time":660.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":656.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, happy to talk through anything that.","index":157,"end_time":663.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":660.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gabe wants to go through.","index":158,"end_time":664.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":663.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":159,"end_time":666.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":665.5,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I mean, yeah, I mean, I can.","index":160,"end_time":667.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":666.46,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"We''re waiting for, I guess Christina or Betty.","index":161,"end_time":670.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":668.78,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And Christina said that she''s not joining today.","index":162,"end_time":673.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":670.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I have to assume that if Betty''s not here yet or Lewis isn''t here yet that they''re probably not joining.","index":163,"end_time":679.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I''m not sure.","index":164,"end_time":680.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":679.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll start, I guess with maybe not question, but just a clarifying point.","index":165,"end_time":687.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":681.98,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I met with Victor and Christina earlier, earlier this week and I know there was some type of excel that was being worked on that first had two categories, one for relationships and one for contacts.","index":166,"end_time":701.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":687.98,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"And Victor, I''m not sure which one is now removed.","index":167,"end_time":705.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":701.81,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Which one was it?","index":168,"end_time":706.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":705.33,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Relationship.","index":169,"end_time":706.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":706.09,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"None of them.","index":170,"end_time":707.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.09,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We were.","index":171,"end_time":708.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":708.13,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We wanted to figure out for this meeting and we were going to either combine them or there was a way, at least on the HubSpot side of things, you know, how we wanted to mix that.","index":172,"end_time":719.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":708.65,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So that was the conversation that we were going to have today with the.","index":173,"end_time":722.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":719.31,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"No, but wait.","index":174,"end_time":722.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":722.07,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"When we, when we met, you were looking at something and you couldn''t reference One of those columns, because it was no longer there.","index":175,"end_time":728.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":722.83,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"No.","index":176,"end_time":729.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":729.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":177,"end_time":730.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":729.99,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay, so there was a list, Colin and G, that you guys had, in that you guys combined Contact and Relationship.","index":178,"end_time":738.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":730.27,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"There was an email that was sent to you guys just confirming that you guys were aware that Contact and Relationship and Salesforce were two different things.","index":179,"end_time":745.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":738.27,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And you guys put that list together, and you guys pretty much said, okay, this is the list that we have that we''re going to use based on those two.","index":180,"end_time":752.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":746.13,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Based on those two fields that we had.","index":181,"end_time":755.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":752.93,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Where is that list?","index":182,"end_time":757.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":756.13,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I think we can pull up that spreadsheet and send that over.","index":183,"end_time":761.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":759.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I will say.","index":184,"end_time":763.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":762.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can send that over after the meeting.","index":185,"end_time":764.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":763.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I will say is that HubSpot, the cool thing about the way that HubSpot handles objects is it''s able to do association, so basically like relationships, so between several different objects in HubSpot.","index":186,"end_time":773.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":764.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It.","index":187,"end_time":774.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":773.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They can, like, update each other''s information and then pass that information back through.","index":188,"end_time":777.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":774.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The API to Salesforce, mulesoft, et cetera.","index":189,"end_time":780.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":777.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even though they''re two separate.","index":190,"end_time":782.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":780.58,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Even though they''re divided in two separate areas in Salesforce, correct?","index":191,"end_time":785.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":782.3,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":192,"end_time":785.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":785.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":193,"end_time":786.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":785.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so then that.","index":194,"end_time":787.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":786.26,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"That.","index":195,"end_time":787.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":787.26,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah, so the integration actually has like.","index":196,"end_time":789.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":787.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A settings per object.","index":197,"end_time":791.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":789.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":198,"end_time":792.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":792.18,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So actually, that was the list that you.","index":199,"end_time":795.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":794.02,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That.","index":200,"end_time":795.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":795.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That we were discussing.","index":201,"end_time":796.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":795.78,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay, so then we should be good with that, because the concern was that there are two different objects in Salesforce, and if we want to use something that''s on the relationship, we need to create a custom field on the contact.","index":202,"end_time":806.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":796.98,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"But if you''re staying from HubSpot, there''s a way to send them in to each object.","index":203,"end_time":811.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":806.73,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Then that clears that up.","index":204,"end_time":813.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":811.81,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah, the Salesforce HubSpot.","index":205,"end_time":815.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":813.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the Salesforce HubSpot integration is pretty robust.","index":206,"end_time":817.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":815.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re able to really control a lot of settings through it.","index":207,"end_time":822.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":819.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And yeah, it has tabs for every different object that you want to integrate.","index":208,"end_time":826.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":209,"end_time":827.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":826.81,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So just for confirmation, Ashley, what we''re doing now as the next step is Christina is confirming which fields from the list that you guys provided from the Relationship and Contact side, which ones we want to use moving forward into HubSpot, so that we can connect that between HubSpot and Salesforce.","index":210,"end_time":845.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":827.21,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That''s our next step.","index":211,"end_time":846.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":845.94,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So you guys are good to go on that end.","index":212,"end_time":848.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":846.98,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":213,"end_time":849.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":848.98,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":214,"end_time":850.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":850.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, Ashley, where we''re at is we just build a placeholder for everything right now because we uploaded the test contacts, and so we can modify and.","index":215,"end_time":858.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":850.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And reduce and change based on whatever the updated list that Christina comes back with.","index":216,"end_time":862.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":859.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":217,"end_time":864.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":863.57,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"If some of those fields are on the relationship, though, we would need to provide a new query with those fields.","index":218,"end_time":871.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":864.61,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"To provide to.","index":219,"end_time":872.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":871.13,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"I guess you call in so that you can import them into HubSpot.","index":220,"end_time":879.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":872.77,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So yeah, build the property.","index":221,"end_time":880.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":879.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":222,"end_time":881.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":880.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":223,"end_time":881.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":881.21,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":224,"end_time":882.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":881.53,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So I guess we''ll wait on that and then we can query those fields.","index":225,"end_time":885.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":882.53,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":226,"end_time":887.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":887.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I guess a bigger.","index":227,"end_time":889.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":888.85,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Oh, sorry, guys.","index":228,"end_time":890.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":889.93,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Sorry, Victor, go ahead.","index":229,"end_time":897.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":896.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no, I was waiting for Betty to say hi because you.","index":230,"end_time":899.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":897.29,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"You said hi.","index":231,"end_time":900.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":899.41,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I can''t hear her for some reason.","index":232,"end_time":902.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":901.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, hi, Betty.","index":233,"end_time":903.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":902.85,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"We see you, but we don''t hear you.","index":234,"end_time":905.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":903.69,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"The pouting face is hilarious.","index":235,"end_time":910.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":908.53,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"She''s probably talking like, why are they ignoring me?","index":236,"end_time":915.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":913.5,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"No, we still can''t hear you.","index":237,"end_time":916.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":915.66,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Do you hear me now?","index":238,"end_time":927.739,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":926.7,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yes.","index":239,"end_time":928.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":928.14,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"It keeps changing because Teams and Zoom are using different microphones.","index":240,"end_time":935.1,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":930.62,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Anyways, good morning.","index":241,"end_time":938.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":937.03,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"That''s what I said, good morning.","index":242,"end_time":940.55,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":938.39,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry, Victor, what were you saying?","index":243,"end_time":943.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":942.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, I mean, maybe we could save this for another conversation because I feel like it''ll be a little bit more of tests in the sandbox at that point.","index":244,"end_time":951.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":944.39,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"The leads process for when somebody goes into our website, fills out a form and potentially, you know, that whole process gets converted.","index":245,"end_time":959.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":951.99,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"How does that information transfer over to Salesforce and back into HubSpot so that we can kind of do that lead managing, you know, hand holding, hand to hand kind of thing?","index":246,"end_time":968.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":959.91,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That might.","index":247,"end_time":969,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":968.56,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That''s a conversation for later, I''m assuming, correct?","index":248,"end_time":971,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":969,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I mean, yeah, but we also have a bunch of documentation built around the entire HubSpot configuration.","index":249,"end_time":975.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":971.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can send that guide over again.","index":250,"end_time":977.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":975.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But basically from the website perspective, HubSpot would be the first source capturing that.","index":251,"end_time":982.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":977.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because it''s a HubSpot form on a HubSpot site.","index":252,"end_time":984.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":982.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it would pass that information through the integration.","index":253,"end_time":987.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":984.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then whenever lifecycle stages are updated.","index":254,"end_time":989.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":987.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let''s say they''ve gone from lead, they talk to sales, they open an.","index":255,"end_time":992.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":989.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Account in xyz, you know, personal or commercial.","index":256,"end_time":995.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":992.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That information then gets updated back through.","index":257,"end_time":997.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":995.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The API to HubSpot so that we can market to them for those specific scenarios.","index":258,"end_time":1000.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":997.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":259,"end_time":1001.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1001.31,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"And then another thing that I had on my agenda, just to make sure that we understood the sync frequencies.","index":260,"end_time":1007.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1001.87,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I know that we spoke about that last time, but I just want a confirmation when.","index":261,"end_time":1011.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1009.07,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"How often are we doing a sync between the systems?","index":262,"end_time":1014.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1012.51,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, so Gabe had come up with some recommendations that we were completely in line with.","index":263,"end_time":1018.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1014.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the cool thing that Gabe had mentioned is we can even go per object if we wanted to, but we were talking in mainly real time syncs.","index":264,"end_time":1026.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1018.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then if needed, batch uploads.","index":265,"end_time":1028.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1026.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gabe, correct me if I''m wrong there.","index":266,"end_time":1029.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1028.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":267,"end_time":1030.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1029.93,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That is kind of like the design that I put together that Ashley was talking about more or less.","index":268,"end_time":1034.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1030.49,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I guess.","index":269,"end_time":1036.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1035.53,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I guess this is a good time for me to share.","index":270,"end_time":1038.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1037.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I think since we''re having this type of conversation, I think I should just go there and kind of show exactly what I''m kind of put together on a high level.","index":271,"end_time":1050.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1038.73,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So let me know once you guys can see my screen.","index":272,"end_time":1054.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1050.97,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So.","index":273,"end_time":1055.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1055.06,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yep.","index":274,"end_time":1056.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1055.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, Let me remove some stuff from here.","index":275,"end_time":1060.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1057.46,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"All right.","index":276,"end_time":1061.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1061.22,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I know there''s a lot of things happening here, Victor, at least on your side, so that you can understand what''s happening here.","index":277,"end_time":1069.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1061.86,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So we.","index":278,"end_time":1070.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.42,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We already know we have Salesforce, we have Hotspot on.","index":279,"end_time":1073.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.82,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"On.","index":280,"end_time":1073.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073.38,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"On each end and myself in the middle kind of doing the communication between the two systems.","index":281,"end_time":1080.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1074.02,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":282,"end_time":1080.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1080.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so I know there''s a lot going on in this diagram.","index":283,"end_time":1083.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1081.15,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Maybe Colin, for you, since you are more used to seeing things like this, it may not be complicated, but for you, Victor, maybe Betty, since you guys are looking at this, I''m going to start at the bottom.","index":284,"end_time":1095.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1083.83,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So one of the things that I want to highlight, Victor, first is you can see this a little kind of like rectangles with brown edges.","index":285,"end_time":1102.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1095.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"They mean that this is.","index":286,"end_time":1104.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1102.91,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"This is where basically we store what we call objects in Salesforce and in HubSpot.","index":287,"end_time":1109.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1104.11,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So this is where the data lives, right.","index":288,"end_time":1111.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1109.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"For we''re looking at person and business.","index":289,"end_time":1113.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1112.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That''s also another object.","index":290,"end_time":1114.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1113.69,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That is where a person.","index":291,"end_time":1115.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1114.77,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That''s also where another.","index":292,"end_time":1118.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1117.25,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"This is where data lives in the Salesforce system.","index":293,"end_time":1121.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1118.85,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So as you can see, there''s none of that lives in mealsoft.","index":294,"end_time":1124.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1121.17,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":295,"end_time":1124.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1124.01,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Meal soft is only making sure that the information is transferred back and forth.","index":296,"end_time":1128.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1124.17,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So if we start over on the Salesforce side, one of the things that I wanted to go over with you guys so that you can have more or less of a holistic view of how things are going to operate for you, Betty and Victor as well.","index":297,"end_time":1139.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1128.61,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Basically, this kind of goes into more granularity of what Colin just explained, right.","index":298,"end_time":1146,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1140.8,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That one to one sync that''s happening.","index":299,"end_time":1148.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1146.96,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So we start at the bottom right now.","index":300,"end_time":1150.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1148.8,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Let''s start at the bottom.","index":301,"end_time":1151.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1150.72,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Since it''s a simple process when it comes to a lead in Salesforce, one of the things that happens with leads is that once they get converted into an opportunity, the lead actually gets removed.","index":302,"end_time":1161.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1151.72,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So one opportunity gets created is actually assigned a relationship, whether it''s person or business.","index":303,"end_time":1166.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1161.58,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So the reason why I have an undefined process in this case is because I don''t think this is necessary for the lead to come over.","index":304,"end_time":1172.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1166.86,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I think it''s more important for the opportunity to come over since it contains more data.","index":305,"end_time":1177.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1172.78,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So now I guess we''re going to have to define some internal process here where that lead conversion needs to happen.","index":306,"end_time":1182.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1177.5,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Can I simplify this real quick?","index":307,"end_time":1185.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1183.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, go ahead.","index":308,"end_time":1186.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1185.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So in HubSpot they actually just recently, in the last like six or eight.","index":309,"end_time":1190.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1186.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Months, created a lead object.","index":310,"end_time":1191.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1190.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The way that we design this though, that is unnecessary.","index":311,"end_time":1195.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1192.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what Salesforce in is splitting as lead versus contact object.","index":312,"end_time":1199.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1195.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"HubSpot traditionally combines through a lifecycle stage.","index":313,"end_time":1202.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1199.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Assigned to that contact.","index":314,"end_time":1203.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1202.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we like we have a lifecycle stage for lead or marketing qualified lead.","index":315,"end_time":1207.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1204.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or sales qualified lead, etc.","index":316,"end_time":1209.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1207.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the original architecture that we had talked about with Betty and Christina.","index":317,"end_time":1214.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1209.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was not tracking deals because we want, we don''t want the sales team to live in HubSpot.","index":318,"end_time":1218.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1214.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s more of a marketing tool.","index":319,"end_time":1219.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1218.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we would need from the opportunity is again more just updating the lifecycle stage to understand that they''re a customer now and then we have a line item for what they are a customer of.","index":320,"end_time":1229.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1220.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":321,"end_time":1230.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1229.94,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I.","index":322,"end_time":1230.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1230.34,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And so one of the.","index":323,"end_time":1232.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1231.62,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That''s one of the things that I.","index":324,"end_time":1234.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1232.82,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Sorry to interrupt you, Betty.","index":325,"end_time":1235.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1234.02,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So one of the things that I started thinking about opportunity and this is kind of what I spoke to Ashley.","index":326,"end_time":1239.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1235.26,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We may not necessarily have to connect opportunities to deal at any point, but this is one of the reasons why this arrow exists because once the opportunity gets created, that is where the opportunity is going to hold some of that information and it can get transferred to either the business, the company or the contact.","index":327,"end_time":1255.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1239.34,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So kind of the reason why I have these arrows in this way right here so that the opportunity may not necessarily come over, but you could actually obey the actual object.","index":328,"end_time":1263.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1255.76,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And so if that''s the case, I might just redesign this as slightly different.","index":329,"end_time":1266.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1263.84,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So.","index":330,"end_time":1267.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1266.88,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I''ll take this additional step, but go ahead, just think before I move.","index":331,"end_time":1271.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1268,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Keep going.","index":332,"end_time":1271.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1271.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I mean Ashley and I had a conversation about the opportunities in the automation that exist at the DAO level.","index":333,"end_time":1278.71,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1271.84,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So I''m assuming your recommendation is also coming from a place of accounting for the.","index":334,"end_time":1285.03,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1278.71,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"The reconfiguration of any is occurring of that automation.","index":335,"end_time":1288.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1285.43,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So one of the things that I wanted to go over with you guys is essentially that, so when an opportunity, let''s say for example, let''s think about a new customer, a new customer comes into the bank.","index":336,"end_time":1297.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1288.63,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"They, they, we create the customer, then we create a deposit for that customer.","index":337,"end_time":1301.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1297.63,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"One of the things that''s going to happen once the deposit is ready for booking is going to be sent to mulesoft.","index":338,"end_time":1306.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1302.22,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Mulesoft handles that In a completely different process.","index":339,"end_time":1309.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1306.62,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s not this block right here.","index":340,"end_time":1310.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1309.54,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Let''s think about this as the HubSpot API rather so this process right here.","index":341,"end_time":1315.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1310.9,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"The reason I''m putting it here is because after that booking completes, then we''re going to trigger this automation so that it can get sent to Hotspot specifically when it''s a new person.","index":342,"end_time":1326.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1316.62,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":343,"end_time":1326.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1326.46,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So one of the things that you mentioned, Betty, one of the things that happened was a deposit books.","index":344,"end_time":1331.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1327.1,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Things go back to Salesforce.","index":345,"end_time":1332.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.35,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":346,"end_time":1332.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1332.63,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"What happens in Salesforce is basically the deposit gets updated with the finance, with the, with the account number, a couple of other things.","index":347,"end_time":1340.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And that triggers what we call an Apex class.","index":348,"end_time":1342.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1340.79,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Or think about this being a piece of code that kind of syncs the deposit with the financial account.","index":349,"end_time":1348.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1342.99,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Since the deposit, Collins deposits is only used for booking.","index":350,"end_time":1352.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1349.59,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But after his book they don''t.","index":351,"end_time":1354.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1353.03,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Bankers don''t typically go to the deposit anymore.","index":352,"end_time":1356.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1354.47,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"They go to the financial account.","index":353,"end_time":1357.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1356.59,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So this Apex Syncs is going to be in charge of making sure that the financial account exists.","index":354,"end_time":1362.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1358.18,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Once this gets created, the opportunity gets created.","index":355,"end_time":1365.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1362.66,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":356,"end_time":1365.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1365.46,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s already close one most likely I''m going to make sure that this Apex Syncs gets automatically turned on or updated so that when that happens, that opportunity gets updated along with the contact and it brings over that additional information that is on the booking process, meaning containing the data that''s probably from the deposit itself.","index":357,"end_time":1384.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.02,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So that is one of the reasons why I kind of design it this way.","index":358,"end_time":1388.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1385.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So that''s basically just from Salesforce to Hotspot, it gets a little trickier when it comes from HubSpot to Salesforce.","index":359,"end_time":1394.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1388.01,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Because now at this point, and this is what, why I was talking about a little more of my concern with Ashley, is that when something gets created in contact, we need to flag it, right?","index":360,"end_time":1403.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1394.77,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That is going to come over or automatically as a person account or a company.","index":361,"end_time":1407.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404.09,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"A company, of course, is going to be a business.","index":362,"end_time":1410.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1408.41,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So let''s imagine that we create a personal account.","index":363,"end_time":1413.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.09,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Essentially, since it''s a warm lead, we want to also create that opportunity.","index":364,"end_time":1417.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1413.57,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Again, if something books for that opportunity, then that opportunity is going to be updated rather than creating a duplicate.","index":365,"end_time":1424.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1417.89,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That is one of the first things that we want to worry about.","index":366,"end_time":1426.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1424.33,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But then the second part is how do we ensure that the bankers go through the process of selecting that exact contact that was created from the hotspot?","index":367,"end_time":1436.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1426.529,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So that is not an automatic process that I can build.","index":368,"end_time":1439.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1436.69,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I think that''s, that''s something that the bankers are actually going to.","index":369,"end_time":1441.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1439.21,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"They''re going to need some type of help so one of the things that we can do, of course, is branch assignment.","index":370,"end_time":1447.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1443.17,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Depending on the branches that this is going to be sent to, I guess we can do notifications, email notifications on Salesforce, then we can create dashboards and reports so that when they create, or let''s say if they need to create a new one or they need to update that, then they choose that correct action and it goes back to creating the deposit with the right person.","index":371,"end_time":1465.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1447.85,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And so one of the main processes that I''m highlighting here is that record check, of course, and I highlighted as a separate process simply because since it''s going to be a live sync, the most important part is that duplicate avoidance, we want to avoid duplicate creation.","index":372,"end_time":1483.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1466.33,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So record check.","index":373,"end_time":1484.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1483.21,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Like Colin said, The API from HubSpot actually supports a lot of get requests.","index":374,"end_time":1490.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1484.73,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So we can actually do that per object.","index":375,"end_time":1491.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1490.21,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I have to build something that''s adaptive and robust enough so that it doesn''t matter what object we''re trying to update.","index":376,"end_time":1499.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1492.09,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It kind of leverages that same process.","index":377,"end_time":1500.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1499.27,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So it''s very much flexible.","index":378,"end_time":1502.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1501.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I think, like I told actually this is when I''m going to spend a little bit of the bulk of the work rather than spend it here because I know for right now, for the beginning stages of the project, we''re dealing with contacts.","index":379,"end_time":1512.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1502.79,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But once a contact, if this is a robust process, it can easily be copied into the company.","index":380,"end_time":1517.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1512.39,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":381,"end_time":1517.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1517.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So this is more or less of I, you know, kind of highlighting.","index":382,"end_time":1522.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1518.47,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I don''t know if you guys want me to share this.","index":383,"end_time":1524.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1522.71,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It looks a little complex, but, you know, things are happening in Salesforce.","index":384,"end_time":1527.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1524.68,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Again, Victor, this is also something that you mentioned and you can see that the website is going to update already HubSpot.","index":385,"end_time":1533.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1527.84,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m already removing that, that that variable from being updated in Salesforce automatically happens to HubSpot.","index":386,"end_time":1540.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1533.24,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"You guys have your own process.","index":387,"end_time":1541.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1540.6,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m sure there''s more granularity to this.","index":388,"end_time":1544.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1542.52,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I could give you guys access to update this file if you guys want to add more things to it.","index":389,"end_time":1549.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1544.92,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"If you think that''s that''s helpful.","index":390,"end_time":1551.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1549.44,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But yeah, that''s essentially what kind of like the process, how and how it looks like.","index":391,"end_time":1556.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1552.74,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I don''t know if that makes sense for everybody.","index":392,"end_time":1558.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1556.46,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It does.","index":393,"end_time":1559.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1559.22,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"One point that I want to call out, just based on what you''re saying and of course is precisely what I sort of shared with Ashley as well, was my worry that manual component and the potential for duplicates to exist.","index":394,"end_time":1574.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1559.94,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"So again, to use your example, we have this customer that came to be as a result of HubSpot outreach right.","index":395,"end_time":1586.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1574.98,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"We started marketing to them.","index":396,"end_time":1589.94,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1587.62,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"They ultimately became a warm lead and ended up in Salesforce as an opportunity.","index":397,"end_time":1595.7,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1590.34,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Can we consider because we know that we''re going to want the bankers to use that one versus creating the duplicate updating the the main dashboards they have on their home screen.","index":398,"end_time":1610.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1596.74,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Maybe we can create one.","index":399,"end_time":1611.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1610.55,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Although opportunities already populate there because it''s not being assigned to any given banker.","index":400,"end_time":1616.55,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1611.67,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Maybe we can have one that lives in the home screen that''s specific to these marketing opportunities.","index":401,"end_time":1624.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1616.87,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Yes.","index":402,"end_time":1625.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1625.19,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So that we can start, you know, at least for everyone that is at any given branch they all have that branch queue in their home screen so that it''s always visible and we can coach the behavior of if this custom walks in the door, look at that list first before you go and open an account.","index":403,"end_time":1644.61,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1625.71,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Right.","index":404,"end_time":1645.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1645.33,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And so that, that''s, that''s one of the things that I kind of mentioned here.","index":405,"end_time":1649.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1645.73,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Anything that comes over from the contact from HubSpot initially we''ll have some backend field that flags that Right.","index":406,"end_time":1655.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1649.33,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Meal solve will say, you know what, this contact was created in HubSpot so that we can actually filter out all types of reporting and dashboards based on those contacts with that flag.","index":407,"end_time":1664.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1655.89,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":408,"end_time":1664.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1664.29,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Another thing that I will have to flag again I''m thinking about using two flags.","index":409,"end_time":1669.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1666.03,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m still kind of thinking about that process is for that record check.","index":410,"end_time":1672.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1669.39,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":411,"end_time":1672.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1672.11,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"When should something be for example, anything that gets created or imported into the HubSpot we already know that that''s going to be a viz key check.","index":412,"end_time":1680.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1672.59,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":413,"end_time":1680.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1680.39,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s not necessarily going to be an email for a contact that came from HubSpot that viz key is not going to exist.","index":414,"end_time":1686.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1680.59,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"For example.","index":415,"end_time":1687.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1686.83,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Let''s say another scenario that I thought about is for example a contact comes into her salesforce but they don''t book an account right away.","index":416,"end_time":1692.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1687.47,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"What if they change their interest and products and they update that opportun?","index":417,"end_time":1696.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1692.91,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So maybe then that''s when I would need to change that and have this record check based still on email because now the interest change not necessarily that the person doesn''t want to bank anymore for example it''s just something they wanted a seven month city but you know what the banker want to reflect it or even in the case of booking the account that opportunity gets updated to that 12 month city is going to automatically update in contact.","index":418,"end_time":1718.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1696.77,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So you know the way that I''m thinking about this is you know having duplicate, not duplicate but multiple checks so that it knows the system can actually reference when something needs to be checked on hotspot be an email property or the vis key property.","index":419,"end_time":1735.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1718.69,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So working through that but I think as I start putting the pieces together then you know it''ll, it''ll make a little more.","index":420,"end_time":1742.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1735.31,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''ll be a little more robust at least.","index":421,"end_time":1744.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1742.35,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But this is more kind of like more or less what I wanted to show you guys.","index":422,"end_time":1747.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1744.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So to see that, you know.","index":423,"end_time":1749.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1747.87,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Colin, just please, you know, let me know if there''s anything that you see here that might.","index":424,"end_time":1754.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1750.18,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Besides the opportunity part.","index":425,"end_time":1756.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1754.98,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":426,"end_time":1757.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1757.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The only thing here that I think would need to be updated is just the, the lead is.","index":427,"end_time":1762.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1757.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is really going to be more of the lifecycle stage that''s direct, that''s directly updated on the contact object.","index":428,"end_time":1766.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1762.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that cleans up that process.","index":429,"end_time":1768.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1766.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But other than that.","index":430,"end_time":1770.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1769.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m seeing the flows of the related relationships flowing from opportunity into the contact or company object.","index":431,"end_time":1775.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1770.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think we''re all good.","index":432,"end_time":1776.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1775.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s.","index":433,"end_time":1776.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1776.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":434,"end_time":1777.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1777.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then just whatever.","index":435,"end_time":1778.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1777.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If there''s anything that we need to.","index":436,"end_time":1779.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1778.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Provide to help with the sales process on your guys side, happy to do that.","index":437,"end_time":1783.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1779.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":438,"end_time":1785.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1784.4,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":439,"end_time":1785.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1785.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s something that we cannot.","index":440,"end_time":1786.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1785.84,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I think I''m going to have to kind of meet up with Ashley and Betty to see exactly what all the steps that we can.","index":441,"end_time":1793.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1787.2,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"All the, all the processes that we, that we want to.","index":442,"end_time":1796.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1793.2,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"You know, anything that''s kind of like in this way kind of involves a user process.","index":443,"end_time":1800.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1796.64,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I have to highlight what needs to be an automation.","index":444,"end_time":1803.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1801.28,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":445,"end_time":1804.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1804.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do leverage some type of automation for leads and branch assignment already.","index":446,"end_time":1807.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1804.41,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So we might have to just reconstruct that for the content instead of the lead for the contact object and then kind of build those reports and those dashboards so that it makes sense for the user.","index":447,"end_time":1817.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1807.93,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So.","index":448,"end_time":1817.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1817.57,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":449,"end_time":1818.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1818.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this is exactly how my brain thinks Gabe.","index":450,"end_time":1820.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1818.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I like this.","index":451,"end_time":1821.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1820.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":452,"end_time":1821.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1821.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One thing that I don''t know if it''s going to make it simpler or more complicated on your guys infrastructure but if it''s.","index":453,"end_time":1827.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1821.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So a contact comes from HubSpot let''s say they fill out a form they open or that they''re interested in some sort of product.","index":454,"end_time":1834.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1828.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if you want a checkbox or some type of property like that on the salesforce side so that you can just say like okay, these.","index":455,"end_time":1839.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1834.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are the ones from HubSpot.","index":456,"end_time":1840.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1839.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re either checking for email or checking for.","index":457,"end_time":1843.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1840.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well the vis key wouldn''t exist.","index":458,"end_time":1844.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1843.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":459,"end_time":1845.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1844.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So checking for email as that.","index":460,"end_time":1846.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1845.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, yeah that''s essentially what I''m trying to do.","index":461,"end_time":1848.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1846.66,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":462,"end_time":1849.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1848.82,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I kind of highlighted that here on this little comments maybe a little bit.","index":463,"end_time":1852.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1849.1,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":464,"end_time":1853.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1852.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah that''s essentially the, the things that I want to put together again.","index":465,"end_time":1857.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1853.42,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And it all, it all has to do boil down to this process right here.","index":466,"end_time":1860.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1857.1,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"This, this is going to be part of the API.","index":467,"end_time":1861.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1860.14,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But I think, you know, this is kind of like the.","index":468,"end_time":1864.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1861.9,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"This should work for any type of communication that''s happening between any objects of the two systems.","index":469,"end_time":1870.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1864.63,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So that''s essentially I''m trying to build something that''s like adaptive or I call flexible, you know.","index":470,"end_time":1875.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1870.47,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, totally with you.","index":471,"end_time":1877.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1875.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":472,"end_time":1878.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1877.87,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":473,"end_time":1880.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1879.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":474,"end_time":1882.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1882.27,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"All right.","index":475,"end_time":1883.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1882.67,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I think we''re in a great spot then.","index":476,"end_time":1884.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1883.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I love it.","index":477,"end_time":1888.11,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1887.31,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Thanks for letting him take over the meeting to share this but you know, as he was sharing it with me and showing it, I found that it was going to be very helpful and useful for, for all of us to take a look at together.","index":478,"end_time":1900.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1888.47,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"So.","index":479,"end_time":1901.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1900.71,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Yes.","index":480,"end_time":1901.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1901.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":481,"end_time":1902.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1901.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Victor, if you don''t mind just adding this to the SharePoint that we have.","index":482,"end_time":1904.469,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1902.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Access to, that''d be great.","index":483,"end_time":1905.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1904.469,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gabe, as soon as you send it, I got you, I''ll send it over to Colin.","index":484,"end_time":1909.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1906.23,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay, no problem.","index":485,"end_time":1910.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1909.67,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":486,"end_time":1910.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1910.39,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":487,"end_time":1911.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1910.95,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right, any other questions?","index":488,"end_time":1914.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1912.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Productive.","index":489,"end_time":1917.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1916.68,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we''re in a good spot.","index":490,"end_time":1918.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1917.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think once.","index":491,"end_time":1919.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1918.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":492,"end_time":1920.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1919.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Once we have that finalized list from Christina on the properties and then.","index":493,"end_time":1923.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1920.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":494,"end_time":1924.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1924.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gabe, any changes on your guys side from the conversation we just had on the flows, mostly on the salesforce side, just let us know.","index":495,"end_time":1930.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1924.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then lastly and honestly, Gabe and Ashley, you.","index":496,"end_time":1934.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1931.08,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Unless there''s anything more colonate they need to speak on, I think we can let them go for this one.","index":497,"end_time":1940.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1934.72,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we''re in.","index":498,"end_time":1941.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1940.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Especially once Christine updates their super admin.","index":499,"end_time":1943.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1941.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just because we don''t have permission to do that.","index":500,"end_time":1945.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1943.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s fine.","index":501,"end_time":1946.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1945.49,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay, so then Gabe and Ashley, you guys are.","index":502,"end_time":1948.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1946.37,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"You guys are good to go.","index":503,"end_time":1949.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1948.61,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I have a question on the website side of things.","index":504,"end_time":1951.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1949.53,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I don''t want to hold you guys up.","index":505,"end_time":1953.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1952.21,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Well, thank you all.","index":506,"end_time":1955.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1954.77,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Have a great.","index":507,"end_time":1955.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1955.49,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":508,"end_time":1956.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1955.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You as well.","index":509,"end_time":1957.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1956.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Stay safe.","index":510,"end_time":1958.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1957.41,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"If we get another snowstorm.","index":511,"end_time":1959.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1958.01,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":512,"end_time":1963.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1962.69,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"No, I just.","index":513,"end_time":1964.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1963.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On that note, my daughter has her one year appointment today and I just buried or just got my car unburied.","index":514,"end_time":1971.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1964.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh my goodness.","index":515,"end_time":1972.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1971.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I hope the appointment went well.","index":516,"end_time":1976.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1974.37,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Well, yeah, we''re taking her at three o'' clock today.","index":517,"end_time":1978.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1976.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was digging it out last night.","index":518,"end_time":1980.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1978.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was like I''m not gonna have.","index":519,"end_time":1980.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1980.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Time to do this.","index":520,"end_time":1981.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1980.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Very fun.","index":521,"end_time":1983.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1982.61,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":522,"end_time":1985.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1985.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have a good one.","index":523,"end_time":1986.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1985.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so deadline for content because I know that with designs and you know, obviously we''re filling in the blanks when it comes to everything for the website.","index":524,"end_time":1999.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1989.01,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"When.","index":525,"end_time":2000.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2000.52,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m sorry, did.","index":526,"end_time":2002,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2001.24,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Did you need me?","index":527,"end_time":2002.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2002,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"You didn''t call my name out you didn''t dismiss me.","index":528,"end_time":2005.08,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2002.72,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"You''re the head honcho on this.","index":529,"end_time":2007.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2006.12,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"If you want to, you know, tune in, you got.","index":530,"end_time":2010.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2007.72,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"You definitely could, but, you know, I''ll drop.","index":531,"end_time":2012.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2010.16,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":532,"end_time":2013.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2012.8,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":533,"end_time":2014.04,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2013.28,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"Have a great weekend.","index":534,"end_time":2015.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2014.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":535,"end_time":2016.04,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2015.56,"speaker_name":"bettycampiz"},{"text":"For all of the content that you guys need, I know that we want to meet deadlines.","index":536,"end_time":2023.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2018.04,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Realistically, if we reach out to the department heads for their input on their pages with the information that we''re already putting into the website, when would you guys want that so that the website is in a pretty good space so that we can send to senior management?","index":537,"end_time":2037.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2024.36,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I have February 18th that you guys put.","index":538,"end_time":2040.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2038.65,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I mean, February 17th, that I have on your timeline.","index":539,"end_time":2043.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2040.97,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But I just want to make sure and confirm that that works for you guys.","index":540,"end_time":2046.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2043.37,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We might be a little late on that, but I just want to make sure.","index":541,"end_time":2049.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2046.57,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":542,"end_time":2050.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2049.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s the thing.","index":543,"end_time":2050.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2050.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think that date works for us.","index":544,"end_time":2052.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2050.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s just if that shifts, then everything shifts.","index":545,"end_time":2054.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2052.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s.","index":546,"end_time":2055.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2054.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s just been the conversation so far, Right?","index":547,"end_time":2057.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2055.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":548,"end_time":2057.879,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2057.559,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":549,"end_time":2059.719,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2058.199,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So, I mean, and I know there''s a lot of calendars to orchestrate and everything, but the.","index":550,"end_time":2065.639,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2060.199,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The delays have really just been, like.","index":551,"end_time":2067.359,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2065.879,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Scheduling and getting review and approval from the external or the internal team members over there.","index":552,"end_time":2072.199,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2067.359,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got you.","index":553,"end_time":2073.078,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2072.439,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So when do you foresee you guys delivering at least the content on the.","index":554,"end_time":2079.199,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2073.078,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"On the pages initially?","index":555,"end_time":2080.519,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2079.199,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Gia, do you know where we''re at with that?","index":556,"end_time":2082.679,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2081.239,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have, like, five or six pages built, but the designers are doing some of the changes that Christina asked maybe Monday to see.","index":557,"end_time":2094.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2084.85,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"},{"text":"Oh, that''s perfect.","index":558,"end_time":2096.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2095.25,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m over here thinking that you were going to say, like, a week, two weeks now, we''re.","index":559,"end_time":2099.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2096.21,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We''re pretty.","index":560,"end_time":2100.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2099.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re cruising along pretty well.","index":561,"end_time":2101.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2100.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We like to make changes, like, immediately.","index":562,"end_time":2104.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2101.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":563,"end_time":2104.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2104.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the way that we set up, like, the.","index":564,"end_time":2106.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2104.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We designed the homepage because we want to get the direction on that that.","index":565,"end_time":2109.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2106.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then, like, filters into all of the other pages we build.","index":566,"end_time":2111.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2109.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we talked through this, right?","index":567,"end_time":2112.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2111.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, parent page structure, and then the.","index":568,"end_time":2114.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2112.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Content''S really easy to replace.","index":569,"end_time":2115.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2114.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So once we''re locked in on the.","index":570,"end_time":2116.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2115.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Design, we can populate the content pretty easily.","index":571,"end_time":2118.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2116.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":572,"end_time":2121.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2120.09,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So, yeah, as soon as I receive that, I''ll push that over to Christina so that we could get that over to every other department head.","index":573,"end_time":2127.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2121.13,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":574,"end_time":2127.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2127.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll go from there because.","index":575,"end_time":2129.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2127.93,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":576,"end_time":2130.089,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2129.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I saw your email about Google Ads.","index":577,"end_time":2132.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2130.089,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m just going to, I guess, continue to argue with them and see what we can do.","index":578,"end_time":2134.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2132.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, they''re, like, blocking my communications.","index":579,"end_time":2137.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2135.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":580,"end_time":2138.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2138.01,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Christina was telling me that I needed to.","index":581,"end_time":2140.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2138.37,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"That.","index":582,"end_time":2141.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2141.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, she was rather requesting that I reach out to somebody from.","index":583,"end_time":2143.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2141.25,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"From their team.","index":584,"end_time":2145.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2145.05,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I''m like.","index":585,"end_time":2146.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2145.85,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But you guys were already kind of doing it.","index":586,"end_time":2148.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2146.49,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We''ve been doing, but they, like, blocked my account.","index":587,"end_time":2150.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2148.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":588,"end_time":2150.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2150.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re seeing what else.","index":589,"end_time":2151.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2150.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They block you?","index":590,"end_time":2152.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2151.57,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, they.","index":591,"end_time":2153.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2152.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They said I can''t appeal anymore.","index":592,"end_time":2154.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2153.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s crazy.","index":593,"end_time":2156.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2155.77,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":594,"end_time":2157.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2156.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wrote out an appeal for you guys to send, but if you can''t log in, then I don''t know what we''re doing.","index":595,"end_time":2160.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2157.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I logged in, but it''s just.","index":596,"end_time":2163.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2161.05,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay, so if you''re able to hit submit, appeal, and copy and paste what I sent, I think Google also may take it more seriously because you have a Pon bank email.","index":597,"end_time":2170.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2163.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Give me one second.","index":598,"end_time":2172.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2171.89,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Let me log into the page real quick just to make sure I know exactly where I''m going.","index":599,"end_time":2177.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2172.65,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right, let me just share my screen.","index":600,"end_time":2182.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2181.01,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":601,"end_time":2187.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2186.85,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Where also go to Tools on the left.","index":602,"end_time":2189.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2187.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Troubleshooting Policy Manager.","index":603,"end_time":2198.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2194.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Between Google Ads and Facebook.","index":604,"end_time":2203.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2202.14,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":605,"end_time":2204.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2203.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, and then you could actually just hit the contact us button up top.","index":606,"end_time":2208.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2204.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s like where it says that your account is suspended, and then there''s hide and contact us.","index":607,"end_time":2213.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2209.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, gotcha.","index":608,"end_time":2214.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2213.38,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So, yeah, if you had submitted an appeal there, I. I gave you guys.","index":609,"end_time":2219.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2216.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A bunch of text to basically copy and paste into the fields and customer.","index":610,"end_time":2225.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2219.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Company name of the company being advertised.","index":611,"end_time":2229.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2225.82,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":612,"end_time":2230.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2229.82,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So but if you have any questions.","index":613,"end_time":2231.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2230.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just let me know.","index":614,"end_time":2232.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2231.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll take a look at that.","index":615,"end_time":2234.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2232.86,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"At that email, and then I''ll go from there.","index":616,"end_time":2236.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2234.46,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":617,"end_time":2236.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2236.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, thank you.","index":618,"end_time":2237.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2236.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See you, Victor.","index":619,"end_time":2237.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2237.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have a great weekend.","index":620,"end_time":2238.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2237.98,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And be safe.","index":621,"end_time":2239.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2238.74,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right, bye.","index":622,"end_time":2240.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2239.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Except G, because you''re in this.","index":623,"end_time":2242.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2240.54,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Bye.","index":624,"end_time":2244.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2244.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have a good one.","index":625,"end_time":2246.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2245.18,"speaker_name":"Ashlie Taska"}],"dateString":"2026-01-30T15:00:00.000Z","host_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82807622497?pwd=1oWxQKkVvrj4tRTln1UgER5pencHWv.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,gabriel.bencosme@poncebank.net,christina.zanca@poncebank.net,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,ashlie.taska@poncebank.net,betty.campiz@poncebank.net,victor.garcia@poncebank.net","gabriel.bencosme@poncebank.net","christina.zanca@poncebank.net","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","ashlie.taska@poncebank.net","betty.campiz@poncebank.net","victor.garcia@poncebank.net"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFNT5BJ8VMJ6CWHEB58RM6H7","or