    '{"id":"01KFNT5BJ8PJ4QXJADX5E0YQ4W","title":"Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Launch and Email Marketing**\n\nThe campaign launch is set for Monday after finalizing translations and email updates to ensure smooth execution.\n\n- **The campaign launch will occur on Monday** once all final translations and email content are confirmed (05:23)  \n    - The email list has been updated with removals and gender annotations as requested  \n    - Colin confirmed test emails will be sent to Axel, Max, and Bettina to verify formatting and content  \n    - Launch timing avoids Friday to maximize impact and engagement  \n    - Multiple links in emails will point to blogs and testimonials, with landing page links added progressively as the page is developed\n\n- **LinkedIn outreach will start simultaneously with emails** using Bettina’s account to ensure coordinated messaging (31:02)  \n    - Bettina will be informed ahead of launch to prepare for incoming responses  \n    - Ads have been redesigned with stronger eye-catching visuals to boost user engagement on LinkedIn  \n    - Consistent text across ad formats is planned, pending final approval from Max and Axel on preferred versions\n\n## **Landing Page and Website Updates**\n\nThe landing page is ready for development with layouts, images, and text updates targeting bench management and process integration.\n\n- **Landing page translations are complete, and development begins immediately** with some sections (like the explainer video) hidden until ready (07:30)  \n    - Axel provided detailed feedback on images needing replacement or cleanup, especially removing distracting backgrounds or irrelevant screenshots  \n    - Text was adjusted to better align with campaign focus areas like bench management and integration rather than general analytics (10:00)  \n    - Layout fixes include resizing and removing awkward line breaks to improve visual coherence  \n    - Max and Colin agreed to finalize image replacements and text so the updated landing page reflects the campaign themes accurately\n\n- **Website updates target better alignment with campaign messaging and visuals** aiming for completion by Monday (31:26)  \n    - Natalie is assigned to update images and layouts on the website to match campaign style and content  \n    - The team plans to replace low-resolution or confusing screenshots with clearer, branded visuals that reflect the actual platform experience  \n    - Max will review and supply new screenshots for the video and website to improve clarity and consistency\n\n## **Explainer Video Production and Localization**\n\nThe explainer video will be produced first in English, then localized into German, with a clear workflow for translation and feedback.\n\n- **English video production starts immediately with a plan for a German version to follow** considering length and synchronization differences between languages (18:33)  \n    - The script is in Google Slides format, allowing easy translation and collaborative feedback  \n    - Video will be produced using Adobe Illustrator, Photoshop, Premiere, and After Effects for high-quality visuals and animation (21:01)  \n    - The team will use the Frame tool for timestamped feedback on translation and content adjustments, improving review efficiency  \n    - Axel expressed concern about longer German text potentially affecting timing, so close coordination during localization is planned\n\n- **Video visuals require new, high-resolution screenshots and clearer storyboarding** to avoid confusing overlays and unrelated backgrounds (22:48)  \n    - Colin clarified the video uses screenshots mimicking mouse movements for transitions, not actual video footage, to simplify production  \n    - Max will provide new screenshots to replace unclear or outdated ones, ensuring the video accurately represents the platform  \n    - The team aims for visuals that complement the text and create a cohesive narrative that supports the campaign’s messaging\n\n## **Benchmark Analysis Report Initiative**\n\nA new benchmark report offer is being developed to attract prospects by comparing their utilization and skills data with industry standards.\n\n- **The benchmark report will collect five key data points from prospects** and generate an automated PDF comparing them to industry averages (26:20)  \n    - Target audience is resource managers who would value insights on utilization, bench health, and staffing efficiency  \n    - The report uses Desi Dollo branding and PSA patterns to illustrate growth and scaling opportunities using the platform  \n    - Colin noted an option in the form for users to select “I don’t know” to funnel uncertain respondents into demo calls, increasing lead qualification  \n    - The report will be hosted on a subdomain and linked to from LinkedIn ads for lead capture, requiring email addresses for follow-up (29:14)\n\n- **Data source concerns were raised regarding proprietary vs. external data** with Axel uncertain if Desi Dollo data represents an industry benchmark (27:45)  \n    - Colin offered to share the draft report and data model for review and feedback  \n    - The initiative aims to generate qualified leads by providing valuable, personalized insights that align with Desi Dollo’s value proposition\n\n## **Operational Tools and Access**\n\nAccess and integration challenges were discussed regarding automation tools and data management systems.\n\n- **Max does not yet have access to the N8N workflow environment** due to configuration restrictions on the shared private server (29:53)  \n    - Colin explained the system is shared among all customers but separated by folders for security and organization  \n    - Max will follow up in a separate meeting with Colin to deep dive into the N8N flow and related questions (31:21)  \n    - Clay exports will be shared to provide data visibility as needed, supporting ongoing collaboration and troubleshooting\n\n- **The team plans to finalize ad text and images quickly** to enable sending test emails and monitoring campaign performance (30:42)  \n    - Once content is locked, test emails will validate formatting and user experience before full campaign launch  \n    - Feedback loops are in place to incorporate adjustments rapidly and keep the timeline on track  \n\n","outline":null,"keywords":["Landing Page","Explainer Video","LinkedIn Ads","Benchmark Report","Email Campaign","Resource Management"],"overview":"- **Campaign Launch:** Launch set for Monday after finalizing translations; email list updated with removals and gender annotations.  \n- **LinkedIn Outreach:** Begins with email launch; ads redesigned for better engagement, consistent messaging pending final approvals.  \n- **Landing Page Development:** Ready to start; translations complete, focusing on bench management and integration with adjustments made.  \n- **Explainer Video Production:** English video to start soon, German version will follow; emphasis on clear visuals and storyboarding discussed.  \n- **Benchmark Report Initiative:** New report to analyze five data points from prospects; aims to attract resource managers and generate leads.  \n- **Access Challenges:** Max lacks access to N8N workflow environment; team plans to finalize ad content for email test monitoring.","action_items":"\n**Axel Völker**\nReview and agree on final versions of ad texts and images with Max and Colin (13:48)\nProvide updated or new screenshots from the current application for video production (22:41)\nCoordinate with Max to select best screenshots for the video storyboard (25:00)\nInform Bettina about upcoming LinkedIn outreach and email campaigns launching next week (31:05)\n\n**Maximilian Rabeler**\nReview and agree on ad text versions with Axel and Colin (15:52)\nMeet separately with Colin to discuss N8N flow in detail (31:21)\nAssist in reviewing and selecting updated screenshots for video (25:32)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend test emails of updated campaign to Axel, Max, and Bettina (07:11)\nDevelop landing page with updated images and feedback incorporated, aiming for completion by Monday (31:38)\nShare Google Slide video storyboard with Axel and team for translation and feedback (20:33)\nProduce first English cut of explainer video, then schedule German version production (19:27)\nProvide tool access (Frame) for video feedback with timestamped comments (21:25)\nUpdate video screenshots based on new images provided by Axel and Max (24:00)\nShare draft of utilization and skills benchmark report for review and feedback (28:56)\nLaunch LinkedIn ads and email outreach simultaneously from Bettina’s account early next week (31:02)\n\n**Natalie B.**\nUpdate landing page images and content as per feedback by Monday (31:41)\nAssist Colin with scheduling video production workload details (19:38)\n"},"duration":32.43000030517578,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":3,"name":"MaximilianRabeler"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Axel.","index":0,"end_time":283.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":1,"end_time":288.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":287.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":2,"end_time":289.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":289.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":3,"end_time":291.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":289.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right.","index":4,"end_time":291.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So.","index":5,"end_time":295.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":295.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hi, Max.","index":6,"end_time":299.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":298.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hey.","index":7,"end_time":301.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":301.15,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Anyone else joining from your side?","index":8,"end_time":305.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":303.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Natalie B.","index":9,"end_time":306.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Joining.","index":10,"end_time":307.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She just had a.","index":11,"end_time":308.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":307.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To restart a computer.","index":12,"end_time":309.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what''s the overall status?","index":13,"end_time":313.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":311.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m a bit lost because we''re doing so much stuff in parallel, but nothing''s really finished yet.","index":14,"end_time":320.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":313.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So when.","index":15,"end_time":320.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":320.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"When can we start?","index":16,"end_time":321.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":320.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Do we have to.","index":17,"end_time":322.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":321.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"The timeline?","index":18,"end_time":323.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":322.63,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Well, that''s what I wanted to talk about today.","index":19,"end_time":325.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":323.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we have like the final translations and everything for the emails and ads that we''ve sent over, then we''re good to hit launch on this campaign.","index":20,"end_time":333.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think Friday is a great day to launch, so I would just turn it on on Monday.","index":21,"end_time":337.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we have the landing page.","index":22,"end_time":340.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have all the feedback built into it.","index":23,"end_time":342.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can just now begin actually developing it.","index":24,"end_time":344.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":342.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll just hide the explainer video section until that video is ready.","index":25,"end_time":348.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":344.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":26,"end_time":351.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":350.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I have a lot of questions around the video.","index":27,"end_time":354.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":351.88,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Also on the website.","index":28,"end_time":357.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":355.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think we need the website probably for the campaign, for the ads on.","index":29,"end_time":364.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":359.64,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because they''re.","index":30,"end_time":364.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":364.1,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They''re pointing to the website or to the landing page or is that going?","index":31,"end_time":369.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":365.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, so we.","index":32,"end_time":371.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have several different links throughout the email, some of them pointing to different blogs speaking about utilization and things like that.","index":33,"end_time":377.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also pointing to testimonials on the website.","index":34,"end_time":382.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":378.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I didn''t want that to hold, like the new landing page to hold us back from launching this campaign.","index":35,"end_time":387.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":383.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can always add in the.","index":36,"end_time":389.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":387.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Change the sequence to add in a link to the landing page as it''s developed.","index":37,"end_time":393.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":389.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":38,"end_time":394.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":393.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And the email, is that set up so with the updated list we gave you and.","index":39,"end_time":402.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":395.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yep, updated list, updated content.","index":40,"end_time":404.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":402.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you removed the ones that we highlighted, basically, and.","index":41,"end_time":411.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":406.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yes.","index":42,"end_time":411.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":411.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You added the gender, like this annotation.","index":43,"end_time":415.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":411.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":44,"end_time":415.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yep.","index":45,"end_time":416.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.57,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Can we send like a test mail to ourselves to see how that comes out?","index":46,"end_time":422.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":417.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, we can do that.","index":47,"end_time":424.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":423.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that will be good