INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
  '## **Campaign Launch and Email Marketing**

The campaign launch is set for Monday after finalizing translations and email updates to ensure smooth execution.

- **The campaign launch will occur on Monday** once all final translations and email content are confirmed (05:23)  
    - The email list has been updated with removals and gender annotations as requested  
    - Colin confirmed test emails will be sent to Axel, Max, and Bettina to verify formatting and content  
    - Launch timing avoids Friday to maximize impact and engagement  
    - Multiple links in emails will point to blogs and testimonials, with landing page links added progressively as the page is developed

- **LinkedIn outreach will start simultaneously with emails** using Bettina’s account to ensure coordinated messaging (31:02)  
    - Bettina will be informed ahead of launch to prepare for incoming responses  
    - Ads have been redesigned with stronger eye-catching visuals to boost user engagement on LinkedIn  
    - Consistent text across ad formats is planned, pending final approval from Max and Axel on preferred versions

## **Landing Page and Website Updates**

The landing page is ready for development with layouts, images, and text updates targeting bench management and process integration.

- **Landing page translations are complete, and development begins immediately** with some sections (like the explainer video) hidden until ready (07:30)  
    - Axel provided detailed feedback on images needing replacement or cleanup, especially removing distracting backgrounds or irrelevant screenshots  
    - Text was adjusted to better align with campaign focus areas like bench management and integration rather than general analytics (10:00)  
    - Layout fixes include resizing and removing awkward line breaks to improve visual coherence  
    - Max and Colin agreed to finalize image replacements and text so the updated landing page reflects the campaign themes accurately

- **Website updates target better alignment with campaign messaging and visuals** aiming for completion by Monday (31:26)  
    - Natalie is assigned to update images and layouts on the website to match campaign style and content  
    - The team plans to replace low-resolution or confusing screenshots with clearer, branded visuals that reflect the actual platform experience  
    - Max will review and supply new screenshots for the video and website to improve clarity and consistency

## **Explainer Video Production and Localization**

The explainer video will be produced first in English, then localized into German, with a clear workflow for translation and feedback.

- **English video production starts immediately with a plan for a German version to follow** considering length and synchronization differences between languages (18:33)  
    - The script is in Google Slides format, allowing easy translation and collaborative feedback  
    - Video will be produced using Adobe Illustrator, Photoshop, Premiere, and After Effects for high-quality visuals and animation (21:01)  
    - The team will use the Frame tool for timestamped feedback on translation and content adjustments, improving review efficiency  
    - Axel expressed concern about longer German text potentially affecting timing, so close coordination during localization is planned

- **Video visuals require new, high-resolution screenshots and clearer storyboarding** to avoid confusing overlays and unrelated backgrounds (22:48)  
    - Colin clarified the video uses screenshots mimicking mouse movements for transitions, not actual video footage, to simplify production  
    - Max will provide new screenshots to replace unclear or outdated ones, ensuring the video accurately represents the platform  
    - The team aims for visuals that complement the text and create a cohesive narrative that supports the campaign’s messaging

## **Benchmark Analysis Report Initiative**

A new benchmark report offer is being developed to attract prospects by comparing their utilization and skills data with industry standards.

- **The benchmark report will collect five key data points from prospects** and generate an automated PDF comparing them to industry averages (26:20)  
    - Target audience is resource managers who would value insights on utilization, bench health, and staffing efficiency  
    - The report uses Desi Dollo branding and PSA patterns to illustrate growth and scaling opportunities using the platform  
    - Colin noted an option in the form for users to select “I don’t know” to funnel uncertain respondents into demo calls, increasing lead qualification  
    - The report will be hosted on a subdomain and linked to from LinkedIn ads for lead capture, requiring email addresses for follow-up (29:14)

- **Data source concerns were raised regarding proprietary vs. external data** with Axel uncertain if Desi Dollo data represents an industry benchmark (27:45)  
    - Colin offered to share the draft report and data model for review and feedback  
    - The initiative aims to generate qualified leads by providing valuable, personalized insights that align with Desi Dollo’s value proposition

## **Operational Tools and Access**

Access and integration challenges were discussed regarding automation tools and data management systems.

- **Max does not yet have access to the N8N workflow environment** due to configuration restrictions on the shared private server (29:53)  
    - Colin explained the system is shared among all customers but separated by folders for security and organization  
    - Max will follow up in a separate meeting with Colin to deep dive into the N8N flow and related questions (31:21)  
    - Clay exports will be shared to provide data visibility as needed, supporting ongoing collaboration and troubleshooting

- **The team plans to finalize ad text and images quickly** to enable sending test emails and monitoring campaign performance (30:42)  
    - Once content is locked, test emails will validate formatting and user experience before full campaign launch  
    - Feedback loops are in place to incorporate adjustments rapidly and keep the timeline on track  

