_id":1,"start_time":711.09,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Yeah, I.","index":152,"end_time":723.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":722.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"My guess would be.","index":153,"end_time":724.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":723.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I''m.","index":154,"end_time":726.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":725.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I''m gonna guess title.","index":155,"end_time":727.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":726.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I haven''t seen Rajiv post anything.","index":156,"end_time":731.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":727.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Actually, I haven''t seen any of the three post anything about it.","index":157,"end_time":735.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":731.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"But operational excellence is such a common manufacturing term.","index":158,"end_time":739.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":736.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I wonder if that has any.","index":159,"end_time":742.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, probably.","index":160,"end_time":745.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.05,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Also something that I noticed is that the video, the short videos from the episode with Julia Atkins, those are getting really good views.","index":161,"end_time":754.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":745.25,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"But the full episode from Rajiv is the one with.","index":162,"end_time":758.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":755.79,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"That is growing by week over week.","index":163,"end_time":762.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":759.23,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So that''s interesting.","index":164,"end_time":763.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":762.27,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Okay, so now for the review section.","index":165,"end_time":772.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":768.27,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Thanks so much for approving this.","index":166,"end_time":774.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":772.91,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"We will include it in the next episode and see if we can start seeing some reviews coming in.","index":167,"end_time":781.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":774.91,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Right now we don''t have any new reviews.","index":168,"end_time":783.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":781.31,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":169,"end_time":784.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":783.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So.","index":170,"end_time":784.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":784.29,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"But we''ll keep an eye out for.","index":171,"end_time":786.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":784.65,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"For those.","index":172,"end_time":786.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":786.13,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"For the outreach campaign.","index":173,"end_time":792.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":790.37,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"The campaign already finished on Smart Lead.","index":174,"end_time":795.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":793.25,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"The open rate was 45%.","index":175,"end_time":798.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":796.05,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"And sorry from Hay Ridge, the connection acceptance rate is 45.","index":176,"end_time":804.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":799.649,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"And we got two replays to replace Sorry from Nikita and Nazaire.","index":177,"end_time":810.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":805.41,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"I know Nasser is trying to schedule some time with you, Josh.","index":178,"end_time":813.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":810.49,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"I don''t know if you had a chance to see the latest message from him.","index":179,"end_time":818.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":813.89,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"I reached out to him.","index":180,"end_time":821.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":820.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, I think he said that he has some issues with the scheduling link, so.","index":181,"end_time":827.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.73,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":182,"end_time":827.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":827.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, I see he responded.","index":183,"end_time":829.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":827.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll have to.","index":184,"end_time":832.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":831.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I don''t know what it''s.","index":185,"end_time":833.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":832.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Because the.","index":186,"end_time":834.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":833.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"The other Natika had a.","index":187,"end_time":842.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":839.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Had no problem.","index":188,"end_time":843.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":842.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, I will reach out to Nikita again and see if she''s gets interesting on scheduling.","index":189,"end_time":850.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":844.68,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Well, she.","index":190,"end_time":851.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":850.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"She did schedule.","index":191,"end_time":852.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":851.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I just emailed her because I noticed she was in Spain and so the time she scheduled for would be super late her time on a Friday.","index":192,"end_time":862.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":853.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So I asked her if she wanted okay to move it.","index":193,"end_time":866.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":863.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":194,"end_time":869.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":867.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Is any of them the ones that are scheduled for Friday or is that different Guys with schedule on Friday?","index":195,"end_time":874.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.37,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Nikita, Natica.","index":196,"end_time":878.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":876.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"She.","index":197,"end_time":879.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":878.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"She wrote Natika in her.","index":198,"end_time":880.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":879.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":199,"end_time":882.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":881.37,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Email schedule for Friday to have that overview discussion.","index":200,"end_time":889.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":882.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"But really need to fill the pipeline because we''re were dry and without that then just look at like.","index":201,"end_time":900.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":890.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Like a Blog post like Sydney had asked for, like we''ve done before.","index":202,"end_time":906.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":901.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":203,"end_time":909.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":909.28,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Bailey, I don''t know if we should start creating a new contact list for next.","index":204,"end_time":917.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":910.4,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we should definitely get something rolling again.","index":205,"end_time":921.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just depends on what approach we want to take.","index":206,"end_time":924.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do we want to try this personalized approach again, or do we want to do a large list and see where that gets us?","index":207,"end_time":932.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, well, it doesn''t seem like the targeted approach in this example yielded too much, so I''m kind of inclined to just do a broader.","index":208,"end_time":946.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":933.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"A broader net.","index":209,"end_time":949.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":948.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we could do.","index":210,"end_time":951.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":950.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You had that, like, big HubSpot list that you gave us.","index":211,"end_time":956.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":953.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we can just pick, like, a different segment of contacts from that.","index":212,"end_time":960.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":956.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We also could even consider, like, reaching out to people again who we''ve contacted before if you wanted.","index":213,"end_time":970.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":961.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, I think enough time has passed for some of those people.","index":214,"end_time":972.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":970.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s worth poking them again.","index":215,"end_time":974.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":972.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, it''s been a couple months.","index":216,"end_time":976.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":974.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you.","index":217,"end_time":978.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you have any preference that one?","index":218,"end_time":980.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We could probably stand up a bit faster because we wouldn''t need to, like, refresh any lists or anything.","index":219,"end_time":986.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":980.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, we can use what we have and just filter out people who have booked or responded and just get a slightly different messaging.","index":220,"end_time":994.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":986.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that''s fine.","index":221,"end_time":996.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":994.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Would be great.","index":222,"end_time":999.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":997.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that.","index":223,"end_time":1001.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1000,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That one''s definitely a lot quicker to go that route.","index":224,"end_time":1004.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1001.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":225,"end_time":1007.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1006.38,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So we can get started on that then.","index":226,"end_time":1009.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1007.34,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Good.","index":227,"end_time":1012.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1012.14,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Now for the video plant, our team is prioritizing the product cover B video based on the latest feedback that you share for the OTG training, taking in consideration all of those comments.","index":228,"end_time":1024.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1013.1,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So we''re working on it.","index":229,"end_time":1026.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1025.34,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"But also we want to talk with you about some issues we have with the rest of the videos in terms of timing.","index":230,"end_time":1036.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1026.78,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Like, some.","index":231,"end_time":1038.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1037.13,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"The voiceover audio is not matching with the current frames that we have.","index":232,"end_time":1042.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1038.09,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So our team suggested just to cut out some.","index":233,"end_time":1045.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1042.89,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Some frames.","index":234,"end_time":1046.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1046.01,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"But I don''t know what are your thoughts of which we''ll redo the voiceover or what is your preference on this?","index":235,"end_time":1056.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1047.93,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Because we want to have, like, a lot of gaps on the rest of the videos in terms of audio and frames.","index":236,"end_time":1063.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1056.81,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"With the audio and frame gaps, that''s due to timing of the product demos themselves.","index":237,"end_time":1078.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1068.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yes.","index":238,"end_time":1079.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1078.74,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"So what I would like to do is we keep the, like, voiceover stuff as is because, like, the.","index":239,"end_time":1090.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1079.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"The length of that is as much as, like, as far as we could push the timing of the video.","index":240,"end_time":1098.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1090.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"You know, I think the longest one was like three and a half minutes.","index":241,"end_time":1101.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1099.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I really don''t want to go over that time frame.","index":242,"end_time":1105.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1102.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So then that puts us into.","index":243,"end_time":1108.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1106.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay, what are things that we can simplify and cut.","index":244,"end_time":1111.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1108.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So then I don''t know.","index":245,"end_time":1121,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1117.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I think I''d have to see it on a.","index":246,"end_time":1123.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1121.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Almost a case by case thing.","index":247,"end_time":1124.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1123.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":248,"end_time":1130.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1129.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":249,"end_time":1132.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1131.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Probably we can reshare the metaboards and you can just choose the frames that we can probably just.","index":250,"end_time":1139.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1132.16,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Good.","index":251,"end_time":1140.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1140.03,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"From the final video.","index":252,"end_time":1141.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1140.23,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"I know there are a lot with text that we don''t need it.","index":253,"end_time":1144.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1141.63,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Instead of removing the.","index":254,"end_time":1146.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1144.99,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"What star is showing the platform itself.","index":255,"end_time":1148.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1146.91,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":256,"end_time":1150.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1149.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"The priority for me visually would be getting to the product as quickly as we can, you know.","index":257,"end_time":1158.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1150.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":258,"end_time":1159.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1158.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you wanted we could leave like a few comments in frame to suggest maybe some sections that could be trimmed so we could take a first pass at it and you can let us know if that makes sense or if you want to do something else.","index":259,"end_time":1174.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":260,"end_time":1175.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1174.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And then I guess some of the other piece would be.","index":261,"end_time":1180.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1178.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"How do we.","index":262,"end_time":1180.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1180.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":263,"end_time":1191.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1190.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I will say the product overview video.","index":264,"end_time":1193.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1191.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Paul and I saw the first cut already and it''s not an issue with that one.","index":265,"end_time":1198.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1194.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"1 like the timing on that one seems to match up pretty well from what we could tell.","index":266,"end_time":1203.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1198.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But I mean the, the one we''ve already sent you, the on the job training one is.","index":267,"end_time":1208.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1203.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean.","index":268,"end_time":1209.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1208.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":269,"end_time":1210.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1209.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There''s some blank space there.","index":270,"end_time":1212.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1210.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":271,"end_time":1212.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1212.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":272,"end_time":1214.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1214.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"When I was listening to it, I was wondering, you know, thinking about like, what are the things that we can cut out visually to get to the.","index":273,"end_time":1225.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1215.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"The product piece.","index":274,"end_time":1226.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1225.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Some of that might be the exposition at the beginning of each video.","index":275,"end_time":1234.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1227.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":276,"end_time":1236.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1235.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I don''t know if I can think of a general rule.","index":277,"end_time":1239.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1237.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"The more that we can make the visuals of the product match the talking points of those things and from there we can explore like.","index":278,"end_time":1249.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1240.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Does that mean we need to speed up some of the visuals with the product or not?","index":279,"end_time":1260.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1252.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll just have to look at them together, maybe even live and just like as we''re watching them together, like collaborate on pieces too.","index":280,"end_time":1272.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1262.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":281,"end_time":1276.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1276.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":282,"end_time":1277.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1277.31,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Do you want to like schedule another meeting and we can try to watch it together or.","index":283,"end_time":1284.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1278.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean we have a few minutes left still.","index":284,"end_time":1287.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1285.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We could try and do that now.","index":285,"end_time":1288.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1287.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":286,"end_time":1289.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1289.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I. I can share my screen.","index":287,"end_time":1301.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1300.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Unless you have it.","index":288,"end_time":1302.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1301.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Paula, you can do it.","index":289,"end_time":1304.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1303.25,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Let me know if you can hear.","index":290,"end_time":1320.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1319.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No.","index":291,"end_time":1323.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1322.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"No.","index":292,"end_time":1323.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1323.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":293,"end_time":1328.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1323.61,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"On the plant floor.","index":294,"end_time":1331.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1330.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Training and knowledge gaps are a common driver of process non conformances leading to defects, scrap and production delays.","index":295,"end_time":1340.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1332.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Current corrective training methods make it hard to stop the same issues from recurring because when a non conformance is found, the workflow breaks down.","index":296,"end_time":1350.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1341.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Supervisors follow up manually operate, operators are trained informally and the details are recorded.","index":297,"end_time":1357.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1351.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"On paper.","index":298,"end_time":1357.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1357.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Without verification, you can''t tell whether the training truly corrected the issue or whether the trainee understood and can apply it in practice.","index":299,"end_time":1367.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1358.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s where ease on the job training comes in.","index":300,"end_time":1370.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1367.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Unlike learning management systems, ease on the job training is built for the plant floor where the work happens and standards are applied every day.","index":301,"end_time":1379.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1371.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It gives every operator on demand access to the training and knowledge they need and helps supervisors document and deliver the know how that keeps operations running safely, efficiently and consistently.","index":302,"end_time":1392.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1380.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"A corporate email isn''t required, so every operator, technician and team member can participate, not just salaried.","index":303,"end_time":1400.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1393.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Staff training becomes part of daily operations, closing the gap between knowledge and performance.","index":304,"end_time":1406.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1400.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll just pause here before we get too deep.","index":305,"end_time":1409.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1407.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I see there''s like already a lot of comments on this that I think capture a lot of things, but is there anything else?","index":306,"end_time":1415.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1409.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just taking another look at.","index":307,"end_time":1416.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1415.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"At it.","index":308,"end_time":1417.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1417.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I think just cutting exposition, the setup and stuff.","index":309,"end_time":1424.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1418.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"You know, simplify, like we hit certain points, remove other points to like, trim.","index":310,"end_time":1431.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1425.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Down the script a bit more.","index":311,"end_time":1433.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1431.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, just cut out some stuff.","index":312,"end_time":1435.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1433.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like I think it was like on the screen for a pretty long time.","index":313,"end_time":1438.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1435.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So this would probably be a section.","index":314,"end_time":1440.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1438.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":315,"end_time":1440.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1440.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":316,"end_time":1441.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1440.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay, so that sounds good.","index":317,"end_time":1444.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1442.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can.","index":318,"end_time":1445.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1444.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we''ll just go like back to our script document and maybe suggest a few areas that we can cut.","index":319,"end_time":1450.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1445.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":320,"end_time":1452.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1452.33,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Then anything else that was the big.","index":321,"end_time":1455.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1452.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"One is just cutting some of those things because we''re a minute 15 and.","index":322,"end_time":1460.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1455.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And we haven''t like, even really gotten to the product demo.","index":323,"end_time":1464.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1461.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re just gonna have to like, you know, like, try to find a way of 10 to 15 seconds max of like the setup.","index":324,"end_time":1473.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1464.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And then boom, we''re into the.","index":325,"end_time":1476.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1473.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"The product side of things.","index":326,"end_time":1478.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1477.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And hopefully we can use the recording Patrick had already done, because I think the way he delivers things is fine.","index":327,"end_time":1485.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1479.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"We just cut certain things out.","index":328,"end_time":1487.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1485.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I know that that has implications on the audio side of things.","index":329,"end_time":1490.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1487.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I''m hoping for the most part, the, you know, the.","index":330,"end_time":1496.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1490.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"The what.","index":331,"end_time":1497.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1496.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"What we''re looking for with that should still be pretty true, which is just that, like build up, repeating, et cetera.","index":332,"end_time":1503.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1497.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":333,"end_time":1504,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1503.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Of the music.","index":334,"end_time":1504.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1504,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Whoever did.","index":335,"end_time":1505.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1505.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I felt like whoever did the action plans audio, like if.","index":336,"end_time":1512.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1506.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"If these were different people working on it.","index":337,"end_time":1514.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1512.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Whoever did the action plans music and talk track, that one clicked the best in my perspective.","index":338,"end_time":1522.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1514.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it was the same person.","index":339,"end_time":1524.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1522.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, really?","index":340,"end_time":1525.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1524.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, the same person.","index":341,"end_time":1527.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1525.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There''s like a totally different approach.","index":342,"end_time":1529.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1527.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Like, if you listen to the music, there''s in on the job training one.","index":343,"end_time":1533.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1529.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And specifically the part that repeats is this part that like builds up and so cuts off, builds up, cuts off, builds up, cuts off.","index":344,"end_time":1540.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1533.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Whereas in the action plans one, that one it''s just.","index":345,"end_time":1542.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1540.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"You know, it''s more consistent.","index":346,"end_time":1546.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1544.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s not rebuilding.","index":347,"end_time":1548.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1546.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, it''s not okay.","index":348,"end_time":1550.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1548.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"But anyway.","index":349,"end_time":1551.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1550.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":350,"end_time":1551.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1551.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So you know, we have to get to the product as quickly as we can.","index":351,"end_time":1555.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1551.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Give us maybe 15 seconds of setup and we''ll just start cutting out things from there.","index":352,"end_time":1564.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1555.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Do you want to keep watching?","index":353,"end_time":1567.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1565.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Not really.","index":354,"end_time":1573.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1572.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I will but.","index":355,"end_time":1574.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1573.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"We don''t have to if you don''t want to.","index":356,"end_time":1578.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1576.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Josh, if you want Paul and I, we can go in and, and make our recommendations to the team and, and then get your sign off on it.","index":357,"end_time":1586.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1578.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, well if we have the scripts, I can look at the scripts.","index":358,"end_time":1591.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1586.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I actually have them here.","index":359,"end_time":1594.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1592.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So we''ll go to the on the job training one in particular.","index":360,"end_time":1601.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1598.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So I feel like.","index":361,"end_time":1615.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1614.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Defects, scrap and production delays.","index":362,"end_time":1630.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1627.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Now I''m hesitating.","index":363,"end_time":1642.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1641.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I think there''s something in here to cut out, maybe even this.","index":364,"end_time":1649.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1642.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"My only concern is leading to defects, scrap, production delays.","index":365,"end_time":1654.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1650.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I mean I think it could make sense to go from here.","index":366,"end_time":1660.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1657.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"That''s where ease on the job training comes in.","index":367,"end_time":1663.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1660.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, that, that''s what I was thinking.","index":368,"end_time":1668.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1663.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we could cut out that whole middle piece.","index":369,"end_time":1670.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1668.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":370,"end_time":1672.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1671.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"We''ll say red for now unlike.","index":371,"end_time":1678.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1672.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So I think.","index":372,"end_time":1682.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1681.639,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"The work happens, standards are applied every.","index":373,"end_time":1689.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1686.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I guess every training becomes part of daily operations.","index":374,"end_time":1698.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1695.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So I think we can probably kill that.","index":375,"end_time":1702.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1700.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"But in non conformity identified training is often part of follow up ease connects train directly, find trainees, review material.","index":376,"end_time":1711.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1703.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So this would be like product demo happening here.","index":377,"end_time":1716.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1712.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":378,"end_time":1717.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1717.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And we''ll see.","index":379,"end_time":1721.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1720.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I think, I think, I think after this point I think this stuff went fine.","index":380,"end_time":1730.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1723.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Some timing here.","index":381,"end_time":1734.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1733.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I think we could probably.","index":382,"end_time":1742.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1741.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I remember this one just kind of sounding awkward and not matching visually and so we could get rid of that.","index":383,"end_time":1751.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1742.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Let''s.","index":384,"end_time":1759.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1759.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Let''s maybe try it that way.","index":385,"end_time":1761.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1759.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"You know, so we cut out that stuff, help us get to the product faster, less need for stock materials and then I don''t know, maybe we just have to look at the other ones as well while we''re here.","index":386,"end_time":1777.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1762.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds great.","index":387,"end_time":1780.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1779.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It depends.","index":388,"end_time":1781.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1780.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I mean if you''ve seen them and if you''ve got a feel for if.","index":389,"end_time":1784.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1781.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Things the other ones aren''t ready yet.","index":390,"end_time":1786.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1784.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So.","index":391,"end_time":1787.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1786.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":392,"end_time":1788.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1788.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So we, I would imagine they run into the same.","index":393,"end_time":1791.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1788.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":394,"end_time":1793.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1793.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"At least with maybe too much exposition up front.","index":395,"end_time":1797.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1794.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":396,"end_time":1798.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1798.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And yeah if we can trim stuff now it''ll save our team time as they''re.","index":397,"end_time":1803.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1798.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They''re tackling these.","index":398,"end_time":1805.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1804.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Potentially get rid of that one.","index":399,"end_time":1818.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1816.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Do you all still have time or you gotta run.","index":400,"end_time":1837.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1834.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I can keep going through this.","index":401,"end_time":1838.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1837.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yes.","index":402,"end_time":1839.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1838.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, I''ve got.","index":403,"end_time":1839.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1839.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ve got some time right now.","index":404,"end_time":1841.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1839.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":405,"end_time":1843.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1843.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"There may be a cut in here somewhere.","index":406,"end_time":1862.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1860.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what I was thinking too.","index":407,"end_time":1866.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1864.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we got to keep this.","index":408,"end_time":1868.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1866.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Most manufacturers silver line manual, disconnect the tools.","index":409,"end_time":1870.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1868.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I like that.","index":410,"end_time":1872.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1871.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"We are calling stuff out by name and then we''re talking about what the problem is with it and the impact of those problems.","index":411,"end_time":1882.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1872.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So I''m having a hard time of finding.","index":412,"end_time":1883.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1882.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"A cut there.","index":413,"end_time":1889.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1888.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Potentially this one, I would love to keep it, but ease changes that, huh?","index":414,"end_time":1900.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1894.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And then.","index":415,"end_time":1901.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1900.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, as long as this would really depend on the flow of the product.","index":416,"end_time":1909.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1904.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Visuals here, Maybe this.","index":417,"end_time":1921.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1909.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Oh, but that was our segue here.","index":418,"end_time":1931.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1929.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":419,"end_time":1932.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1931.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Signals that point to risk.","index":420,"end_time":1935.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1933.78,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Easier for the trends look over to find it.","index":421,"end_time":1938.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1936.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"The signals that point to risk.","index":422,"end_time":1939.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1938.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I think that''s fine.","index":423,"end_time":1944.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1943.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"That visibility comes from a new digital experience built for the front line.","index":424,"end_time":1947.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1944.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I think we could potentially kill this transition too.","index":425,"end_time":1953.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1950.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So the signals that point to risk.","index":426,"end_time":1956.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1954.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And now we''re going to the library.","index":427,"end_time":1957.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1956.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"These auto inspections are easy to digitize, standardize and reuse across shifts and sites.","index":428,"end_time":1962.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1957.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"These are all pretty specific.","index":429,"end_time":1964.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1963.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Let''s try, I guess.","index":430,"end_time":1988.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1987.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Let''s try with that.","index":431,"end_time":1989.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1988.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I forgot what our screen is here.","index":432,"end_time":1995.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1992.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I can grab the Miro board if that helps.","index":433,"end_time":2007.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2005.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just sent the mirror board in the chat.","index":434,"end_time":2024.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2022.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":435,"end_time":2026.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2025.7,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Oh, the zoom chat.","index":436,"end_time":2033.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2031.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, the zoom chat.","index":437,"end_time":2034.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2033.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All right.","index":438,"end_time":2060.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2060.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"If we.","index":439,"end_time":2061.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2060.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"If we do have to cut something, I think we can cut that.","index":440,"end_time":2064.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2061.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I would love to keep it.","index":441,"end_time":2066.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2064.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Or.","index":442,"end_time":2066.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2066.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Or we change the text and we just have, you know, this source of continuous improvement.","index":443,"end_time":2081.959,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2076.919,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"We could just turn this into, like text under the screen.","index":444,"end_time":2086.359,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2083.399,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"You know, like complete more audits, resolve issues faster, uncover or make an impact on performance.","index":445,"end_time":2096.919,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2086.999,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":446,"end_time":2098.039,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2097.559,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":447,"end_time":2108.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2108.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Action plans.","index":448,"end_time":2110.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2109.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I''m eager to see how the action plans one comes out because this one, thinking of the audio, I feel like it''s one of the ones that gets to the product the quickest.","index":449,"end_time":2139.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2126.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And then we just looked at the on the job training one.","index":450,"end_time":2153.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2150.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, we can try and leave this one.","index":451,"end_time":2158.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2157.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It sounds like the audio.","index":452,"end_time":2160.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2158.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You really like the audio for this one.","index":453,"end_time":2161.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2160.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think this one was the shortest video or the shortest audio too.","index":454,"end_time":2167.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2163.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":455,"end_time":2169.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2168.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we can.","index":456,"end_time":2169.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2169.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can keep this one as is for now and we could cut this.","index":457,"end_time":2174.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2169.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes.","index":458,"end_time":2175.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2174.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I think this is that one.","index":459,"end_time":2189.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2183.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Is there a way from here to navigate to the action plans?","index":460,"end_time":2195.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2190.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"That would be cool.","index":461,"end_time":2199.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2198.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t know if there is.","index":462,"end_time":2200.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2199.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can grab the link, though.","index":463,"end_time":2204.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2203.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s on the job training.","index":464,"end_time":2210.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2209.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":465,"end_time":2212.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2211.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":466,"end_time":2212.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2212.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"You have it?","index":467,"end_time":2214.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2213.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, I don''t have it.","index":468,"end_time":2216.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2215.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":469,"end_time":2217.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2216.19,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Oh, Paula''s got it.","index":470,"end_time":2218.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2217.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":471,"end_time":2220.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2219.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":472,"end_time":2220.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2220.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":473,"end_time":2231.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2231.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"See, we get to the product quickly in this one.","index":474,"end_time":2235.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2231.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":475,"end_time":2247.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2246.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":476,"end_time":2251.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2250.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay.","index":477,"end_time":2252.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2252.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Let''s see how it works.","index":478,"end_time":2254.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2252.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Like that.","index":479,"end_time":2255.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2254.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay, we will work through that.","index":480,"end_time":2258.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2255.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you for sharing your screen so we can keep moving.","index":481,"end_time":2263.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2258.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, this is great.","index":482,"end_time":2264.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2263.52,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":483,"end_time":2264.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2264.48,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Yeah, I appreciate it.","index":484,"end_time":2266.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2265.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"I''m getting a lot of.","index":485,"end_time":2268.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2267.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Where are the videos?","index":486,"end_time":2269.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2268.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Where the videos?","index":487,"end_time":2270.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2269.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Where are the videos?","index":488,"end_time":2271.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2270.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"So you''ll probably start feeling that coming from me as well.","index":489,"end_time":2274.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2271.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"And then, you know, if there''s a different approach or process that we need to take, if you''ve seen things work better, differently with other folks that you work with, like, please let me know, because I''m just doing what I think makes sense, but that doesn''t necessarily mean it''s the best way.","index":490,"end_time":2293.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2276.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we''re.","index":491,"end_time":2296.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2295.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re getting close to the end, Paul.","index":492,"end_time":2299.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2296.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we''ll keep just doing what we''re doing.","index":493,"end_time":2301.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2299.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll review stuff first, try and get as much feedback before we send it to you, and then we can do final edits from there.","index":494,"end_time":2308.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2301.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Great.","index":495,"end_time":2309.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2308.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"If you could maybe just update us when it''s.","index":496,"end_time":2315.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2309.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Hey, we got it.","index":497,"end_time":2316.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2315.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"We''re reviewing it.","index":498,"end_time":2317.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2316.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":499,"end_time":2318.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2317.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You know, just so that there''s visibility.","index":500,"end_time":2321.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2319.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Otherwise, people come to me and I want to be like, look, I''ll tell you when they''re done.","index":501,"end_time":2327.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2322.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"How about that?","index":502,"end_time":2328.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2327.799,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, don''t ask.","index":503,"end_time":2330.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2328.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Yeah, totally understand that.","index":504,"end_time":2333.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2331.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll keep you in the loop there.","index":505,"end_time":2335.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2333.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":506,"end_time":2336.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2335.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll look forward to seeing the overview end of week.","index":507,"end_time":2341.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2336.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Cool.","index":508,"end_time":2342.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2342.5,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Cool.","index":509,"end_time":2343.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2342.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll see ya.","index":510,"end_time":2343.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2343.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":511,"end_time":2344.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2344.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Santo"},{"text":"Bye.","index":512,"end_time":2345.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2345.14,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"}],"dateString":"2026-01-28T21:00:00.000Z","host_email":"paula.ocampo@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us04web.zoom.us/j/79575488295?pwd=XICgOPQC72fNribEyiumBtwmCmim8i.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,paula.ocampo@marketersindemand.com,josh.santo@ease.io","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","josh.santo@ease.io"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFH60Z7FDV1WYFZC8HG0WC6Z","organizer_email":"paula.ocampo@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.88,"bullets":["Scheduled next podcast episode for February 10; blog post to follow on February 12.","Episode 15 saw strongest performance: +46 YouTube views and +12 Spotify plays week over week.","Team aligned on simplifying videos to prioritize product visuals over lengthy exposition.","Decided to transition outreach to broader email targeting after limited results from personalized campaigns.","Josh confirmed action plan video audio timing works; on-the-job training video to be trimmed further."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We have to get to the product as quickly as we can.","speaker":"Josh Santo"},{"quote":"Episode 15 is really standing now... strongest growth across platforms.","speaker":"Paula Ocampo"},{"quote":"I''m just doing what I think makes sense, but that doesn''t necessarily mean it''s the best way.","speaker":"Josh Santo"}],"topics":["delivery","video","campaign","analytics","podcast"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-30T21:30:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Performance and Outreach**\n\nThe podcast episode featuring **Rajiv** is showing the strongest growth with clear week-over-week gains, signaling positive audience engagement (12:02).\n\n- **Episode 15 posted a 20-download increase on Buzzsprout, 46 more YouTube views, and 12 new Spotify plays** compared to previous weeks, indicating rising listener interest.\n- Paula highlighted that while other episodes lacked growth in downloads, short clips from the Julia Atkins episode performed well on YouTube, showing different content formats drive varied engagement.\n- The team plans to leverage these insights by continuing to monitor reviews and audience feedback, although there are currently no new reviews to report.\n- Josh suggested that episode titles might impact discoverability, noting \"operational excellence\" is a common term possibly affecting search traction.\n\nThe outreach campaign on **Smart Lead closed with a 45% open rate and 45% connection acceptance rate**, but pipeline activity remains low, prompting a shift to broader contact lists (13:03).\n\n- Josh confirmed outreach issues with scheduling links for some contacts and noted the need to refill the pipeline with new prospects urgently.\n- Baylee recommended restarting outreach using a larger contact list from HubSpot, including re-engaging past contacts with refreshed messaging to accelerate results.\n- Josh agreed to this broader approach as the prior targeted campaign yielded limited returns, enabling a faster ramp-up without list refresh delays.\n- The team agreed to begin work immediately on this expanded outreach strategy to maintain momentum.\n\n## **Video Production and Content Refinement**\n\nThe video team is prioritizing the **Product Cover B video** and addressing timing mismatches between voiceover audio and visuals in other videos to enhance flow and clarity (16:46).\n\n- Josh emphasized keeping voiceover audio as is to maintain message integrity while trimming or cutting visual frames to fit within a **maximum three and a half minute runtime**.\n- The goal is to minimize gaps by simplifying or removing exposition sections, speeding up product visuals, and aligning them tightly with the script.\n- Baylee and Paula proposed submitting frame cut suggestions for Josh’s review to identify areas for trimming before final edits.\n- Josh recommended live collaborative video reviews to quickly decide on cuts and pacing changes, allowing faster iteration and better alignment.\n\nThe **“On the Job Training” video requires significant cuts** to reduce pre-product exposition from over a minute to about 10–15 seconds, enabling quicker focus on the product demo (24:12).\n\n- Josh and Baylee agreed to remove large sections of the script that delay product introduction, including some repetitive or awkward phrasing, to improve viewer engagement.\n- The team will finalize script edits and then apply cuts to video footage accordingly, saving production time and improving message impact.\n- The **“Action Plans” video received positive feedback for its concise audio and pacing** and will remain mostly unchanged for now.\n- Josh stressed the importance of timely visibility into video review status to manage expectations internally and externally, requesting updates at key milestones.\n\n## **Process Improvements and Collaboration**\n\nThe team is refining review and feedback workflows for video content to increase efficiency and reduce turnaround times (38:15).\n\n- Baylee committed to sharing early reviews with Josh to minimize delays and prevent unnecessary status inquiries.\n- Josh encouraged openness to alternative processes if they improve the review cycle, reflecting a flexible mindset toward optimizing collaboration.\n- The group agreed to maintain current practices of internal review before sending materials to Josh for final approval, balancing thoroughness with speed.\n- Josh expressed eagerness to receive the final overview video by week’s end to maintain project momentum.\n\n## **Client and Task Management**\n\nThe team acknowledged challenges with some **Ideometry clients expecting same-day edits**, prompting adjustments to set clearer expectations about turnaround times (05:36).\n\n- Baylee left instructions for Ron to tackle design and development tasks sequentially, aiming for design completion early in the day to facilitate development.\n- Paula noted that some client requests, like removing sections, are quick fixes, but adding new models or images takes longer, informing client communication.\n- Baylee emphasized the need to provide clients with **a one- or two-day notice** for edits to manage workload and avoid rushed last-minute changes.\n- This approach aims to improve client satisfaction by setting realistic delivery timelines while maintaining quality.\n\n## **Technical and Strategic Considerations**\n\nJosh shared insights into **audio and visual consistency across videos**, highlighting that audio tracks with steady builds and less repetition resonate better with viewers (25:04).\n\n- The team will prioritize audio tracks similar to the preferred “Action Plans” style for future videos.\n- Josh stressed visual priorities, focusing on quickly showcasing the product rather than extended exposition or text-heavy frames.\n- The discussion underscored the strategic need to balance detailed explanations with viewer engagement, ensuring videos are concise and impactful.\n- The team will continue to analyze and iterate on video content presentation to align with internal standards and audience expectations.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast updates","Outreach campaign","Video production","Script edits","Scheduling coordination","Client expectations"],"overview":"- **Podcast Growth:** Episode 15 saw 20 downloads, 46 YouTube views, and 12 Spotify plays increase, indicating audience interest.  \n- **Outreach Campaign Results:** Smart Lead outreach had a 45% open and connection rate, but low pipeline activity prompts a wider contact approach.  \n- **Video Production Focus:** Prioritizing Product Cover B video; aiming for maximum runtime of 3.5 minutes by trimming visuals for clarity.  \n- **Video Review Process:** Early reviews shared for faster feedback; flexibility encouraged for improved workflows and faster project completion.  \n- **Client Expectations:** Emphasized one-to-two day notice for edits to manage workloads and ensure client satisfaction on turnaround times.  \n- **Audio-Visual Consistency:** Prioritize steady audio and concise visuals for future videos, aligning with audience engagement and strategic presentation.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nAdd notes to Ron’s task to prioritize design work for end of day and confirm scheduling with Gary for next day’s development (05:36)\nReview script document and identify sections to cut to streamline ''on the job training'' video and related videos (24:02)\nCoordinate with Paula on outreach list segmentation and refresh campaign using HubSpot lists or prior contacts with revised messaging (15:18)\nProvide feedback and make recommendations to video production team on potential frame cuts and timing adjustments (19:18)\nKeep Josh updated on video review status and progress for visibility (38:47)\n\n**Paula Ocampo**\nManage scheduling and communication with outreach contacts Nikita, Nazaire, and Nasser to resolve scheduling link issues and confirm meetings (13:40)\nOpen tasks for Gary promptly upon receiving design completion to keep development on track (06:00)\nShare metaboards and video materials with Josh for review of product demo videos (33:25)\nContinue monitoring podcast episode 15 and outreach stats for progress and prepare for upcoming episode recording (10:11)\nMonitor client expectations on timing and communicate feasibility of same day edits and turnaround (06:15)\n\n**Josh Santo**\nReach out to Nasser to resolve scheduling issues and coordinate outreach meetings (13:40)\nReview scripts for ''on the job training'' and other videos to provide cut recommendations to reduce exposition and improve timing (26:26)\nCollaborate live or asynchronously with Baylee and Paula to optimize video timing and pacing before finalizing (20:12)\nProvide feedback on video audio and music quality; prefer consistent pacing as in ''action plans'' video (24:57)\nCommunicate regularly for visibility on video review progress and final delivery to manage stakeholder expectations (38:28)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"4aaa5f08-b697-4075-8d36-68802d219f0f","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
