    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87477024015?pwd=gVpnKPDuNsoZ0giaFoA7gicVcI6afV.1',
    '{"id":"01KFKMRPY76TQZWM9FT1QBFYBA","title":"PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **HubSpot Audit and Data Integrity**\n\nThe HubSpot system requires a thorough cleanup and standardization to improve data quality, lead source tracking, and reporting accuracy.\n\n- **The audit revealed over 500 contact properties with 95% rarely used, plus 200 overlapping active workflows causing confusion and inefficiency** (28:10)  \n    - This complexity leads to inconsistent data, reducing confidence in marketing and sales reports.  \n    - Colin explained that seven different lead source fields create confusion and unclear attribution.  \n    - The team plans to clean up unused properties, unify lead source definitions, and streamline workflows.  \n    - This cleanup is critical to accurately measure campaign effectiveness and optimize resource allocation.\n\n- **Lead source properties for deals must remain unchanged due to their importance in sales compensation and reporting** (33:20)  \n    - Josh emphasized that deal-level source fields like \"Inbound\" or \"Demanding Event\" are required and heavily used.  \n    - Contact-level lead sources are separate and need clearer definitions and better management.  \n    - Carmen noted the need for alignment and suggested an additional meeting between marketing and sales to finalize source tracking structure.\n\n- **Data quality issues include 237,000 contacts with many duplicates and non-business emails like Gmail and iCloud** (40:50)  \n    - Nina and Natalie acknowledged that duplicate merging is manual and time-consuming but feasible.  \n    - The team agreed on prioritizing cleanup of contacts without emails and possibly restricting demo requests to business emails only.  \n    - Natalie noted some companies accept personal emails to maintain long-term nurture despite job changes, requiring nuanced rules.  \n    - Rob pushed for removing irrelevant contacts, like venture capitalists, and questioned the value of personal email contacts.\n\n- **The HubSpot cleanup and lead management improvements are part of three main initiatives: database integrity, attribution reporting, and lead management process** (47:53)  \n    - Colin offered to map out property definitions, responsibilities, and workflows as part of their retainer.  \n    - Carmen and Josh plan to discuss specifics next week with Rob to align on priorities and resource allocation.  \n    - The team recognized the need for clear sales enablement instructions and communication to prevent past issues with property usage.  \n    - Sam, the current HubSpot administrator, is involved as a contractor to assist transition and provide historical context.\n\n## **Lead Management and Marketing-Sales Alignment**\n\nEstablishing clear lead qualification criteria and handoff processes is essential to improve pipeline visibility and conversion tracking.\n\n- **Current lead qualification lacks clarity on MQL vs. SQL definitions and lead disqualification tracking** (35:54)  \n    - Stephanie highlighted the importance of defining these terms clearly and tracking reasons for lost deals or unqualified leads.  \n    - Carmen observed that marketing and sales roles overlap, causing inconsistent lead management.  \n    - Colin emphasized cleaning up lifecycle and lead status stages to unify communication between teams.  \n    - The goal is to enable clear handoffs and ensure leads are properly nurtured or disqualified with documented reasons.\n\n- **A structured lead management process including SLAs, qualification criteria, and next steps will align marketing and sales teams** (50:39)  \n    - Rob suggested using company email verification as a gate for demo requests to improve lead quality.  \n    - Carmen agreed and explained that demo requests are high-commitment leads likely to be SQLs, bypassing MQL stages.  \n    - The team agreed to develop a tight lead management framework covering budget, authority, timeline, and other qualification factors.  \n    - This will reduce wasted effort on unqualified leads and optimize sales follow-up.\n\n- **Sales enablement materials and clear communication of new processes are needed for successful adoption** (29:42)  \n    - Josh asked if New North provides sales enablement, and Colin confirmed it is standard practice.  \n    - Past gaps in communication about HubSpot changes led to unused properties.  \n    - The team will formalize documentation and training to prevent future misalignment.\n\n## **Marketing Campaigns and Reporting Improvements**\n\nCampaign design and reporting need refinement to improve attribution, lead capture, and conversion tracking.\n\n- **Current reporting dashboards provide high-level views but lack detailed campaign attribution and source cleanup** (05:37)  \n    - Colin showed reports tracking contacts created, MQLs, SQLs, meetings, and closed deals by source.  \n    - Carmen noted the audit identified lead management and attribution tracking as key areas needing improvement.  \n    - The team plans to standardize source fields and break out channels more granularly, separating paid, organic, and other traffic sources.\n\n- **New campaign designs include lead magnets focused on PTO assessment and healthcare employee retention, aimed at LinkedIn lead gen** (07:54)  \n    - Colin explained LinkedIn lead gen forms reduce friction by keeping users on the platform with pre-filled info.  \n    - Campaign assets include landing pages and infographics based on existing research and whitepapers.  \n    - Upon approval, email and LinkedIn nurture sequences will roll out to promote these campaigns.\n\n- **Website feedback highlighted the need for clearer UX strategy, brand consistency, and content audit** (16:34)  \n    - Carmen requested a sitemap and rationale for page structures, personas, and navigation to understand the user journey.  \n    - Nina offered to compile existing brand and persona discussions into one document for clarity.  \n    - Rob flagged issues with duplicate testimonials and stock or AI-generated images; immediate removal of fake testimonials was prioritized.  \n    - Carmen will lead a content audit to validate testimonials and enforce no AI image usage as a brand guideline.\n\n## **Website UX and Content Strategy**\n\nThe website needs ongoing development with clearer UX direction and authentic content to support marketing goals.\n\n- **Current website builds lack a unified UX strategy and persona research, causing uncertainty about navigation and content flow** (17:31)  \n    - Carmen expressed that previous work felt like disconnected page creation without clear user journey mapping.  \n    - The team agreed to push live agreed-upon pages like homepage and industry pages, then iterate based on user feedback.  \n    - A living, evolving website approach was endorsed to allow continuous improvement.\n\n- **Content authenticity and brand trust are critical; fake or duplicated testimonials and AI images must be removed** (20:17)  \n    - Rob emphasized real images and names for testimonials to avoid competitor comparisons showing fake content.  \n    - Josh highlighted privacy concerns and lack of image permissions as reasons for absent real photos.  \n    - The immediate fix involves removing problematic images and possibly hiding images until permission is secured.  \n    - Carmen will conduct a content audit to ensure all website content aligns with brand authenticity standards.\n\n- **Future website updates will incorporate industry-specific research and statistics to demonstrate domain expertise** (25:58)  \n    - Josh shared plans to include turnover data and challenges in healthcare and other industries on relevant pages.  \n    - This approach aims to increase visitor trust and engagement by showing understanding of sector-specific pain points.  \n    - The website will serve as a dynamic resource reflecting ongoing research and marketing priorities.\n\n## **Team Coordination and Next Steps**\n\nThe team is aligning on communication, meeting cadence, and responsibilities to drive execution on audit findings and marketing initiatives.\n\n- **Weekly or biweekly meetings will be established between Carmen, Natalie, Nina, and others to dive deeper into strategy and initiatives** (55:30)  \n    - Josh and Rob will be involved as needed to provide sales and leadership input.  \n    - These sessions will focus on campaign execution, reporting improvements, and lead management processes.\n\n- **New North will draft a detailed plan outlining cleanup steps, responsibilities, and timelines as part of their current retainer** (37:44)  \n    - This plan will include database cleanup, attribution tracking, and lead management process improvements.  \n    - Carmen will review and coordinate with Josh and Rob to finalize priorities and resource needs.\n\n- **Sam will support the transition as a contractor, providing historical knowledge and helping answer process questions** (53:24)  \n    - The team agreed his involvement is essential to efficiently resolve technical and data issues.  \n    - Coordination between Sam and New North will ensure continuity and knowledge transfer.\n\n- **Immediate technical fixes include removing duplicate testimonials and fake images from the homepage to improve brand trust** (24:58)  \n    - New North will prioritize these updates while broader content audits and UX strategy develop.  \n    - Carmen will gather examples of preferred image styles to guide future content decisions.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot Audit","Lead Management","Campaign Attribution","Website UX","Database Cleanup","Marketing Qualified Lead (MQL)"],"overview":"- **HubSpot Audit:** Over 500 contact properties audited; 95% unused. Cleanup needed for better data quality and lead source tracking.  \n- **Lead Source Management:** Deal-level source fields essential for sales. Contact-level fields require clear definitions to prevent confusion.  \n- **Data Quality Issues:** 237,000 contacts contain duplicates and non-business emails. Prioritize cleaning up and removing irrelevant contacts.  \n- **Lead Management Process:** Need for clear SLAs and qualifications to align marketing and sales, reducing wasted efforts on unqualified leads.  \n- **Website Improvements:** Focus on genuine content; remove duplicates and AI images. Regular updates needed to showcase industry-specific insights.  \n- **Team Coordination:** Establish weekly meetings to dive into strategy and assign clear responsibilities for ongoing cleanup and marketing initiatives.","action_items":"\n**Carmen Williams**\nCoordinate with Josh and Rob for additional weekly strategic deep-dive meetings post wider team calls (39:11)\nLead content audit focusing on testimonials, image authenticity, and brand guidelines including prohibiting AI-generated images (21:01)\nReview and clarify UX strategy, sitemap, and persona insights by receiving compiled documentation from Nina (18:30)\nCollaborate with New North to outline how to address database, attribution, and lead management cleanup initiatives and who is responsible for each (43:42)\nConduct ABM strategy development focused on Healthcare Enterprise segment with Natalie, Nina, Josh, and Rob (55:22)\nPrepare for upcoming detailed lead management discussions to define MQL/SQL criteria and lead qualification workflows (50:41)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nDiscuss CTA strategies and website feedback with Carmen and team to refine approach and policy (13:09)\nSupport database cleanup by providing insights into deal properties and participation in discussions on data rules and merging duplicates (40:50)\nCollaborate with Carmen and New North team to kick off lead management process refinement and data integrity initiatives (43:42)\nCoordinate to involve Sam (former HubSpot admin) in knowledge transfer to aid cleanup and optimization efforts (46:33)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nShare documentation and presentations related to campaign background, research, and lead magnet strategy with Carmen and team (08:38)\nCompile all brand, persona, and copy discussions into one comprehensive document for Carmen’s review to aid alignment on UX and navigation (19:19)\nCollaborate with Natalie and Colin on database audit cleanup plan and proposal of actionable next steps for PTO Exchange (56:17)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nAssist in sharing campaign and audit presentations and related documentation (08:38)\nHelp lead the database assessment and manage developer resources to explore automation or improved workflows for cleanup (42:32)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nProvide full presentation and report links to Carmen and wider team including the HubSpot audit and campaign tracking overviews (05:24)\nPrioritize removing duplicate testimonial and replacing/removing AI-generated or stock images on homepage (24:58)\nSupport setup of standardized data definitions, property mapping, and cleanup workflows within HubSpot in collaboration with New North team (35:54)\nPrepare a summary of next steps and processes as part of existing retainer, clarifying scope and timeline (38:09)\n\n**Rob Whalen**\nFlag and encourage quick removal of duplicate testimonials and images lacking authenticity on website (20:41)\nProvide user perspective and feedback on CTA, navigation, and marketing content authenticity (14:28)\nAssist in evaluating quality of contact database and prioritizing clean filters (44:32)\n"},"duration":56.939998626708984,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Carmen Williams"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Nina Belina"},{"id":3,"name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"id":4,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":5,"name":"Rob Whalen"},{"id":6,"name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Colin, how''s it going?","index":0,"end_time":180.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.87,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Hey, how are you doing?","index":1,"end_time":181.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":180.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":2,"end_time":182.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.07,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Great to see you.","index":3,"end_time":185.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":184.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t believe the week has already passed since we last spoke.","index":4,"end_time":190.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.83,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I know, it flies.","index":5,"end_time":191.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":190.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s crazy.","index":6,"end_time":192.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.75,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s been, you know.","index":7,"end_time":194.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.79,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"How''s your week been so far?","index":8,"end_time":197.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, good.","index":9,"end_time":198.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.83,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":10,"end_time":199.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":198.63,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Besides the getting chased by coyotes?","index":11,"end_time":203.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":200.87,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"That''s been.","index":12,"end_time":204.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":203.51,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But no, we''re good.","index":13,"end_time":206.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":205.31,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Still doing the morning walks with your dogs?","index":14,"end_time":209.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":206.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":15,"end_time":209.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.39,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Going a different route.","index":16,"end_time":210.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.75,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":17,"end_time":211.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":211.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":18,"end_time":212.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":211.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":19,"end_time":212.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.19,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Hi, Nina.","index":20,"end_time":213.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.99,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Hi.","index":21,"end_time":214.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.03,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I just came into coyotes and then I''m not sure what the conversation was about, but I hope everybody''s safe.","index":22,"end_time":221.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":214.43,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yes.","index":23,"end_time":222.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":222.27,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, I think I''m getting.","index":24,"end_time":226.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":224.03,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":25,"end_time":227.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.75,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"What''s that?","index":26,"end_time":230.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":229.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I think I might have had Nina and Natalie''s name mixed up.","index":27,"end_time":234.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.89,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So if I did any cross naming, apologies for that.","index":28,"end_time":238.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.09,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"No, no, it''s.","index":29,"end_time":239.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":238.57,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I think it''s a little bit confusing now because Natalie''s taking over PTO and then, you know, I''m still here and it''s.","index":30,"end_time":245.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":239.33,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, okay, cool.","index":31,"end_time":247.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.57,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, no, it was, it was a good week for me.","index":32,"end_time":251.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yesterday was my daughter''s first birthday, so that was a lot of fun.","index":33,"end_time":253.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":251.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, that is so, so exciting.","index":34,"end_time":256.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":253.89,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Oh my gosh.","index":35,"end_time":256.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.17,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Goes fast.","index":36,"end_time":258.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":257.55,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Enjoy it.","index":37,"end_time":259.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.67,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I know.","index":38,"end_time":259.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":259.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t believe it was already a year.","index":39,"end_time":261.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":259.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wow.","index":40,"end_time":262.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.79,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Hey, Steph.","index":41,"end_time":264.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":263.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, guys.","index":42,"end_time":265.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.91,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So obviously you saw Colin, that Josh is going to be a little late getting on the call so we can maybe.","index":43,"end_time":274.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.47,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay.","index":44,"end_time":275.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Get started, audit till the end or whatever.","index":45,"end_time":278.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.95,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good.","index":46,"end_time":279.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":278.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":47,"end_time":282.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":281.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Can you see my screen?","index":48,"end_time":283.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":49,"end_time":284.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.44,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"All right, so we''ll go through project updates, items we''re working on.","index":50,"end_time":290.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":288.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do have the HubSpot audit in here, so.","index":51,"end_time":292.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":52,"end_time":292.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When Josh joins, we can start going through the high level overview of that and then go through some data as well.","index":53,"end_time":297.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So getting started.","index":54,"end_time":300.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":299.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I know you were asking a few questions in the channel about like reports and things to find in HubSpot.","index":55,"end_time":305.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":300.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we do have so for measuring MQLs and SQLs.","index":56,"end_time":309.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I believe.","index":57,"end_time":309.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You believe built this report so quickly.","index":58,"end_time":311.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Colin, this presentation that you just, you just started with.","index":59,"end_time":316.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.98,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Will you put that somewhere so that I can go like.","index":60,"end_time":320.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":316.62,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And click on these links?","index":61,"end_time":321.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.3,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can share it with you.","index":62,"end_time":323.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":322.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":63,"end_time":324.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.14,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Maybe on your.","index":64,"end_time":325.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.5,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Wherever the shared location is.","index":65,"end_time":327.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.42,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, we can put it in the channel.","index":66,"end_time":330.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":328.14,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":67,"end_time":330.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.46,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":68,"end_time":332.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":331.66,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":69,"end_time":332.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.18,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"We''ve got these reports set for these campaigns.","index":70,"end_time":335.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.02,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Nice.","index":71,"end_time":336.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":335.82,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yes.","index":72,"end_time":336.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":336.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":73,"end_time":337.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":337,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have traffic by source contacts created per month, MQL is generated and then SQL''s first meetings and then close deals.","index":74,"end_time":347.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":337.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So everything broken up by source fields.","index":75,"end_time":351.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":350.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that.","index":76,"end_time":352.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s go back to what exactly?","index":77,"end_time":354.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":353,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Let''s go back to what exactly.","index":78,"end_time":356.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":354.88,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"This is.","index":79,"end_time":356.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.36,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So this is all campaigns.","index":80,"end_time":360.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So for.","index":81,"end_time":361,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.44,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Or is this.","index":82,"end_time":361.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"What.","index":83,"end_time":362.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.76,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"What is this reporting on?","index":84,"end_time":363.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":362.04,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":85,"end_time":364.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":364.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie, do you want to walk through that with the dashboard?","index":86,"end_time":366.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":364.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do I want to walk through this dashboard?","index":87,"end_time":370.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":368.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":88,"end_time":371.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that your team built this, Carmen.","index":89,"end_time":374.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":372.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Right.","index":90,"end_time":374.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.58,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You have shared this link with us in the channel, in the Slack channel.","index":91,"end_time":379.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":375.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I just don''t know.","index":92,"end_time":381.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":380.38,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But what I work with, whoever''s the expert on your team on building, like getting good reporting in place.","index":93,"end_time":388.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.3,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"That market board, was it.","index":94,"end_time":390.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":388.22,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Was this built by Sam Colin?","index":95,"end_time":391.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":390.03,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"That''s.","index":96,"end_time":392.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":391.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what it looks like.","index":97,"end_time":392.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think so, yeah.","index":98,"end_time":394.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":392.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Also.","index":99,"end_time":396.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":396.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hi.","index":100,"end_time":396.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":396.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this is.","index":101,"end_time":397.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":396.87,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And this is within our HubSpot, is that correct?","index":102,"end_time":399.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":397.31,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Statement.","index":103,"end_time":399.59,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":399.35,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And I think out of the audit and the recommendations that you''re going to speak to shortly, lead management and the whole attribution tracking is.","index":104,"end_time":410.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":401.35,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Are the key things that are needing to be improved.","index":105,"end_time":413.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.39,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And so this reporting will come out of that?","index":106,"end_time":416.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":413.35,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yes.","index":107,"end_time":416.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":108,"end_time":417.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":417.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":109,"end_time":418.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":417.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It does look like at a high level, it''s just broken down kind of like across every channel.","index":110,"end_time":422.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":418.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, got it.","index":111,"end_time":423.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":422.61,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay.","index":112,"end_time":423.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.33,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So it''s just a very macro view.","index":113,"end_time":425.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":423.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":114,"end_time":426.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.73,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I thought you were presenting reports that you had set up for the campaigns you were doing, but what you''re doing is just showing me where these legacy reports are.","index":115,"end_time":434.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":426.21,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, thank you.","index":116,"end_time":435.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":434.61,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Got it.","index":117,"end_time":436.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.65,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Cool.","index":118,"end_time":437.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I know you''re also talking about, like for the benchmark report and LinkedIn and things like that.","index":119,"end_time":441.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do have just a contact table.","index":120,"end_time":444.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":441.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So under CRM and contacts, this lives here with just the filters based on the campaigns that we''re running.","index":121,"end_time":449.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":444.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":122,"end_time":450.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":449.97,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And what we''re going to do, I think we spoke about last time, was break those out.","index":123,"end_time":453.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450.29,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So that New north is not a channel that we''re going to have paid, digital, paid, whatever, you know, organic, this, that.","index":124,"end_time":461.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.89,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":125,"end_time":462.489,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":462.049,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s a big piece of the audit is like there''s currently seven source properties that we need to clean up and have like the actual source of truth.","index":126,"end_time":469.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":462.489,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":127,"end_time":470.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.13,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, thank you.","index":128,"end_time":472.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.53,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"We''ve also generated designs for new campaigns.","index":129,"end_time":478.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":474.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is for the liability or exposure assessment that we pitched to Steph.","index":130,"end_time":485.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":479.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''ll remember the meeting from a week or two ago, I think two weeks ago, where we talked through four new campaigns.","index":131,"end_time":491.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":485.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the start to a landing page to calculate or to give a score of assessments.","index":132,"end_time":497.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":491.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This then leads into that first conversation.","index":133,"end_time":499.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":497.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Question on something like this.","index":134,"end_time":502.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":499.97,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Do you have the documentation that leads up to this, as in the research and insights gathering and then the strategy, you know, like that kind of thing.","index":135,"end_time":512.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":502.85,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Is there any background?","index":136,"end_time":513.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":512.61,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Can you share that with me at some point?","index":137,"end_time":515.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":513.81,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''d love to understand what the.","index":138,"end_time":517.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.89,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, cool, cool.","index":139,"end_time":518.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":517.61,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":140,"end_time":518.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":518.41,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I will share it with the presentation.","index":141,"end_time":520.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":518.69,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":142,"end_time":521.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":520.69,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Nice.","index":143,"end_time":521.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.05,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yep.","index":144,"end_time":522.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":521.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so, Robin, Steph, on the sales calls, we''ve talked to Josh a lot about the different metrics you can pull out of a spreadsheet if you do get some basic numbers from a prospect.","index":145,"end_time":532.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s what we''re trying to collect here so that we can have an informed conversation with the prospect.","index":146,"end_time":537.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":533.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":147,"end_time":538.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":538.4,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And then another one was more focused on the PTO gap.","index":148,"end_time":547.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":543.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we see this a lot.","index":149,"end_time":551.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":548.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This was an infographic that we created.","index":150,"end_time":552.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":551.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So zoom out.","index":151,"end_time":553.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":552.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is six pages.","index":152,"end_time":555.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":554.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But this goes over and heavily utilized the information that was collected in the research you guys did for the.","index":153,"end_time":562.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t remember the exact name of the white paper.","index":154,"end_time":566.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":563.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was the PTO time shift, I think, where it was comparing how the older generation and the younger generation have skewed use of pto.","index":155,"end_time":576.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Looks like we may have lost carbon.","index":156,"end_time":580.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you back, Carmen?","index":157,"end_time":581.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":580.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I guess it was my Internet.","index":158,"end_time":582.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":581.61,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Darn it.","index":159,"end_time":583.21,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":582.69,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Okay, can you hear me now?","index":160,"end_time":585.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":161,"end_time":586.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.89,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":162,"end_time":587.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":586.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":163,"end_time":588.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":587.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this goes over the research that was in the white paper that you guys had previously.","index":164,"end_time":593.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":588.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just presenting it in a different way with some updated copy around the different use of or the purpose that people want to use their PTO for and how companies need flexible options.","index":165,"end_time":602.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":593.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And also, just to mention, this is one of the situations where we combined the research that we did previously with something that was already available in pto.","index":166,"end_time":612.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":603.25,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So because I know the two asked about how we get around things.","index":167,"end_time":616.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":612.45,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So that would be a lead magnet campaign, and then also a lead magnet campaign, a playbook specifically for the healthcare industry, for employee retention.","index":168,"end_time":628.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":618.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it was actually kind of funny because we had shared Nina had pulled together some research on the healthcare industry and Josh asked if we were in your curated content channel, because I think Dan had sent like a very similar article that same day, which is to see the alignment there.","index":169,"end_time":645.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But this goes through how, especially with RNs and different titles in the healthcare field, they experience a lot of burnout from not having options in their pto.","index":170,"end_time":654.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":645.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And also just the age ranges that go through all of that.","index":171,"end_time":658.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":655.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So another lead magnet here that would be run on LinkedIn ads is our suggestion.","index":172,"end_time":664.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":661.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions around these lead magnets?","index":173,"end_time":670.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously share them for review and everything.","index":174,"end_time":673.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":671.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where are these going to live?","index":175,"end_time":678.6,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":676.88,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Are these going to be on the website or you say lead magnets, like, where are they meant to capture?","index":176,"end_time":684.24,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":678.6,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":177,"end_time":685.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":684.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one thing that we''ve seen the most success with so far is LinkedIn lead generation forms, because it doesn''t Force a user to leave LinkedIn, then fill out a form on the website.","index":178,"end_time":693.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That being said, I do like having an organic option for someone to land there on the website.","index":179,"end_time":698.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":694.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So still having a landing page dedicated to this resource, but running it more of a paid perspective on LinkedIn.","index":180,"end_time":704.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":698.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The LinkedIn Lead Gens are just a really low barrier because that information is already filled out if they click on the ad, like their name and email address and things like that.","index":181,"end_time":714.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":707.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":182,"end_time":715.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.77,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And then we''re tracking the success of these, obviously.","index":183,"end_time":720.21,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":717.97,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yep, yep, yep.","index":184,"end_time":721.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":720.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":185,"end_time":724.38,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":723.98,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So we''ll send those over for review.","index":186,"end_time":726.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":724.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Once they are approved, we''ll develop some email and LinkedIn sequences to start promoting these as well.","index":187,"end_time":731.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":726.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":188,"end_time":734.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":734.14,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Any questions so far?","index":189,"end_time":736.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":734.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, not for me.","index":190,"end_time":742.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":741.18,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":191,"end_time":744.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":743.58,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So thank you.","index":192,"end_time":745.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Question, sorry.","index":193,"end_time":746.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.74,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So those are not, in addition to those are related to those four campaigns that you guys had provided.","index":194,"end_time":753.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":746.94,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay.","index":195,"end_time":753.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.28,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Correct.","index":196,"end_time":754.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":753.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":197,"end_time":754.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":754.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you, you''ve got the background on the rationale and all that.","index":198,"end_time":759.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":755.4,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, yeah, you know, share that over.","index":199,"end_time":761.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":759.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Cool.","index":200,"end_time":761.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":761.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":201,"end_time":762.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":761.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":202,"end_time":762.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":762.12,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":203,"end_time":763,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":762.52,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":204,"end_time":764.36,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":763.8,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Thank you guys for giving feedback on the website as well.","index":205,"end_time":767.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":764.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to go through for the homepage call to action strategy.","index":206,"end_time":772.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":767.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s a comment around the employee login button taking up too much real estate.","index":207,"end_time":777,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":773.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So right here we know that historically what we had heard was that many people were clicking request a demo who were current customers.","index":208,"end_time":789.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":782.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I spoke with Josh about this and so we should probably have a discussion about CTA with Josh.","index":209,"end_time":803.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":789.72,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So, so, but thank you.","index":210,"end_time":806.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":803.56,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"He actually gave me the background that there was that thinking of too many leads going through, but I think there''s other ways to solve that.","index":211,"end_time":812.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.21,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So that''s, that''s my perspective.","index":212,"end_time":814.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":812.41,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But we can.","index":213,"end_time":814.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.21,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":214,"end_time":815.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.29,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay.","index":215,"end_time":816.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.85,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"All right.","index":216,"end_time":816.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":816.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So too many, too many leads going through the employee login.","index":217,"end_time":819.53,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":816.65,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"They were going through the requested demo.","index":218,"end_time":822.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":819.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And one of the issues that Colin''s going to get to here soon with the audit is we, we''re really, we don''t know.","index":219,"end_time":829.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":822.49,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Right.","index":220,"end_time":829.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":829.53,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Like, like we should be able to know.","index":221,"end_time":832.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":830.01,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Well, how many leads.","index":222,"end_time":833.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":832.66,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You know, we send marketing qualified leads over and they have to be worked by the sales and qualified.","index":223,"end_time":839.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.94,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And then there should be a status of, oh, this is not a qualified lead.","index":224,"end_time":843.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.5,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"This is a employee, an existing customer employee.","index":225,"end_time":846.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":843.38,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So that should be the disqualification.","index":226,"end_time":848.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.54,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And we''re not tracking that right now.","index":227,"end_time":850.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":848.78,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So this is a perfect example of a decision where we''re making a decision and we don''t really have, you know, the details behind it.","index":228,"end_time":857.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.7,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And so I think that''s, that''s a, that''s the opportunities to fix that and then.","index":229,"end_time":861.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":857.38,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But we can talk more about CTAs, I think, with Josh.","index":230,"end_time":866.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":862.31,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And it doesn''t have to be right now because I think we''ll run out.","index":231,"end_time":868.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.03,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":232,"end_time":869.23,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":868.95,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"The other thing I''m just thinking about is I. I don''t know why we have requested demo up there and to the right where the login is.","index":233,"end_time":874.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":869.23,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"The other thing too is.","index":234,"end_time":876.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.43,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I mean, I just, I. I kind of feel like that''s where login should be and that we shouldn''t have them next to each other.","index":235,"end_time":881.75,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":877.03,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Well, but best practices, Rob.","index":236,"end_time":884.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.07,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So if you look at any other website, you''re going to have your.","index":237,"end_time":887.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":884.59,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"The main goal of this marketing site is to drive Legion.","index":238,"end_time":890.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.27,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And so that is the most.","index":239,"end_time":892.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":891.31,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"The biggest real estate.","index":240,"end_time":894.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":893.07,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"That''s where every.","index":241,"end_time":894.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":894.19,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Every other website is going to have that there in the right corner.","index":242,"end_time":897.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":894.91,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So that treatment, I actually think is right.","index":243,"end_time":899.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.79,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I think that''s the right treatment, to be honest with you.","index":244,"end_time":902.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.19,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, I see.","index":245,"end_time":904.27,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":903.23,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Based on, you know, every other website out there.","index":246,"end_time":907.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":904.75,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And that''s.","index":247,"end_time":908.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":907.39,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"That''s.","index":248,"end_time":908.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":908.35,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So I. I think that''s the right strategy there.","index":249,"end_time":911.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":908.79,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Got it.","index":250,"end_time":911.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":911.27,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I see it.","index":251,"end_time":912.27,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":911.67,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":252,"end_time":912.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":912.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''m looking at a few others.","index":253,"end_time":913.79,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":912.75,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"My.","index":254,"end_time":914.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.19,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Another thing, we don''t have to go into details now because I think we''re out of time, but for example, the research I''ve done, what I''ve all heard is you should have cons.","index":255,"end_time":921.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.59,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You shouldn''t have, like, if requested demo is your main cta.","index":256,"end_time":925.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.93,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I would not change the wording of See how it works.","index":257,"end_time":928.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.53,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Unless See how it works is like a demo experience or some other kind of.","index":258,"end_time":933.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.05,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You know, so those are the kinds of things.","index":259,"end_time":935.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933.93,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But let''s.","index":260,"end_time":935.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.37,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Let''s table a.","index":261,"end_time":936.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.93,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Let''s, as an action item, have a CTA discussion and let''s do some sort of research gathering or some thoughts gathering and come to that, is what I would say.","index":262,"end_time":946.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.97,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":263,"end_time":946.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":946.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, cool.","index":264,"end_time":948.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":946.77,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Just write that down.","index":265,"end_time":950.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":949.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":266,"end_time":952.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":952.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":267,"end_time":955.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":954.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yes, we can go through that.","index":268,"end_time":956.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":955.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, Kermit, I know you also had a question just about like HubSpot as a CMS versus, you know, a platform like WordPress or something else.","index":269,"end_time":963.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":956.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":270,"end_time":964.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":963.87,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Oh, I''d rather.","index":271,"end_time":965.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":964.35,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''d rather table that.","index":272,"end_time":967.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.75,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And if you guys could bring some thoughts to the meeting with Natalie or Nina or if you''re.","index":273,"end_time":972.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":967.15,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''d rather not discuss it here now because I want to gather facts and come with a recommendation.","index":274,"end_time":978.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":973.07,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So.","index":275,"end_time":978.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.56,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, table that.","index":276,"end_time":980.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":979.12,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":277,"end_time":980.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":980.32,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":278,"end_time":981.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":980.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we just wanted to check on your.","index":279,"end_time":984.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":982.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your progress through reviewing the pages.","index":280,"end_time":986.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":984.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you expecting.","index":281,"end_time":986.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":986.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is anyone else reviewing.","index":282,"end_time":987.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":986.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you still going through pages?","index":283,"end_time":988.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":987.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just wanted to check if we''re good to start going through and making changes.","index":284,"end_time":991.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":988.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I Mean, I think, I think the urgent things are what like Rob talked about, you know, one of the things we haven''t done is fully fleshed out the brand.","index":285,"end_time":1003.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":994.88,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So that''s kind of one of the things I want to work with you guys on.","index":286,"end_time":1005.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1003.89,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But we would have a brand guidelines that says no AI images that like, that''s just like a brand, you know, criteria.","index":287,"end_time":1013.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1006.17,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But that''s.","index":288,"end_time":1014.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.61,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So that''s the kind of feedback that I think is urgent.","index":289,"end_time":1016.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1014.25,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And I think we gave you the other feedback, you know, and I think these pages kind of evolve.","index":290,"end_time":1024.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1016.57,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I would say my big pushback is just not understanding the UX strategy.","index":291,"end_time":1030.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1024.29,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Right.","index":292,"end_time":1031.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1031.08,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Like the, you know, what, what is the staff going to look like?","index":293,"end_time":1034.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1031.48,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So that maybe that''s another session, we have to discuss that.","index":294,"end_time":1039.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1036.12,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Or maybe you just push some of these pages live that we all agree on and then we can evolve and fix that next phase.","index":295,"end_time":1046.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1039.48,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But that''s, I think that''s my.","index":296,"end_time":1050.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1046.52,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, let''s dive into that a little bit.","index":297,"end_time":1052.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1051,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So can you, can you elaborate a bit on what you mean with the UX strategy?","index":298,"end_time":1055.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1052.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":299,"end_time":1056.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1055.86,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So, you know, I don''t have the background.","index":300,"end_time":1059.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1056.26,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Right.","index":301,"end_time":1059.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1059.14,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So I''m coming in at, you know, day seven and how it looks to me is we''re just building a bunch of pages.","index":302,"end_time":1065.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1059.7,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So I don''t understand the rationale and think.","index":303,"end_time":1068.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1065.86,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''m not saying there are like, these are good pages, like yay.","index":304,"end_time":1070.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1068.02,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''m feeling like, oh, glad that they''re solving some of the things I quickly noticed that were, you know, like the industry pages.","index":305,"end_time":1076.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.98,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But, but typically the approach I''m used to is where there''s a little bit more and maybe you''ve done this all.","index":306,"end_time":1083.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1076.82,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I just haven''t seen it right.","index":307,"end_time":1084.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1083.86,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Like the discovery phase of like looking at compet competitor sites and doing the Persona insights and doing all that stuff to then fit and the customer journey.","index":308,"end_time":1092.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1084.9,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And therefore this is what the UX recommendation is.","index":309,"end_time":1095.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.48,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So I don''t have that information.","index":310,"end_time":1097.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1095.44,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So I don''t.","index":311,"end_time":1098.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1097.36,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So, so I don''t.","index":312,"end_time":1099.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1098.24,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And I.","index":313,"end_time":1099.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1099.56,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And when I''m sort of saying what is the site map?","index":314,"end_time":1101.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1099.84,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"What''s it going to look like?","index":315,"end_time":1102.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1101.8,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Where, where are these industry pages going?","index":316,"end_time":1104.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1102.64,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Where are the Persona pages going?","index":317,"end_time":1105.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1104.44,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I don''t understand that at this point.","index":318,"end_time":1108,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1105.88,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"That''s, that''s a gap, you know.","index":319,"end_time":1110.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1108,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So yeah, yeah, we, we had a table that we had originally shared.","index":320,"end_time":1113.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1110.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can show a site map so we can put that together for you so that everything is a bit more clear.","index":321,"end_time":1117.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1113.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":322,"end_time":1118.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1118.44,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So.","index":323,"end_time":1119.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1118.84,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And then I''d like to see that and then I''ll have a better take on the Personas because I don''t really understand those.","index":324,"end_time":1124.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1119.12,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"That, that doesn''t make sense to me.","index":325,"end_time":1126.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1124.44,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But again, I there.","index":326,"end_time":1127.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1126.04,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I don''t think the deep Persona insights gathering has been done.","index":327,"end_time":1131.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1127.4,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So would it be beneficial if I compile one document with all the discussions that we had about brand Personas and how we want to decide to move and the copy?","index":328,"end_time":1144.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1132.68,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So maybe it would give a bit more of, a bit more context because I understand it''s difficult to see, especially because it was not one discussion but a lot of them.","index":329,"end_time":1155.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1144.64,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So I can just collect them and then you can read them out and maybe it will be.","index":330,"end_time":1159.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1155.11,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, if that''s going to help answer the rationale between.","index":331,"end_time":1162.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.67,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"First of all, I don''t even know what the proposal is other than here''s a bunch of pages we''re adding.","index":332,"end_time":1166.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1162.71,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Right?","index":333,"end_time":1167.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1167.03,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":334,"end_time":1168.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1168.23,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So if you''ve got something that says we are proposing this new UX, new nav structure and then the rationale, that would be great.","index":335,"end_time":1177.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1168.59,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And then, then I can chime in on that.","index":336,"end_time":1179.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1177.36,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Otherwise we just go, okay, we agree on certain pages, like obviously the homepage.","index":337,"end_time":1185.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1180.96,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"We''re all aligned on evolving that.","index":338,"end_time":1187.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1185.2,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"We''re aligned on adding industry pages, updating the pricing.","index":339,"end_time":1192.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1187.92,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So yeah, push those live, you know, and then because we can, it''s a living, breathing thing.","index":340,"end_time":1198,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1192.12,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"We can, we can evolve from here.","index":341,"end_time":1199.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1198,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"It''s not.","index":342,"end_time":1199.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1199.4,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Nothing''s the end of the world.","index":343,"end_time":1200.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1199.72,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, great.","index":344,"end_time":1203.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1201.66,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Hey, Josh.","index":345,"end_time":1204.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1203.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, guys.","index":346,"end_time":1207.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1206.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Any other feedback?","index":347,"end_time":1208.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1207.5,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":348,"end_time":1208.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1208.54,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"On the website was.","index":349,"end_time":1210.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1208.98,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Did anybody else want to chime in on the question from Colin on additional website feedback?","index":350,"end_time":1216.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1210.06,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I know that I put in that we have two Lindsey''s on our homepage.","index":351,"end_time":1223.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1217.58,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I''m not even quite sure how that even happened, but because these, I''m assuming these, you know, customer comments are real from our list of, you know, hundreds that we have.","index":352,"end_time":1237.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1223.82,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So I''m not quite sure.","index":353,"end_time":1238.95,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1237.91,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And I don''t even know where these images come from.","index":354,"end_time":1241.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1238.95,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Rob, I, I don''t know if Sam used real testimonials or if honestly I have no, I have no idea what, what Sam did with that.","index":355,"end_time":1249.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1241.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I would hope that we use real customer funnels.","index":356,"end_time":1253.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1250.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have thousands of them.","index":357,"end_time":1254.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1253.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I don''t know what''s ended.","index":358,"end_time":1256.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1254.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, at least kill it.","index":359,"end_time":1259.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1257.12,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"At least get it off the page today.","index":360,"end_time":1261.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1259.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And one of the takeaways was a need for a content audit.","index":361,"end_time":1265.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1261.84,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So I''m going to take that on.","index":362,"end_time":1266.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1265.24,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So I could certainly also audit the testimonials, figure out where they came from, make sure they''re legit.","index":363,"end_time":1272.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1267.2,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But it sounds like Rob, in the meantime, we can go live or we can push this with what they''ve got for now until that audit is done.","index":364,"end_time":1282.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1274.08,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Is you.","index":365,"end_time":1282.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1282.62,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Are you thinking.","index":366,"end_time":1283.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1282.98,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''m just thinking.","index":367,"end_time":1285.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1284.5,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":368,"end_time":1285.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1285.3,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I don''t want two Lindsey''s up on my website.","index":369,"end_time":1287.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1285.66,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":370,"end_time":1288.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1288.02,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So.","index":371,"end_time":1289.14,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1288.74,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So however we get that done, however we get that done today, that''s what I want because I just think it''s lame.","index":372,"end_time":1294.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1289.54,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And I also, the other thing that I''m pretty adamant about is I don''t want photos of fake people on my website.","index":373,"end_time":1301.38,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1294.66,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":374,"end_time":1302.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1301.78,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Especially if it''s testimonials.","index":375,"end_time":1304.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1303.14,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Right.","index":376,"end_time":1305.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1305.07,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And the reason why I do that is because I can go to my competitors and you can actually do an image search.","index":377,"end_time":1311.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1306.11,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And it''s a bunch of bs.","index":378,"end_time":1312.91,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1311.43,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And I don''t.","index":379,"end_time":1314.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1313.47,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And I don''t want that.","index":380,"end_time":1314.63,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1314.07,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I want to be real.","index":381,"end_time":1315.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1314.63,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So if there''s no image to go with it, then I just want the name.","index":382,"end_time":1318.83,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1315.79,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"But if we have an image and some of them, we do, I want their image or we pull it from their LinkedIn or wherever.","index":383,"end_time":1324.75,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1319.07,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"But I.","index":384,"end_time":1326.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1325.47,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Any, anyhow, I think then, Rob, I''m like, I''m going off memory, but I would.","index":385,"end_time":1331.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1326.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think we don''t have the images of a lot of these people.","index":386,"end_time":1335.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1331.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And we also were thinking that we didn''t have their blessing to be able to show their image, which is why we didn''t pull anything from.","index":387,"end_time":1342.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1335.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"From LinkedIn.","index":388,"end_time":1343.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1342.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think, I think.","index":389,"end_time":1345.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1344.6,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I think when they give us the testimonial, I think we have the right to use their image and anything they give us.","index":390,"end_time":1353.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1345.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So I think that''s in the agreement.","index":391,"end_time":1356.44,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1355.16,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I''ll check receive, though.","index":392,"end_time":1358.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1356.92,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":393,"end_time":1358.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1358.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I would.","index":394,"end_time":1359.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1358.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":395,"end_time":1359.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1359.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":396,"end_time":1360.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1359.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":397,"end_time":1361.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1361.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Josh, I know that you mean.","index":398,"end_time":1362.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1361.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or you mean.","index":399,"end_time":1363.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1362.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nina and Sam have talked about that a few times where we asked about the testimonial.","index":400,"end_time":1367.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1363.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think with like.","index":401,"end_time":1368.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1367.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think Nina had noticed it was a stock image of a lady.","index":402,"end_time":1371.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1368.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":403,"end_time":1372.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1371.89,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":404,"end_time":1374.449,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1373.969,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I didn''t know if that was intentional or maybe a mistake.","index":405,"end_time":1378.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1374.69,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I mean, I''m sure we just did it at the time, but my feeling is it that should not be something we do.","index":406,"end_time":1385.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1379.57,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":407,"end_time":1386.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1385.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":408,"end_time":1386.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1386.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in the immediate, it''s kind of.","index":409,"end_time":1389.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1387.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like the AI imaging.","index":410,"end_time":1390.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1389.74,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Like, I don''t mind images if they don''t look like AI, but, you know, if they look like AI, I don''t.","index":411,"end_time":1396.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1390.74,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Think we should and say no AI images.","index":412,"end_time":1399.979,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1396.22,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Honestly, Rob, because.","index":413,"end_time":1401.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1399.979,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"What''s that?","index":414,"end_time":1402.3,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1401.66,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I would just literally say no AI images because they look like AI is subjective.","index":415,"end_time":1407.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1402.46,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And when it comes to images.","index":416,"end_time":1411.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1409.58,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Since you''re doing a content audit, Carmen, it would be really beneficial if you find certain images that you like either from other websites.","index":417,"end_time":1419.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1411.1,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Or just, I know, scrolling through even Instagram or Pinterest or wherever to show us how far you''re willing to go when it comes to, you know, what''s shown on the picture.","index":418,"end_time":1429.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1419.72,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Could they be a little bit warmer?","index":419,"end_time":1431.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1430.12,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Does it only have to be an officer environment?","index":420,"end_time":1433.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1431.6,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So that would be really useful.","index":421,"end_time":1435.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1433.88,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":422,"end_time":1436.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1435.96,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":423,"end_time":1438.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1437.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, for the homepage in the immediate.","index":424,"end_time":1440.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1438.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Rob, I hear you.","index":425,"end_time":1441.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1440.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll get the second of that testimonial off and then for an image, Josh, should we just find her LinkedIn profile and swap out with a real image?","index":426,"end_time":1450.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would rather, I think we have to figure out if we''re allowed to do that.","index":427,"end_time":1454.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1452.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I, I, I don''t love that idea personally, because I think we do our best at PTO Exchange to make our LinkedIn profiles look as professional as possible.","index":428,"end_time":1463.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1454.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know that everybody does that.","index":429,"end_time":1465.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1464.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And if we''re just using someone else''s image, it could be a selfie they took, like.","index":430,"end_time":1470.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1465.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":431,"end_time":1471.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1470.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And, and you know, we have the name of the people in the company they work for.","index":432,"end_time":1477.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1471.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I agree.","index":433,"end_time":1479.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1478.71,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You can just remove, like, hide the image.","index":434,"end_time":1481.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1479.23,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Hide the image, yeah.","index":435,"end_time":1483.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1481.67,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Cool.","index":436,"end_time":1485.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1484.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so that''s what we''ll do today.","index":437,"end_time":1486.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1485.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll work through the changes from the feedback that you guys provided so that we can get that page push live.","index":438,"end_time":1491.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":439,"end_time":1494.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1494.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any other questions around the website or ready to move into HubSpot audit?","index":440,"end_time":1498.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1494.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, and I''m, I''m sorry that I''m late, and I''m assuming Carmen probably said this because her and I talked about this on the side, but I do think that there will be more changes to it.","index":441,"end_time":1509.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1498.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think Carmen''s idea of, like, push it now and then, we can always update it and stuff.","index":442,"end_time":1514.559,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1509.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I think on those industry pages, we do want to do more research and show we know their industries more.","index":443,"end_time":1522.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1514.559,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I included some industry statistics on the couple of the pages where we have them.","index":444,"end_time":1528.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1522.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And we''ve done the research in the past, but showing we know what, like, turnover challenges there are in certain industries is really relevant.","index":445,"end_time":1537.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1528.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And we''re like, and we''re pulling these from articles and research that we''ve done.","index":446,"end_time":1542.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1537.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So it''s not like our necessarily our own data, it''s using other people''s data, but I think that there is value in that.","index":447,"end_time":1549.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1542.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So as we''re evolving these pages, I think that there''s certainly improvements we can make, especially on the industries side of things.","index":448,"end_time":1557.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1549.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep, 100%.","index":449,"end_time":1559.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1558.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":450,"end_time":1560.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1559.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And as Carmen mentioned, also, it''s a living, breathing thing.","index":451,"end_time":1562.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1560.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A website is organic.","index":452,"end_time":1563.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1562.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It should always be constantly updated.","index":453,"end_time":1564.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1563.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":454,"end_time":1567.449,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1566.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You mean not Every two years like we''ve been doing now.","index":455,"end_time":1569.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1567.449,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That leaves a lot of things to be updated.","index":456,"end_time":1572.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1571.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":457,"end_time":1573.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1572.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":458,"end_time":1575.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1575.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we sent over the full audit.","index":459,"end_time":1577.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1576.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Carmen, I know you''ve had this for a few days and then Josh, I know we just sent it over to you and Rob recently, so I imagine you haven''t had time to read through every page.","index":460,"end_time":1586.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1577.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not.","index":461,"end_time":1588.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1588.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I read through the like the initial key findings and like the recommended approach and expected impact stuff at the top.","index":462,"end_time":1600.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1588.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So all like the executive overview section, but I haven''t dug into it.","index":463,"end_time":1604.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1601.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, as expected.","index":464,"end_time":1606.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1604.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":465,"end_time":1607.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1606.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":466,"end_time":1608.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1607.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Carmen asked us to pull together just some high level overview.","index":467,"end_time":1611.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1608.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s what we have here.","index":468,"end_time":1613.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1611.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, I mean basically what we''ve discovered through an audit of several different objects as well as the companies that Carmen asked us to add in HubSpot is functional, but there''s a really important piece that needs to be established for integrity to just support scale attribution and like having overall pipeline visibility on the marketing side, on the sales side and as a leadership team.","index":469,"end_time":1637.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1613.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anyone that''s a user in HubSpot.","index":470,"end_time":1639.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1637.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this happens naturally with, with some HubSpot companies grow over time.","index":471,"end_time":1646.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1639.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They change their approach to something but then there isn''t like a cleanup effort to go back and change, you know, what is basically can be totally removed now.","index":472,"end_time":1655.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1646.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that leads to a gap in, well, what property do we report this on?","index":473,"end_time":1661.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1656.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What are the options in that drop down?","index":474,"end_time":1663.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1661.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Carmen has a great idea to say we should be breaking things down by channel and then have another bucket that goes into more detail.","index":475,"end_time":1670.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1663.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We completely agree with that.","index":476,"end_time":1671.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1670.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right now there''s seven different lead source fields as an example and not all of them are consistently updated.","index":477,"end_time":1677.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1671.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that leads to inconsistent data.","index":478,"end_time":1679.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1677.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That means that we have to do more work manually to really understand what''s going on inside the data, which then leads to a lack of confidence in that reporting.","index":479,"end_time":1688.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1679.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And when we''re trying to stay a new campaign and we''re saying like, hey, this one is delivering leads, but then we don''t have visibility on if it converts further down the line, then we don''t know what the best campaign to put forward is.","index":480,"end_time":1700.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1690.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I know that I shared a scary number in our last week''s meeting, but it is real.","index":481,"end_time":1711.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1705.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I mean there''s over 500 properties in HubSpot just for contacts, for example, and 95% of them roughly are very rarely if ever used or populated.","index":482,"end_time":1723.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1711.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s just a lot of extra space happening in HubSpot that is not being utilized really in any way with that there''s also 200 active workflows.","index":483,"end_time":1734.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1723.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Am I frozen?","index":484,"end_time":1734.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1734.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sorry.","index":485,"end_time":1736.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1735.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"200 active workflows that overlap in their logic.","index":486,"end_time":1740.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1737.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Josh, remember, we pulled up a contact, and they go through several different workflows that are almost like arguing each other.","index":487,"end_time":1744.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1740.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so those all need to be cleaned up.","index":488,"end_time":1746.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1745.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we just need to establish what the standardized approach is for, what properties we need, what workflows they need to go through so that when Steph or Dan or Josh gets a lead, and we''re like, hey, they filled out this benchmark report by clicking on a LinkedIn ad.","index":489,"end_time":1761.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1747.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you have all this information on them.","index":490,"end_time":1764.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1762.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Steph goes, okay, cool, I''m going to follow up because these are my nets, met my next steps.","index":491,"end_time":1769.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1764.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, hey, you know what?","index":492,"end_time":1770.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1769.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe they went cold.","index":493,"end_time":1771.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1770.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, next step, put them into nurture sequence.","index":494,"end_time":1774.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1771.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Put them into whatever we need to do.","index":495,"end_time":1775.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1774.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need.","index":496,"end_time":1776.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1775.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just need all of that clearly outlined.","index":497,"end_time":1778.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1776.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s what we were uncovering in this audit.","index":498,"end_time":1779.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1778.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just high level.","index":499,"end_time":1785.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1782.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"When we start to actually correct this kind of stuff, do you guys provide, like, sales enablement instructions so that our team kind of, like, knows what.","index":500,"end_time":1800.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1787.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What to do?","index":501,"end_time":1801.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1800.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, you can see Nina nodding aggressively because most of the clients that we work on together, we do that piece.","index":502,"end_time":1806.599,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1801.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":503,"end_time":1807.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1806.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":504,"end_time":1807.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1807.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I think that that, I mean, this is obviously way worse than whatever I would have imagined it was going to be, but I do think that there have been times in the past where we, like, thought we had a good idea.","index":505,"end_time":1821.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1808.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sam did something in HubSpot.","index":506,"end_time":1823.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1821.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It was never, like, really fully communicated what Sam was doing or what everybody should do, or it was verbally told to everyone.","index":507,"end_time":1830.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1824.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And there was like, you know, as soon as you forget it, it''s.","index":508,"end_time":1833.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1830.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s out the window.","index":509,"end_time":1834.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1833.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And now we have a property in there that doesn''t get used.","index":510,"end_time":1836.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1834.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, I think that''s how some of these properties came to be.","index":511,"end_time":1839.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1836.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":512,"end_time":1840.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1840.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It seems like it was a closing the loop that was lacking.","index":513,"end_time":1842.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1840.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":514,"end_time":1844.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1844.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And this isn''t me.","index":515,"end_time":1845.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1844.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, I''m not trying to say anything bad about Sam said or anything.","index":516,"end_time":1848.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1845.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just wanted an objective audit across the entire HubSpot instance.","index":517,"end_time":1851.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1848.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what really?","index":518,"end_time":1852.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1851.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We recommend being cleaned up.","index":519,"end_time":1854.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1852.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":520,"end_time":1854.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1854.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And I think it.","index":521,"end_time":1855.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1854.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think, Carmen, correct me if I''m wrong, but it goes.","index":522,"end_time":1857.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1855.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can hurt.","index":523,"end_time":1859.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1858.65,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We can hurt Sam''s feelings.","index":524,"end_time":1860.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1859.25,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"He''s not here.","index":525,"end_time":1860.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1860.25,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I''m gonna be honest with you.","index":526,"end_time":1863.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1861.69,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''m not sure I''ve ever met a company or client that''s like.","index":527,"end_time":1867.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1863.29,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"This is very, very common.","index":528,"end_time":1868.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1867.25,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So don''t feel bad.","index":529,"end_time":1869.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1868.79,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":530,"end_time":1870.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1869.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I thought you Were saying you''ve never met a client that was like this bad.","index":531,"end_time":1873.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1870.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No, no, no, no, no.","index":532,"end_time":1875.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1873.83,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''ve met worse.","index":533,"end_time":1876.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1875.11,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You''re good.","index":534,"end_time":1876.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1876.03,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I met worse.","index":535,"end_time":1879.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1878.31,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I met worse.","index":536,"end_time":1880.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1879.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So.","index":537,"end_time":1881.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1880.87,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So we''re.","index":538,"end_time":1882.59,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1882.07,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We''re good.","index":539,"end_time":1883.11,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1882.59,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Put that on the website.","index":540,"end_time":1884.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1883.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Rob.","index":541,"end_time":1884.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1884.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The bar is low.","index":542,"end_time":1885.75,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":1884.79,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Steph, welcome to the company.","index":543,"end_time":1889.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1888.23,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":544,"end_time":1894.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1893.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So here, you know, even just more representation.","index":545,"end_time":1895.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1894.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like the seven plus different fields that are calculating sources, some of them to what aren''t.","index":546,"end_time":1902.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1895.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We really need to establish a definition of what source meets.","index":547,"end_time":1906.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1903.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that because I know Carmen feels strongly that it shouldn''t be New north as a source.","index":548,"end_time":1910.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1906.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we agree with that.","index":549,"end_time":1911.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1910.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We should be able to break down by the activity, the channel, the medium that is being utilized versus and then ultimately that should still be able to tie back into whatever agency you have relationship wise, who''s working on these different pieces.","index":550,"end_time":1925.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1911.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But you guys need an easier method to understand like what is this group doing versus what is this group doing?","index":551,"end_time":1931.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1927.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But also by channel and to understand the lead quality.","index":552,"end_time":1935.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1931.58,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for example, what you mentioned about if a lead is unqualified or qualified, it would require for the salespeople to once they have a discussion with a lead to market as closed one, unqualified.","index":553,"end_time":1947.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1935.5,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then we know if everything is working.","index":554,"end_time":1950.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1947.58,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So just so I understand what we''re talking about here, are we talking about contacts here?","index":555,"end_time":1958.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1951.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we audited contact records and like every property for contacts as well as companies as well as deals and then did an audit on the companies in the actual HubSpot system.","index":556,"end_time":1969.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1960.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":557,"end_time":1970.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1969.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because like where we, where we''ve been using HubSpot or how we''ve been using HubSpot, I guess mostly for the last six years has been like our focus has been on the deal.","index":558,"end_time":1987.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1970.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":559,"end_time":1988.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1988,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sam was trying to do stuff with contacts and we''re trying to do stuff with companies.","index":560,"end_time":1992.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1988.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But like I think we''ve put most of our effort and attention into the deal part of HubSpot.","index":561,"end_time":2000.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1992.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep.","index":562,"end_time":2001.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2000.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The lead sources that we have there for, for actual opportunities.","index":563,"end_time":2007.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2001.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t really want to change anything there.","index":564,"end_time":2011.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2008.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like such as New north versus demanding channel.","index":565,"end_time":2017.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2013.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Inbound, demanding event.","index":566,"end_time":2022.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2020.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"To me like that, that is very, that''s very important for me on the sales side.","index":567,"end_time":2030.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2023.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And I, and I.","index":568,"end_time":2032.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2031.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And we use those like I would be.","index":569,"end_time":2034.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2032.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know that we even could have anything where those fields are not populated on a deal today.","index":570,"end_time":2040.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2034.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think it''s set up that those are required fields and we use those in a ton of reporting and we use those for a lot of decisions we make.","index":571,"end_time":2046.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2040.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Lead source for a contact is totally, totally different.","index":572,"end_time":2054.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2048.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But from an opportunity.","index":573,"end_time":2057.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2054.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We need to know where did the opportunity come from.","index":574,"end_time":2059.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2057.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I just want to make sure we''re not touching those kind of deal properties.","index":575,"end_time":2065.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2060.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So.","index":576,"end_time":2068.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2067.95,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So to have one property is deal source and another property property is contact source.","index":577,"end_time":2076.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2070.11,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, those are different properties.","index":578,"end_time":2080.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2078.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That, that''s fine.","index":579,"end_time":2081.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2080.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But we need to know we compensate people on it differently.","index":580,"end_time":2087.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2082.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We pay, commit like commissions and rev share on things differently.","index":581,"end_time":2092.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2087.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we need to have that tracked in the deals.","index":582,"end_time":2098.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2092.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, okay, I gotcha.","index":583,"end_time":2102.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2100.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, I mean, what this leads me to is that we just need alignment.","index":584,"end_time":2104.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2102.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Carmen, this is probably just an extra meeting where maybe if you talk to Josh in between now and then, and then we just align on exactly how we break this up.","index":585,"end_time":2111.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2104.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, and I''ll wait till you''re.","index":586,"end_time":2114.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2113.26,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I will let you finish your whole thing.","index":587,"end_time":2116.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2114.98,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":588,"end_time":2117.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2117.18,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yep.","index":589,"end_time":2119.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2118.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So also just cleaning up how life cycle stages are used, lead status stages, everything like that.","index":590,"end_time":2126.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2120.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again, when we''re doing marketing efforts and Steph and Dan and whoever else on the sales team are doing efforts, everyone is communicating the same.","index":591,"end_time":2133.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2126.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have an understanding of why someone was qualified, why they weren''t qualified, and then we can boil that down into like the campaign on a new AB test, things like that.","index":592,"end_time":2142.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2133.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s really just about cleaning up all of these fields, eliminating historical options that haven''t been used in a long time, and then establishing what that flow should look like across HubSpot.","index":593,"end_time":2151.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2142.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just coming from an outside perspective, I totally agree with this because I think that''s different for me joining this organization where there''s no clear kind of understanding of what an MQL is versus an SQL, because it''s a different definition for every organization.","index":594,"end_time":2171.51,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2154.16,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"But yeah, I think they''re.","index":595,"end_time":2174.39,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2173.11,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"That kind of establishing what is considered an SQL for me is really important.","index":596,"end_time":2180.23,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2174.39,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"And like you said, to be able to kind of close things out or put them into kind of like a loss category and like what the reason is.","index":597,"end_time":2187.83,"speaker_id":6,"start_time":2180.23,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So glad to hear this.","index":598,"end_time":2189.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2187.83,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry, Carmen, I thought you were.","index":599,"end_time":2194.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2190.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, just the other thing that''s different that I haven''t seen before is typically there''s a little bit of walling off with this is marketing and this is handed over to sales, and then this is sales, whereas I feel it''s a little bit of a free for all.","index":600,"end_time":2209.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2194.67,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So that''s another thing that as we kind of figure out definitions and SLAs and the lead management process and all of that, that will probably become a little bit more structured, I''m thinking.","index":601,"end_time":2224.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2211.31,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But my question, Colin, is like, what''s next and how do we solve this and so what does your team.","index":602,"end_time":2229.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2224.19,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''d love to hear what your team offers by way of being a third party facilitator.","index":603,"end_time":2235.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2229.47,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"We have marketing me now and sales.","index":604,"end_time":2238.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2235.95,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And how do we, you know, bring that alignment, bring the, you know, service level agreement and all that in place to get the work done and fixed?","index":605,"end_time":2247.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2238.67,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"There''s a lot here.","index":606,"end_time":2248.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2247.87,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, absolutely.","index":607,"end_time":2250.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2249.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re a HubSpot partner.","index":608,"end_time":2251.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2250.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do HubSpot projects all the time.","index":609,"end_time":2252.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2251.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I would say and recommend as next steps.","index":610,"end_time":2255.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2253.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Carmen, can you hear me?","index":611,"end_time":2256.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2255.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s frozen again.","index":612,"end_time":2257.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2256.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you hear me now?","index":613,"end_time":2262.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2261.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I never understand why in Seattle there would be an Internet issue.","index":614,"end_time":2268.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2264.29,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But anyway, sorry, I''ll try to be quick.","index":615,"end_time":2270.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2268.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m four minutes late to another meeting.","index":616,"end_time":2272.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2270.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But what we.","index":617,"end_time":2274.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2272.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re HubSpot partners.","index":618,"end_time":2275.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2274.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we usually do as next steps is set up like the spreadsheets of how we want to map all these properties, what they actually mean, and then who''s responsible for them.","index":619,"end_time":2282.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2275.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So then we get started with that approach.","index":620,"end_time":2285.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2283.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you like, is there a proposal you need to send us or is it part of our retainer?","index":621,"end_time":2289.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2285.95,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"This is part of the retainer.","index":622,"end_time":2291.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2289.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":623,"end_time":2292.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2291.87,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":624,"end_time":2294.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2292.75,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Do you want to just send over a recap of what exactly you''ll do as next steps then, or.","index":625,"end_time":2298.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2294.39,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, sure, we can put that together.","index":626,"end_time":2299.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2298.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we should probably set a. Yeah, I''m going to talk a little bit more with Josh and Rob next Tuesday morning about this, but so maybe we can set something for.","index":627,"end_time":2311.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2299.63,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"For next week after that time?","index":628,"end_time":2312.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2311.49,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":629,"end_time":2314.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2313.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":630,"end_time":2315.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2315.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like I said, I''m five minutes late to another meeting.","index":631,"end_time":2318.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2316.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I apologize.","index":632,"end_time":2319.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2318.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I do need to jump.","index":633,"end_time":2319.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2319.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll send over Nina and Allie, we''ll send over the presentation and all the links and everything that we talked through.","index":634,"end_time":2325.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2319.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then if you guys have any questions, please do not hesitate to let us know.","index":635,"end_time":2328.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2325.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Rob, we''ll prioritize getting that image removed on the testimonial and the double Wendy on the homepage.","index":636,"end_time":2334.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2328.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lindsay.","index":637,"end_time":2335.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2335.01,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Nice.","index":638,"end_time":2336.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2335.61,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And Natalie, are we going to stay on or do a different link?","index":639,"end_time":2338.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2336.01,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"We can stay on this one if you want.","index":640,"end_time":2341.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2340,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":641,"end_time":2342.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2341.28,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":642,"end_time":2342.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2342.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then you''re welcome to stay on as well.","index":643,"end_time":2344.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2342.8,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":644,"end_time":2346.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2345.84,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, thank you, guys.","index":645,"end_time":2347.96,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2346.88,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"All right, see you.","index":646,"end_time":2348.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2347.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, so, Josh, I was thinking I needed a little extra time each week with the strategy team.","index":647,"end_time":2357.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2351.04,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So it looks like Nina is eventually transitioning out and Natalie taking over, if I got that right.","index":648,"end_time":2364.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2357.72,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I know I keep getting your news mixed up, but sorry about that.","index":649,"end_time":2367.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2364.77,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So, yeah, Josh hoping to use this time.","index":650,"end_time":2371.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2367.93,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So right after the wider team meeting having just a deeper dive into some of these initiatives.","index":651,"end_time":2376.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2371.13,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So that was.","index":652,"end_time":2377.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2376.61,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"That''s the goal of this.","index":653,"end_time":2378.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2377.17,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Maybe we can use this time a little bit to talk about any of things that came up on the call today, Josh, because I know you missed a little bit and it was a whirlwind.","index":654,"end_time":2388.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2379.45,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m.","index":655,"end_time":2392.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2392.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''m not sure what I missed.","index":656,"end_time":2394.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2392.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I didn''t really have.","index":657,"end_time":2396.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2394.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t have too many questions from what I.","index":658,"end_time":2398.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2396.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"From the 15 minutes that I heard towards the end.","index":659,"end_time":2401.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2398.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, there''s a lot of work we need to do.","index":660,"end_time":2404.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2402.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":661,"end_time":2406.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2405.3,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I mean, I guess that''s my.","index":662,"end_time":2407.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2406.38,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"One of the questions I came out of the audit is like, there''s a lot of cleanup.","index":663,"end_time":2412.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2407.5,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Right.","index":664,"end_time":2412.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2412.18,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Like, for example, I just went in and I don''t.","index":665,"end_time":2414.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2412.58,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''m not the HubSpot person at all.","index":666,"end_time":2416.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2414.7,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Right.","index":667,"end_time":2416.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2416.22,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But I was trying to figure out how to create a list of everybody that does not have an email because that would kind of be a starting point for, you know, like, cleaning up the database.","index":668,"end_time":2425.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2416.38,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Like, because, you know, if237,000 records, like, are these quality.","index":669,"end_time":2429.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2425.2,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Are they our audience?","index":670,"end_time":2431.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2429.92,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You know.","index":671,"end_time":2431.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2431.24,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So how do you guys.","index":672,"end_time":2435.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2433.24,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"What do you recommend on.","index":673,"end_time":2436.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2435.16,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"On that data integrity cleanup piece?","index":674,"end_time":2439.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2436.6,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Like, a lot of duplicates.","index":675,"end_time":2440.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2439.28,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''m searching for a company like a client, a deal, and there''s duplicates.","index":676,"end_time":2445.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2440.76,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So, you know, how do we.","index":677,"end_time":2447.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2445.32,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry.","index":678,"end_time":2448.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2447.73,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Curious on that.","index":679,"end_time":2449.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2449.01,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I mean, it''s going to be hard to do a lot of this stuff without Sam.","index":680,"end_time":2453.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2450.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"To be totally honest.","index":681,"end_time":2455.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2454.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I, I really like let Sam manage HubSpot because I''m not a HubSpot.","index":682,"end_time":2461.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2456.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like.","index":683,"end_time":2462.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2462.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":684,"end_time":2463.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2463.01,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Expert is.","index":685,"end_time":2465.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2464.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is the first time I''ve ever used HubSpot in my career.","index":686,"end_time":2468.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2465.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I do like, I do like HubSpot a lot, but I, but I''m not.","index":687,"end_time":2473.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2469.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know how Sam set things up.","index":688,"end_time":2475.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2473.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I do.","index":689,"end_time":2475.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2475.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We run into that issue like you''re talking about with duplicate companies.","index":690,"end_time":2479.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2476.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If someone comes in and their email domain, like if, if a company had like PTO exchange.com or trypto exchange.com that I think automatically creates two different companies inside of.","index":691,"end_time":2499.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2479.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Of HubSpot, which is part of the issue that we have.","index":692,"end_time":2503.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2499.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s like automated.","index":693,"end_time":2504.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2503.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":694,"end_time":2504.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2504.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Or if somebody had like a job change, it would create two different profiles for the same person.","index":695,"end_time":2510.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2505.62,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Right.","index":696,"end_time":2511.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2511.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Or a company acquires another company and now the legacy emails are still used.","index":697,"end_time":2515.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2511.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, I think that that has caused a lot of duplications inside of HubSpot.","index":698,"end_time":2520.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2515.78,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know how to fix that.","index":699,"end_time":2522.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2520.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I get.","index":700,"end_time":2523.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2523.14,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"That was my.","index":701,"end_time":2524.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2523.7,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"More my question.","index":702,"end_time":2524.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2524.22,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":703,"end_time":2525.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2525.06,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Josh.","index":704,"end_time":2525.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2525.58,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But my question was actually more for Nina and Natalie.","index":705,"end_time":2528.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2525.86,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Like does your team or do you guys have resources?","index":706,"end_time":2531.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2528.54,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And I''m assuming there''s like rules and settings you could do to mitigate this going forward that was never in place.","index":707,"end_time":2537.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2531.22,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I mean, we could make a test to merge all contacts.","index":708,"end_time":2543.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2539.6,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I mean it would require a little bit of time, but we can discuss with Colin if we can have a member of our team take on the task.","index":709,"end_time":2551.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2543.28,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":710,"end_time":2552.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2552.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We have developers that are very experienced in HubSpot.","index":711,"end_time":2555.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2552.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This could be something that we take back to them and just see what their thoughts are like.","index":712,"end_time":2559.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2555.72,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I almost feel like, Josh, that now that we have this audit, we''re like, okay, we have these problems.","index":713,"end_time":2565.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2559.77,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Is it.","index":714,"end_time":2565.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2565.29,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"How do we tackle each of those three key areas?","index":715,"end_time":2568.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2565.81,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Right.","index":716,"end_time":2569.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2568.73,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So what does your team recommend?","index":717,"end_time":2572.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2569.37,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And you know, whether it''s additional resources and additional costs to do this?","index":718,"end_time":2578.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2573.13,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You know, the data architecture, the attribution reporting and the lead management.","index":719,"end_time":2582.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2578.29,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"There''s kind of three separate initiatives that comes out of this.","index":720,"end_time":2586.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2582.57,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Right.","index":721,"end_time":2586.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2586.13,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So, all right, what''s the recommendation to solve this?","index":722,"end_time":2589.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2586.69,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And you know, and, and knowing that we don''t have a full time HubSpot administrator over here.","index":723,"end_time":2597.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2590.29,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Right.","index":724,"end_time":2598.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2597.81,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So this is my thoughts, Josh.","index":725,"end_time":2601.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2598.45,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And, and then coming up with a game plan of what, you know, what needs to happen and what''s going to take to solve it.","index":726,"end_time":2608.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2601.81,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Because I think, Josh, you''re, you had a dedicated person, which is good.","index":727,"end_time":2612.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2609.33,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But maybe not so much because we, it''s.","index":728,"end_time":2615.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2612.97,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"The result has been, it''s kind of where we''re at, which is a lot to clean up.","index":729,"end_time":2620.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2615.82,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":730,"end_time":2622.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2622.42,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"A lot of it.","index":731,"end_time":2623.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2623.06,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"It''s manual work.","index":732,"end_time":2624.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2623.74,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for example, if you have duplicates in HubSpot, it happens in almost every company, especially if they work with a lot of contacts, if they have lead lists or if they use third party lists.","index":733,"end_time":2635.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2624.94,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And from my experience, we usually had like one person take on the database and then do a whole cleanup.","index":734,"end_time":2645.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2635.86,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But since it''s manual and it has to be merged from one contact to the other, it takes a little bit more time.","index":735,"end_time":2651.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2645.12,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I would almost do a matrix of this has to get done.","index":736,"end_time":2655.639,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2652.6,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And then whether it''s manual, which is PTO exchange, or whether it''s you guys as developer.","index":737,"end_time":2660.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2655.639,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Right.","index":738,"end_time":2661,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2660.72,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Like map out.","index":739,"end_time":2661.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2661,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And then we can decide, Josh, whether I go in and do the duplicate fix or how we solve it.","index":740,"end_time":2668.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2663,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"If it''s on our and to fix.","index":741,"end_time":2670.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2668.48,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"That''s what I would do.","index":742,"end_time":2672.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2671.36,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":743,"end_time":2672.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2672.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Rob, I don''t know if you''re out there, but I am.","index":744,"end_time":2676.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2672.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What.","index":745,"end_time":2676.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2676.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"When we''re talking about we have 237,000 contacts in HubSpot, do we know how many of them are users?","index":746,"end_time":2685.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2678,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t think we do.","index":747,"end_time":2688.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2687.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I mean, I, I think that like what I''m hearing right now is I think there''s a lot of duplicates.","index":748,"end_time":2692.96,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2688.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"That''s one issue.","index":749,"end_time":2694.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2694,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Duplicates is one issue.","index":750,"end_time":2696.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2694.88,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But your question, Josh, about whether they''re a customer and a user.","index":751,"end_time":2700.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2696.12,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I thought I saw somewhere in the deep dive audit that you guys sent that son of listed that.","index":752,"end_time":2706.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2700.85,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So I jumped to the inclusion you guys were.","index":753,"end_time":2709.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2706.65,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"There was a field in there that there is tracking on whether someone''s a customer or not, that these 237,000 contacts in your database are not customers necessarily like users.","index":754,"end_time":2720.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2709.33,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But I don''t know for sure that, Josh.","index":755,"end_time":2722.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2720.53,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I was, I was leading, you know, I was thinking it anyway.","index":756,"end_time":2727.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2722.77,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So what do you guys think, Natalie?","index":757,"end_time":2729.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2727.33,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Do you guys know?","index":758,"end_time":2729.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2729.13,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Have you dug into the data?","index":759,"end_time":2731.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2729.93,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So right now in the audit, just looking at the life cycle stages, it says there are 46,000 marketing under, under customer.","index":760,"end_time":2744.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2732.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, so you''re saying there are 46, 000 customers, but are those buyers customers or they''re people that interesting?","index":761,"end_time":2754.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2745.05,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Okay, there''s your answer, Josh.","index":762,"end_time":2757.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2754.29,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":763,"end_time":2759.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2758.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"To be honest, if it''s users, I''m surprised it''s not higher.","index":764,"end_time":2764.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2759.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Again, it''s.","index":765,"end_time":2773.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2771.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s like really hard to do this without Sam.","index":766,"end_time":2776.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2773.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know how, if we can get Sam involved in this process, but I feel like some of these answers.","index":767,"end_time":2781.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2776.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sam just knows because he''s, because he set it up so.","index":768,"end_time":2785.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2781.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have Sam on retainer so we can have Sam join a meeting.","index":769,"end_time":2789.59,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2786.95,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"It''s just gonna have to be on his time.","index":770,"end_time":2791.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2789.59,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Time schedule.","index":771,"end_time":2792.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2791.51,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":772,"end_time":2793.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2792.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I would say for the, this project, for the HubSpot cleanup project, let''s see if we need Sam in on it.","index":773,"end_time":2800.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2793.83,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think there are definitely going to be some aspects where we can try to like make assumptions or poke around and try to figure it out.","index":774,"end_time":2813.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2802.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Whereas if we just got Sam involved, he would just tell us what the answer.","index":775,"end_time":2815.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2813.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What the answer was.","index":776,"end_time":2816.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2815.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So if we have, if we do some preliminary work so that we have a list of questions that we can ask them, we could probably knock out a ton of stuff on like a half an hour or an hour call with him where we''re like, okay, right, we need to understand how this was.","index":777,"end_time":2831.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2817.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Structured, set up and structured.","index":778,"end_time":2835.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2833.56,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":779,"end_time":2835.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2835.08,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"The other thing, the other thing is we obviously should take all the venture capitalists out of this thing that we have in here.","index":780,"end_time":2843.08,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2836.04,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Right.","index":781,"end_time":2845.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2845.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We had VCS in here at one point in time and I''m sure they''re still there.","index":782,"end_time":2848.92,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2845.56,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t think there.","index":783,"end_time":2850.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2849.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There''s a ton that are in there.","index":784,"end_time":2852,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2850.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But you''re right, there''s.","index":785,"end_time":2852.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2852,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know.","index":786,"end_time":2853.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2852.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I still think if, if I may the.","index":787,"end_time":2857.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2853.88,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I think the next step is for New north to go to the next step which is to give us.","index":788,"end_time":2864.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2857.89,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Here''s how we''re going to solve this and these are the things that we''re going to do and these are the things you guys need to do.","index":789,"end_time":2871.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2864.85,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And.","index":790,"end_time":2874.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2873.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Then we can kind of take this as an probably the three is three separate initiatives.","index":791,"end_time":2878.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2874.37,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So database cleanup or database integrity.","index":792,"end_time":2881.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2878.57,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Right.","index":793,"end_time":2881.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2881.09,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And then the attribution and the tracking and reporting and the lead management.","index":794,"end_time":2884.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2881.49,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And so that''s why I would break it out.","index":795,"end_time":2890.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2886.13,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And these things that need to do and who does what and.","index":796,"end_time":2894.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2890.69,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And then we can kick those off and figure out where.","index":797,"end_time":2898.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2894.45,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Where we need.","index":798,"end_time":2899.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2898.21,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":799,"end_time":2899.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2899.01,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":800,"end_time":2899.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2899.41,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Anyway, I mean can''t we.","index":801,"end_time":2901.97,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2899.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I mean I would think you could go through here and I''m just kind of playing around in here.","index":802,"end_time":2905.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2902.05,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"I mean there''s a ton of Gmail on icloud and you know.","index":803,"end_time":2910.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2906.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"You know, kill them or just records that don''t have an email because it''s.","index":804,"end_time":2914.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2910.94,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Not or they don''t have it.","index":805,"end_time":2915.38,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2914.3,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah, they don''t have an email.","index":806,"end_time":2916.34,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2915.38,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Like there''s.","index":807,"end_time":2917.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2916.34,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Right.","index":808,"end_time":2918.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2917.9,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I mean I don''t know why we would keep anyone with a Gmail account.","index":809,"end_time":2920.7,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2918.22,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So I almost think that database.","index":810,"end_time":2923.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2921.34,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Josh, would you.","index":811,"end_time":2924.38,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2923.58,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Do you see any reason why we keep anyone with a Gmail account?","index":812,"end_time":2926.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2924.38,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"No, we.","index":813,"end_time":2928.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2927.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No.","index":814,"end_time":2928.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2928.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But we get.","index":815,"end_time":2929.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2928.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Or an icloud.","index":816,"end_time":2930.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2929.34,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We do get a lot of people that come to the site and request a demo or fill out a form and use a personal email address.","index":817,"end_time":2938.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2931.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we should change that.","index":818,"end_time":2939.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2938.95,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"We should make.","index":819,"end_time":2940.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2940.07,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"It has to be a business email.","index":820,"end_time":2941.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2940.63,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":821,"end_time":2942.71,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2942.15,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So those are the fixes.","index":822,"end_time":2945.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2943.83,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"That''s what would come out of this audit essentially.","index":823,"end_time":2948.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2945.51,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So what happens if they go in and they try to download something and use a Gmail email account?","index":824,"end_time":2954.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2948.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, an error pops up on the form fill out.","index":825,"end_time":2958.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2955.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":826,"end_time":2959.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2959.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We could develop it in a way that says they have to use a business domain in order to submit it.","index":827,"end_time":2964.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2959.47,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"One note there though is I do see some people, some companies moving more toward accepting Gmail accounts because it does allow you to follow prospects as they change jobs.","index":828,"end_time":2974.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2965.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So if you have a prospect that submits a form with the business email, they change their job and then that email no longer works.","index":829,"end_time":2982.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2975.59,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You then lose contact with them versus with Gmails you are able to nurture for a long, longer term.","index":830,"end_time":2987.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2982.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The other thing you can do, Natalie, is we could make the Request a demo which is high commitment, low funnel.","index":831,"end_time":2995.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2988.79,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"We could a business email only and you can have your upper funnel content pieces and such and demo experience, whatever.","index":832,"end_time":3005.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2995.95,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Those could be the personal emails.","index":833,"end_time":3006.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3005.01,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"That''s the less of an issue.","index":834,"end_time":3008.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3006.97,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I just think.","index":835,"end_time":3008.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3008.09,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Then that does lead to Gmails and iclouds being in the database.","index":836,"end_time":3016.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3011.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":837,"end_time":3016.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3016.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If we''re allowing them to download the form.","index":838,"end_time":3018.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3016.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":839,"end_time":3018.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3018.33,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"What I''m saying is I''m not so concerned about that as being as far as cleanup.","index":840,"end_time":3023.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3018.65,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So like database cleanup is the thing we''re solving.","index":841,"end_time":3026.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3023.57,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"That''s one of the things to look at is what type of email.","index":842,"end_time":3029.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3026.81,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But I think there''s a whole lot of things we can look at before that to clean up the database.","index":843,"end_time":3034.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3029.65,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"What if Carmen, that''s the wall between MQL and SQL.","index":844,"end_time":3038.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3035.29,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":845,"end_time":3040.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3039.93,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I mean so what we need, I.","index":846,"end_time":3041.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3040.29,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Mean like if it''s a demo.","index":847,"end_time":3043.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3041.53,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Josh.","index":848,"end_time":3043.45,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3043.05,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Right.","index":849,"end_time":3043.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3043.45,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And I''m.","index":850,"end_time":3044.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3043.73,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"And I want my company address.","index":851,"end_time":3045.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3044.29,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So the first meeting when we get to lead management and defining that there''s a whole process around like the bank criteria and that that we should think about like do they have the budget, do they have the authority, the timeline?","index":852,"end_time":3056.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3046.17,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So that whole initiative of getting a tight lead management process in place is one of these initiatives that we should tackle.","index":853,"end_time":3065.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3057.57,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And so you''re right Rob.","index":854,"end_time":3068.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3065.97,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So as in better qualification of that lead before it''s handed over to sales and worked is essentially what you''re saying.","index":855,"end_time":3077.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3068.77,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And I agree.","index":856,"end_time":3077.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3077.17,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":857,"end_time":3078.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3078.37,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I''m just thinking like if it''s a demo.","index":858,"end_time":3081.77,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3080.13,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Right.","index":859,"end_time":3081.93,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3081.77,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"It''s kind of a first meeting.","index":860,"end_time":3082.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3081.93,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"It''s kind of an SQL.","index":861,"end_time":3084.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3082.89,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"We''re going to have someone jump on, one of the salespeople is going to take that, take that lead.","index":862,"end_time":3088.57,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3084.33,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"It kind of skipped over the marketing qualified lead.","index":863,"end_time":3091.61,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3088.89,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Right.","index":864,"end_time":3091.93,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3091.61,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":865,"end_time":3092.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3092.25,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You can''t get that without a real company email.","index":866,"end_time":3097.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3093.13,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":867,"end_time":3098.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3098.01,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":868,"end_time":3099.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3098.49,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"So these are the things that we would tackle and agree upon and have alignment on as we''re establishing this lead management process.","index":869,"end_time":3107.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3099.45,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":870,"end_time":3108.81,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3108.33,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":871,"end_time":3109.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3109.05,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I think, I do think again going back to like the way we use HubSpot, I, I think that there are improvements that need to be made in the, the deal silo of HubSpot but, but I don''t think it''s a ton.","index":872,"end_time":3127.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3109.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think so.","index":873,"end_time":3129.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3127.46,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I agree actually from deal.","index":874,"end_time":3131.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3129.38,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"From your sales pipeline and deal is in pretty good shape because.","index":875,"end_time":3134.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3132.1,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yes.","index":876,"end_time":3135.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3134.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You guys have been sort of driven from a sales LED approach and what we need to do is get the top of funnel sorted out.","index":877,"end_time":3143.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3135.46,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"We need to do that so we can do better marketing.","index":878,"end_time":3146.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3143.79,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yes.","index":879,"end_time":3147.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3146.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"100 working.","index":880,"end_time":3148.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3147.31,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":881,"end_time":3148.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3148.43,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So we''re.","index":882,"end_time":3149.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3148.91,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You''re this Is not.","index":883,"end_time":3150.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3149.63,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You''re right.","index":884,"end_time":3151.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3150.75,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"We''re going to find a lot of the part.","index":885,"end_time":3152.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3151.27,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You know, low funnel is probably fine, but we needed to find what is an mql, when do we hand it off and then what has to happen with it to be qualified.","index":886,"end_time":3162.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3152.91,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And that is the pieces we''re missing to measure and do a better job.","index":887,"end_time":3166.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3162.35,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"And so I think we''re all in alignment.","index":888,"end_time":3167.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3166.31,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"New north, me and you too.","index":889,"end_time":3170.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3168.11,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So.","index":890,"end_time":3170.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3170.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s just a.","index":891,"end_time":3172.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3170.97,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"It''s a painful process, but it''ll be worth it to go.","index":892,"end_time":3175.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3172.49,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"It will be worth it.","index":893,"end_time":3175.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3175.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I, I just, I don''t know much about that side of.","index":894,"end_time":3180.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3175.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We do.","index":895,"end_time":3180.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3180.01,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"I know a ton.","index":896,"end_time":3182.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3181.05,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"The reason I would like New north, though is because I''m marketing and I. I''d like a third party facilitator to hold our hands and get the alignment as.","index":897,"end_time":3192.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3182.05,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"But I''ve done a ton of these.","index":898,"end_time":3194.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3192.57,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Not HubSpot.","index":899,"end_time":3195.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3194.25,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Some HubSpot that like.","index":900,"end_time":3196.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3195.25,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"You know what I''m saying?","index":901,"end_time":3197.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3196.42,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"The process piece.","index":902,"end_time":3198.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3197.1,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"So, yeah, perfect.","index":903,"end_time":3199.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3198.14,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Let''s.","index":904,"end_time":3199.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3199.42,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Let''s do it.","index":905,"end_time":3200.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3199.82,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"It''s worth it.","index":906,"end_time":3201.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3200.38,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"It''s.","index":907,"end_time":3201.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3201.26,"speaker_name":"Carmen Williams"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":908,"end_time":3204.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3204.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And just so we''re on the same page, we do have Sam just as a contractor.","index":909,"end_time":3209.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3204.78,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"Right.","index":910,"end_time":3209.34,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3209.02,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"To.","index":911,"end_time":3209.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3209.34,"speaker_name":"Rob Whalen"},{"text":"To bridge us through this.","index":912,"end_time":3211.1,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":3209.98,"speaker_name":"R