WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '965b21f3-8748-420c-aaf3-b3fdcaa2f504',
    '2026-01-29 16:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KG168PCZATVBJTNA6VTWK878',
    'Quick Sync',
    '{"Colin Costigan","Ruby Pontbriand"}'::text[],
    815,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85849508006?pwd=4FU9MNih5bbzAJfDjhmtIaqfCDfxad.1',
    '{"id":"01KG168PCZATVBJTNA6VTWK878","title":"Quick Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Client Account Financial Management**\n\nThe main focus is on resolving a significant points overage while realigning the monthly commitment for better value and sustainability.\n\n- **Colin Costigan outlined a current $87,000 points overage accumulated over two years and noted a previous gift of 443 points worth about $45,000 at year-end to cover some of it** (04:00)  \n    - The client is currently paying for **65 points monthly at $6,500**, but consistently uses between **90 and 100 points**.  \n    - Colin proposed increasing the monthly spend to **$7,500 for 75 points**, which would include a **$2,500 monthly gift in services**, effectively $10,000 worth of work for $7,500.  \n    - The rationale is to better align spending with usage while offering extra value to maintain momentum without abrupt hikes.  \n    - The increase seeks to stabilize finances while enabling expanded marketing efforts, aiming to avoid billing surprises or client dissatisfaction.  \n\n- **Ruby Pontbriand acknowledged the gifting and understood the need for realistic budgeting but indicated hesitation from Cook due to unclear ROI on current spend** (05:30)  \n    - She stressed the importance of clear ROI data to justify any increase, noting the client is currently questioning whether to continue the partnership.  \n    - Ruby agreed the proposed increase is fair but highlighted the need for stronger evidence of value before approval.  \n    - She emphasized the difficulty in attributing marketing efforts like ads and SEO directly to customer conversions, which complicates ROI justification.  \n\n## **Marketing ROI Attribution and Strategy Adjustment**\n\nThere is a strategic need to improve ROI clarity and possibly shift marketing focus toward more measurable channels like SEO.\n\n- **Ruby explained that paid media has not directly produced customers, but SEO and content efforts have added value through website revamps and optimized landing pages** (09:30)  \n    - She noted that SEO contributed indirectly to lead generation, although its impact has not been fully showcased as ROI to the client’s leadership.  \n    - Ruby described the challenge in tracking multi-touch attribution across channels, making it hard to connect marketing spend to conversions.  \n    - She suggested that paid ads might not be the right fit given the lack of infrastructure and team capacity to run cohesive campaigns.  \n\n- **Colin agreed on the attribution challenge and proposed possibly shifting budget from paid media to SEO to better match the client’s strengths and goals** (11:30)  \n    - He acknowledged that modern marketing journeys are complex, with many touchpoints before conversion.  \n    - Colin indicated the new system under development will improve tracking, but full visibility remains difficult without expensive tools.  \n    - This potential pivot to SEO aims to maximize budget efficiency and align marketing tactics with measurable outcomes.  \n\n## **Client Partnership Alignment and Roadmap Development**\n\nStrengthening collaboration through a structured alignment process is key to rebuilding trust and setting clear goals for 2026.\n\n- **Colin offered to set up a series of alignment meetings with the client team to review company goals, marketing data, and build a shared roadmap for the year** (07:00)  \n    - This exercise would help clarify ROI and campaign impacts, providing a foundation to revisit budget increases confidently.  \n    - Colin plans to engage internal stakeholders Justin and Tristan to coordinate these discussions.  \n    - The meetings will be provided at no additional charge to deepen partnership and ensure mutual understanding.  \n\n- **Ruby supported this approach, recognizing her role requires justifying continued investment and partnership to leadership** (07:45)  \n    - She stressed the importance of clearly demonstrating past and projected marketing value to secure buy-in from decision makers.  \n    - This alignment aims to address current uncertainty and create a data-driven business case for future spending.  \n\n## **Resource and Personnel Update**\n\nThe team structure includes advisory support rather than full-time involvement from former key personnel.\n\n- **Colin confirmed that Joe Michielowski is now serving as an advisor rather than a full-time team member** (12:30)  \n    - Joe’s shift to advisory status reflects his engagement with other ventures but maintains a connection to the client account.  \n    - Ruby noted internal interest in Joe’s status, indicating his past involvement was valued by the client.  \n    - This update clarifies the current leadership and resource allocation on the client’s account.","outline":null,"keywords":["Account Management","ROI Justification","ABM Program","Marketing Attribution","SEO Strategy","Client Alignment"],"overview":"- **Points Overage:** Current $87,000 points overage; client uses 90-100 points monthly but pays for 65 points at $6,500.  \n- **Proposed Spend Increase:** Suggested increase to $7,500 for 75 points, including $2,500 monthly service gift, providing $10,000 value.  \n- **ROI Concerns:** Unclear ROI on spending; need strong data to justify proposed budget increase and maintain partnership.  \n- **Marketing Strategy Shift:** Proposal to reallocate budget from paid media to SEO for better alignment with measurable outcomes and client strengths.  \n- **Alignment Meetings:** Plan for series of client meetings to clarify goals and marketing data, deepen partnership, and address uncertainty.  \n- **Team Update:** Joe Michielowski now an advisor, maintaining connection to client; reflects current leadership structure.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nDiscuss with Justin and Tristan about organizing and gifting a series of alignment meetings with iCorps to clarify goals and roadmap (11:52)\nCommunicate to iCorps about the proposed increased monthly point package and related marketing service value after alignment and ROI demonstration (04:19)\nRelay greetings to Joe Michielowski and update Ruby on his advisor status (12:27)\n\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nCoordinate internally at iCorps regarding the partnership justification and potential budget decisions post alignment meetings (06:36)\nParticipate in upcoming alignment meetings to review data, company goals for 2026, and build a strategic roadmap (12:21)\n"},"duration":13.59000015258789,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Ruby Pontbriand"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Sa.","index":0,"end_time":0.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":1,"end_time":168.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":168.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":2,"end_time":169.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.259,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":3,"end_time":171.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":170.3,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Doing well.","index":4,"end_time":171.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":5,"end_time":172.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Doing good, thank you.","index":6,"end_time":174.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":172.78,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Sorry about the delay there.","index":7,"end_time":175.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.62,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"One thing to another.","index":8,"end_time":177.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":176.7,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":9,"end_time":178.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then always switching between teams.","index":10,"end_time":180.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Zoom always has its fair share of fun as well.","index":11,"end_time":183.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":180.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Totally awesome.","index":12,"end_time":185.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":184.01,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Well, Ruby, thanks for the time.","index":13,"end_time":187.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ve actually taken on a new role at Marketers In Demand.","index":14,"end_time":191.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":188.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m the head of client operations now.","index":15,"end_time":193.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So looking at things, things much more from, like, I''m helping out with sales.","index":16,"end_time":197.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":193.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m helping out with, like, the operations and tools and everything that we''re doing, building new ABM approaches and tech stacks and all sorts of things.","index":17,"end_time":204.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so I''m looking at accounts where I think we can do more.","index":18,"end_time":208.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And one of those is yours.","index":19,"end_time":209.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think so we''re already underway of bringing your guys ABM program into a new system that we''ve built with many more signals and grouping together a lot more tools.","index":20,"end_time":220.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I did want to just have an open conversation around, like, where points stand.","index":21,"end_time":226.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And because I know we had a conversation yesterday, Cook''s not super happy with, like, cost per lead on paid activities, so I don''t want to, like, ruffle any feathers there.","index":22,"end_time":234.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to keep some good momentum that we have going, but I want to see, like, how we can best serve you guys.","index":23,"end_time":239.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So today, I''m not sure if Natalie mentioned it.","index":24,"end_time":243.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":240.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know I missed a meeting.","index":25,"end_time":244.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":243.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Um, so at the end of December, we actually gifted you guys 443 points to help cover an overage.","index":26,"end_time":250.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":244.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s.","index":27,"end_time":252.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":251.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s about $45,000 and that.","index":28,"end_time":254.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":252.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And there''s still actually about an $87,000 overage.","index":29,"end_time":258.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s over, like, two years of working together.","index":30,"end_time":261.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My aim is not to just be like, hey, guys, here''s a bill for $87,000.","index":31,"end_time":264.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re not going to do that.","index":32,"end_time":265.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What a few things that I was thinking through, though, is you guys are currently at 6,500amonth, so you get 65 points.","index":33,"end_time":273.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":265.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re pretty consistently doing between 90 and 100 points a month.","index":34,"end_time":277.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I was thinking one option is we could, if you guys were willing to go to 7,500 per month, we would gift you $2,500 per month in marketing services.","index":35,"end_time":288.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you get $10,000 worth of work for $7,500 a month.","index":36,"end_time":292.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know Cook may not react greatly to that.","index":37,"end_time":295.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again, I don''t want to ruffle any feathers.","index":38,"end_time":297.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to see how we can best help each other.","index":39,"end_time":299.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":40,"end_time":301.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301.17,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And if it''s not, then we just kind of need to have a realistic conversation.","index":41,"end_time":304.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":301.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of what we can do at this 65 point clip.","index":42,"end_time":306.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":304.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":43,"end_time":308.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.61,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That absolutely makes sense.","index":44,"end_time":310.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.01,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Totally.","index":45,"end_time":310.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.09,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I appreciate it because, I mean, you''re absolutely right.","index":46,"end_time":313.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.53,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I''ve known, I''ve been aware like since the beginning that, that there''s been like a lot of gifting of points and you know, there''s definitely been, you know, this like, hey, let''s prove our value and all of that stuff.","index":47,"end_time":324.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.53,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''ve like greatly respected and understood.","index":48,"end_time":326.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":324.73,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So, yeah, I definitely appreciate it.","index":49,"end_time":329.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.06,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I didn''t know about the stuff at the end of the year, but that''s really nice.","index":50,"end_time":331.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":329.46,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":51,"end_time":332.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":331.86,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":52,"end_time":333.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Merry Christmas.","index":53,"end_time":333.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I also totally get where you''re coming from in that, you know, you''re analyzing these accounts and ours is definitely one that pops and that, you know, you guys need to be able to scale forward.","index":54,"end_time":345.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.38,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We need to scale forward, all of those things.","index":55,"end_time":347.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":345.98,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I also like really want it to be, I want it to be good for you guys and good for us.","index":56,"end_time":354.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.78,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But that I think definitely is where we''re at in terms of the decision tree or whatever is like, we''re in flux right now with like all these reports and, you know, justification of ROI and all these things and the, you know, kind of figuring out what to do next.","index":57,"end_time":371.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.14,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I do think that you are right in like Cook might not be, you know, because yeah, if I were to go to them today and say New north wants to do 75 instead of 65, they would be like, no, because they, from their perspective, they''re not understanding the return.","index":58,"end_time":391.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":372.34,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s as simple as that.","index":59,"end_time":395.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":394.23,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":60,"end_time":396.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That being said, I personally don''t think that it''s out of line.","index":61,"end_time":399.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":396.63,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And also as a marketer, I don''t think that this is a very tall ask.","index":62,"end_time":404.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":401.11,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think it''s very generous and also makes the business sense for you and likely for us as well in depending on the perspective you use.","index":63,"end_time":414.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.67,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right, that''s what I''ll say about that.","index":64,"end_time":416.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":414.61,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that.","index":65,"end_time":417.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":416.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that makes total sense.","index":66,"end_time":419.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One other thing that I would be more than happy to do is go through like an alignment series of meetings with you guys.","index":67,"end_time":425.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":419.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So where we again, dig into all the data set, you know, talk about where you guys are at for your company goals for 2026.","index":68,"end_time":431.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we could work through that.","index":69,"end_time":434,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we have like a, a really strong roadmap for the year.","index":70,"end_time":437.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":434,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did that at the beginning of last year.","index":71,"end_time":438.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":437.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that would be a really good exercise for us again.","index":72,"end_time":440.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, get the team on, on a call.","index":73,"end_time":443.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":441.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then when we lay out the roadmap, if we get People excited.","index":74,"end_time":446.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":443.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we have the reports that are demonstrating the ROI.","index":75,"end_time":448.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe we can then have that conversation about 7, 500 for $10,000 worth of work per month.","index":76,"end_time":453.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":448.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because, again, we.","index":77,"end_time":454.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":454.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We really value this partnership.","index":78,"end_time":456.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":454.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We don''t want to, like, just ruffle any feathers or call anything.","index":79,"end_time":459.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":456.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just want to say, like, hey, we can do more.","index":80,"end_time":461.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just need a little bit more to be able to do that.","index":81,"end_time":465.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":462.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I understand.","index":82,"end_time":466.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.21,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that sounds like a good approach.","index":83,"end_time":470.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":468.49,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And, you know, your intuition is correct that.","index":84,"end_time":472.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":470.25,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s because, like, I''m.","index":85,"end_time":478.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":475.21,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''m in a. I''m in a spot right now where I''m.","index":86,"end_time":480.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":478.13,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They''re looking at me to justify the partnership overall.","index":87,"end_time":484.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":480.81,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":88,"end_time":484.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just so you''re under.","index":89,"end_time":487.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":486.08,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I mean, I''m sure that''s probably already clear, but, like, from their perspective, they''re in a spot where they''re wondering, should we continue?","index":90,"end_time":494.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":488.08,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''ll put that bluntly, just because, you know, you need information so that you can do what you need to do, and that.","index":91,"end_time":503.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":496,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That''s kind of like where they''re coming from is, you know, whether to continue this or not.","index":92,"end_time":508.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":505.04,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then I think pairing that with an ask of more is going to be okay as long as we can, like, really, really back it up and get them to understand the.","index":93,"end_time":521.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":509.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"The investment that was made in the past year also in 2024, what actually came out of that.","index":94,"end_time":534.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.42,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because it''s tough.","index":95,"end_time":536.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.38,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And we talked about this yesterday, that.","index":96,"end_time":538.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":536.94,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And, you know, this.","index":97,"end_time":541.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.55,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"As a marketer, so much of what we do is hard to pin down.","index":98,"end_time":546.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":541.11,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And the stuff we can pin down.","index":99,"end_time":547.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":546.07,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We do.","index":100,"end_time":548.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":547.71,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But, you know, it''s tough to know, oh, somebody saw an ad and then, you know, hung out for a couple of months, and then maybe they got an email and maybe, I don''t know, whatever.","index":101,"end_time":559.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":548.87,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Things just, like, it''s very hard to attribute back sometimes, which is tough.","index":102,"end_time":564.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":559.67,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":103,"end_time":564.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And our new system does a stronger job at that.","index":104,"end_time":567.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I mean, to be completely honest, I mean, probably still 40% of the Internet is hard to track any activity unless you have, like, dream Data, which is 100, $120,000 a year just to track data.","index":105,"end_time":578.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":567.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":106,"end_time":579.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Which we don''t.","index":107,"end_time":581.239,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.96,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We don''t.","index":108,"end_time":582.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":581.56,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So it''s tough.","index":109,"end_time":585.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.88,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But I do think that there are concrete things that we can point to that maybe just haven''t been as.","index":110,"end_time":591.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":585.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I mean, they haven''t really been showcased to them as roi, because that''s not what they were looking for.","index":111,"end_time":601.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":594.51,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They were looking for customers that came out of paid media when we didn''t get that, but we did get a lot of content And a lot of SEO, which I think those get attributed back to this relationship in some way because obviously content came from the website.","index":112,"end_time":622.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":601.63,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"The website was completely redesigned and revamped, optimized for SEO, landing pages, optimized for conversion, contact forms, optimized for meetings.","index":113,"end_time":633.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":622.7,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like we did a lot.","index":114,"end_time":634.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":633.7,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So.","index":115,"end_time":635.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":634.78,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":116,"end_time":635.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":635.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s, I mean, you understand, like, it''s a journey.","index":117,"end_time":637.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":635.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":118,"end_time":637.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":637.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, there''s so many touch points that go into this.","index":119,"end_time":639.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":637.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wish we were still in the day and age of like, hey, they saw this one ad and they converted and now they''re a customer.","index":120,"end_time":644.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":639.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s just times have changed so much.","index":121,"end_time":646.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":122,"end_time":647.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":646.66,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And, you know, maybe ads aren''t right for us and that''s fine.","index":123,"end_time":652.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":649.86,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We never did them before.","index":124,"end_time":655.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":654.42,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I just know that it''s very much, you know, an industry thing that a lot of, you know, companies do, and we didn''t really have like, the infrastructure or the, the team to be able to launch stuff like that and really put a whole, you know, cohesive campaign behind it.","index":125,"end_time":668.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":656.18,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But I still think that the disconnect between that effort and what comes out of it is a little too, too big of a disconnect where if we did, you know, the SEO thing, I think that would be.","index":126,"end_time":688.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":669.38,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And we did want to, like, if you look back in the stuff, like we talked to Joe last year around this time and it was like, we''re definitely going to shift towards more SEO and we did build out something, some pretty good stuff.","index":127,"end_time":699.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":688.18,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s just, I think it.","index":128,"end_time":700.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":699.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We had to still be able to focus on ABM and then.","index":129,"end_time":703.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":700.36,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":130,"end_time":703.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":703.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know.","index":131,"end_time":704.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":704.16,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":132,"end_time":705.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":133,"end_time":705.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And maybe we land somewhere where it''s like, hey, maybe we do an SEO approach and we turn off paid, and then that budget is now available for more SEO.","index":134,"end_time":712.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":135,"end_time":712.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":712.16,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Things like that.","index":136,"end_time":713.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":712.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":137,"end_time":714.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so let me talk about what.","index":138,"end_time":716.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m thinking next steps.","index":139,"end_time":717.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":716.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll talk to Justin and Tristan and I''ll talk about doing an aligned series with you guys for a couple meetings, gifting that for free.","index":140,"end_time":725.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":717.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That way we.","index":141,"end_time":727.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":726.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re all in a room and we kind of to like an alignment.","index":142,"end_time":731.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pretty, pretty spot on name of like, where the business needs to grow and how we can best support that and really how we make that work for both sides.","index":143,"end_time":739.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":731.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does that sound good?","index":144,"end_time":741.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":740.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that does sound good.","index":145,"end_time":742.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":741.5,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Is Joe, Joe Michielowski, Is he still with you guys?","index":146,"end_time":746.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.18,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"He''s.","index":147,"end_time":747.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":747.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s more of an advisor right now.","index":148,"end_time":749.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":747.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s not really working full time yet.","index":149,"end_time":751.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":150,"end_time":752.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.5,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Mike asks all the time.","index":151,"end_time":754.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":752.94,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"He''s like, where is Joe?","index":152,"end_time":756.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":755.18,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I''m like, I don''t know.","index":153,"end_time":757.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":756.46,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''ll ask.","index":154,"end_time":758.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":757.54,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, he''s more serving an advisor role.","index":155,"end_time":760.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":758.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s got a whole other venture going.","index":156,"end_time":762.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":760.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re very happy for him.","index":157,"end_time":764.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":762.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":158,"end_time":765,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":764.52,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Well, me, too.","index":159,"end_time":765.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"He''s a good dude.","index":160,"end_time":766.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765.64,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Tell him I say hey.","index":161,"end_time":767.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":766.36,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Will do.","index":162,"end_time":768.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":767.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":163,"end_time":769.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":768.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, Ruby, I really appreciate your time.","index":164,"end_time":770.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":769.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I always appreciate when we can have candor as well, from one marketer to another.","index":165,"end_time":775,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":770.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And again, we want to make this work as best as it possibly can for I Corps.","index":166,"end_time":778.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":167,"end_time":778.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":778.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll talk to Justin and Tristan about setting up that series of meetings, and then we''ll.","index":168,"end_time":783.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll talk more.","index":169,"end_time":783.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":783.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, that sounds great.","index":170,"end_time":785.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":784.2,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":171,"end_time":786.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":785.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":172,"end_time":786.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":786.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":173,"end_time":786.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":786.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, have a great rest of your day.","index":174,"end_time":787.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":786.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You, too.","index":175,"end_time":788.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":787.96,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Bye.","index":176,"end_time":788.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.48,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Bye.","index":177,"end_time":789.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.76,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"}],"dateString":"2026-01-29T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85849508006?pwd=4FU9MNih5bbzAJfDjhmtIaqfCDfxad.1","participants":["rpontbriand@icorps.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","rpontbriand@icorps.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KG168PCZATVBJTNA6VTWK878","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.82,"bullets":["Colin proposed raising monthly retainer to $7,500 with $10,000 in marketing value in return.","Ruby confirmed leadership doubts ROI and is reassessing whether to continue the partnership.","Both sides acknowledged difficulty in attributing paid media impact but cited SEO and content gains.","Colin committed to offering free alignment meetings to clarify roadmap and support 2026 goals.","Team agreed to revisit ROI framing with detailed reporting to support potential budget increases."],"highlights":[{"quote":"They''re in a spot where they''re wondering, should we continue?","speaker":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"quote":"We just want to say, like, hey, we can do more.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["budget","roi","retention","alignment"],"model":"gpt-4-0125-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-29T10:27:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Client Account Financial Management**\n\nThe main focus is on resolving a significant points overage while realigning the monthly commitment for better value and sustainability.\n\n- **Colin Costigan outlined a current $87,000 points overage accumulated over two years and noted a previous gift of 443 points worth about $45,000 at year-end to cover some of it** (04:00)  \n    - The client is currently paying for **65 points monthly at $6,500**, but consistently uses between **90 and 100 points**.  \n    - Colin proposed increasing the monthly spend to **$7,500 for 75 points**, which would include a **$2,500 monthly gift in services**, effectively $10,000 worth of work for $7,500.  \n    - The rationale is to better align spending with usage while offering extra value to maintain momentum without abrupt hikes.  \n    - The increase seeks to stabilize finances while enabling expanded marketing efforts, aiming to avoid billing surprises or client dissatisfaction.  \n\n- **Ruby Pontbriand acknowledged the gifting and understood the need for realistic budgeting but indicated hesitation from Cook due to unclear ROI on current spend** (05:30)  \n    - She stressed the importance of clear ROI data to justify any increase, noting the client is currently questioning whether to continue the partnership.  \n    - Ruby agreed the proposed increase is fair but highlighted the need for stronger evidence of value before approval.  \n    - She emphasized the difficulty in attributing marketing efforts like ads and SEO directly to customer conversions, which complicates ROI justification.  \n\n## **Marketing ROI Attribution and Strategy Adjustment**\n\nThere is a strategic need to improve ROI clarity and possibly shift marketing focus toward more measurable channels like SEO.\n\n- **Ruby explained that paid media has not directly produced customers, but SEO and content efforts have added value through website revamps and optimized landing pages** (09:30)  \n    - She noted that SEO contributed indirectly to lead generation, although its impact has not been fully showcased as ROI to the client’s leadership.  \n    - Ruby described the challenge in tracking multi-touch attribution across channels, making it hard to connect marketing spend to conversions.  \n    - She suggested that paid ads might not be the right fit given the lack of infrastructure and team capacity to run cohesive campaigns.  \n\n- **Colin agreed on the attribution challenge and proposed possibly shifting budget from paid media to SEO to better match the client’s strengths and goals** (11:30)  \n    - He acknowledged that modern marketing journeys are complex, with many touchpoints before conversion.  \n    - Colin indicated the new system under development will improve tracking, but full visibility remains difficult without expensive tools.  \n    - This potential pivot to SEO aims to maximize budget efficiency and align marketing tactics with measurable outcomes.  \n\n## **Client Partnership Alignment and Roadmap Development**\n\nStrengthening collaboration through a structured alignment process is key to rebuilding trust and setting clear goals for 2026.\n\n- **Colin offered to set up a series of alignment meetings with the client team to review company goals, marketing data, and build a shared roadmap for the year** (07:00)  \n    - This exercise would help clarify ROI and campaign impacts, providing a foundation to revisit budget increases confidently.  \n    - Colin plans to engage internal stakeholders Justin and Tristan to coordinate these discussions.  \n    - The meetings will be provided at no additional charge to deepen partnership and ensure mutual understanding.  \n\n- **Ruby supported this approach, recognizing her role requires justifying continued investment and partnership to leadership** (07:45)  \n    - She stressed the importance of clearly demonstrating past and projected marketing value to secure buy-in from decision makers.  \n    - This alignment aims to address current uncertainty and create a data-driven business case for future spending.  \n\n## **Resource and Personnel Update**\n\nThe team structure includes advisory support rather than full-time involvement from former key personnel.\n\n- **Colin confirmed that Joe Michielowski is now serving as an advisor rather than a full-time team member** (12:30)  \n    - Joe’s shift to advisory status reflects his engagement with other ventures but maintains a connection to the client account.  \n    - Ruby noted internal interest in Joe’s status, indicating his past involvement was valued by the client.  \n    - This update clarifies the current leadership and resource allocation on the client’s account.","outline":null,"keywords":["Account Management","ROI Justification","ABM Program","Marketing Attribution","SEO Strategy","Client Alignment"],"overview":"- **Points Overage:** Current $87,000 points overage; client uses 90-100 points monthly but pays for 65 points at $6,500.  \n- **Proposed Spend Increase:** Suggested increase to $7,500 for 75 points, including $2,500 monthly service gift, providing $10,000 value.  \n- **ROI Concerns:** Unclear ROI on spending; need strong data to justify proposed budget increase and maintain partnership.  \n- **Marketing Strategy Shift:** Proposal to reallocate budget from paid media to SEO for better alignment with measurable outcomes and client strengths.  \n- **Alignment Meetings:** Plan for series of client meetings to clarify goals and marketing data, deepen partnership, and address uncertainty.  \n- **Team Update:** Joe Michielowski now an advisor, maintaining connection to client; reflects current leadership structure.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nDiscuss with Justin and Tristan about organizing and gifting a series of alignment meetings with iCorps to clarify goals and roadmap (11:52)\nCommunicate to iCorps about the proposed increased monthly point package and related marketing service value after alignment and ROI demonstration (04:19)\nRelay greetings to Joe Michielowski and update Ruby on his advisor status (12:27)\n\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nCoordinate internally at iCorps regarding the partnership justification and potential budget decisions post alignment meetings (06:36)\nParticipate in upcoming alignment meetings to review data, company goals for 2026, and build a strategic roadmap (12:21)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"f82e3788-6326-452f-9763-347a13be5921","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
