-- Meeting: Aligned Growth Engine | Roadmap Presentation (2026-01-28 20:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '3b39d1e2-cf4e-41b0-942a-7cb3d536b84b',
    '2026-01-28 20:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KFEGV9Y8K4NGH1ES550AQXNA',
    'Aligned Growth Engine | Roadmap Presentation',
    '{"Colin Costigan","Georgi Funtarov","Justin Brown","Tristan"}'::text[],
    3296,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87013246367?pwd=b9uHJJfMRy1YuIcQOmEtaE9EsPwqQb.1',
    '{"id":"01KFEGV9Y8K4NGH1ES550AQXNA","title":"Aligned Growth Engine | Roadmap Presentation","summary":{"notes":"## **Target Audience and ICP Definition**\n\nThe team agreed on three core **Ideal Customer Profiles (ICPs)** to sharpen messaging and sales focus, aiming to improve conversion by addressing distinct pain points and behaviors (04:52).\n\n- **Multi-location operators with 2 to 9 locations** are primarily problem-driven, outgrowing existing systems and lacking reliable support, making messaging around **reliability, visibility, and scalability** crucial to prevent technology struggles as they grow.\n    - These customers often use legacy or competitor systems like **Toast** but face operational issues across locations, increasing churn risk.\n    - Messaging must assure seamless support and tech reliability to reduce friction in scaling.\n- **Single-location owners** are more skeptical and defensive, requiring messaging focused on **building trust through transparent pricing and clear onboarding**, addressing fears of hidden fees and system failures.\n    - Education is key here, showing real scenarios like system failures during peak hours and responsive support availability.\n- **Fast-growing QSR chains** demand **speed, accuracy, and operational efficiency**, searching specifically for POS solutions that handle high transaction volumes with delivery integration.\n    - Messaging should be direct, feature-focused, and demonstrate operational strengths rather than emotional appeals.\n- Georgi emphasized segmenting prospects into **three main pathways** to streamline marketing and sales alignment, avoiding over-segmentation while increasing relevance at every touchpoint (13:05).\n\n## **Brand Positioning and Competitive Landscape**\n\nResQ’s core competitive edge lies in **service differentiation**, especially **24/7 U.S.-based support with first call resolution**, positioning it as a reliable partner compared to competitors (22:01).\n\n- **Toast** dominates brand awareness, SEO, and paid media but suffers declining service quality due to rapid scaling, shifting from white-glove support to a ticketing model, causing deal losses.\n    - The strategy is not to outspend Toast but to target their dissatisfied customers and demonstrate superior support.\n- **Lightspeed** focuses more on retail than restaurants, with a broad but diluted paid keyword strategy, making them less relevant for ResQ’s core audience.\n- **Skytab** is a closer peer, leaning heavily on education and training, supporting the team''s plan to emphasize pre-sale education and content marketing.\n- Paul’s insight was adopted: focus the market around two clear choices—Toast or ResQ—simplifying decision-making and reducing confusion caused by many legacy competitors (16:37).\n- The team plans to create messaging highlighting the **cost of delayed decisions** in the restaurant market to push faster action, especially given rising operational pressures like minimum wage increases (18:58).\n\n## **Marketing and Lead Generation Strategy**\n\nThe agreed marketing goal is to increase **qualified inbound demo bookings** to scale sales pipeline efficiently, with phased targets set at **20 qualified demos per month in 90 days, scaling to 30, then 40 by year-end** (26:01).\n\n- Google Ads historically cost around **$400 per lead**, but quality is inconsistent, so multi-channel approaches will be combined with improved messaging and landing pages to lower costs and raise lead quality.\n- The team plans **four dedicated landing pages focused on high-intent campaigns** to improve conversion from clicks to demos while monitoring cost per lead continuously.\n- Retargeting will be used across platforms including **YouTube and programmatic display via Adroll**, supported by dynamic email nurture sequences to keep prospects engaged post-initial contact (40:35).\n- The marketing funnel will incorporate multiple call-to-actions (CTAs) reflecting different buyer readiness levels, recognizing some prospects need education before committing to demos.\n- Data integration and tracking will leverage tools like **RBDB, Factors AI, N8N workflows, and Supabase** to de-anonymize website visitors and track engagement, improving lead scoring and targeting.\n- Georgi and Tristan emphasized the importance of combining **account-based marketing (ABM)** and lead generation tactics, with clear ICP confirmation and account list building using tools like **Clay and Zoom Info** (52:45).\n- The team acknowledged privacy constraints limit full visitor identification but expects to resolve **40-60% of web traffic** for targeting purposes, using IP resolution and cookie data compliant with GDPR for U.S. customers.\n\n## **Sales and Marketing Alignment on Lead Quality**\n\nAlignment on the definition of a **qualified lead and demo** is critical to avoid finger-pointing between sales and marketing and drive revenue responsibility across teams (36:37).\n\n- Georgi proposed tying marketing efforts directly to **revenue metrics**, weighting lead sources by conversion rates (e.g., white paper leads converting at 40% vs. ad leads at 10%) to assign fair revenue quotas to marketing.\n- Justin and Tristan highlighted that marketing’s accountability ends at delivering **sales-qualified leads (SQLs)**, with sales responsible for closing, but collaboration is needed to refine qualification criteria.\n- The group agreed that **pre-demo educational content consumption** (measured via video views or downloads) correlates with shorter sales cycles and higher close rates, supporting investments in content marketing.\n- Lead scoring frameworks will assign points based on engagement (e.g., form fills, content consumption), with thresholds determining CRM handoffs and sales outreach priority.\n- Justin explained flexibility is needed based on sales team size and capacity, with some clients preferring only demos from explicit form fills, others wanting lower-threshold leads assigned for outreach (47:36).\n- A formal **performance reporting plan** will document lead quality metrics and alignment on accepted ratios (e.g., 80% qualified vs. 20% disqualified leads), ensuring transparency and continuous improvement (38:09).\n\n## **90-Day Roadmap and Investment Plan**\n\nThe initial 90-day plan centers on **building a scalable paid media and conversion foundation** with clear deliverables and flexible resource allocation (39:39).\n\n- Month 1 focuses on foundational work: rewriting messaging, creating new landing pages, developing the paid media plan, and building the content series framework.\n- Month 2 emphasizes campaign setup: launching Google Ads with intent filtering, activating retargeting on multiple platforms, and starting dynamic email outreach.\n- Month 3 includes developing **4 new web pages, sales enablement materials (e.g., decks, one-pagers), and producing content episodes** for syndication in marketing and sales outreach.\n- The plan operates on a **points system**, equating 1 point to **$100**, with a monthly budget of **80 points ($8,000)** plus **20 gifted points**, allowing flexibility to shift resources month-to-month and roll over unused points.\n- Justin encouraged quick feedback and collaboration to pull activities forward for faster impact, highlighting that some channels could start running within the first month.\n- Account list building for ABM relies on confirmed ICP parameters and job titles, enabling targeted email sequences tailored to specific pain points per role (52:45).\n- The team agreed to review the detailed research and roadmap, targeting a follow-up meeting next **Wednesday for final alignment and potential project kickoff** (54:10).","outline":null,"keywords":["Posing System","Target Audience","Marketing Strategy","Lead Qualification","Competitive Analysis","ABM"],"overview":"- **Ideal Customer Profiles:** Three ICPs defined: multi-location operators, single-location owners, and fast-growing QSR chains to enhance messaging.\n\n- **Competitive Positioning:** ResQ offers 24/7 U.S. support, aiming to attract Toast''s dissatisfied customers by highlighting superior service.\n\n- **Marketing Goal:** Aim for **20 qualified demos/month in 90 days**, increasing targets to **30, then 40 by year-end**.\n\n- **Lead Generation Strategy:** Use multi-channel marketing and dedicated landing pages to improve lead quality and lower costs.\n\n- **Sales-Marketing Alignment:** Define qualified leads clearly, tying marketing efforts to revenue metrics for better accountability and collaboration.\n\n- **90-Day Plan:** Month 1 focuses on foundational work; Month 2 on campaign setup; Month 3 on content production and sales enablement materials.","action_items":"\n**Georgi Funtarov**\nReview and confirm the accuracy of the ICP to enable account list building for ABM campaigns (52:40)\nProvide feedback on the ABM and paid media plans promptly to allow for acceleration of initial marketing activities (49:30)\nCoordinate internally to assess the proposed roadmap and respond with next steps by early next week (54:05)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare the detailed 90+ page research document and slide deck post-meeting with the ResQ team (03:00)\nBuild foundational documentation outlining customer journeys, messaging strategies, and handoff processes for sales and marketing alignment in month one (49:45)\nSet up paid media campaigns including Google Ads, retargeting, YouTube ads, and programmatic display with Adroll (50:30)\nDevelop four new landing pages tailored to high-intent campaigns to improve demo conversion rates within the first 90 days (50:45)\nCreate sales enablement materials such as slide decks and one-pagers aligned with refreshed messaging (50:55)\nCoordinate production of content series episodes to amplify educational marketing efforts (51:00)\nDesign and implement performance reporting document to track and align all activities and results for full transparency (38:20)\n\n**Justin Brown**\nSend over meeting materials and timeline for next steps and follow-up meeting scheduling (54:10)\nFacilitate scheduling a next meeting for Wednesday, ensuring timing works for all participants to discuss progress and launch (54:10)\n\n**All Participants**\nAlign on the exact definition and qualification criteria for demo leads to ensure marketing and sales agreement and minimize finger-pointing (36:30)\n"},"duration":54.939998626708984,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"id":2,"name":"Justin Brown"},{"id":3,"name":"Tristan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Worries.","index":0,"end_time":0.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great to see you guys.","index":1,"end_time":1.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good to see you.","index":2,"end_time":2.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":3,"end_time":3.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":4,"end_time":3.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was your travel earlier this week?","index":5,"end_time":6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was chaotic.","index":6,"end_time":7.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.72,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"We went to Dallas, and with all the storm, it was a little bit.","index":7,"end_time":11.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.08,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"We had to change flights and things.","index":8,"end_time":13.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":11.76,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"We didn''t get stuck.","index":9,"end_time":13.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, you know, it was.","index":10,"end_time":15.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.96,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"It was.","index":11,"end_time":16.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.76,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"It was weird.","index":12,"end_time":16.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.24,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"It was raining.","index":13,"end_time":17.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.72,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"It was snowing and icy in Dallas, and everything was shut down, the whole state.","index":14,"end_time":20.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.2,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"They actually shut down the entire town.","index":15,"end_time":22.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.96,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Well, that''s where we''re.","index":16,"end_time":25.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":24.24,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That''s where we''re all, like, generally.","index":17,"end_time":27.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":25.68,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Are you from.","index":18,"end_time":29.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":28.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I actually grew up, like, 10 minutes from Dulles.","index":19,"end_time":31.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":29.07,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I grew up in Chantilly, Virginia, so I know the airport like the back.","index":20,"end_time":36.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":31.75,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Of my hand, but, yeah.","index":21,"end_time":36.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tristan.","index":22,"end_time":37.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":36.87,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Dallas.","index":23,"end_time":38.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":37.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, Dallas.","index":24,"end_time":39.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":38.99,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Dallas.","index":25,"end_time":40.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":26,"end_time":41.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I think he said Dulles.","index":27,"end_time":42.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":41.31,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re talking Texas here.","index":28,"end_time":43.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.83,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Big hats, lots of cattle.","index":29,"end_time":44.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":43.83,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Nope, not Texas here at all.","index":30,"end_time":48.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":45.31,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I misheard.","index":31,"end_time":49.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":48.43,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Thought we''re talking about an airport.","index":32,"end_time":50.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":49.47,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We also got ice and snow, and it''s been a disaster here in Virginia.","index":33,"end_time":57.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":51.31,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Sorry to hear that.","index":34,"end_time":59.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.97,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"I didn''t lose power.","index":35,"end_time":62.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":61.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That was the most important.","index":36,"end_time":63.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":62.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Looks nice and sunny outside your beautiful windows there.","index":37,"end_time":65.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.17,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"The door.","index":38,"end_time":65.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.33,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":39,"end_time":66.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Today.","index":40,"end_time":66.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":66.61,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And we''re supposed to get hit again this weekend, so can''t get away from it, but that''s all right.","index":41,"end_time":73.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":66.97,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":42,"end_time":74.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m about two.","index":43,"end_time":76.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Two and a half hours north of them, and I got 13 inches of snow with a nice layer of ice on top of.","index":44,"end_time":81.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wow.","index":45,"end_time":82.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":81.94,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Time for tobogganing.","index":46,"end_time":83.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":82.5,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":47,"end_time":84.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":84.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, Colin, you want to take us through.","index":48,"end_time":88.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":85.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we have the roadmap presentation for today.","index":49,"end_time":90.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":88.42,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Excited to take you through a few things, our ideas, and we will go from there.","index":50,"end_time":95.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":91.54,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"All right, can everyone see my screen?","index":51,"end_time":100.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":98.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":52,"end_time":101.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":100.58,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":53,"end_time":102.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":101.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if at any point, if you guys testing your setup.","index":54,"end_time":105.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":102.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":55,"end_time":107.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":106.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re good.","index":56,"end_time":107.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.3,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Okay.","index":57,"end_time":108.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":108.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we''re getting some echo pretty bad all of a sudden.","index":58,"end_time":113.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":110.25,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":59,"end_time":115.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":115.21,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":60,"end_time":117.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":116.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":61,"end_time":119.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, thanks for making the time today.","index":62,"end_time":122.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":119.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The way that we use this session is to walk you through everything that we have synthesized from our conversation so far.","index":63,"end_time":128.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":122.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The knowledge that we have of the market, the knowledge that you guys have shared, the data that you''ve shared, and also the research that we''ve conducted.","index":64,"end_time":134.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":129.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if any marketing agency is telling you, hey, this is the exact plan that you''ll follow, and you guys are just going to 10x your business, I highly recommend questioning that agency heavily.","index":65,"end_time":144.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The plans that we put forth are based on data research, and everything that we can pull together to say, this is a strategy that we need to start with.","index":66,"end_time":152.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we make database decisions on the pivots that we are constantly making on a weekly, monthly, quarterly basis.","index":67,"end_time":158.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when I present this, it''s not like, hey guys, this is.","index":68,"end_time":160.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":158.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you take and run with this for a year, you''re just going to absolutely crush it.","index":69,"end_time":165.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":160.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is the hope.","index":70,"end_time":166.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is, that is our goal out of this.","index":71,"end_time":167.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":166.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But everything we do is based on data, making quick pivots based on that data coming in.","index":72,"end_time":171.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So to get into our agenda, we''ll start by grounding on the audiences, the ICPs that we''ve developed.","index":73,"end_time":179,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":173.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll talk through some positioning and products and also your competitive landscape.","index":74,"end_time":184.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":179.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve gone through several of your competitors and put together just a matrix of where they have strengths from an SEO, paid branding, content perspective, social media perspective, all of these things, as well as how that compares to ResQ.","index":75,"end_time":197.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then really where we''ll spend most of our conversation is in the roadmap goals, quarterly initiatives and the overall plan.","index":76,"end_time":204.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have detailed out exactly what we are expecting to do in the first 90 days if we do move forward with this and how we define success and what that success looks like.","index":77,"end_time":213.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does that sound like a good agenda or any questions before we dive in?","index":78,"end_time":216.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":213.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, that sounds good.","index":79,"end_time":219.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":219.12,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah, go for it.","index":80,"end_time":220.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":219.92,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":81,"end_time":221.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, you guys are pretty familiar with this slide, how we work.","index":82,"end_time":225.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":222.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you have any questions, happy to dive into it, but this kind of goes with what I started with.","index":83,"end_time":230.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everything we do goes through a heavy analysis phase on a weekly, monthly, quarterly basis.","index":84,"end_time":235.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''re always tweaking the approach that we''re making based on that data coming in.","index":85,"end_time":238.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":235.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also have a massive research document that we''ve compiled.","index":86,"end_time":242.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is about 90 pages.","index":87,"end_time":244.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":242.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll share this with you, but this goes through really everything in fine detail of how you guys are currently positioned in the market, the strategies that you guys have been invoking historically, competitor landscape, all of these things that we''ll address at a higher level in this slide deck.","index":88,"end_time":258.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":244.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So getting into the target market, you know, we feel strongly that there''s a lot of similarities between these different ICPs.","index":89,"end_time":268.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But the reason that they are ICPs and they have differentiators is because they''re not all experiencing the same pain points.","index":90,"end_time":273.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They need a little bit of different messaging to get them to convert, to get across the finish line.","index":91,"end_time":278.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the first one that we have here is the multi location.","index":92,"end_time":282,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In our conversations we talked about that sweet spot being at the 2 to 9 location.","index":93,"end_time":286.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what stood out there is that their behavior is really almost always problem driven.","index":94,"end_time":292.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":287.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They have some other solution.","index":95,"end_time":294.879,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe they''re using toast, maybe they''re using some other competitor or maybe some homegrown system that they''ve established and they are outgrowing it.","index":96,"end_time":303.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.879,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re realizing they don''t have the customer support that they need.","index":97,"end_time":306.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They, they are just having an issue with these systems working across all of their locations.","index":98,"end_time":312.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so the messaging here that resonates with these people is really about reliability, visibility and not having to fight against your technology provider as you continue to scale.","index":99,"end_time":323.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":312.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we go through a whole matrix as well here about the things these people are thinking, seeing, saying.","index":100,"end_time":333.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this all relates heavily into the messaging that we will develop for all of these campaigns.","index":101,"end_time":337.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The next breakout of the ICP is going to be the single location owners.","index":102,"end_time":345.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they vary differently in their behavior, even though on paper sometimes they may look a little bit similar in revenue and other numbers.","index":103,"end_time":353.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they tend to be very skeptical.","index":104,"end_time":355.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":353.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''ve heard big promises before, you know, things may feel a little bit existential for them and so they, they get a little bit more defensive.","index":105,"end_time":363.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Their messaging isn''t about scale, it''s about building trust.","index":106,"end_time":366.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They need to understand the onboarding process.","index":107,"end_time":369.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":366.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They need to understand your guys transparent pricing.","index":108,"end_time":371.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":369.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''ve probably heard some horror stories from the restaurant next door that was using toast and then a year later they got hit with a bunch of hidden fees.","index":109,"end_time":379.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this restaurant owner is now scared to death to do anything like that because if they get hit with hidden fees they might have to shut their restaurant down.","index":110,"end_time":386.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.899,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s really about answering all of those questions, pain points or worries or concerns that they have, as well as support, always answering the phone, getting back to them within a timely manner, things like that.","index":111,"end_time":398.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Brett, one thing that you mentioned a lot in our calls was the education factor here.","index":112,"end_time":403.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":398.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And education is really important with this audience.","index":113,"end_time":405.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":403.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again, going through the onboarding, going through examples like hey it''s Friday night, what happens if the system breaks?","index":114,"end_time":412.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What support are you guys able to provide?","index":115,"end_time":414.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Things like that.","index":116,"end_time":415.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":414.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we have their matrix here as well.","index":117,"end_time":419.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And again we''ll send over this whole slide deck for you guys to review after this call.","index":118,"end_time":423.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":419.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like to go over the high level.","index":119,"end_time":424.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a lot of information in here.","index":120,"end_time":426.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":424.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The next and last ICP that we have built out is the fast growing QSR chains.","index":121,"end_time":432.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":427.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kind of a completely different mindset here.","index":122,"end_time":434.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Speed and throughput are basically non negotiable for these types of businesses.","index":123,"end_time":439.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":434.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know, if they''re processing hundreds of transactions during a lunch rush or, or really just have like a rush overall, a few seconds in delay in their system can be a game breaker for them.","index":124,"end_time":452.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when they''re looking you know, on Google or different channels that we would be advertising on.","index":125,"end_time":457.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Their searches are very specific.","index":126,"end_time":458.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":457.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re looking for a high volume pos, you know, QSR POS with delivery integrations, a POS for fast casual chains.","index":127,"end_time":466.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":458.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not very emotional.","index":128,"end_time":467.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":466.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They are looking for operational language.","index":129,"end_time":470.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They need speed, they need accuracy, they need, they need reliability.","index":130,"end_time":474.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so education here isn''t about reassuring them.","index":131,"end_time":477.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":474.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s about being very clear about your skill sets, the features that you guys are able to provide and the support that you''re able to provide.","index":132,"end_time":483.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":477.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What RESQ overall does best, where it fits best, and what the expectation should be.","index":133,"end_time":489.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions on the icps before we kind of break into some of the brand positioning deck that we have?","index":134,"end_time":496.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":491.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no, I think we''re good.","index":135,"end_time":499.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.03,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"That looks pretty good.","index":136,"end_time":500.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":499.39,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":137,"end_time":501.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":500.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just thought the very first slide that icp, I think we''ve internally talked about it and we know where reliability comes in.","index":138,"end_time":511.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":502.15,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"I definitely think that there''s a lot of switching happening that seems like now to lower cost and capture strong functionality.","index":139,"end_time":521.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":512.71,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"I think reliability would be somewhere down on the list, just FYI.","index":140,"end_time":525.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":522.47,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, totally hear you there.","index":141,"end_time":529.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":526.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think it''s, it''s not about just having like the main, you know, one word pain point that''s going to get them to convert.","index":142,"end_time":536.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s about having representation for everything that they could be experiencing.","index":143,"end_time":539.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because even within this icp, there''s still a spectrum that exists.","index":144,"end_time":543.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":539.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a snowflake.","index":145,"end_time":547.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":546.1,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":146,"end_time":547.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":547.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And you want to make sure that you''re fitting that pattern so you can get alignment.","index":147,"end_time":552.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":547.46,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":148,"end_time":552.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":149,"end_time":553.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":150,"end_time":555.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":554.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so then for your brand positioning and messaging, what we do is we take a story brand approach.","index":151,"end_time":560.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":556.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not sure if you guys have read through storybrand, but it''s a great approach that positions your prospect as the hero in the journey and positions rescue as the solution that they need.","index":152,"end_time":572.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":560.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So overall, we didn''t want to over engineer the messaging here.","index":153,"end_time":575.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Through our conversations, through our research, what came through very clearly is that Resku wins when expectations are set correctly, when the operators understand the support difference that you guys are able to provide.","index":154,"end_time":586.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Georgie, you even mentioned system failures during peak service.","index":155,"end_time":591.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":587.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not a theory, it''s an immediate revenue loss.","index":156,"end_time":593.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":591.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":157,"end_time":593.999,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":593.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so that''s a big piece of what these prospects are concerned about.","index":158,"end_time":597.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":593.999,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so that''s what we''ve baked into this overall story brand approach.","index":159,"end_time":601.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":598.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again, positioning your customer as the hero.","index":160,"end_time":605.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They have a challenge, whether it is external, internal, philosophical, oftentimes, sometimes a mix of all of these things.","index":161,"end_time":611.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":605.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They then do some research and Find resq, they find Toast Tab, they find a couple other solutions.","index":162,"end_time":617.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":611.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But where are we able to differentiate ourselves?","index":163,"end_time":620.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":618.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What plan are we able to provide?","index":164,"end_time":621.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":620.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are we calling them to to action, to convert, to have that demo conversation with your team and ultimately helping them experience success where they have a reliable system that performs, whether it''s peak hours or slow hours, that they have access to data and reporting, that they have a simplified operations set that reduces maybe staff training time or some other pain points that they may experience, as well as responsive call support.","index":165,"end_time":648.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":622.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so what we''re helping them transform from and into is from anxiety about unreliable technology, unresponsive vendors, into having confidence in their POS system that it works consistently, it''s growing with their business, so scalability isn''t an issue, and that you''re able to deliver support when they need it most.","index":166,"end_time":669.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":649.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you guys ever looked at a story brand framework before?","index":167,"end_time":672.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":168,"end_time":675.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":674.82,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yes.","index":169,"end_time":675.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.26,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Okay.","index":170,"end_time":676.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":675.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":171,"end_time":676.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions here before I jump into products and solutions?","index":172,"end_time":681.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Questions?","index":173,"end_time":683.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, we''re good.","index":174,"end_time":685.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":684.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":175,"end_time":686.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I probably won''t spend too much time on the products and solutions.","index":176,"end_time":689.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys are very familiar with what you offer.","index":177,"end_time":690.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":689.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We didn''t list out every feature set that you offer, but we kind of listed the main differentiator.","index":178,"end_time":696.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we wanted to show again the things that when you deals, the reliability, the onboarding support.","index":179,"end_time":701.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":696.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Brett, totally hear you.","index":180,"end_time":702.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":701.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Every.","index":181,"end_time":703.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Every deal here is a snowflake and there''s going to be a different thing that we need to pull out of rescues main offering, messaging and positioning to get that deal across the finish line.","index":182,"end_time":712.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":703.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one thing that we are intentional about is not treating.","index":183,"end_time":715.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":713.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I''m sorry.","index":184,"end_time":717.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":716.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we wanted to do here is just kind of have a breakdown.","index":185,"end_time":720.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This really also helps our team internally when we''re developing the messaging, when we putting together designs.","index":186,"end_time":726.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":720.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Who are we speaking to?","index":187,"end_time":727.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":726.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it going to be a man or a woman?","index":188,"end_time":729.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Using the system that resonates better with the audience.","index":189,"end_time":732.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":729.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oftentimes very male led in these industries as well.","index":190,"end_time":735.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How much do we show technology versus a human in these things?","index":191,"end_time":738.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":735.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So having an understanding of your product matrix really helps us develop all of these things.","index":192,"end_time":743.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":739.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Downstream.","index":193,"end_time":743.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":743.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Column.","index":194,"end_time":747.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":747.1,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"I think it''s really important to have sort of a build your own ending or build your own story type of approach.","index":195,"end_time":754.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":747.66,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"In sales, we want to be able to segment people based on question probably three paths.","index":196,"end_time":758.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":754.45,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"We get, you know, the top of the call is the most difficult.","index":197,"end_time":761.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":759.33,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Once we can get on the right problem, then we can start to build alignment and momentum and then start to future cast success.","index":198,"end_time":767.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":761.45,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So I, I do think that it''s Important to kind of chunk out the, the problem solution so that we are in alignment when people come through a landing page or funnel and then then we can start to assume the close as we find where people are.","index":199,"end_time":781.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":767.81,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"We instantly add relevance and value at every touch point.","index":200,"end_time":785.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":781.3,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":201,"end_time":786.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":785.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you know, when we get into the finer detail of exactly what we''ve laid out in the first 90 days, it''s a lot about building that connection on the landing pages, in the ad campaigns, the search intent, but also on the sales side, the collateral and having a better understanding of the quality leads coming through and how we''re able to.","index":202,"end_time":802.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":786.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is exactly what they need at this step.","index":203,"end_time":803.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":802.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the questions that they may have at this step.","index":204,"end_time":805.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":803.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is what we''re able to provide, things like that.","index":205,"end_time":807.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess I''m just trying to do the antithesis though.","index":206,"end_time":811.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":808.55,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"The snowflake.","index":207,"end_time":811.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":811.11,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"We wanted to want to chunk people into probably three major pathways, which makes it easier on the marketing side and then also easier for sales to pick up and take clothes.","index":208,"end_time":820.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":811.71,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So just want to make sure, you know, we''re not trying to count nits.","index":209,"end_time":825.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":820.87,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":210,"end_time":826.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":826.55,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Have you laid out your products and services in that way in the past, like in terms of the three chunks or like the three pathways?","index":211,"end_time":834.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":826.91,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Not that I''m aware of, no, no, no.","index":212,"end_time":839.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":837.82,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"But it''s always how I see getting a hold of.","index":213,"end_time":842.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":840.22,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So we''re trying to streamline everything and make it replicatable as much as possible and take people through the funnel and, and make it ensure success as much.","index":214,"end_time":853.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":842.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As much as possible.","index":215,"end_time":854.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":853.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":216,"end_time":855.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":854.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It can be challenging when you''re like, when you''re trying to speak to so many people in different ways and then what ends up happening is you end up speaking to no one and trying to.","index":217,"end_time":866.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":855.78,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"80% of people.","index":218,"end_time":867.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":866.5,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Right.","index":219,"end_time":868.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":867.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any industry, 80% buy for the same reasons.","index":220,"end_time":870.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":868.06,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":221,"end_time":870.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":870.34,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Typically just switching up the top.","index":222,"end_time":872.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":870.82,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"The top buying motives align with the top pain points and asking does that sound familiar?","index":223,"end_time":879.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":873.54,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"When they say hell yes, then you move down that path.","index":224,"end_time":881.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":879.62,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":225,"end_time":885.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":884.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":226,"end_time":887.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":886.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So then we''ll dive into the competitive matrix that we''ve built as well.","index":227,"end_time":892.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":889.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in here we''ll have Toast, Lightspeed, Sky Tab Rescue and we''ll go through high level overview of those as well.","index":228,"end_time":900.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":892.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we do have a matrix again with five main points that we were measuring.","index":229,"end_time":905.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":901.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We used a bunch of different LLMs for, to scrape social media profiles, ad accounts, websites, and really measure all of these things as.","index":230,"end_time":914.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":905.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As quantified as we can and then putting the qualitative layer on top of it.","index":231,"end_time":919.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So with Toast, you know, the approach that we''re going to recommend is not just trying to outspend Toasts.","index":232,"end_time":927.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know that that''s even going to be possible.","index":233,"end_time":929.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re the name in the game, they have a large budget.","index":234,"end_time":932.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But competition isn''t going to drive like the exact decision that we make here.","index":235,"end_time":936.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s going to inform the campaigns and where it makes sense to operate.","index":236,"end_time":941.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Toast being a category leader leader, they''re dominating in brand awareness, SEO, paid media.","index":237,"end_time":947.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":941.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But they''ve grown and scaled so quickly that we are seeing more and more complaints every day.","index":238,"end_time":953.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":948.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Georgie, I think you mentioned this and Brett probably directly as well, that that scale has cost them their service.","index":239,"end_time":960.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":953.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, they, they''ve been losing deals left and right.","index":240,"end_time":963.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":961.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''ve been moving from white glove support and more creating like a ticketing model.","index":241,"end_time":968.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":964.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They.","index":242,"end_time":970.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":970.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s why we don''t recommend just going really aggressively against Toast on like let''s just spend $30,000 every month on Google Ads and we''ll get some junk leads and we''ll get some quality leads.","index":243,"end_time":980.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":971.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to fix things at a more foundational level.","index":244,"end_time":983.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":980.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we do see some opportunities in Toast, especially with current customers and that are looking for a new solution and that are experiencing those pain points.","index":245,"end_time":993.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":983.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think Paul had a great way of simplifying the marketplace and that is there''s approximately four or five competitors which are behind in terms of innovation.","index":246,"end_time":1013.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":997.51,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"And what we want to do is bump them out so it becomes either us or Toast.","index":247,"end_time":1017.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1014.31,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"I think that was brilliant.","index":248,"end_time":1021.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1019.51,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"There''s a lot of conversations with people going to POS''s that they should not be considering that that delay.","index":249,"end_time":1028.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1022.68,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"You know, here it is.","index":250,"end_time":1030.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1028.92,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"We want to help people get on the right buyer''s journey that leads to success, not go on their journey which may lead to nowhere or bad decision.","index":251,"end_time":1037.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1030.28,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So the market, the restaurant market, rental restaurants get more and more difficult to do.","index":252,"end_time":1045.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1038.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Especially in California because of increase in minimum wage and increase in regulations is getting more and more difficult.","index":253,"end_time":1052.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1045.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so a restaurateur has to rely more and more on technology.","index":254,"end_time":1056.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1052.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And as the market changes, there are not a lot between us and Toast.","index":255,"end_time":1064.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1058.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There are not other point of sales who are adapting to the new technology and new way of doing business.","index":256,"end_time":1070.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1064.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even like lightspeed, I mean they just do not do very much development anymore.","index":257,"end_time":1076.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1072.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And there''s five of them who basically they have a point of sale and that''s it.","index":258,"end_time":1082.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1077.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s where they want to stop.","index":259,"end_time":1083.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They want to stop at a point of sale, their products done.","index":260,"end_time":1087.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1084.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They don''t want to innovate.","index":261,"end_time":1088.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1087.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we''re Seeing restaurateurs are looking for something new to get.","index":262,"end_time":1093.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1088.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To get market share, to stay in business more, basically.","index":263,"end_time":1097.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1093.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":264,"end_time":1099.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1098.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, they''re hearing buzzwords everywhere from the restaurant next door, the competitors that they''re dealing with.","index":265,"end_time":1104.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1099.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they need an understanding and a solution that''s going to help them continue to grow and scale with the.","index":266,"end_time":1109.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1104.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The ever changing, you know, technology landscape.","index":267,"end_time":1112.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1109.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not something that''s just like, yep, this is what we do.","index":268,"end_time":1115.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1112.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is what we''ll always do.","index":269,"end_time":1116.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1115.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Logically, the customer is faced with this tyranny of too much choice.","index":270,"end_time":1122.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1118.63,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"There''s plenty of marketing from these, maybe like legacy systems, but they occupy too much space in the decision part of the mind.","index":271,"end_time":1130.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1122.19,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":272,"end_time":1131.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1130.91,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We want to silence that, make it easy.","index":273,"end_time":1133.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1131.27,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"We got two choices.","index":274,"end_time":1134.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1133.19,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yep.","index":275,"end_time":1135.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1134.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I actually that would really help.","index":276,"end_time":1137.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1135.65,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":277,"end_time":1138.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1138.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I just wrote that on my board to quantify the issues with delayed decisions, meaning on these landing pages showing, you know, how much a restaurant can be impacted financially from delaying their decision by going and talking to too many vendors versus just looking at these top two solutions.","index":278,"end_time":1154.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1138.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":279,"end_time":1154.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1154.21,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"And so when you look at the five competitors, they''re actually all very similar in their weaknesses.","index":280,"end_time":1160.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1155.41,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"And so it''s easy to sort of chunk those out and say, probably don''t want to select from these.","index":281,"end_time":1165.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1160.61,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yep, absolutely.","index":282,"end_time":1167.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1166.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, F1, I think, I think that would be exciting if we come up with messaging like that.","index":283,"end_time":1171.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1167.63,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah, awesome.","index":284,"end_time":1173.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1171.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, the next one is Lightspeed.","index":285,"end_time":1174.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1173.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was just gonna say, Colin, let''s take a look at those competitors.","index":286,"end_time":1177.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1175.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":287,"end_time":1178.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1177.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Lightspeed, you know, they went on sophistications and global reach.","index":288,"end_time":1182.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1178.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it actually can be rather intimidating.","index":289,"end_time":1184.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1182.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It almost kind of works in an inverse way for more of the independent or regional operators.","index":290,"end_time":1190.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1184.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But they do have very strong brand positioning.","index":291,"end_time":1195.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1192.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Their content is lacking, but from an SEO standpoint, they do have, you know, a very strong foundation there.","index":292,"end_time":1203.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1195.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"204,000 linking domains.","index":293,"end_time":1206.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1204.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then on the paid media side, they are tracking or what we were able to identify over 11,000 paid keywords, which is the highest quantity of keywords, not the highest spend or cost of those keywords.","index":294,"end_time":1221.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1207.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they are trying to spread themselves out across many different search intents out.","index":295,"end_time":1227.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1221.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lightspeed is if sort of.","index":296,"end_time":1229.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1227.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They don''t do very much marketing in the restaurant space anymore.","index":297,"end_time":1232.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1229.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They really focus on retail.","index":298,"end_time":1233.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1232.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The retail has become.","index":299,"end_time":1235.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1233.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which we don''t do.","index":300,"end_time":1236.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1235.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":301,"end_time":1236.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1236.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"It sort of conceded to toast in this space.","index":302,"end_time":1241.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1237.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, absolutely.","index":303,"end_time":1244.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1242.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":304,"end_time":1247.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1246.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":305,"end_time":1248.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1247.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we have Skytab.","index":306,"end_time":1250.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1248.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is the closest peer that we found in terms of positioning.","index":307,"end_time":1253.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1250.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They lean very heavily into education and training.","index":308,"end_time":1257.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1254,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which is reinforcing to us the, the path that we need to take or have a component of which is that education before the sale and how important it is in this category, a relatively decent domain authority.","index":309,"end_time":1270.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1257.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They, they are a few points above you in that, not a huge LinkedIn following.","index":310,"end_time":1275.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Again, I don''t think LinkedIn is the strongest place or platform for this audience.","index":311,"end_time":1279.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1275.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They do have a decent YouTube channel with just under 300 videos, under a thousand paid keywords.","index":312,"end_time":1285.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1279.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So probably not a massive budget that we''re seeing as the keywords weren''t incredibly expensive.","index":313,"end_time":1289.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1285.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But from the other perspectives they do seem to be relatively close to what Rescue has done historically in marketing.","index":314,"end_time":1297.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1290.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then lastly we have RESQ in here in our competitive matrix.","index":315,"end_time":1305.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1301.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So strongest advantage being the service differentiation.","index":316,"end_time":1308.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1305.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So 24, seven U.S. based support, first call resolution.","index":317,"end_time":1311.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1308.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know that''s not just saying it for marketing sake, right?","index":318,"end_time":1315.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is actual, you know, things that you guys live by, that''s operational reality that you''re able to provide.","index":319,"end_time":1320.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1315.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we do see a lot of opportunities to improve things across several channels.","index":320,"end_time":1324.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1321.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, one thing that we''ll talk through is a content series that we can use to syndicate across multiple channels as well by just having, you know, a 30 minute conversation with you guys.","index":321,"end_time":1333.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1325.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that can go into blogs, white papers, ads, videos, all sorts of things that we can produce to hit these people on the channel that they are when they''re there.","index":322,"end_time":1342.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s multiple steps that go into the prospect, making up their mind.","index":323,"end_time":1345.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1342.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Brett, you know, to your point, they''ve made up 80% of their decision before they''re even talking to you.","index":324,"end_time":1350.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1346.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we need to give them a lot of different resources to convince them to have that first conversation.","index":325,"end_time":1354.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1350.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Second point, under Dimension Insights it says something like, if you look at it, the second line toast requiring immediate social investment.","index":326,"end_time":1365.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1356.89,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"What''s social investment?","index":327,"end_time":1366.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1365.93,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Not heard of that.","index":328,"end_time":1367.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1366.97,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Oh, you mean social media I guess, right?","index":329,"end_time":1369.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1367.65,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":330,"end_time":1370.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1369.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So social investment is in like having more representation of yourselves across social channels, having more, you know, brand recognition.","index":331,"end_time":1376.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1370.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":332,"end_time":1377.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1377.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":333,"end_time":1380.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1380.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions on the, on the competitive matrix that we put together before we get into the, the actual roadmap?","index":334,"end_time":1387.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1380.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No.","index":335,"end_time":1389.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1389.06,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":336,"end_time":1390.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1389.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so also Georgie, thank you for sending over the, the export out of the CRM.","index":337,"end_time":1398.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1391.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So and I believe, and if you can confirm that you guys weren''t running Google Ads this month, is that correct?","index":338,"end_time":1404.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1398.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":339,"end_time":1407.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1407.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the Google Ads, I think they stopped running right around mid of December.","index":340,"end_time":1411.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1407.64,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So they''re currently not running and they.","index":341,"end_time":1412.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1411.2,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Were not running the whole month.","index":342,"end_time":1413.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1412.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct?","index":343,"end_time":1414.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1413.96,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":344,"end_time":1414.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1414.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":345,"end_time":1415.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1414.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know, we see, we see the third party partners that are coming in with results there.","index":346,"end_time":1421.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1415.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''d be interested to see, you know, how much of those are converting to sales qualified leads or really into like the true demo calls and qualified leads that are coming through to potentially become customers.","index":347,"end_time":1432.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1421.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But through our conversations, what we really understand is that you''re paying for everything at this point, whether it''s high quality or whether it''s junk and especially with Google Ads.","index":348,"end_time":1443.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1433.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we need to do there is it''s not an approach of just dump more money in and yes, you''ll get more junk, but yes you''ll get more high quality.","index":349,"end_time":1450.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1444.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s an approach of how can we group several different channels together to improve the quality while maintaining a relatively low cost per lead.","index":350,"end_time":1459.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1450.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that that''s a sort of North Star metric that you guys have been utilizing historically.","index":351,"end_time":1463.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1459.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we set our goals on an OKR model.","index":352,"end_time":1470.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1466.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So objectives and key results.","index":353,"end_time":1471.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1470.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so based on the historical data that you guys provided and through our conversations, you know, the business outcome here would be improving or increasing the qualified leads that are coming inbound.","index":354,"end_time":1483.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1471.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For demo requests from restaurant operators, we like to be very clear in this language what marketing is accountable for here is inbound demo booking.","index":355,"end_time":1492.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1483.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So form fills, demo requests, scheduled conversations.","index":356,"end_time":1495.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1492.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any CTA that we''re going to put on these new landing pages that we would spin up, we''d like to have a mix of them because again, the buyer journey can be so different.","index":357,"end_time":1502.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1495.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not everyone is willing to sign up for a demo call right away.","index":358,"end_time":1505.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1502.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sometimes they need a leave behind, sometimes they need some sort of tangible thing before they''re willing to hop on a call.","index":359,"end_time":1511.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1505.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re going to need several different calls to actions across these things.","index":360,"end_time":1514.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1511.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so given that historical, historically Google Ads has performed around $400 cost per lead.","index":361,"end_time":1522.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1515.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Georgie, I know that that was like a range that we kind of landed on because, you know, sometimes it''s, it''s very high, sometimes it''s very low.","index":362,"end_time":1529.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1522.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s across several different channels.","index":363,"end_time":1530.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1529.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have qualified, we have junk.","index":364,"end_time":1531.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1530.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we like to ground ourselves in, in the reality there.","index":365,"end_time":1536.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1533.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And also in our conversations, you guys had mentioned that while there is, you know, follow up from the sales team after the qualification of an email and a phone call, we think that there are some extra steps that can be added into that journey so that we can stay in front of the prospect after they''ve already shown some intent to talk to you guys, we can do that all through some automated campaigns as well to really unify that conversion flow.","index":366,"end_time":1560.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1537.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we want to establish here is a growing Scale of qualified leads.","index":367,"end_time":1565.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1561.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in the first month we''ll be putting together a lot of the foundation, you know, rewriting messaging, making new landing pages, coming up with new designs for different channels, coming up with a content plan and series, everything like that.","index":368,"end_time":1578.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1566.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The first 90 days, getting that number up to 25 qualified, I''m sorry, 20 qualified demos per month as we continue to scale getting to 30 qualified demos per month and then at the end of the year up to 40 qualified demos per month.","index":369,"end_time":1591.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1578.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All of that being measured through your guys, CRM and Colin.","index":370,"end_time":1596.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1591.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are we talking about Google only here on this slide or is this I guess like all of them or the sources or Google only or.","index":371,"end_time":1602.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1596.39,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah, so we would be heavily utilizing Google but we don''t want to just be on that channel.","index":372,"end_time":1607.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1603.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So as part of this I also really want to get a stronger understanding of your guys third party partners and how we can influence and improve the messaging and calls to action and landing pages there and then really also how we can expand into email and a few different other channels.","index":373,"end_time":1624.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1608.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":374,"end_time":1626.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1625.75,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Okay, thank you.","index":375,"end_time":1627.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1626.19,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Okay, Are you taking questions on the slide now?","index":376,"end_time":1632.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1630.63,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":377,"end_time":1633.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1632.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Questions at any time.","index":378,"end_time":1634.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1633.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you go into rationale to the third bullet, marketing, Marketing accountability, can you speak to that?","index":379,"end_time":1641.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1634.87,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":380,"end_time":1642.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1642.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is just where we define that we are not hopping on the sales demo call that our accountability is for driving those qualified leads to hand them off to the sales team to continue your normal process.","index":381,"end_time":1653.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1642.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s chuck it over the cubicle wall it sounds like to me.","index":382,"end_time":1657.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1654.8,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Well, it''s, it''s, you know, we have, we have provided a marketing qualified lead.","index":383,"end_time":1661.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1657.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys have qualified it on your end.","index":384,"end_time":1663.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1661.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is where our journey stops.","index":385,"end_time":1664.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1663.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean you guys can obviously we would be creating sales enablement materials and things like that, but we wouldn''t be in those conversations with the prospects.","index":386,"end_time":1672.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1665.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but that''s still like 1985 metric there versus a performance marketing metric that would share an implied quota.","index":387,"end_time":1686.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1674.41,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Share an implied quote.","index":388,"end_time":1689.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1687.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, go ahead.","index":389,"end_time":1689.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1689.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so what I would say is this, right?","index":390,"end_time":1691.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1689.77,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"How come marketing goes home at 5 o'' clock and sales is there to 9?","index":391,"end_time":1694.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1691.82,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Sales owns revenue.","index":392,"end_time":1696.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1695.1,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":393,"end_time":1697.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1696.86,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Can we make that even?","index":394,"end_time":1698.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1697.18,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Can we?","index":395,"end_time":1699.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1698.7,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Let''s say for example that a just top of mind a white paper converts leads to 40%, an ad converts leads to 10%.","index":396,"end_time":1711.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1699.26,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":397,"end_time":1711.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1711.58,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Marketing can decide, you can get me fewer of white paper leads, they convert higher.","index":398,"end_time":1716.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1712.06,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Or you could get me more of the advertising leads, they convert less.","index":399,"end_time":1721.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1716.86,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"But now we''re able to assign a revenue quota to the marketing function that drives roi.","index":400,"end_time":1728.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1722.44,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"And that, that is, you know, has equal weight at the boardroom table in terms of the revenue impact that''s being generated.","index":401,"end_time":1738.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1729.32,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"In other words, MQLs may mean nothing.","index":402,"end_time":1740.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1738.84,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"That''s often why, like, salespeople say marketing can''t make a buck if they see a dollar going across the street.","index":403,"end_time":1747.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1742.76,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":404,"end_time":1748.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1747.69,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Want to make sure that there can be some revenue metric tied to the marketing effort rather than just providing leads.","index":405,"end_time":1754.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1748.29,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":406,"end_time":1756.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1755.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So what?","index":407,"end_time":1756.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1756.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"One thing here, if I could jump in for a moment, just.","index":408,"end_time":1758.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1756.57,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"That just gives you more clout.","index":409,"end_time":1760.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1759.25,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely.","index":410,"end_time":1762.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1761.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So, so how would you tie those together?","index":411,"end_time":1764.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1762.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Like what would give you an example?","index":412,"end_time":1767.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1765.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, just give the example off the top of my head.","index":413,"end_time":1770.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1767.97,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"If you know, well, you just have better quality though.","index":414,"end_time":1773.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1770.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Right.","index":415,"end_time":1773.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1773.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So, like, what.","index":416,"end_time":1774.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1773.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"But what is the.","index":417,"end_time":1775.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1774.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Oh, I, I did not.","index":418,"end_time":1776.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1775.65,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"I said that I gave you a conversion.","index":419,"end_time":1778.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1776.69,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Percentage is 40 and 10%.","index":420,"end_time":1780.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1778.65,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Deal close conversions based on marketing funnel, tactic, endpoint, however you wish to call it.","index":421,"end_time":1791.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1782.61,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":422,"end_time":1791.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1791.29,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Whether that be a white paper, an ad.","index":423,"end_time":1793.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1791.49,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess just to make it simple, not just the challenges.","index":424,"end_time":1801.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1795.01,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"When leads don''t convert, no one''s happy.","index":425,"end_time":1803.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1801.69,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":426,"end_time":1804.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1803.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Right.","index":427,"end_time":1805.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1804.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And so when we can tie conversion percentages into revenue, then marketing and sales both share a revenue responsibility and we get alignment.","index":428,"end_time":1817.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1806.57,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Otherwise we get marketing and sales pointing fingers at each other.","index":429,"end_time":1820.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1817.85,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"That''s.","index":430,"end_time":1821.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1820.65,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"That''s been the conversation last 15 years.","index":431,"end_time":1823.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1821.45,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":432,"end_time":1823.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1823.49,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"There''s aligning into what we call revenue operations.","index":433,"end_time":1827.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1823.69,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":434,"end_time":1828.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1828.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So.","index":435,"end_time":1828.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1828.42,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So what we have, that would be awesome if we could approach something like that.","index":436,"end_time":1831.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1828.66,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":437,"end_time":1833.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1832.66,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So what we have here is inbound demo booking.","index":438,"end_time":1835.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1833.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So different than, than like an ebook download or, you know, these are hand raisers versus, you know, someone that''s more of a content lead or more of a nurtured lead, so higher intent.","index":439,"end_time":1849.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1835.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"I think what Brett is trying to say is that, you know, you can give us 100 leads, but if all those leads were like, we''re running them down a path that don''t convert, they''re, they''re, they''re worthless to us.","index":440,"end_time":1864.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1850.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we can get 40 leads from a different source that convert, that''s the value.","index":441,"end_time":1869.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1864.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":442,"end_time":1870.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1869.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s not the lead.","index":443,"end_time":1872.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1870.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a lead that has been led down the proper path to convert.","index":444,"end_time":1875.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1872.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Am I saying 100%?","index":445,"end_time":1877.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1875.81,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So here''s.","index":446,"end_time":1877.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1877.13,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Let me just give you an example, Tristan.","index":447,"end_time":1879.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1877.77,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So let''s say we, we''re basically saying buy now.","index":448,"end_time":1882.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1879.73,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":449,"end_time":1882.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1882.62,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Get a demo with the.","index":450,"end_time":1884.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1882.94,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"You''re going to purchase it within 30 days.","index":451,"end_time":1886.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1884.94,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"That''s one funnel.","index":452,"end_time":1888.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1886.86,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Another funnel might be how to drive revenue.","index":453,"end_time":1893.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1888.7,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Make your boss happy.","index":454,"end_time":1894.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1893.26,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"If you''re the manager.","index":455,"end_time":1896.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1894.3,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":456,"end_time":1896.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1896.3,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"The operations manager, maybe that brings in more educated Buyers and maybe more educated buyers convert.","index":457,"end_time":1903.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1896.5,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"I''m basically saying there''s two different conversion end goals there and we might find there''s lift and revenue that differs amongst the two.","index":458,"end_time":1914.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1905.58,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So I think that we need to do like A, B and C testing to see where we''re actually getting the conversions.","index":459,"end_time":1920.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1915.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The, the leads that convert and focus on those.","index":460,"end_time":1924.419,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1921.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What happens before the demo may be meaningful in revenue.","index":461,"end_time":1927.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1924.66,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":462,"end_time":1928.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1927.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":463,"end_time":1929.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1928.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"I mean but when we talk about.","index":464,"end_time":1931.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1929.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So we''re like on this slide here, this is inbound demo booking.","index":465,"end_time":1935.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1931.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So that, that is a hand raiser.","index":466,"end_time":1937.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1935.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"I want a demo, I want to see what the solution look.","index":467,"end_time":1939.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1937.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"If so are we talking about like trying to get a full picture of the, the customer journey before that and trying to predict like how much education has this lead had or like what''s.","index":468,"end_time":1954.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1940.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"I think that''s a good starting point.","index":469,"end_time":1956.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1955.36,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"That''s right.","index":470,"end_time":1957.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1956.6,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So if I think it''s shown now, right.","index":471,"end_time":1959.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1957.36,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"That conversion to demo may not be the best way to buy market share and that perhaps assisting the lead in, in their due diligence might drive better quality demos, more qualified demos.","index":472,"end_time":1976.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1959.88,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah, and, and that is so, yeah, I think we''re in alignment there.","index":473,"end_time":1980.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1977.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"In fact, that that''s one of the things that Colin''s going to get into.","index":474,"end_time":1983.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1980.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"As far as, I mean if we think about like 80 to 90 of the education is done before someone reaches out, for the most part we don''t, we don''t always know what they''ve done beforehand, but part of what we''re proposing is providing a lot more of that information and trying to then understand how much activity can we monitor before they do reach out.","index":475,"end_time":2008.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1983.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"We do have some technology that we would integrate to try to detect those accounts and stuff.","index":476,"end_time":2013.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2008.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So, so I think there is some of that and I agree it''s like how, how much of that journey can we understand before they do reach out?","index":477,"end_time":2021.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2013.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And that will ideally help us make some better decisions on the marketing side.","index":478,"end_time":2026.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2021.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Like what, what content is being consumed earlier, etc.","index":479,"end_time":2028.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2026.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"That''s right.","index":480,"end_time":2029.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2028.83,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Good, good.","index":481,"end_time":2029.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2029.23,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So in other words, we''re shorting the sales cycle before demo.","index":482,"end_time":2032.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2029.91,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":483,"end_time":2034.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2033.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With all the, all the front loading of education and you guys can be.","index":484,"end_time":2038.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2034.15,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Sending us lots of, lots of leads, but if they''re not, I mean, and we could maybe be doing everything we can do on our end but they''re not converting.","index":485,"end_time":2048.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2038.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if we do something a little bit different, they could convert.","index":486,"end_time":2052,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2048.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean if we put them down the right path or they have the right expectations and what, what''s the product differentiators and all that stuff.","index":487,"end_time":2061.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2052.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Before that might help them.","index":488,"end_time":2063.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2061.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":489,"end_time":2064.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2063.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we don''t know what that is.","index":490,"end_time":2065.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2064.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to figure out what that is with you.","index":491,"end_time":2067.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2065.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But you just saying, oh, we were successful because we sent you leads.","index":492,"end_time":2072.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2068.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is not success to us because you can send us a million leads and if we can''t pay you, we can''t pay you, then you''re, you''re, you''re nothing to us.","index":493,"end_time":2081.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2073.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":494,"end_time":2082.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2081.8,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"We want good leads.","index":495,"end_time":2083.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2082.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, and you know, maybe that''s the word qualified leads but so we want it, we want to see what''s converting and what''s making the most sense and go in that direction.","index":496,"end_time":2092.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2083.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m sure Colin gonna get to it.","index":497,"end_time":2094.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2092.56,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"There''s another very specific criteria that we have that is there''s the quantity and then also have given them percentages of what is acceptable of qualified versus not qualified.","index":498,"end_time":2104.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2094.56,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So there is percentages that we''ve talked about that they will have a target behind.","index":499,"end_time":2108.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2104.34,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Like what do we consider acceptable or not acceptable?","index":500,"end_time":2111.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2108.86,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So 80% qualified, 20% non qualified, whatever that is.","index":501,"end_time":2114.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2111.5,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So there is a metric like that too.","index":502,"end_time":2116.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2114.7,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So I think that''s the last thing that might be interesting and simple to understand.","index":503,"end_time":2121.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2117.62,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Like let''s say we had five videos, that''s 100% of content.","index":504,"end_time":2124.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2121.38,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Okay.","index":505,"end_time":2125.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2124.74,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"We post those all in Wistia.","index":506,"end_time":2127.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2125.38,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"We could monitor each lead coming in, how much of the 100 of content they''re consuming.","index":507,"end_time":2131.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2127.02,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"And as we find leads are at 25% content consumed.","index":508,"end_time":2135.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2132.05,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"They''re not, they''re not closing or that sales cycle is beyond 90 days.","index":509,"end_time":2139.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2135.53,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"And as we drive more pre sales content consumption towards 75% we''re getting a 15 to 30 day sales cycle and we''re seeing the close rate go up.","index":510,"end_time":2149.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2139.33,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"That would be a great way to monitor how marketing is able to add an education component of qualified leads.","index":511,"end_time":2158.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2149.69,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":512,"end_time":2161.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2160.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s, I mean I think maybe we''re just having different wording here.","index":513,"end_time":2165.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2161.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is really what we mean by qualified leads and qualified demos.","index":514,"end_time":2169.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2165.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I mean we''re not just going to say hey guys, here''s a hundred leads.","index":515,"end_time":2172.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2169.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These 80 of them downloaded white papers and that''s why they''re qualified.","index":516,"end_time":2175.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2172.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s, it''s really the people that have taken this journey and have raised their hands and they are in the exact space and, and metrics and ratio that we''re looking for and that''s why they''re signing up for the qualified demo.","index":517,"end_time":2185.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2175.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":518,"end_time":2187.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2186.62,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"This is, everyone in the room I think has been burned by that situation.","index":519,"end_time":2190.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2187.18,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So we want to make sure we have, I guess just continue on.","index":520,"end_time":2194.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2190.7,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"We''re excited to see how we can get to what you''re just articulating now.","index":521,"end_time":2197.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2194.1,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":522,"end_time":2197.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2197.34,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I think the big thing here is just going to be making sure that the definition of qualified demos is very clear amongst all parties.","index":523,"end_time":2207.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2197.98,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"The big thing is, like you said with the finger pointing with sales is we want sales or whomever to agree when they say that, when we say these are the qualified demos and sales says yes, those are the types of meetings that I want.","index":524,"end_time":2225.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2207.9,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Maybe they have budget, maybe they have authority, need time on whatever it may be.","index":525,"end_time":2228.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2225.36,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Maybe it''s all for.","index":526,"end_time":2229.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2228.88,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We need to all agree on what that is.","index":527,"end_time":2231.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2229.96,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And that''s where the finger pointing goes away is because this entire annual goal alignment, we use the word align all over the place.","index":528,"end_time":2240.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2232.2,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"The whole purpose of this, this is.","index":529,"end_time":2242.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2240.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"To mitigate finger pointing and get rid of that.","index":530,"end_time":2245.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2242.88,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And if sales says yes, marketing, if you bring me 20 of those over on average over the next 90 days, I''m going to be pumped.","index":531,"end_time":2255.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2245.8,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Like bring me that.","index":532,"end_time":2256.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2255.48,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then it goes to sales to make sure that.","index":533,"end_time":2258.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2256.32,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Because we can''t close the deal.","index":534,"end_time":2259.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2258.04,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So that''s where kind of we''re trying to find a middle ground.","index":535,"end_time":2262.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2259.6,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"No 100%.","index":536,"end_time":2267.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2266.24,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"But if you can define what a qualified lead is.","index":537,"end_time":2270.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2267.16,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"We talked about that within the last call.","index":538,"end_time":2272.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2270.9,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Okay, that''s, that''s great.","index":539,"end_time":2273.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2272.42,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":540,"end_time":2273.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2273.34,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Unfortunately.","index":541,"end_time":2275.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2274.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":542,"end_time":2276.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2276.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"It looks like Justin''s literally frozen both in the camera and.","index":543,"end_time":2280.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2276.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And must be like 12 degrees.","index":544,"end_time":2283.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2280.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"It is.","index":545,"end_time":2284.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2283.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is.","index":546,"end_time":2284.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2284.26,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":547,"end_time":2285.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2284.9,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":548,"end_time":2286.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2286.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He.","index":549,"end_time":2286.659,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2286.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He keeps freezing.","index":550,"end_time":2287.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2286.659,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s going in and out.","index":551,"end_time":2288.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2287.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"All right, Colin, go ahead.","index":552,"end_time":2289.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2288.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"I think we''re.","index":553,"end_time":2289.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2289.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, but cool.","index":554,"end_time":2291.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2289.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it sounds like we''re on the same page and, and Georgie and also in the first 30 days and we''ll go through the.","index":555,"end_time":2297.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2291.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Every task item in the, in the first 90 days that we have in the plan.","index":556,"end_time":2300.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2297.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But one of those is a performance report document.","index":557,"end_time":2302.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2300.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We clearly identify everything and then we get you guys sign off on it and then that''s how we operate.","index":558,"end_time":2307.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2302.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":559,"end_time":2308.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2308.16,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"I had some great points, guys.","index":560,"end_time":2310.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2309.52,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It was gold.","index":561,"end_time":2311.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2310.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I, I''ll.","index":562,"end_time":2312.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2312,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I''ll record them and send them to you later.","index":563,"end_time":2314.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2312.64,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I am having some Internet struggles here.","index":564,"end_time":2316.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2314.44,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":565,"end_time":2318,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2317.44,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So we, we''ll get into more detail than this, but the, the main quarterly initiatives are building paid Media and Conversion Foundation.","index":566,"end_time":2325.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2319.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you guys have, you know, a lot of historical metrics in your systems, but based on all of our conversations, I think there''s still a need for some cleanup and new messaging approaches, new keyword ad groups and things, you know, just to look at even Google specifically also getting retargeting in the mix and then understanding Better the relationships with your third party providers and how we can impact and update the messaging there as well as the landing page you''re sending them to, the content journey that they are going on and how we''re able to understand and track what they''re consuming and what that kind of final conversion point is that gets them to sign up for that demo.","index":567,"end_time":2361.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2325.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So after that then getting into Google Ads, specifically relaunching with new campaigns with also intent filtering, activating, retargeting and then generating those inbound leads as well as creating a full conversion experience with that understanding of the performance scaling.","index":568,"end_time":2379.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2363.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in the first quarter we''ll be building four dedicated landing pages for high intent campaigns, looking always to improve conversion rates from click to demo and always keeping an eye on the cost per lead that''s coming in, all so that we can build a repeatable foundation or marketing function that works hand in hand with sales and that everyone is aligning on.","index":569,"end_time":2399.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2379.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, this is a qualified lead that came in and we closed them and then we''re able to say okay, cool, well they consumed X, Y and Z.","index":570,"end_time":2406.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2399.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So now we need to amplify those a little more.","index":571,"end_time":2407.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2406.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And let''s get in another a B test into here as a new piece of content or a new landing page or a new really anything in these channels so that we can continue to test.","index":572,"end_time":2417.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2407.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because if you put all your eggs in one basket because it worked this month, it there''s a good chance it''s not going to work next month.","index":573,"end_time":2423.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2417.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we always need to have that next thing in line.","index":574,"end_time":2425.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2423.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is a snapshot of some of the tools that we''re going to put in place.","index":575,"end_time":2433.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2429.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, go ahead.","index":576,"end_time":2434.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2433.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":577,"end_time":2435.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2435.19,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Paul had a question.","index":578,"end_time":2436.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2435.55,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":579,"end_time":2436.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2436.15,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Do you guys do retargeting with YouTube as well?","index":580,"end_time":2438.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2436.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do.","index":581,"end_time":2439.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2439.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":582,"end_time":2441.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2440.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ve seen YouTube actually, actually was just announced today that YouTube just took a a very strong share of ChatGPT''s source prompting from Reddit.","index":583,"end_time":2453.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2441.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s another thing that we''re going to dive heavily into with all the people doing search intent through ChatGPT.","index":584,"end_time":2458.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2453.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is a small glimpse of some of the marketing infrastructure that we would put in place.","index":585,"end_time":2466.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2463.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So identifying the right prospects, you know, even more than we would be able to do based on their search intent, identifying the, the actual list of customers that are fit for what Resq is looking to serve so that we can track them across several different channels.","index":586,"end_time":2480.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2467.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like I mentioned, we would have the several different paid ad channels as a part of this and then we would have an organic email nurture type sequence that would Also be following up with these people, keeping RESQ constantly in front of mind, promoting new educational materials to them, new announcements, new feature unlocks things like that.","index":587,"end_time":2499.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2481.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kind of taking a step up on a newsletter to a more personalized approach so that they feel like hey, next time I have a conversation with my provider currently or we''re looking to open a new location, it''s time to evaluate my system.","index":588,"end_time":2512.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2499.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that RESQ is top of mind in that we also de anonymize the traffic coming to the website through two different tools, one being RBDB and the others being factors AI.","index":589,"end_time":2521.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2512.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we work all of these through several different workflow platforms that we have established through N8N as well as a massive database and Supabase that we hold.","index":590,"end_time":2530.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2521.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This will hold all of the contact information and track the engagement that they are making as far as we can identify.","index":591,"end_time":2536.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2530.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because obviously some people have a browser that doesn''t show their IP address and we can''t get past that from a technology standpoint.","index":592,"end_time":2543.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2536.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But and then looping all of that back into and this would be a question for you guys whether you''re comfortable with us integrating this directly into your CRM or sometimes clients have a stand up a free or very very low cost version of HubSpot for example and then we would just batch upload leads instantly through an API connection.","index":593,"end_time":2562.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2543.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions around some of this technology infrastructure.","index":594,"end_time":2566.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2564.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But the 10,000 square foot this is ABM not, not I guess lead.","index":595,"end_time":2577.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2568.56,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Gen well paid would be a large component of this.","index":596,"end_time":2581.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2577.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so.","index":597,"end_time":2583.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2582.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So one good thing probably helpful to, to point out Colin is this infrastructure works for both ABM as well as detecting any folks that are consuming ads on the the platforms that where we can recognize their IP address or if they''re cookied in in other ways.","index":598,"end_time":2598.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2583.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And so that''s what factors in our B2B does.","index":599,"end_time":2602.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2598.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"We''re able to detect who comes to the website and we do this to support paid as well as proactive specific outreach that we have for you know, that comes out of smartly for, for those folks that we''ve identified as a good fit proactively.","index":600,"end_time":2619.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2603.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So this works on both sides.","index":601,"end_time":2622.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2620.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And so if you look at Supabase, which is our, that''s our own database where we''re tracking events.","index":602,"end_time":2628.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2623.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So this is before anyone would fill out a content download form, for example or fill out like maybe an email address before they watch a video.","index":603,"end_time":2638.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2628.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"You.","index":604,"end_time":2641.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2641.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Know, before they actually fill out a form for a demo request.","index":605,"end_time":2644.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2641.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"We''re trying our best to identify those folks beforehand so we can identify our own first party Signals.","index":606,"end_time":2652.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2644.53,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And that goes into the conversation we were just having earlier about that journey.","index":607,"end_time":2656.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2652.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"How much of that picture can we put together before they do reach out ultimately for the demo request?","index":608,"end_time":2662.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2656.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Very interesting.","index":609,"end_time":2664.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2663.97,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"How much of this is impacted or reduced because of data privacy?","index":610,"end_time":2669.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2664.77,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Well, so, so factors is IP address resolution.","index":611,"end_time":2676.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2672.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So they''re using clear bit to drive most of that RB2B.","index":612,"end_time":2682.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2677.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Some companies don''t, or, you know, they don''t elect to put that on there.","index":613,"end_time":2686.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2682.679,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"It is GDPR compliant.","index":614,"end_time":2687.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2686.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"It''s only used for US customers.","index":615,"end_time":2690.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2688.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So there are some things that we could go into about that.","index":616,"end_time":2693.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2691.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"But then on the flip side, like Colin mentioned, you know, we''re trying to really resolve about 40 to 60% of the folks that, that do land on the website.","index":617,"end_time":2703.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2694.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"There are, you know, still 30, 40% that we can''t identify.","index":618,"end_time":2707.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2703.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And that''s just, that''s the life of a marketer, like moving forward.","index":619,"end_time":2712.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2708.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"I mean that, that is part of the deal now.","index":620,"end_time":2714.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2712.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"That''s why we, we do need some, you know, at least other signals from the platform.","index":621,"end_time":2719.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2714.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Like, for example, you know, if you run something, you know, you''re trying to get an understanding of how long people are watching videos.","index":622,"end_time":2727.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2720.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And then what we can do is just try to target as much as we can using custom audiences.","index":623,"end_time":2732.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2727.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And then, you know, ultimately we''re saying if our customer audience is good and the platforms and we''re reaching the right people and this is the right message, you know, for the folks that we can identify, we should deduce that, hey, we''re still getting in front of the right folks.","index":624,"end_time":2746.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2733.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So that''s kind of the, the thought process there.","index":625,"end_time":2749.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2746.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry.","index":626,"end_time":2752.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2751.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":627,"end_time":2752.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2752.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"I''m just curious where lead scoring may come in, you know, down downstream from this.","index":628,"end_time":2758.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2753.5,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":629,"end_time":2760.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2759.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So lead touring is, is something that would be discussed in that performance marketing operations plan that I was talking about, where we would get full alignment on exactly how these are all, you know, hey, did they download this white paper and that''s plus 5.","index":630,"end_time":2770.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2760.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do they need to reach 100 before sales is going to even reach out?","index":631,"end_time":2774.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2770.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does a demo just automatically equal 100 if they''re qualified?","index":632,"end_time":2777.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2774.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all of that is laid out directly in that plan.","index":633,"end_time":2779.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2777.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, and, and to even echo on that more, that is where we make the determination at times of what goes into Supabase and what would go into your CRM.","index":634,"end_time":2792.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2780.16,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So if you determine that even though somebody didn''t fill out a form or they didn''t respond to an email, but they''ve clicked an ad 17 times, they''ve been to your website 22 times, and they have an Incredibly high lead score.","index":635,"end_time":2806.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2792.64,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You still may want to have.","index":636,"end_time":2808.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2807.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You still may want that to go into your CRM and get assigned to a salesperson to reach out to them.","index":637,"end_time":2813.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2808.98,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So that''s the difference between Supabase.","index":638,"end_time":2816.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2813.86,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Supabases that know they have not qualified yet to go into the CRM.","index":639,"end_time":2820.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2816.02,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"CRM is for whatever the threshold is, whether it''s only forms and responses, that''s fine.","index":640,"end_time":2827.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2821.06,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But some of our customers who are more sales led, the salespeople are like, look, they''ve shown some intent signals and they''re really excited.","index":641,"end_time":2835.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2828.31,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I want to get assigned a task.","index":642,"end_time":2836.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2835.79,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I want to go reach out to that person.","index":643,"end_time":2838.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2836.99,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That''s what we have to work on together.","index":644,"end_time":2840.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2838.79,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We have clients who have only founder led sales, and that founder does not have time to go reach out to those people.","index":645,"end_time":2845.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2840.39,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And they''re like, I''m only talking to somebody who fills out a form.","index":646,"end_time":2848.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2845.99,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We have other clients who have very large sales teams and they''re like, I need a relatively low lead score for me to want to go after people.","index":647,"end_time":2856.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2848.47,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So that is very custom and something we''re going to have to discuss together of what the right fit is for you.","index":648,"end_time":2863.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2856.8,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That adds a lot of clarity.","index":649,"end_time":2866.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2865.6,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":650,"end_time":2867.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2866.8,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":651,"end_time":2869.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2869.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So then getting into what the investment would look like.","index":652,"end_time":2873.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2870.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll show the the points plan again for the three months, but we want to do 100 points per month to get back into points.","index":653,"end_time":2881.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2873.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just so everyone''s clear, one point equals $100.","index":654,"end_time":2884.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2881.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But this would be you guys paying $8,000 per month for 80 points.","index":655,"end_time":2888.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2884.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we will be gifting you 20 points per month as well as the 60 points for this process that we are going through right now.","index":656,"end_time":2894.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2888.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we wanted to put a little skin in the game here.","index":657,"end_time":2898.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2895.98,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Want to do a lot of things.","index":658,"end_time":2899.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2898.38,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"There''s the paid layer, of course.","index":659,"end_time":2902.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2900.38,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That''s what led you to us.","index":660,"end_time":2903.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2902.02,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"There are things that we want to do that is, you know, abm.","index":661,"end_time":2906.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2903.34,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You know that your audiences aren''t going to be living on LinkedIn.","index":662,"end_time":2910.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2907.76,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we''re not really doing anything there.","index":663,"end_time":2911.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2910.4,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But there''s emails we want to send, there are ads that we want to run, and then there''s content that we want to create.","index":664,"end_time":2916.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2911.76,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And Colin''s going to get into that in a moment.","index":665,"end_time":2918.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2916.88,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And, you know, as we try and put a good foot forward here, we want to put a little bit in, you know, in the kitty as well to try and do as much as we possibly can in this first six months.","index":666,"end_time":2929.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2919.12,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And we can see somewhere on there it looks like the exact breakdown of the activities.","index":667,"end_time":2937.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2933.45,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Right?","index":668,"end_time":2937.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2937.49,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Yep.","index":669,"end_time":2938.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2938.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Go.","index":670,"end_time":2938.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2938.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Next slide, Colin.","index":671,"end_time":2939.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2938.73,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":672,"end_time":2940.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2939.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me pull that table up.","index":673,"end_time":2941.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2940.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And just one thing.","index":674,"end_time":2945.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2944.41,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Subject to change points.","index":675,"end_time":2947.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2946.17,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"The beauty of them.","index":676,"end_time":2949.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2948.01,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If you come to me in a month, you''re like, Justin, out of nowhere.","index":677,"end_time":2952.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2949.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We got to go to Dallas again.","index":678,"end_time":2954.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2952.89,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re doing a big presentation.","index":679,"end_time":2955.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2954.13,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We need some stuff for an event.","index":680,"end_time":2956.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2955.53,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Points can move around.","index":681,"end_time":2958.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2957.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So as it stands today, this is what we have envisioned for our 90 days.","index":682,"end_time":2963.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2958.77,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So you''ll see about 110 on average.","index":683,"end_time":2967.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2963.89,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You have that 60 points that''s going to get sprinkled in there as well.","index":684,"end_time":2971.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2967.89,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then we''re gifting 20 points per month.","index":685,"end_time":2974.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2971.17,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And points roll over each month.","index":686,"end_time":2976.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2974.45,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If you don''t use them, you don''t lose them.","index":687,"end_time":2977.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2976.21,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so for February, Colin, you could probably talk about what you want to do over the course of the next three months and we''ll go from there.","index":688,"end_time":2984.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2978.53,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":689,"end_time":2985.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2985.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the, the first month is really us putting together all of the foundations.","index":690,"end_time":2989.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2985.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is writing a lot of documentation so that we''re on the same page.","index":691,"end_time":2991.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2989.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We, we very strongly believe in, do what we say.","index":692,"end_time":2994.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2992,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s one of our core values.","index":693,"end_time":2995.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2994.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So everything we write in documentation is very transparent.","index":694,"end_time":2998.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2995.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is who we''re talking to, this is how we''re talking to them.","index":695,"end_time":3001.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2998.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the journey that we expect them to take and this is when they get handed off to sales.","index":696,"end_time":3005.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3001.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we need those documents to outline how we''re going to take this again from the, the quasi ABM approach, the content plan and the, the series that we want to build for ResQ, the paid media plan, how we would manage all of that, as well as the big one being the performance reporting plan that really pulls all of this together and an understanding so that we are in pure alignment.","index":697,"end_time":3025.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3005.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re gonna send this to us, correct?","index":698,"end_time":3029.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3027.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":699,"end_time":3030.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3029.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"After that we would roll up our sleeves into the actual platform.","index":700,"end_time":3035.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3032.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we would set up paid media, the, the text ads, some graphic ads for retargeting YouTube, for example.","index":701,"end_time":3042.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3035.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we also partner up with Adroll for programmatic display across several different major websites, setting up the actual dynamic email outreach that would accompany the education resources and the paid media plans, and then managing the actual accounts themselves.","index":702,"end_time":3060.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3042.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then in the third month, developing four new web pages, developing sales material.","index":703,"end_time":3066.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3061.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that could be slide decks, one pagers, etc.","index":704,"end_time":3070.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3067.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Developing an episode that would be as part of that content series.","index":705,"end_time":3073.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3070.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we would set you guys up.","index":706,"end_time":3074.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3073.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It would be, you know, maybe a 20, 30 minute conversation.","index":707,"end_time":3077.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3074.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It could be between the three of you, it could be between us and you.","index":708,"end_time":3080.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3077.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s, there''s many different flavors as to how our clients Run a client.","index":709,"end_time":3083.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3080.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You had a prospect, we could have prospects visa, you know, we could have this, this series be part of the outreach that we do during that, the, the outreach campaigns of like, you know, maybe two of them to the outreach emails or for an offer that we have of people to be able to benchmark themselves or something along those lines.","index":710,"end_time":3101.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3083.86,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And maybe one of them is like, hey, we love to tell, you know, founder or owner stories or operator stories.","index":711,"end_time":3107.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3101.65,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And maybe we do that as well.","index":712,"end_time":3108.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3107.53,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So there''s a lot of options there.","index":713,"end_time":3110.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3108.93,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''ll build that out in the content plan.","index":714,"end_time":3112.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3110.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"One other thing I just want to point out, I definitely think that we can have at least one of these channels running in the first month.","index":715,"end_time":3119.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3113.09,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So points can move forward or backwards.","index":716,"end_time":3122.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3120.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So if we want to pull some points forward and you guys are like really on it and you get us feedback on ABM plan, paid plan, etc, very quickly, we can also move very quickly.","index":717,"end_time":3133.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3123.37,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So that''s just, you know, determinant on you.","index":718,"end_time":3135.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3133.53,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And we''re happy to pull some things forward, extend some things out, etc.","index":719,"end_time":3139.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3135.97,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then in month three here, what you see is column.","index":720,"end_time":3141.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3139.25,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You know, some of these might change.","index":721,"end_time":3142.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3141.13,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We may not do four web pages.","index":722,"end_time":3143.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3142.53,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We may decide to do two episodes for a series and a new ad set.","index":723,"end_time":3147.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3143.97,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But I would say the first month and second month, it''s just a matter of where they''re going to be sprinkled, where those, where those line items are going to go, whether they''re more in the first month, more in the second month.","index":724,"end_time":3159.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3148.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It goes exactly as Colin had laid out.","index":725,"end_time":3161.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3159.22,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Either is fine.","index":726,"end_time":3163.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3162.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"On line six there, manage abm.","index":727,"end_time":3167.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3165.42,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"What do you need from us to help you build out account lists?","index":728,"end_time":3172.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3168.14,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"So, I mean, we have our icp so it would be confirmation that the ICP is accurate.","index":729,"end_time":3177.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3173.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That would enable us to go into.","index":730,"end_time":3179.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3177.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One of the tools we use is Clay because we''re able to pull a bunch of different aggregators such as Zoom Info and other tools into that and basically put in their parameters for the companies get that list and then the parameters for the job titles that are best to reach out to.","index":731,"end_time":3192.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3179.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The part of the dynamic email sequence that I referenced is in Clay.","index":732,"end_time":3196.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3192.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re also able to say, okay, well if they''re at this title, they''re going to have this pain point.","index":733,"end_time":3200.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3196.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they''re going to resonate with this email.","index":734,"end_time":3201.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3200.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if they have this title, they''re going to have this pain point resonate with that email.","index":735,"end_time":3204.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3201.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":736,"end_time":3205.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3205.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":737,"end_time":3206.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3206.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"All right, well, there''s a lot in here, gentlemen.","index":738,"end_time":3213.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3209.09,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Colin didn''t even pull up the research you''re welcome to look into it.","index":739,"end_time":3218.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3214.13,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"He did build that out into those nice graphics.","index":740,"end_time":3220.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3218.21,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And we''ll send all this over as soon as we get off the call.","index":741,"end_time":3224.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3221.41,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then I guess, you know, the question for me is, what do next steps look like on your side, and.","index":742,"end_time":3229.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3224.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"What does timeline look like?","index":743,"end_time":3230.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3229.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I want to, you know, make sure that we hit the ground running when you''re ready.","index":744,"end_time":3234.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3230.53,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Well, let''s give us some time to talk, to talk about it and look at it on our side, and then, you know, give us sometime next week.","index":745,"end_time":3243.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3235.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can talk.","index":746,"end_time":3243.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3243.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll tell you Monday and Tuesday, we''re really busy.","index":747,"end_time":3246.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3244.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re doing training sessions on Monday and Tuesday, so maybe Wednesday next week would be good.","index":748,"end_time":3250.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3246.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":749,"end_time":3251,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3250.52,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":750,"end_time":3251.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3251.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I know you guys are sitting there in.","index":751,"end_time":3253.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3251.76,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"In this conference room.","index":752,"end_time":3255.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3253.72,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I''ll send over a time for us to all connect next Wednesday, and if time doesn''t work, just counter with something that does.","index":753,"end_time":3260.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3255.12,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re excited to get this all over to you.","index":754,"end_time":3262.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3260.77,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re excited about where we can go with this, and I hope we can get started soon.","index":755,"end_time":3266.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3262.77,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Thanks for your time.","index":756,"end_time":3269.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3268.37,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Thank you, guys.","index":757,"end_time":3269.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3269.13,"speaker_name":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"text":"Thank you, guys.","index":758,"end_time":3270.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3269.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":759,"end_time":3271.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3270.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Take care.","index":760,"end_time":3271.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3271.13,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"See ya.","index":761,"end_time":3272.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3271.57,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"}],"dateString":"2026-01-28T20:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87013246367?pwd=b9uHJJfMRy1YuIcQOmEtaE9EsPwqQb.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,dan.renyi@marketersindemand.com,justin.brown@marketersindemand.com,gfuntarov@rezku.com,brett.martin@rezku.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","dan.renyi@marketersindemand.com","justin.brown@marketersindemand.com","gfuntarov@rezku.com","brett.martin@rezku.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFEGV9Y8K4NGH1ES550AQXNA","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.95,"bullets":["Outlined data-driven roadmap prioritizing ICP segmentation, trust messaging, and adaptive campaign structure","Compared competitors across SEO, media, and support; RESQ positioned as agile and service‑led","Proposed shifting marketing from lead volume to qualified demo pipeline with shared revenue metrics","Agreed to define marketing-qualified demo criteria and track content engagement pre-conversion","Set goal of 40 qualified demos/month by year’s end using ABM, content strategy, and cross-channel tracking"],"highlights":[{"quote":"Everything we do is based on data, making quick pivots based on that data coming in.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"We want good leads... we want to see what''s converting and go in that direction.","speaker":"Georgi Funtarov"},{"quote":"The whole purpose of this... is to mitigate finger pointing and get rid of that.","speaker":"Justin Brown"}],"topics":["lead_quality","alignment","strategy","ABM","competitive_analysis"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-0613","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-29T16:03:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Target Audience and ICP Definition**\n\nThe team agreed on three core **Ideal Customer Profiles (ICPs)** to sharpen messaging and sales focus, aiming to improve conversion by addressing distinct pain points and behaviors (04:52).\n\n- **Multi-location operators with 2 to 9 locations** are primarily problem-driven, outgrowing existing systems and lacking reliable support, making messaging around **reliability, visibility, and scalability** crucial to prevent technology struggles as they grow.\n    - These customers often use legacy or competitor systems like **Toast** but face operational issues across locations, increasing churn risk.\n    - Messaging must assure seamless support and tech reliability to reduce friction in scaling.\n- **Single-location owners** are more skeptical and defensive, requiring messaging focused on **building trust through transparent pricing and clear onboarding**, addressing fears of hidden fees and system failures.\n    - Education is key here, showing real scenarios like system failures during peak hours and responsive support availability.\n- **Fast-growing QSR chains** demand **speed, accuracy, and operational efficiency**, searching specifically for POS solutions that handle high transaction volumes with delivery integration.\n    - Messaging should be direct, feature-focused, and demonstrate operational strengths rather than emotional appeals.\n- Georgi emphasized segmenting prospects into **three main pathways** to streamline marketing and sales alignment, avoiding over-segmentation while increasing relevance at every touchpoint (13:05).\n\n## **Brand Positioning and Competitive Landscape**\n\nResQ’s core competitive edge lies in **service differentiation**, especially **24/7 U.S.-based support with first call resolution**, positioning it as a reliable partner compared to competitors (22:01).\n\n- **Toast** dominates brand awareness, SEO, and paid media but suffers declining service quality due to rapid scaling, shifting from white-glove support to a ticketing model, causing deal losses.\n    - The strategy is not to outspend Toast but to target their dissatisfied customers and demonstrate superior support.\n- **Lightspeed** focuses more on retail than restaurants, with a broad but diluted paid keyword strategy, making them less relevant for ResQ’s core audience.\n- **Skytab** is a closer peer, leaning heavily on education and training, supporting the team''s plan to emphasize pre-sale education and content marketing.\n- Paul’s insight was adopted: focus the market around two clear choices—Toast or ResQ—simplifying decision-making and reducing confusion caused by many legacy competitors (16:37).\n- The team plans to create messaging highlighting the **cost of delayed decisions** in the restaurant market to push faster action, especially given rising operational pressures like minimum wage increases (18:58).\n\n## **Marketing and Lead Generation Strategy**\n\nThe agreed marketing goal is to increase **qualified inbound demo bookings** to scale sales pipeline efficiently, with phased targets set at **20 qualified demos per month in 90 days, scaling to 30, then 40 by year-end** (26:01).\n\n- Google Ads historically cost around **$400 per lead**, but quality is inconsistent, so multi-channel approaches will be combined with improved messaging and landing pages to lower costs and raise lead quality.\n- The team plans **four dedicated landing pages focused on high-intent campaigns** to improve conversion from clicks to demos while monitoring cost per lead continuously.\n- Retargeting will be used across platforms including **YouTube and programmatic display via Adroll**, supported by dynamic email nurture sequences to keep prospects engaged post-initial contact (40:35).\n- The marketing funnel will incorporate multiple call-to-actions (CTAs) reflecting different buyer readiness levels, recognizing some prospects need education before committing to demos.\n- Data integration and tracking will leverage tools like **RBDB, Factors AI, N8N workflows, and Supabase** to de-anonymize website visitors and track engagement, improving lead scoring and targeting.\n- Georgi and Tristan emphasized the importance of combining **account-based marketing (ABM)** and lead generation tactics, with clear ICP confirmation and account list building using tools like **Clay and Zoom Info** (52:45).\n- The team acknowledged privacy constraints limit full visitor identification but expects to resolve **40-60% of web traffic** for targeting purposes, using IP resolution and cookie data compliant with GDPR for U.S. customers.\n\n## **Sales and Marketing Alignment on Lead Quality**\n\nAlignment on the definition of a **qualified lead and demo** is critical to avoid finger-pointing between sales and marketing and drive revenue responsibility across teams (36:37).\n\n- Georgi proposed tying marketing efforts directly to **revenue metrics**, weighting lead sources by conversion rates (e.g., white paper leads converting at 40% vs. ad leads at 10%) to assign fair revenue quotas to marketing.\n- Justin and Tristan highlighted that marketing’s accountability ends at delivering **sales-qualified leads (SQLs)**, with sales responsible for closing, but collaboration is needed to refine qualification criteria.\n- The group agreed that **pre-demo educational content consumption** (measured via video views or downloads) correlates with shorter sales cycles and higher close rates, supporting investments in content marketing.\n- Lead scoring frameworks will assign points based on engagement (e.g., form fills, content consumption), with thresholds determining CRM handoffs and sales outreach priority.\n- Justin explained flexibility is needed based on sales team size and capacity, with some clients preferring only demos from explicit form fills, others wanting lower-threshold leads assigned for outreach (47:36).\n- A formal **performance reporting plan** will document lead quality metrics and alignment on accepted ratios (e.g., 80% qualified vs. 20% disqualified leads), ensuring transparency and continuous improvement (38:09).\n\n## **90-Day Roadmap and Investment Plan**\n\nThe initial 90-day plan centers on **building a scalable paid media and conversion foundation** with clear deliverables and flexible resource allocation (39:39).\n\n- Month 1 focuses on foundational work: rewriting messaging, creating new landing pages, developing the paid media plan, and building the content series framework.\n- Month 2 emphasizes campaign setup: launching Google Ads with intent filtering, activating retargeting on multiple platforms, and starting dynamic email outreach.\n- Month 3 includes developing **4 new web pages, sales enablement materials (e.g., decks, one-pagers), and producing content episodes** for syndication in marketing and sales outreach.\n- The plan operates on a **points system**, equating 1 point to **$100**, with a monthly budget of **80 points ($8,000)** plus **20 gifted points**, allowing flexibility to shift resources month-to-month and roll over unused points.\n- Justin encouraged quick feedback and collaboration to pull activities forward for faster impact, highlighting that some channels could start running within the first month.\n- Account list building for ABM relies on confirmed ICP parameters and job titles, enabling targeted email sequences tailored to specific pain points per role (52:45).\n- The team agreed to review the detailed research and roadmap, targeting a follow-up meeting next **Wednesday for final alignment and potential project kickoff** (54:10).","outline":null,"keywords":["Posing System","Target Audience","Marketing Strategy","Lead Qualification","Competitive Analysis","ABM"],"overview":"- **Ideal Customer Profiles:** Three ICPs defined: multi-location operators, single-location owners, and fast-growing QSR chains to enhance messaging.\n\n- **Competitive Positioning:** ResQ offers 24/7 U.S. support, aiming to attract Toast''s dissatisfied customers by highlighting superior service.\n\n- **Marketing Goal:** Aim for **20 qualified demos/month in 90 days**, increasing targets to **30, then 40 by year-end**.\n\n- **Lead Generation Strategy:** Use multi-channel marketing and dedicated landing pages to improve lead quality and lower costs.\n\n- **Sales-Marketing Alignment:** Define qualified leads clearly, tying marketing efforts to revenue metrics for better accountability and collaboration.\n\n- **90-Day Plan:** Month 1 focuses on foundational work; Month 2 on campaign setup; Month 3 on content production and sales enablement materials.","action_items":"\n**Georgi Funtarov**\nReview and confirm the accuracy of the ICP to enable account list building for ABM campaigns (52:40)\nProvide feedback on the ABM and paid media plans promptly to allow for acceleration of initial marketing activities (49:30)\nCoordinate internally to assess the proposed roadmap and respond with next steps by early next week (54:05)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare the detailed 90+ page research document and slide deck post-meeting with the ResQ team (03:00)\nBuild foundational documentation outlining customer journeys, messaging strategies, and handoff processes for sales and marketing alignment in month one (49:45)\nSet up paid media campaigns including Google Ads, retargeting, YouTube ads, and programmatic display with Adroll (50:30)\nDevelop four new landing pages tailored to high-intent campaigns to improve demo conversion rates within the first 90 days (50:45)\nCreate sales enablement materials such as slide decks and one-pagers aligned with refreshed messaging (50:55)\nCoordinate production of content series episodes to amplify educational marketing efforts (51:00)\nDesign and implement performance reporting document to track and align all activities and results for full transparency (38:20)\n\n**Justin Brown**\nSend over meeting materials and timeline for next steps and follow-up meeting scheduling (54:10)\nFacilitate scheduling a next meeting for Wednesday, ensuring timing works for all participants to discuss progress and launch (54:10)\n\n**All Participants**\nAlign on the exact definition and qualification criteria for demo leads to ensure marketing and sales agreement and minimize finger-pointing (36:30)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"1b3ce047-ca9a-4fc8-aac5-1dde1cb47eda","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
