INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Aligned Growth Engine | Roadmap Presentation',
  '## **Target Audience and ICP Definition**

The team agreed on three core **Ideal Customer Profiles (ICPs)** to sharpen messaging and sales focus, aiming to improve conversion by addressing distinct pain points and behaviors (04:52).

- **Multi-location operators with 2 to 9 locations** are primarily problem-driven, outgrowing existing systems and lacking reliable support, making messaging around **reliability, visibility, and scalability** crucial to prevent technology struggles as they grow.
    - These customers often use legacy or competitor systems like **Toast** but face operational issues across locations, increasing churn risk.
    - Messaging must assure seamless support and tech reliability to reduce friction in scaling.
- **Single-location owners** are more skeptical and defensive, requiring messaging focused on **building trust through transparent pricing and clear onboarding**, addressing fears of hidden fees and system failures.
    - Education is key here, showing real scenarios like system failures during peak hours and responsive support availability.
- **Fast-growing QSR chains** demand **speed, accuracy, and operational efficiency**, searching specifically for POS solutions that handle high transaction volumes with delivery integration.
    - Messaging should be direct, feature-focused, and demonstrate operational strengths rather than emotional appeals.
- Georgi emphasized segmenting prospects into **three main pathways** to streamline marketing and sales alignment, avoiding over-segmentation while increasing relevance at every touchpoint (13:05).

## **Brand Positioning and Competitive Landscape**

ResQ’s core competitive edge lies in **service differentiation**, especially **24/7 U.S.-based support with first call resolution**, positioning it as a reliable partner compared to competitors (22:01).

- **Toast** dominates brand awareness, SEO, and paid media but suffers declining service quality due to rapid scaling, shifting from white-glove support to a ticketing model, causing deal losses.
    - The strategy is not to outspend Toast but to target their dissatisfied customers and demonstrate superior support.
- **Lightspeed** focuses more on retail than restaurants, with a broad but diluted paid keyword strategy, making them less relevant for ResQ’s core audience.
- **Skytab** is a closer peer, leaning heavily on education and training, supporting the team''s plan to emphasize pre-sale education and content marketing.
- Paul’s insight was adopted: focus the market around two clear choices—Toast or ResQ—simplifying decision-making and reducing confusion caused by many legacy competitors (16:37).
- The team plans to create messaging highlighting the **cost of delayed decisions** in the restaurant market to push faster action, especially given rising operational pressures like minimum wage increases (18:58).

## **Marketing and Lead Generation Strategy**

The agreed marketing goal is to increase **qualified inbound demo bookings** to scale sales pipeline efficiently, with phased targets set at **20 qualified demos per month in 90 days, scaling to 30, then 40 by year-end** (26:01).

- Google Ads historically cost around **$400 per lead**, but quality is inconsistent, so multi-channel approaches will be combined with improved messaging and landing pages to lower costs and raise lead quality.
- The team plans **four dedicated landing pages focused on high-intent campaigns** to improve conversion from clicks to demos while monitoring cost per lead continuously.
- Retargeting will be used across platforms including **YouTube and programmatic display via Adroll**, supported by dynamic email nurture sequences to keep prospects engaged post-initial contact (40:35).
- The marketing funnel will incorporate multiple call-to-actions (CTAs) reflecting different buyer readiness levels, recognizing some prospects need education before committing to demos.
- Data integration and tracking will leverage tools like **RBDB, Factors AI, N8N workflows, and Supabase** to de-anonymize website visitors and track engagement, improving lead scoring and targeting.
- Georgi and Tristan emphasized the importance of combining **account-based marketing (ABM)** and lead generation tactics, with clear ICP confirmation and account list building using tools like **Clay and Zoom Info** (52:45).
- The team acknowledged privacy constraints limit full visitor identification but expects to resolve **40-60% of web traffic** for targeting purposes, using IP resolution and cookie data compliant with GDPR for U.S. customers.

## **Sales and Marketing Alignment on Lead Quality**

Alignment on the definition of a **qualified lead and demo** is critical to avoid finger-pointing between sales and marketing and drive revenue responsibility across teams (36:37).

- Georgi proposed tying marketing efforts directly to **revenue metrics**, weighting lead sources by conversion rates (e.g., white paper leads converting at 40% vs. ad leads at 10%) to assign fair revenue quotas to marketing.
- Justin and Tristan highlighted that marketing’s accountability ends at delivering **sales-qualified leads (SQLs)**, with sales responsible for closing, but collaboration is needed to refine qualification criteria.
- The group agreed that **pre-demo educational content consumption** (measured via video views or downloads) correlates with shorter sales cycles and higher close rates, supporting investments in content marketing.
- Lead scoring frameworks will assign points based on engagement (e.g., form fills, content consumption), with thresholds determining CRM handoffs and sales outreach priority.
- Justin explained flexibility is needed based on sales team size and capacity, with some clients preferring only demos from explicit form fills, others wanting lower-threshold leads assigned for outreach (47:36).
- A formal **performance reporting plan** will document lead quality metrics and alignment on accepted ratios (e.g., 80% qualified vs. 20% disqualified leads), ensuring transparency and continuous improvement (38:09).

## **90-Day Roadmap and Investment Plan**

The initial 90-day plan centers on **building a scalable paid media and conversion foundation** with clear deliverables and flexible resource allocation (39:39).

- Month 1 focuses on foundational work: rewriting messaging, creating new landing pages, developing the paid media plan, and building the content series framework.
- Month 2 emphasizes campaign setup: launching Google Ads with intent filtering, activating retargeting on multiple platforms, and starting dynamic email outreach.
- Month 3 includes developing **4 new web pages, sales enablement materials (e.g., decks, one-pagers), and producing content episodes** for syndication in marketing and sales outreach.
- The plan operates on a **points system**, equating 1 point to **$100**, with a monthly budget of **80 points ($8,000)** plus **20 gifted points**, allowing flexibility to shift resources month-to-month and roll over unused points.
- Justin encouraged quick feedback and collaboration to pull activities forward for faster impact, highlighting that some channels could start running within the first month.
- Account list building for ABM relies on confirmed ICP parameters and job titles, enabling targeted email sequences tailored to specific pain points per role (52:45).
- The team agreed to review the detailed research and roadmap, targeting a follow-up meeting next **Wednesday for final alignment and potential project kickoff** (54:10).',
  '2026-01-28 20:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Review and confirm the accuracy of the ICP to enable account list building for ABM campaigns (52:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide feedback on the ABM and paid media plans promptly to allow for acceleration of initial marketing activities (49:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate internally to assess the proposed roadmap and respond with next steps by early next week (54:05)","completed":false},{"text":"Share the detailed 90+ page research document and slide deck post-meeting with the ResQ team (03:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Build foundational documentation outlining customer journeys, messaging strategies, and handoff processes for sales and marketing alignment in month one (49:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Set up paid media campaigns including Google Ads, retargeting, YouTube ads, and programmatic display with Adroll (50:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Develop four new landing pages tailored to high-intent campaigns to improve demo conversion rates within the first 90 days (50:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Create sales enablement materials such as slide decks and one-pagers aligned with refreshed messaging (50:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate production of content series episodes to amplify educational marketing efforts (51:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Design and implement performance reporting document to track and align all activities and results for full transparency (38:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Send over meeting materials and timeline for next steps and follow-up meeting scheduling (54:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Facilitate scheduling a next meeting for Wednesday, ensuring timing works for all participants to discuss progress and launch (54:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Align on the exact definition and qualification criteria for demo leads to ensure marketing and sales agreement and minimize finger-pointing (36:30)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
