-- Meeting: iCorps + New North Weekly (2026-01-28 15:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '965b21f3-8748-420c-aaf3-b3fdcaa2f504',
    '2026-01-28 15:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KFXJRG9YW8BD9PDJWR55NEZ6',
    'iCorps + New North Weekly',
    '{"Nathalie Mintjens","Samuel Bagnall","Ruby Pontbriand","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    1658,
    'https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_NWVjNDBkODktN2I3OS00ZWQ0LTgzMDEtMWNkNDk5OGVlYjQ2@thread.v2/0?context={"Tid":"0188564a-93de-489c-bf54-1927d4a9ed28","Oid":"bdae9fd3-d481-4c5e-aeea-7272e37b7d07"}',
    '{"id":"01KFXJRG9YW8BD9PDJWR55NEZ6","title":"iCorps + New North Weekly","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Performance and ROI**\n\nThe team agreed that **content and SEO were the main drivers** of customer conversion and ROI in 2024, with paid media showing limited direct customer impact (03:18).\n\n- **Ruby Pontbriand** shared that despite generating many **MQLs and SQLs**, the paid campaigns only produced **two SQLs** that converted, which has caused concern about the ROI from paid efforts.\n    - The focus for leadership, particularly **Cook**, is on customer conversions, not just leads.\n    - Ruby is working on refining historical totals for **MQLs, SQLs, and customers** across **2023, 2024, and 2025**, including spend data to better align reporting with decision-maker expectations.\n    - Challenges in HubSpot reporting stem from lifecycle stages moving over time, making year-based attribution difficult.\n    - The team plans to tweak dashboards for clearer visibility on **conversion rates** and marketing source breakdowns.\n\n- **Nathalie Mintjens** and Ruby discussed shifting budget focus from paid to SEO, citing SEO''s history of success dating back to 2022.\n    - The website’s content and SEO efforts consistently show higher conversion to customers compared to paid media.\n    - They proposed scaling back paid campaigns and reallocating resources toward producing and optimizing SEO blog posts monthly.\n    - This shift aligns with long-term lead quality and customer acquisition, balancing immediate MQL generation with sustainable growth.\n\n- Ruby emphasized the team''s success in generating **MQLs and SQLs**, despite not meeting aggressive monthly goals fully.\n    - She highlighted that marketing controls lead quality but not the sales qualification or final customer conversion.\n    - This disconnect contributes to tension around accountability for conversion metrics beyond marketing''s influence.\n\n- **Colin Costigan** reinforced that poor customer conversion after SQL stage points to sales process issues, not marketing.\n    - He suggested exploring improvements in sales conversations and qualification criteria.\n    - Collaboration with SDRs or augmenting sales resources may be needed to close the gap.\n    - Recognized long sales cycles and existing contracts with competitors complicate immediate conversions.\n\n## **Sales and Lead Qualification Process**\n\nThe conversation pinpointed a need to better align marketing and sales on lead qualification and conversion metrics (13:24).\n\n- **Ruby** noted some leads moved backward in lifecycle stages from SQL to MQL due to sales reconsidering qualification, which skews reporting accuracy.\n    - She found about **five or six** such cases in 2025.\n    - This rollback conflicts with best practice and may distort pipeline metrics.\n\n- **Colin** advised that it’s poor practice to move leads backward through lifecycle stages.\n    - Instead, changes in qualification criteria should be noted separately without altering historical data.\n    - This preserves metric integrity and avoids confusion over numbers.\n    - He recalled prior work showing **5-10% conversion rates** from SQL to customer, emphasizing the challenge.\n\n- The team agreed to rely on the **lead detail property** in HubSpot to track reasons for leads not advancing rather than moving them back.\n    - This approach will improve clarity on why deals stall.\n    - They plan to analyze common deal loss reasons to create sales support materials like **one-pagers or custom slide decks** to help push hesitant prospects.\n\n- Collaboration between marketing and sales will be key to improving pipeline flow.\n    - Nathalie and Colin committed to reviewing data for trends that could inform these sales aids and process improvements.\n\n## **Reporting and Dashboard Enhancements**\n\nReporting clarity and data accuracy were focal points to better measure performance and ROI (03:20).\n\n- Ruby praised the **existing dashboards** for marketing tracking but requested tweaks to better capture historical totals and spend.\n    - She is working on **historical MQL, SQL, and customer numbers for 2023-2025**.\n    - Nathalie will pull **monthly actual paid media spends** for 2025, including details on budget reallocations between platforms like Reddit and LinkedIn.\n    - Dashboards were updated to show only **MQLs from marketing sources** and to use **custom lead sources** for more granular tracking.\n\n- The team noted some discrepancies in lifecycle stage reporting due to timing of stage changes.\n    - Colin offered to help refine HubSpot report logic to improve accuracy.\n    - Ruby is balancing budget tracking alongside performance metrics to better correlate spend with results.\n\n- Nathalie shared updates on website and SEO performance dashboards.\n    - They track rankings of key pages, e.g., a **New York page now ranking fourth**, and a Microsoft Azure video page at **seventh place**.\n    - The executive dashboard was refined to focus on **SQLs and opportunities from marketing sources** and includes detailed lead reasons.\n\n- A plan was set to run a **year-over-year website performance analysis** comparing three months after launch with the prior year.\n    - This will highlight gains in visits, engagement, and conversions to demonstrate content and SEO impact.\n    - Ruby welcomed this to build a stronger case for marketing’s ROI.\n\n## **SEO and Content Strategy for 2025**\n\nThe team plans to double down on SEO and content as proven long-term growth drivers while scaling back paid media (10:00).\n\n- Ruby proposed focusing heavily on SEO for 2025 based on consistent historical success.\n    - SEO and content combined drove most customer conversions over the past three years.\n    - The team recognizes the need to fine-tune SEO efforts, particularly keyword targeting informed by recent research and Loom explanations provided by Nathalie.\n\n- Nathalie agreed that SEO should receive more budget and points allocation, reducing spending on ABM and paid.\n    - This shift reflects the data showing that ABM brought short-term MQL growth but less customer conversion.\n    - They suggested publishing a few new blog posts monthly and optimizing existing content to keep SEO momentum.\n\n- Ruby wants to create a clear **SEO strategy pitch or plan** to present this shift to stakeholders.\n    - The goal is to align marketing efforts with proven ROI drivers and justify resource changes.\n    - The team agreed this is a priority for early 2025 planning.\n\n## **Website and Content Updates**\n\nWebsite content and SEO pages are actively improving rankings and user engagement, supporting marketing goals (18:30).\n\n- Nathalie shared progress on content updates with Jeff reviewing the **assessment pages** linking AI readiness and Copilot assessments.\n    - The **New York page recently published is ranking fourth** in search results.\n    - The **Microsoft Azure pros and cons video page** climbed to **seventh place**.\n    - A new blog post on **outsourcing IT departments** reached **eighth place**.\n\n- The team is updating the executive dashboard to reflect these marketing source improvements.\n    - This dashboard will also track conversion rates from MQL to SQL and include detailed lead reasons.\n\n- Nathalie committed to delivering an updated **Microsoft Copilot Consulting page** by the end of the day.\n    - This update ties into strengthening content related to AI offerings.\n\n- Ruby expressed interest in tying website redesign and content efforts directly to marketing ROI.\n    - They plan to run comparative reports to quantify improvements in traffic, engagement, and conversions since the redesign launch.\n\n## **Collaboration and Next Steps**\n\nClear coordination between marketing, sales, and analytics is key to improving conversion rates and demonstrating ROI (15:00).\n\n- The team will analyze deal loss reasons in HubSpot to identify where sales support tools could help move prospects forward.\n    - Colin suggested creating tailored sales materials based on common objections or deal stalling points.\n\n- Ruby and Nathalie will continue refining reports and dashboards for clearer visibility on marketing contribution.\n    - Nathalie will provide monthly spend data and support SEO performance analysis.\n\n- Jeff’s feedback on AI landing pages is expected later this week or early next week, allowing the team to finalize related content.\n\n- The group acknowledged challenges in measuring marketing success beyond lead generation, emphasizing the need for shared accountability with sales.\n\n- Ruby will continue building the case for SEO and content investments, focusing on proven long-term gains rather than paid media shortfalls.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot reporting","paid media ROI","SEO strategy","MQL to SQL conversion","sales enablement","website performance"],"overview":"- **Marketing Focus Shift:** Team agrees to prioritize content and SEO over paid media for better customer conversion rates in 2024.\n\n- **Paid Media Concerns:** Paid campaigns produced only two SQLs; ROI concerns lead to reallocating budget towards SEO strategies and blog content.\n\n- **Sales Process Improvement:** Poor conversion post-SQL indicates sales process issues, requiring collaboration between marketing and sales to enhance lead qualification.\n\n- **Reporting Enhancements Needed:** Dashboard tweaks are necessary for clearer historical performance metrics and tracking of MQLs, SQLs, and customer conversions.\n\n- **SEO and Content Strategy:** Plans to double down on SEO efforts for 2025, reflecting historical success in driving customer conversions and engagement.\n\n- **Collaboration Agreement:** Ongoing analysis of deal loss reasons and tailored sales materials will improve conversion rates, emphasizing shared accountability for results.","action_items":"\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nContinue refining paid media ROI reporting by compiling MQL, SQL, and client numbers with historical spend data for 2023-2025 (05:30)\nProvide more detailed data inputs to integrate reallocation of paid media budget by month between platforms (07:20)\nInvestigate why certain MQLs revert to earlier lifecycle stages and communicate insights for data accuracy (25:50)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nPull receipts and actual paid media spending for each month in 2025 and note month(s) of budget reallocations (08:10)\nDeliver updated Microsoft Copilot Consulting page today (21:35)\nPrepare website performance analysis reports comparing one year post-launch metrics versus pre-launch (22:45)\nCreate reports showing MQLs from marketing sources with reasons for non-conversion to identify marketing vs. sales issues (23:50)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nTroubleshoot HubSpot reporting to improve accuracy of MQL, SQL, opportunity, and customer attribution by lifecycle dates (06:40)\nExplore and define tools like sales decks or one-pagers to aid sales teams in advancing SQLs and opportunities (15:30)\nAssist in analyzing lead detail and closed reason data to identify common sales pipeline challenges contributing to low customer conversions (16:15)\n\n**Samuel Bagnall**\nMonitor Jeff’s feedback on AI landing page updates and communicate expected delivery timeline (20:20)\n"},"duration":27.6299991607666,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":1,"name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"id":2,"name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello.","index":0,"end_time":8.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hey, natalie.","index":1,"end_time":10,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":9.2,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":10.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Good.","index":3,"end_time":11.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How are you?","index":4,"end_time":12.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Good.","index":5,"end_time":13.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.2,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Can you see?","index":6,"end_time":20.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.68,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Is your teens okay?","index":7,"end_time":22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.64,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Like, is it acting normal?","index":8,"end_time":23.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":22.48,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"My teens?","index":9,"end_time":25.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":24.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":10,"end_time":26.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":26.28,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, I think so.","index":11,"end_time":28.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":12,"end_time":28.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.36,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So mine is.","index":13,"end_time":29.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.84,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I see everybody''s, like, where their picture should be, like, where their image should be, but it''s just gray.","index":14,"end_time":36.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":30.36,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"And I did this yesterday.","index":15,"end_time":39.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.04,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"You can''t see us?","index":16,"end_time":41.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"No, I can''t see myself either.","index":17,"end_time":43.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":41.959,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"It''s so weird.","index":18,"end_time":44.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":43.28,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"But whatever, it''s fine.","index":19,"end_time":46.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.2,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Well, I can see you.","index":20,"end_time":49.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.8,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":21,"end_time":49.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":49.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"If you want to try hanging up.","index":22,"end_time":51.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":49.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Starting again, maybe I''ll try restarting teams or something.","index":23,"end_time":56.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":52.81,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I mean, I thought.","index":24,"end_time":57.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.65,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Let me do that, and I''ll come.","index":25,"end_time":59.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.49,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Back in a second.","index":26,"end_time":60.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":27,"end_time":61.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":60.49,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"All right.","index":28,"end_time":61.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hey.","index":29,"end_time":79.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":79.22,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Hey, Ruby.","index":30,"end_time":81.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":80.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":31,"end_time":82.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":81.38,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Good.","index":32,"end_time":83.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How are you?","index":33,"end_time":84.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":34,"end_time":85.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":84.82,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Sam''s joining back because his team''s just having issues.","index":35,"end_time":90.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":87.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, no worries.","index":36,"end_time":90.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":90.18,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It happens.","index":37,"end_time":92.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":91.86,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That it does.","index":38,"end_time":96.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":95.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How did the presentation go last week, Ruby?","index":39,"end_time":102.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":100.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It went okay, but I need.","index":40,"end_time":108.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":103.62,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I still have to.","index":41,"end_time":110.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":108.96,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They wanted some other numbers, so I working on a re.","index":42,"end_time":114.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":110.8,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like, revising some of the stuff so I can get them what they were looking for.","index":43,"end_time":118.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":114.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I also.","index":44,"end_time":121.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":119.68,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I mean, Chris isn''t totally happy about the numbers for the leads and for.","index":45,"end_time":132.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":124,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Well, he''s mostly just not happy that we didn''t get any customers out of.","index":46,"end_time":135.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":132.72,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Out of the paid efforts that we did.","index":47,"end_time":141.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":139.11,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And so that conversion rate is really what he''s looking at for our ROI for the paid piece.","index":48,"end_time":151.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":143.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then I explained, you know, we did get a lot of MQLs and we did get SQLs and opportunities from paid, but there was only two.","index":49,"end_time":163.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":153.35,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think that made it to, like, SQL or opportunity.","index":50,"end_time":167.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":163.6,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So that''s really, like, what they count as, I think.","index":51,"end_time":172.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":168.16,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"What.","index":52,"end_time":173.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":173.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"What Cook counts as, like, a success, I guess.","index":53,"end_time":176.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":173.6,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So just kind of.","index":54,"end_time":179.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":178.72,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They want it.","index":55,"end_time":180.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":180.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They want me to go back through, and they just want, like, what do they want?","index":56,"end_time":186.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":180.96,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And the reporting that you guys did for us is awesome.","index":57,"end_time":188.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":186.28,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I did show it to them briefly, and I think it''s really good data.","index":58,"end_time":195.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":189.73,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Is that the dashboard?","index":59,"end_time":199.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":198.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":60,"end_time":200.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":200.37,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So the dashboards, I think, are good going forward.","index":61,"end_time":203.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":201.25,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think we just might need to, like, tweak them a little bit to be a little more.","index":62,"end_time":208.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":204.13,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Well, I know we had talked about tweaking it last week, so I think those tweaks are good.","index":63,"end_time":218.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":214.78,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then we''ll just kind of, like, monitor and see how it goes.","index":64,"end_time":222.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":218.86,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But I think that kind of thing is good for, like, me and Mike and Jeff when we meet.","index":65,"end_time":225.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":222.26,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then Cook is definitely just focusing on, like, the return.","index":66,"end_time":230.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":226.78,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So, like, that''s, like, the part where we have, like, how Much we''ve paid for paid media, like media spend and all that stuff is good but also like for him it''s like oh my God, we, we''re spending, we spent, you know this and we''re not getting X, Y and Z.","index":67,"end_time":246.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":231.9,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So that is that.","index":68,"end_time":250.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":246.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then I just need to do they want the number ofmqls number SQLs and sorry, let''s go.","index":69,"end_time":262.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":250.95,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Oh, here it is.","index":70,"end_time":266.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":265.39,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So they want 20, they want historical totals so I need to pull 23, 24 and like redo 25 and they also want like spend for those years which we didn''t do paid in 23 but we did in 24 and 25.","index":71,"end_time":282.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":266.19,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then they don''t really care about opportunities but they just want MQLs, SQLs and clients.","index":72,"end_time":290.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":282.55,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I, I''ve started doing those in HubSpot and I have a start at the numbers.","index":73,"end_time":298.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":293.11,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Um, it''s.","index":74,"end_time":300.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":298.54,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''m just running into issues because.","index":75,"end_time":301.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":300.5,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like if I look at 2024 and I look and I try to run a report of like show me everybody who has ever had the life cycle stage MQL and the create date was between was, you know, in the year 2024 and the source was just our sources and the like status has never been unqualified.","index":76,"end_time":332.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.94,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Then I get a number that''s cool.","index":77,"end_time":337.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":333.08,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But then if I do the same thing for SQL and opportunity and customer, if I do that like has ever been thing I don''t think it''s accurate because for the, at least for the historical ones like for 24 and 23, if they were like a contact that was created in that year and their stage has ever been something, it means that they have actually moved through but I don''t know when exactly they moved through.","index":78,"end_time":368.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":337.88,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":79,"end_time":368.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":368.22,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So that total number of like SQLs or, or clients, I don''t feel like it''s accurate for that year because for I know for sure that there''s a lot of them that didn''t make it to customer until after the close of the year.","index":80,"end_time":385.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":368.7,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":81,"end_time":385.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So like they were still in opportunity or they''re still stuck in SQL or we hadn''t quite moved them through yet.","index":82,"end_time":389.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":385.91,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I don''t know if it''s better for those ones if I do like I have to do specific dates of date entered SQL is this date exited is this or like what you guys would recommend.","index":83,"end_time":402.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":389.95,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Colin, any idea?","index":84,"end_time":406.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, to be honest Ruby, I''d just have to hop into HubSpot and play around with the report and how it''s pulling everything because I mean theoretically your approach should work.","index":85,"end_time":417.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":407.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll just play around and sometimes that create date does throw just some issues because again, you just said like customers maybe closed after the beginning of the new year or maybe they were in MQL two years ago and then they saw a bunch of stuff and moved to an SQL just this past year.","index":86,"end_time":434.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":419.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s a couple of different variables that I just need to put play around with in there.","index":87,"end_time":438.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":434.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":88,"end_time":439.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":438.56,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":89,"end_time":440.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, and then I was also for, for paid media.","index":90,"end_time":445.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.4,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''m just like balancing the budget for last year and I know we had budgeted like a certain amount for each, each like month.","index":91,"end_time":455,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":446.8,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then we had changed stuff a little bit towards the end because like Reddit wasn''t doing well.","index":92,"end_time":458.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":455,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then we reallocated some stuff to LinkedIn, blah, blah, blah.","index":93,"end_time":460.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":458.36,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I just need, and maybe we already have this somewhere, but I need the actual, like the actual spend per month for the, for each month of the year.","index":94,"end_time":474.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":461.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"For 2025 at one point I know we did have like a folder that you would put stuff in for like paid media receipts when I needed to submit them for co op reimbursement, but I don''t think we really did that this year.","index":95,"end_time":487.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":474.23,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think that was more of like a last year thing.","index":96,"end_time":489.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":487.47,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, we can pull together the receipts for.","index":97,"end_time":493.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So for each month.","index":98,"end_time":494.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":493.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Last year, you mean?","index":99,"end_time":495.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":100,"end_time":496.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":496.4,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":101,"end_time":498.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":497.44,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, total spend for each month.","index":102,"end_time":500.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":498.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Just so I can pop that into my budget for the actuals.","index":103,"end_time":504,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":500.16,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then if you''re able to just put in like what, whatever month it was that we switched from, whatever, whatever month it was that we switched from, like there''s going to be this like 3,000 for this and then we''re going to just make 5,000 for this.","index":104,"end_time":523.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":507.52,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, okay, I can pull that because I know we, yeah, we moved some stuff over to Reddit and then we moved away from it and away from AdRoll too.","index":105,"end_time":534.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":525.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I''ll look back on our records when we did that.","index":106,"end_time":537.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":535.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":107,"end_time":538.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":537.85,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But overall, the key takeaway was content and SEO were major drivers of ROI for the year.","index":108,"end_time":545.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":539.45,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Looking at who actually converted from MQL all the way to customer, the primary was content followed by SEO, which tells us that or tells me that the website is content.","index":109,"end_time":559.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":547.19,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":110,"end_time":559.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":559.51,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So that''s like direct traffic and you know, our website itself.","index":111,"end_time":565.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":559.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then SEO is the efforts that we''re doing for the keyword research and they, you know, they get there from, you know, bang or Google or chat, GBT and things like that.","index":112,"end_time":572.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":565.19,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So, um, that is a takeaway and they''re looking for.","index":113,"end_time":577.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":572.87,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I''m kind of putting some thoughts Together around this, based on the keyword research that you provided for last week and the loom, which is awesome.","index":114,"end_time":585.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":578.77,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you for doing that.","index":115,"end_time":586.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":585.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They kind of just want to see like an idea of an SEO strategy, kind of like plan or pitch or something for the year.","index":116,"end_time":596.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":587.65,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because we, at this time last year we were, from what I remember, like really wanting to dive into SEO pretty heavily and.","index":117,"end_time":605.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":596.85,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And we did.","index":118,"end_time":607.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.65,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"You know, we''ve definitely done those efforts for SEO and so but I think we, because we were also doing the ABM and the paid and you know, because of the way that everything gets allocated with timing and points and all that stuff, like we.","index":119,"end_time":624.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.37,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We still continue to keep the SEO engine running, but obviously we had to split the focus right across ABM and any other.","index":120,"end_time":630.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":624.05,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I was thinking that maybe for this coming this year we could really just like dig our heels into SEO because we have seen success with it in the past.","index":121,"end_time":640.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":631.06,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And when I say the past, I mean like when I do this historical stuff for like 22 and 23, SEO was, you know, definitely like a driver back then as well.","index":122,"end_time":649.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":640.98,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I think a lot of what we''ve done this year has been, has been really good for SEO and I think maybe just like fine tuning that a little bit more and then maybe pulling back.","index":123,"end_time":659.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":651.46,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I say maybe, but it''s probably going to be a definite on pulling back on paid.","index":124,"end_time":664.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":660.56,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that makes sense.","index":125,"end_time":668.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And no, you''re right with the like splitting the focus.","index":126,"end_time":671.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think when it comes to the points, we focused more on using the points for abm because that''s what brought in some of those more immediate results in terms of bringing in MQLs that we want, which is important to your team.","index":127,"end_time":685.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":671.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Long term, though the data does say that it is content and SEO that brings in the actual customers.","index":128,"end_time":690.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we can definitely discuss shifting the focus or if there''s a way to maybe scale back a bit on the amount of ABM campaigns we do in a year and instead move some of those points towards like developing new SEO blog posts or optimizing some that already exist on the site.","index":129,"end_time":709.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":691.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just doing a few of those per month also.","index":130,"end_time":711.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":710.08,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that sounds like a good idea.","index":131,"end_time":715.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":712.64,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I mean, as far as like the MQLs and SQLs go, I know we set like really, what''s the word?","index":132,"end_time":724.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":715.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Aggressive goals, right.","index":133,"end_time":728.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":726.72,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"For those per month.","index":134,"end_time":729.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":728.28,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I just wanted to just point out like, yeah, we didn''t meet those goals every month, but from where Sam and I sit, we brought in a lot of MQLs and SQLs this year and So I consider that to be lead gen and I consider that to be a measure of success for our team in that we identified, okay, we want to generate leads, this is how we''re going to do it and we did it.","index":135,"end_time":753.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":730.4,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I just want to put that out there.","index":136,"end_time":755.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":754.01,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think we did a great job and.","index":137,"end_time":757.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":756.17,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But that''s again, that''s my perspective because I''m just marketing right where the other folks are looking at the full, the full thing.","index":138,"end_time":764.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.62,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But I still come back to, I struggle that our measure of success is primarily that customer conversion, but we don''t have any control over that measurement after it becomes an mql.","index":139,"end_time":785.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":765.82,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like all that we have control over is generating high quality MQLs that are in the right industry with the right factors that are good quality enough that sales has a really good chance of having that call and having them truly be sales qualified, which again is sales decision.","index":140,"end_time":804.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":785.62,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":141,"end_time":804.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":804.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We decided that like they, they''re the ones who get to decide whether it''s truly sales qualified after they speak to the people.","index":142,"end_time":810.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":804.94,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So with that being the case, the only thing we can control is quality and everything after that is very hard to pin down.","index":143,"end_time":825.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":811.42,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think for us to be able to steer the ship or move the needle on moving them through.","index":144,"end_time":832.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":825.8,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"The only thing I can think of is obviously the obvious, which is like, oh, sales needs some sort of deck or some sort of materials or something to help push the needle forward with this SQL that''s like on the fence or this opportunity that is also on the fence.","index":145,"end_time":847.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":832.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But they want to know a little bit more about what a deliverable look like.","index":146,"end_time":850.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":847.91,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":147,"end_time":850.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":850.55,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like we can, we could have influence on that for sure, but other than that it''s very tough.","index":148,"end_time":856.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":850.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That''s what I struggle with.","index":149,"end_time":858.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":857.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think it''s like the, the pieces that we can''t control but being held very strongly accountable for them.","index":150,"end_time":865.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":858.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":151,"end_time":866.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You know when you brought that up earlier, like talking about how they''re happy to see the MQLs and SQLs coming in, but it''s the customer conversion.","index":152,"end_time":873.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":868.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It kind of made the hair on the back of my neck stand up because of exactly what you just described.","index":153,"end_time":876.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":873.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when I''m diagnosing a problem, like in our business, for example, If I''m seeing MQLs come in, if I''m seeing the sales team say, yes, this is qualified, this is a sales qualified lead and then it''s not converting further.","index":154,"end_time":887.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":876.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not looking at marketing, I''m looking at sales.","index":155,"end_time":890.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":888.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m looking at what process should we enhance.","index":156,"end_time":892.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":890.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are we being too relaxed on our qualification like do we need to redefine what that actually means rather than saying like it''s marketing, not delivering a full customer.","index":157,"end_time":904.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":893.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s not what marketing''s job is in this relationship.","index":158,"end_time":906.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":904.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I feel that would be more of like us working directly with SDRs.","index":159,"end_time":910.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":906.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":160,"end_time":910.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like, or having an SDR augmentation part of our staff where we could say like yeah, we qualified this person, we didn''t get to them to convert, that''s on us.","index":161,"end_time":918.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":910.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, but if it''s being qualified in both places and then not moving, I think our scope needs to shift towards like that sales conversation of how can we enhance their conversations.","index":162,"end_time":926.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":918.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean there''s a long sales cycles.","index":163,"end_time":928.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":927.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are also long contracts that they''re in with your competitors.","index":164,"end_time":931.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":928.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So sometimes even though they''re interested, they''re experiencing frustration.","index":165,"end_time":934.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":931.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They know I core and they''re going to come to you at some point.","index":166,"end_time":937.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":934.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They might be in a two or five year contract.","index":167,"end_time":939.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":937.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s only so many elements that we can control.","index":168,"end_time":942.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":940.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s just.","index":169,"end_time":942.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":942.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Those are the things that go through my head is I think we really need to focus on the sales aspect here.","index":170,"end_time":946.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":942.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I would agree.","index":171,"end_time":948.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":947.22,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":172,"end_time":953.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Well, yeah, we should definitely talk through Natalie like some, I don''t know if it''s one pagers or custom slide decks or some other tools that maybe we can create for the sales team but we''ll dive into the data and see kind of where that''s.","index":173,"end_time":965.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":953.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If there''s any notes on like it didn''t move forward because of this.","index":174,"end_time":968.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":965.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe we can see some, some commonalities that direct us towards what to create.","index":175,"end_time":973.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":969.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":176,"end_time":974.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":973.98,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":177,"end_time":974.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":974.34,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":178,"end_time":975.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":975.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Would we find that in the lead detail ruby if you want to click.","index":179,"end_time":978.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":975.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"What?","index":180,"end_time":979.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":181,"end_time":979.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":979.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":182,"end_time":980.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":979.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, so it''s.","index":183,"end_time":981.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":980.38,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, Lead detail would show it and then we also do have.","index":184,"end_time":987.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":982.86,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Sometimes Lead detail doesn''t get filled good if they actually like make it to the deal stage where you would just need to do closed one reason or closed last reason for a deal property to pull.","index":185,"end_time":1004.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":991.1,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But those are there and they exist and they have to fill them out if they close it or win it.","index":186,"end_time":1012.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1006.53,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That was a enhancement that we made last year I believe because we, we had the same issue last year of like hey, we''re not closing stuff, what''s going on?","index":187,"end_time":1021.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1012.85,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And a lot of it was like there was no value for why it didn''t happen.","index":188,"end_time":1027.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1023.81,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I was like we gotta make sure that gets filled out so we can.","index":189,"end_time":1031.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1027.81,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, I remember that data.","index":190,"end_time":1032.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1031.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we were looking at like 5 to 10 conversion rates on the sales qualified leads, which is pretty low.","index":191,"end_time":1038.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1032.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":192,"end_time":1039.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1038.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":193,"end_time":1039.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1039.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":194,"end_time":1040.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1039.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":195,"end_time":1041.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1040.67,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"All good conversations.","index":196,"end_time":1042.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1041.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, we''ll definitely dive into those numbers.","index":197,"end_time":1043.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1042.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":198,"end_time":1044.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1044.43,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"All right, can do our regular scheduled programming now.","index":199,"end_time":1053.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1050.75,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thanks for listening to me rant.","index":200,"end_time":1055.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1053.79,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Of course.","index":201,"end_time":1057.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1056.75,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":202,"end_time":1059.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1058.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just following up on the ABM notes here.","index":203,"end_time":1062.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1059.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we had another lead come in for the AI safety for law firm document download on LinkedIn.","index":204,"end_time":1068.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1063.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then our for the paid media specifically, we have those document downloads running, but also the ones that have the more interactive quiz so that those ads specifically, they''re getting clicks but no submissions.","index":205,"end_time":1083.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The document ones are performing a lot better.","index":206,"end_time":1085.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1083.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So if that continues on for the next couple of weeks, you might want to think about pausing those ones and then allocating more budget to the document downloads, which you''ve been doing well at following up with people for those ones.","index":207,"end_time":1098.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1085.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we have quite a strong conversion rate this month as well.","index":208,"end_time":1104.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1100.54,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Last month we ended at almost 13%.","index":209,"end_time":1107.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1104.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This month we''re at almost 22% from MQL to SQL.","index":210,"end_time":1111.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1107.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":211,"end_time":1115.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1115.1,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then for SEO.","index":212,"end_time":1119.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1118.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we are.","index":213,"end_time":1120.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1119.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This is the one that you sent over with Jeff''s note.","index":214,"end_time":1123.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1120.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''re updating this on the preview page and we''re going to have that ready for you today.","index":215,"end_time":1127.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1123.27,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then also wanted to show you an update on last week we looked at this New York page which we published, which is now ranking fourth.","index":216,"end_time":1139.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1129.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I took a look at some of the other ones.","index":217,"end_time":1140.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1139.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This Pros and cons of Microsoft Azure.","index":218,"end_time":1143.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1141.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This is a video page that you''ve had for a while, but it just recently started ranking in seventh place.","index":219,"end_time":1149.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1143.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This is a. I think it was a Jeff video.","index":220,"end_time":1152.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1150.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s ranking.","index":221,"end_time":1156.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1152.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then also this new blog post that we published a couple months ago is now at eighth place for outsourcing IT department.","index":222,"end_time":1164.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1156.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Cool.","index":223,"end_time":1165.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1164.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Nice.","index":224,"end_time":1166.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1166.12,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":225,"end_time":1167.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1166.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then I know Ruby with that keyword list that I sent over, if you have any questions about that.","index":226,"end_time":1174.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1169.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I tried to explain it in the loom about how we think about it or what keywords to target, but if you have any questions, happy to help there.","index":227,"end_time":1181.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1174.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, no, it was awesome.","index":228,"end_time":1183,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1181.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":229,"end_time":1183.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1183,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Sure.","index":230,"end_time":1184.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1184.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then for the project.","index":231,"end_time":1188.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1187.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I think Jeff is still reviewing these updates to the assessment page, where we''re just linking in the copilot assessment and the AI readiness assessment throughout.","index":232,"end_time":1200.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1189.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we did update the executive dashboard this, so you have the link to this.","index":233,"end_time":1206.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1200.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And this should be updating live as well.","index":234,"end_time":1208.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1206.71,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But we updated the sections that we talked about so only showing SQLs and opportunities with marketing sources.","index":235,"end_time":1217.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1209.07,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we''re using the custom lead source instead of just the lead source, just to break it down.","index":236,"end_time":1222.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1217.71,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"More conversion rate from MQL to SQL and then.","index":237,"end_time":1228.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1222.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh yeah, we also added the lead detail here.","index":238,"end_time":1230.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1228.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":239,"end_time":1231.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1231.04,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I have an update on the AI landing pages.","index":240,"end_time":1238.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1235.52,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I think you mentioned them, but.","index":241,"end_time":1241.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1239.6,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, so Jeff said he''s going to get his feedback this week, but I think he''s still out on vacation, so maybe later this week, maybe early next week.","index":242,"end_time":1249.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1241.04,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"But.","index":243,"end_time":1249.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1249.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, so we''ll have something free.","index":244,"end_time":1250.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1249.6,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":245,"end_time":1253,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1251.8,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":246,"end_time":1256.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1256.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this should, this dashboard should be more clear for your team as well.","index":247,"end_time":1261.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1256.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''re only showing MQLs from marketing sources and then updated it just to be the custom lead source.","index":248,"end_time":1267.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1261.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":249,"end_time":1269.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1268.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Website stats here.","index":250,"end_time":1272.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Were there any other notes for this dashboard that they had?","index":251,"end_time":1275,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1272.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I don''t believe so.","index":252,"end_time":1278.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1277.47,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":253,"end_time":1286.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1286.35,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":254,"end_time":1295.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1294.59,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s good though.","index":255,"end_time":1297.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1296.91,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":256,"end_time":1298.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1297.95,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Great.","index":257,"end_time":1302.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1302.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll wait for the updates on these pages and then get those done.","index":258,"end_time":1308.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1304.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I will deliver this updated Microsoft Copilot Consulting page to you today.","index":259,"end_time":1314.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1308.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":260,"end_time":1315.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1314.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Only other thing I can think of would be I''m, you know, I''m making this case for SEO and I''m also making this case for, you know, just ROI in general.","index":261,"end_time":1330.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1318.04,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"On.","index":262,"end_time":1331.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1330.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We know that SEO did good.","index":263,"end_time":1336.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1334.87,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We know content did good.","index":264,"end_time":1337.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1336.47,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"How do we tie that back to marketing''s efforts and our efforts with you guys?","index":265,"end_time":1347.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1338.07,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I know we did stuff right.","index":266,"end_time":1350.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1347.75,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We did a lot with SEO, we did a lot with the website.","index":267,"end_time":1352.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1350.19,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We did a whole website redesign.","index":268,"end_time":1353.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1352.15,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like, these are.","index":269,"end_time":1354.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1353.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"These are things that I think we can.","index":270,"end_time":1356.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1354.55,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That I want to be able to showcase as we got those, you know, the return right.","index":271,"end_time":1365.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1357.24,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"On the partnership and the investment of the partnership, regardless of.","index":272,"end_time":1368.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1365.48,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Obviously we know that the paid media spend was a lot.","index":273,"end_time":1371.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1368.76,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We didn''t get the return on that.","index":274,"end_time":1373.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1371.96,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But I''d like to be able to build the case for the return on content and SEO.","index":275,"end_time":1377.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1373.28,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That being said, what do you think is the best way for me to tell that story or show them that story?","index":276,"end_time":1387.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1379.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, we can.","index":277,"end_time":1391.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1390.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think a couple of months ago we did do an analysis of the website.","index":278,"end_time":1395.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1391.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"3 months of performance after launch versus the 3 months before.","index":279,"end_time":1399.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1396.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Given that was very early data, we can run a similar one again.","index":280,"end_time":1405.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1401.17,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just looking at what was the performance of the website a year before launching.","index":281,"end_time":1409.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1405.17,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So how good was our content results?","index":282,"end_time":1411.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1409.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How good were our SEO results versus now almost a year later?","index":283,"end_time":1415.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that might help to see do we have more visits?","index":284,"end_time":1420.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1416.8,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Is there higher engagement on the site and are there more conversions happening?","index":285,"end_time":1424.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1420.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, those are good.","index":286,"end_time":1427.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1426.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":287,"end_time":1431.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1430.64,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be good.","index":288,"end_time":1440.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1437.85,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I can''t think of anything else though.","index":289,"end_time":1442.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1441.13,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay, so I have.","index":290,"end_time":1450.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1448.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, all those reports will put together for you.","index":291,"end_time":1455.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1453.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''ll look at the content And SEO performance for the website now versus before launch.","index":292,"end_time":1461.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1455.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''ll also look at the lead detail.","index":293,"end_time":1463.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1462.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So showing MQLs that did come in for marketing sources, what were the biggest reasons for them not converting and whether that does point to a marketing quality issue or is it more of an issue once it gets through the pipeline and why they''re not being closed once they get there?","index":294,"end_time":1483.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1464.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds good.","index":295,"end_time":1485.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1484.37,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I will say for 2025, I did find a handful of MQLs that went backwards.","index":296,"end_time":1493.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1485.97,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So they were SQL, they, they came in MQL, then they went to SQL and then they were moved back to MQL.","index":297,"end_time":1503.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1495.66,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"The reasoning behind that is Kirk decided that they weren''t really sales qualified and put them back to mq, which I don''t love, but I get it.","index":298,"end_time":1519.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1505.34,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But it also skews the reality is like sales did talk to them, they did book a meeting, they did convert.","index":299,"end_time":1528.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1521.27,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They did, you know, they did the, they did the things and those are the ones where again I think it''s just like the drill down of like the reason.","index":300,"end_time":1539.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1528.87,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But there''s only like five, five or six of them.","index":301,"end_time":1545.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1543.44,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So not a big deal.","index":302,"end_time":1546.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1545.64,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But.","index":303,"end_time":1546.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1546.6,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, I think maybe it from, from what I know Colin, I think it is like not best practice to move leads backwards.","index":304,"end_time":1559.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1551.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Right?","index":305,"end_time":1560.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1559.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":306,"end_time":1561.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1560.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I think using the lead detail that you have been using is probably the best way to go about it.","index":307,"end_time":1566.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1561.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So they think they stay in SQL but then updating the reason why they''re not moving forward.","index":308,"end_time":1571.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1567.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yep, I agree.","index":309,"end_time":1573.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1572.34,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":310,"end_time":1573.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1573.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And even if, even if qualification criteria changes, it''s still not a good practice to change historical metrics because you should.","index":311,"end_time":1581.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1573.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It should more be an anecdotal note of like, well, our criteria change.","index":312,"end_time":1585.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1582.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like two years ago it was this.","index":313,"end_time":1587.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1585.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we got this many SQLs, we upped our criteria and then there''s a lot of variables to weigh into it.","index":314,"end_time":1592.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1587.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, typically it''s pretty bad practice to move people back as far as life cycle stage.","index":315,"end_time":1597.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1592.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I knew that.","index":316,"end_time":1599.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1598.38,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That''s why I brought it up.","index":317,"end_time":1600.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1599.5,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because I was like, oh no, what''s happening here?","index":318,"end_time":1603.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1600.58,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then we start to go crazy.","index":319,"end_time":1607.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1606.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":320,"end_time":1607.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1607.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because it''s like I swore that number was higher.","index":321,"end_time":1609.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1607.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, right.","index":322,"end_time":1610.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1609.5,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I''m like, well wait a minute, like they did book him.","index":323,"end_time":1614.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1610.46,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like they.","index":324,"end_time":1615.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1614.94,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Ah.","index":325,"end_time":1616.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1616.54,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So anyway, we''ll figure it out.","index":326,"end_time":1621.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1618.54,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":327,"end_time":1626.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1625.75,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Cool.","index":328,"end_time":1630.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1629.51,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay, that''s all I got.","index":329,"end_time":1631.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1630.31,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you guys.","index":330,"end_time":1633.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1632.15,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":331,"end_time":1633.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1633.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":332,"end_time":1635.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1634.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Have a good one.","index":333,"end_time":1636.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1635.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":334,"end_time":1637.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1636.55,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Bye.","index":335,"end_time":1637.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1637.11,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Bye.","index":336,"end_time":1638.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1638.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"}],"dateString":"2026-01-28T15:30:00.000Z","host_email":"rpontbriand@icorps.com","meeting_link":"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_NWVjNDBkODktN2I3OS00ZWQ0LTgzMDEtMWNkNDk5OGVlYjQ2@thread.v2/0?context={\"Tid\":\"0188564a-93de-489c-bf54-1927d4a9ed28\",\"Oid\":\"bdae9fd3-d481-4c5e-aeea-7272e37b7d07\"}","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,rpontbriand@icorps.com,sbagnall@icorps.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","sbagnall@icorps.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFXJRG9YW8BD9PDJWR55NEZ6","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.83,"bullets":["Identified weak conversion from paid media despite high lead generation; SEO shown as stronger ROI driver.","Ruby to revise reporting to include historical MQL, SQL, and client data for 2023–2025.","Agreed on building SEO-focused strategy for 2026; content shown to convert better than paid channels.","Colin to investigate CRM reporting issues and explore sales side blockers to customer conversion.","Team to compile receipts and spend shifts to finalize 2025 paid media budget reconciliation."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We did a lot with SEO, we did a lot with the website.","speaker":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"quote":"If it''s being qualified in both places and then not moving, I think our scope needs to shift towards... sales.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"We brought in a lot of MQLs and SQLs this year and... I consider that to be a measure of success.","speaker":"Ruby Pontbriand"}],"topics":["reporting","seo","conversion","paid media","measurement","alignment"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-vision","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-28T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Performance and ROI**\n\nThe team agreed that **content and SEO were the main drivers** of customer conversion and ROI in 2024, with paid media showing limited direct customer impact (03:18).\n\n- **Ruby Pontbriand** shared that despite generating many **MQLs and SQLs**, the paid campaigns only produced **two SQLs** that converted, which has caused concern about the ROI from paid efforts.\n    - The focus for leadership, particularly **Cook**, is on customer conversions, not just leads.\n    - Ruby is working on refining historical totals for **MQLs, SQLs, and customers** across **2023, 2024, and 2025**, including spend data to better align reporting with decision-maker expectations.\n    - Challenges in HubSpot reporting stem from lifecycle stages moving over time, making year-based attribution difficult.\n    - The team plans to tweak dashboards for clearer visibility on **conversion rates** and marketing source breakdowns.\n\n- **Nathalie Mintjens** and Ruby discussed shifting budget focus from paid to SEO, citing SEO''s history of success dating back to 2022.\n    - The website’s content and SEO efforts consistently show higher conversion to customers compared to paid media.\n    - They proposed scaling back paid campaigns and reallocating resources toward producing and optimizing SEO blog posts monthly.\n    - This shift aligns with long-term lead quality and customer acquisition, balancing immediate MQL generation with sustainable growth.\n\n- Ruby emphasized the team''s success in generating **MQLs and SQLs**, despite not meeting aggressive monthly goals fully.\n    - She highlighted that marketing controls lead quality but not the sales qualification or final customer conversion.\n    - This disconnect contributes to tension around accountability for conversion metrics beyond marketing''s influence.\n\n- **Colin Costigan** reinforced that poor customer conversion after SQL stage points to sales process issues, not marketing.\n    - He suggested exploring improvements in sales conversations and qualification criteria.\n    - Collaboration with SDRs or augmenting sales resources may be needed to close the gap.\n    - Recognized long sales cycles and existing contracts with competitors complicate immediate conversions.\n\n## **Sales and Lead Qualification Process**\n\nThe conversation pinpointed a need to better align marketing and sales on lead qualification and conversion metrics (13:24).\n\n- **Ruby** noted some leads moved backward in lifecycle stages from SQL to MQL due to sales reconsidering qualification, which skews reporting accuracy.\n    - She found about **five or six** such cases in 2025.\n    - This rollback conflicts with best practice and may distort pipeline metrics.\n\n- **Colin** advised that it’s poor practice to move leads backward through lifecycle stages.\n    - Instead, changes in qualification criteria should be noted separately without altering historical data.\n    - This preserves metric integrity and avoids confusion over numbers.\n    - He recalled prior work showing **5-10% conversion rates** from SQL to customer, emphasizing the challenge.\n\n- The team agreed to rely on the **lead detail property** in HubSpot to track reasons for leads not advancing rather than moving them back.\n    - This approach will improve clarity on why deals stall.\n    - They plan to analyze common deal loss reasons to create sales support materials like **one-pagers or custom slide decks** to help push hesitant prospects.\n\n- Collaboration between marketing and sales will be key to improving pipeline flow.\n    - Nathalie and Colin committed to reviewing data for trends that could inform these sales aids and process improvements.\n\n## **Reporting and Dashboard Enhancements**\n\nReporting clarity and data accuracy were focal points to better measure performance and ROI (03:20).\n\n- Ruby praised the **existing dashboards** for marketing tracking but requested tweaks to better capture historical totals and spend.\n    - She is working on **historical MQL, SQL, and customer numbers for 2023-2025**.\n    - Nathalie will pull **monthly actual paid media spends** for 2025, including details on budget reallocations between platforms like Reddit and LinkedIn.\n    - Dashboards were updated to show only **MQLs from marketing sources** and to use **custom lead sources** for more granular tracking.\n\n- The team noted some discrepancies in lifecycle stage reporting due to timing of stage changes.\n    - Colin offered to help refine HubSpot report logic to improve accuracy.\n    - Ruby is balancing budget tracking alongside performance metrics to better correlate spend with results.\n\n- Nathalie shared updates on website and SEO performance dashboards.\n    - They track rankings of key pages, e.g., a **New York page now ranking fourth**, and a Microsoft Azure video page at **seventh place**.\n    - The executive dashboard was refined to focus on **SQLs and opportunities from marketing sources** and includes detailed lead reasons.\n\n- A plan was set to run a **year-over-year website performance analysis** comparing three months after launch with the prior year.\n    - This will highlight gains in visits, engagement, and conversions to demonstrate content and SEO impact.\n    - Ruby welcomed this to build a stronger case for marketing’s ROI.\n\n## **SEO and Content Strategy for 2025**\n\nThe team plans to double down on SEO and content as proven long-term growth drivers while scaling back paid media (10:00).\n\n- Ruby proposed focusing heavily on SEO for 2025 based on consistent historical success.\n    - SEO and content combined drove most customer conversions over the past three years.\n    - The team recognizes the need to fine-tune SEO efforts, particularly keyword targeting informed by recent research and Loom explanations provided by Nathalie.\n\n- Nathalie agreed that SEO should receive more budget and points allocation, reducing spending on ABM and paid.\n    - This shift reflects the data showing that ABM brought short-term MQL growth but less customer conversion.\n    - They suggested publishing a few new blog posts monthly and optimizing existing content to keep SEO momentum.\n\n- Ruby wants to create a clear **SEO strategy pitch or plan** to present this shift to stakeholders.\n    - The goal is to align marketing efforts with proven ROI drivers and justify resource changes.\n    - The team agreed this is a priority for early 2025 planning.\n\n## **Website and Content Updates**\n\nWebsite content and SEO pages are actively improving rankings and user engagement, supporting marketing goals (18:30).\n\n- Nathalie shared progress on content updates with Jeff reviewing the **assessment pages** linking AI readiness and Copilot assessments.\n    - The **New York page recently published is ranking fourth** in search results.\n    - The **Microsoft Azure pros and cons video page** climbed to **seventh place**.\n    - A new blog post on **outsourcing IT departments** reached **eighth place**.\n\n- The team is updating the executive dashboard to reflect these marketing source improvements.\n    - This dashboard will also track conversion rates from MQL to SQL and include detailed lead reasons.\n\n- Nathalie committed to delivering an updated **Microsoft Copilot Consulting page** by the end of the day.\n    - This update ties into strengthening content related to AI offerings.\n\n- Ruby expressed interest in tying website redesign and content efforts directly to marketing ROI.\n    - They plan to run comparative reports to quantify improvements in traffic, engagement, and conversions since the redesign launch.\n\n## **Collaboration and Next Steps**\n\nClear coordination between marketing, sales, and analytics is key to improving conversion rates and demonstrating ROI (15:00).\n\n- The team will analyze deal loss reasons in HubSpot to identify where sales support tools could help move prospects forward.\n    - Colin suggested creating tailored sales materials based on common objections or deal stalling points.\n\n- Ruby and Nathalie will continue refining reports and dashboards for clearer visibility on marketing contribution.\n    - Nathalie will provide monthly spend data and support SEO performance analysis.\n\n- Jeff’s feedback on AI landing pages is expected later this week or early next week, allowing the team to finalize related content.\n\n- The group acknowledged challenges in measuring marketing success beyond lead generation, emphasizing the need for shared accountability with sales.\n\n- Ruby will continue building the case for SEO and content investments, focusing on proven long-term gains rather than paid media shortfalls.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot reporting","paid media ROI","SEO strategy","MQL to SQL conversion","sales enablement","website performance"],"overview":"- **Marketing Focus Shift:** Team agrees to prioritize content and SEO over paid media for better customer conversion rates in 2024.\n\n- **Paid Media Concerns:** Paid campaigns produced only two SQLs; ROI concerns lead to reallocating budget towards SEO strategies and blog content.\n\n- **Sales Process Improvement:** Poor conversion post-SQL indicates sales process issues, requiring collaboration between marketing and sales to enhance lead qualification.\n\n- **Reporting Enhancements Needed:** Dashboard tweaks are necessary for clearer historical performance metrics and tracking of MQLs, SQLs, and customer conversions.\n\n- **SEO and Content Strategy:** Plans to double down on SEO efforts for 2025, reflecting historical success in driving customer conversions and engagement.\n\n- **Collaboration Agreement:** Ongoing analysis of deal loss reasons and tailored sales materials will improve conversion rates, emphasizing shared accountability for results.","action_items":"\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nContinue refining paid media ROI reporting by compiling MQL, SQL, and client numbers with historical spend data for 2023-2025 (05:30)\nProvide more detailed data inputs to integrate reallocation of paid media budget by month between platforms (07:20)\nInvestigate why certain MQLs revert to earlier lifecycle stages and communicate insights for data accuracy (25:50)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nPull receipts and actual paid media spending for each month in 2025 and note month(s) of budget reallocations (08:10)\nDeliver updated Microsoft Copilot Consulting page today (21:35)\nPrepare website performance analysis reports comparing one year post-launch metrics versus pre-launch (22:45)\nCreate reports showing MQLs from marketing sources with reasons for non-conversion to identify marketing vs. sales issues (23:50)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nTroubleshoot HubSpot reporting to improve accuracy of MQL, SQL, opportunity, and customer attribution by lifecycle dates (06:40)\nExplore and define tools like sales decks or one-pagers to aid sales teams in advancing SQLs and opportunities (15:30)\nAssist in analyzing lead detail and closed reason data to identify common sales pipeline challenges contributing to low customer conversions (16:15)\n\n**Samuel Bagnall**\nMonitor Jeff’s feedback on AI landing page updates and communicate expected delivery timeline (20:20)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"8606b8b9-f6f2-4b3c-8090-eb259393efad","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
