WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'b1f3ae44-0316-492e-aef1-bb260b814482',
    '2026-01-27 20:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KFVMZ6X58G44BZH75BW18RM9',
    'Techmode+New North',
    '{"Matthew Look","Christopher Quigley","Colin Costigan","Lindsay Hall"}'::text[],
    1709,
    'https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_ODBmZWFjMWYtMWIxYi00NmZmLTgyMDEtOWFiZWJhYWEwYzVh@thread.v2/0?context={"Tid":"3801011d-e732-48ee-be2a-e499b1a29ba4","Oid":"e804fbe9-a623-4d26-a887-992e62fb92d1"}',
    '{"id":"01KFVMZ6X58G44BZH75BW18RM9","title":"Techmode+New North","summary":{"notes":"## **Website Content and SEO Strategy**\n\nThe team is finalizing the **RingCentral page design and content** to improve SEO alignment and user engagement (01:39).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** integrated extensive keyword research with Matthew Look’s document to create page copy ready for design and review.\n- The page will include multiple blog posts, a carousel feature for dynamic blog display, and embedded assessments to guide user journeys.\n- Matthew emphasized embedding competitor-related queries directly in the content to capture search intent like “RingCentral Alternatives” or complaints, ensuring visitors find answers immediately.\n- Future pages, starting with a **Comcast page next week**, will follow this model, including customized assessments tailored to specific user questions rather than generic forms.\n- This approach aims to boost organic search relevance and engagement by linking blogs, assessments, and rich content within the main pages.\n\nContent evolution will combine **new competitor-focused blogs with repurposed content** enhanced for AI search intent (23:01).\n\n- Colin recommended a balanced mix of fresh competitor content, repurposed blogs optimized for AI and search engines, and thought leadership pieces on communication system importance.\n- Matthew plans to rewrite existing blogs with AI-friendly titles and formats to capitalize on their established authority.\n- Christopher Quigley supported maintaining existing blog authority rather than discarding older posts.\n- This strategy targets both competitive keywords and broader industry topics to widen reach and maintain relevance.\n\n## **Form Management and Integration**\n\nThe team resolved issues with **Gravity Forms and HubSpot email integration**, opting to send emails via HubSpot for reliability (04:05).\n\n- Colin explained that Gravity Forms will feed data into HubSpot, which then sends confirmation emails, avoiding SMTP failures.\n- This setup requires building and connecting each form in HubSpot, which costs about **one “Colin V Buck” ($100)** per form creation (06:00).\n- To optimize costs and efficiency, the team agreed to **batch build forms** ahead of demand, enabling quick updates and deployment.\n- Forms may differ in fields per assessment, so some customization will remain necessary, but shared infrastructure will speed execution.\n\nThis system balances user experience with backend reliability and reduces email delivery failures affecting lead capture.\n\n## **Advertising Campaign Performance and Optimization**\n\nSeveral **Google ad campaigns are underperforming**, prompting a review and formal process for campaign evaluation and adjustment (13:04).\n\n- The **3Cx “looking to move” ad group is inactive**, while the “3Cx support” group shows stronger traffic and engagement, per Lindsey Hall and Matthew Look.\n- The **Amazon Connect campaign has minimal traffic and no results** and will be discontinued immediately (15:10).\n- Matthew proposed a **formal campaign lifecycle:** run new campaigns for 4–6 weeks, then review and adjust based on quality and volume; re-evaluate at 3 months; kill if ineffective after 6 months.\n- Colin agreed to document this evaluation and decision process to ensure consistent campaign management.\n- **Performance Max (PMax) campaigns have not yielded good results** and will be discontinued, with an audit underway to decide whether to rebuild as standard search campaigns or pivot (16:00).\n\nThis structured approach aims to maximize marketing ROI by focusing on high-quality leads and stopping ineffective spend quickly.\n\n## **User Journey and Landing Page Optimization**\n\nLanding pages will be designed to **answer user search queries directly and guide visitors through relevant content journeys** (16:56).\n\n- Lindsey emphasized the need to audit landing pages to ensure they cover all potential search intents and provide clear paths to related content.\n- Colin is incorporating multiple options for users to click through from pages like RingCentral, including blogs and assessments.\n- Matthew wants these linked resources integrated as core content, not afterthoughts, to keep users engaged and better informed.\n- The strategy focuses on creating seamless journeys from landing pages to deeper content, improving user experience and conversion potential.\n\nThis will help capture users’ intent fully and nurture them toward conversion through targeted, layered content.\n\n## **Technology Tools and Development Initiatives**\n\nColin shared recent work building tools using **Supabase database, Claude code AI, and Lovable front-end** to support internal and client solutions (08:57).\n\n- These tools enable dynamic design and data integration, showing the company is advancing automation and user-friendly platforms.\n- Colin mentioned plans for a **new client portal rollout** incorporating these technologies to enhance client interactions and operational efficiency.\n- Matthew is exploring options to automate blog rewriting for AI optimization but prefers manual control for quality assurance.\n\nThese tech initiatives aim to scale operations, improve the client experience, and keep pace with evolving AI and web design tools.","outline":null,"keywords":["RingCentral","HubSpot integration","Google campaigns","blog layout","Gravity Forms","AI content strategy"],"overview":"- **Website SEO Strategy:** Finalizing RingCentral page to enhance SEO and user engagement through blogs and assessments.\n\n- **Content Evolution:** Combining new competitor blogs with optimized existing posts to broaden reach and maintain authority.\n\n- **Form Management:** Gravity Forms will integrate with HubSpot for reliable email confirmation, costing $100 per form built.\n\n- **Ad Campaign Review:** Underperforming Google ad campaigns will follow a structured lifecycle for evaluation and adjustment every few weeks.\n\n- **User Journey Focus:** Landing pages will guide visitors by answering queries and linking to related content for better engagement.\n\n- **Tech Initiatives:** Developing tools with Supabase and AI to improve client interactions and operational efficiency, plus a new client portal.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend RingCentral page design and copy for team review (02:09)\nBuild blog post category templates once Lindsey provides category list (04:03)\nFinalize HubSpot forms integration, handling routing for multiple Gravity Forms (08:15)\nConduct thorough audit of price offer campaign and evaluate future direction (16:22)\nCreate written process for campaign evaluations with timelines for testing, changes, and kills (15:40)\nReview and send recommendations for underperforming Google ad groups including 3Cx and Amazon Connect (13:50)\nImplement enhanced internal linking and embed blog and assessment content directly into competitor landing pages like RingCentral (19:10)\nCheck Bing ads platform for RingCentral trademark blocking and provide update (26:49)\n\n**Lindsay Hall**\nProvide list of blog categories to Colin for template building (04:03)\nSend batch of form IDs needed for HubSpot implementation to Colin (07:59)\nConduct internal audits on customer journey flows on landing pages to ensure full query coverage and funnel paths (16:56)\n\n**Matthew Look**\nContinue writing RingCentral and Comcast competitor blogs including assessments (20:14)\nPrepare content revisions focused on AI intent for existing blogs and coordinate rewriting (24:51)\nProvide batch lists of new form IDs for HubSpot integration to Colin (07:59)\n"},"duration":28.489999771118164,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Matthew Look"},{"id":1,"name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Lindsay Hall"}],"sentences":[{"text":"What''s going on, gang?","index":0,"end_time":4.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.92,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Hey.","index":1,"end_time":7.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.8,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Christopher.","index":2,"end_time":12.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.36,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"How you doing, buddy?","index":3,"end_time":12.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":12.04,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''m doing good, Matt.","index":4,"end_time":14.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.68,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":5,"end_time":15.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":14.76,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Good.","index":6,"end_time":16.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.24,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"These other I see all the time, col.","index":7,"end_time":22.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":17.84,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Hey, guys, can you hear me?","index":8,"end_time":27.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":26.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, Chris, what were you gonna say?","index":9,"end_time":28.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.29,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I was just gonna say, are you up north?","index":10,"end_time":30.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":29.05,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Are you heading back?","index":11,"end_time":33.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.89,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right after this.","index":12,"end_time":33.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.05,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Hey, Colin, you like my hat?","index":13,"end_time":34.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.69,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I do.","index":14,"end_time":35.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":35.21,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Oh, wow.","index":15,"end_time":36.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":36.17,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Look at you forgetting to wear it.","index":16,"end_time":38.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.81,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I was gonna wear it on a call, so I got my hat on.","index":17,"end_time":42.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":38.85,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Do you like it?","index":18,"end_time":42.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.17,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I do.","index":19,"end_time":43.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":42.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s comfy, isn''t it?","index":20,"end_time":44.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":43.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s nice.","index":21,"end_time":45.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.89,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"My head''s big.","index":22,"end_time":46.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":45.57,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I need to stretch it out.","index":23,"end_time":47.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":46.33,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s a problem.","index":24,"end_time":48.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.37,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Got a big ass head.","index":25,"end_time":49.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.65,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''m a water head.","index":26,"end_time":51.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.65,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''ve never thought that about you.","index":27,"end_time":54.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":52.77,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Never thought.","index":28,"end_time":57.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":56.69,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You never saw me as a waterhead?","index":29,"end_time":58.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.17,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"No.","index":30,"end_time":59.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":58.85,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yep.","index":31,"end_time":63.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":62.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you guys doing?","index":32,"end_time":64.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":63.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":33,"end_time":65.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":65.25,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"How are you?","index":34,"end_time":66.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":65.53,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Pretty good.","index":35,"end_time":66.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":66.29,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":36,"end_time":68.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":67.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Trying to stay warm.","index":37,"end_time":68.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":68.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":38,"end_time":72.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":71.81,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Good luck with that.","index":39,"end_time":72.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":72.13,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, we got about 13 inches with some ice on top of.","index":40,"end_time":77.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":73.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you end up canceling their party?","index":41,"end_time":79.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":78.46,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, we had a much smaller party.","index":42,"end_time":82.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":80.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was just my brother in law and sister in law and their kids and my mom.","index":43,"end_time":87.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":82.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have a friend that went to Boston for the weekend and has not been able to come home.","index":44,"end_time":95.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":89.58,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"She''s been stuck in Boston for a couple days.","index":45,"end_time":97.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":95.02,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"That checks out.","index":46,"end_time":99.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":99.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, I got some updates for the Ringcentral page.","index":47,"end_time":109.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":105.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we put together a bunch of keyword research.","index":48,"end_time":111.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":109.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Matt, I also combined this with the document that you sent over in your email.","index":49,"end_time":115.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":111.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Felt pretty well aligned.","index":50,"end_time":117.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":116.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what we turned this into was the actual page copy.","index":51,"end_time":120.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":117.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re going to start designing this.","index":52,"end_time":122.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":121.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have the layout and wireframe and everything.","index":53,"end_time":124.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":122.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to start designing this and putting this together and then send it over to you guys to review.","index":54,"end_time":128.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":125.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, Sounds good.","index":55,"end_time":136.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":129.81,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And then we also have updated blog layout options.","index":56,"end_time":148.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":142.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":57,"end_time":150.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":149.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I know you were looking forward to these, Lindsey, So got three new options here.","index":58,"end_time":154.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":150.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like this one.","index":59,"end_time":160.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.58,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s nice.","index":60,"end_time":161.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":160.7,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I like it.","index":61,"end_time":179.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.38,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s nice too.","index":62,"end_time":180.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":179.34,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Man.","index":63,"end_time":190.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":190.31,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I''m going to need a lot of images.","index":64,"end_time":191.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":190.43,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, so obviously placeholders, you.","index":65,"end_time":194.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":192.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can only.","index":66,"end_time":195.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":194.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You only have to use whatever you want, but we can build as many of these as you like.","index":67,"end_time":200.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":195.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we recommend is having these tied to like categories almost.","index":68,"end_time":204.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":200.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like what you''re posting about, maybe you want the layout a little bit different just so you can.","index":69,"end_time":209.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":204.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you wanted the freedom to like.","index":70,"end_time":210.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":209.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to post it looking like this.","index":71,"end_time":211.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":210.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to post this one looking like this.","index":72,"end_time":213.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":211.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think that''s the best approach there.","index":73,"end_time":215.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":213.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that works.","index":74,"end_time":217.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":216.41,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So like Categories as in like topics?","index":75,"end_time":220.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":218.01,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Like, like tag type topics.","index":76,"end_time":222.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":220.09,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":77,"end_time":223.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":222.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So on the right side, we can create a list of categories for the post type and you can just select those and we can build these to match basically a category.","index":78,"end_time":232.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":223.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that works for me.","index":79,"end_time":235.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":232.57,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So I''ll send these over for you guys to review.","index":80,"end_time":237.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":235.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you have any feedback, let me know.","index":81,"end_time":238.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":237.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can tweak the design.","index":82,"end_time":239.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":238.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Other than that, just let me know, like the categories you have in mind and we can build these as the template there.","index":83,"end_time":243.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":239.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":84,"end_time":244.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":243.62,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":85,"end_time":246.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":245.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":86,"end_time":247.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":247.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Matt, I wanted an update on your tool because I know that we were working through Gravity Forms setup and that is the reason that the email wasn''t going through.","index":87,"end_time":257.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":247.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lindsey, we changed the email because of the issues we ran into a while ago to come from HubSpot, not from Gravity Forms.","index":88,"end_time":264.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":257.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why the SMTP wasn''t working.","index":89,"end_time":266.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":264.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To send you from marketing.","index":90,"end_time":267.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":266.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A tech mode.","index":91,"end_time":268.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":267.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":92,"end_time":269.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":268.36,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Wait, so you''re telling me I can''t use Gravity Forms?","index":93,"end_time":272.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.4,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"No, no, you can.","index":94,"end_time":273.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":272.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just like we build it in HubSpot so it pulls from Gravity Forms into HubSpot and then HubSpot sends you the email instead of directly from Gravity Forms.","index":95,"end_time":280.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":273.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":96,"end_time":282.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.56,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t know that that makes sense to me, but can I continue to do what I''m doing?","index":97,"end_time":285.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.16,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":98,"end_time":286.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":285.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pretty much the same process.","index":99,"end_time":290.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":289.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I am concerned.","index":100,"end_time":292.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":291.01,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I''m a little concerned because is there an easy way for me to connect a pre built form and gravity forms to HubSpot or does it have to be done in the other direction?","index":101,"end_time":304.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":292.09,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Well, we would be.","index":102,"end_time":305.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could build the form.","index":103,"end_time":306.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":305.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I already have our team like slated to do that in HubSpot.","index":104,"end_time":308.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So taking what''s already been built in Gravity Forms with the REST API that you have connected in there and building that in HubSpot.","index":105,"end_time":313.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":308.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, we''ve been, we''ve done three form.","index":106,"end_time":316.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.94,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''ve done three of those so far.","index":107,"end_time":318.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.5,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s.","index":108,"end_time":319.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":318.94,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"We''ve been sending it to a new form every time, a new form number.","index":109,"end_time":322.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.58,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So basically we just update it to a new form.","index":110,"end_time":325.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.82,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So does that mean you got to go in and connect all those forms?","index":111,"end_time":327.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.7,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Well, it''ll just be like id 22, id 23, id 24 and then we would just change the routing.","index":112,"end_time":333.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":327.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the answer is yeah, we have to do it every time.","index":113,"end_time":336.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.86,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yes.","index":114,"end_time":337.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":337.26,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And we can''t get Gravity Forms to work.","index":115,"end_time":341.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":339.89,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Gravity Forms works.","index":116,"end_time":343.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":342.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was just the cleaner way to get everything populated in HubSpot and to have HubSpot sending the email was to make it this way.","index":117,"end_time":350.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":343.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":118,"end_time":351.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":350.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, but I don''t know that I care enough to ask enough questions about it.","index":119,"end_time":355.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.21,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay, so let me ask you this.","index":120,"end_time":362.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":360.37,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"If I send you an ID of a form that I need built out in HubSpot, how many New north bucks does that cost?","index":121,"end_time":371.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":362.85,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"New north bucks?","index":122,"end_time":372.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":371.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, maybe one.","index":123,"end_time":375.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":373.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, that''s 100.","index":124,"end_time":377.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.22,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Every time, though, if you send me a batch of them, he''s like, it''s just one.","index":125,"end_time":383.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.34,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"100.","index":126,"end_time":384.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383.9,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"One.","index":127,"end_time":384.859,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":384.46,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"One buck.","index":128,"end_time":385.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":384.94,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"One.","index":129,"end_time":386.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":386.46,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s one V buck.","index":130,"end_time":387.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":386.78,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"One Colin V buck.","index":131,"end_time":389.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.86,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":132,"end_time":391.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":390.7,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I''m just curious.","index":133,"end_time":391.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":391.02,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Is there a way Colin either knows what a V buck is or he doesn''t?","index":134,"end_time":396.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":392.14,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Based on these kids are.","index":135,"end_time":397.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396.02,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"No.","index":136,"end_time":397.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":397.48,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right?","index":137,"end_time":398.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":398.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":138,"end_time":399.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":398.72,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":139,"end_time":400.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":400.16,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I think we''ve all had kids who''ve just magically grabbed a card and bought a bunch of bee box, haven''t they?","index":140,"end_time":406.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":401.12,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And you''re like, what the hell is this $200 charge so many times?","index":141,"end_time":411.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.4,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Well, I have multiple kids.","index":142,"end_time":412.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":411.52,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Right?","index":143,"end_time":413.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":412.88,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So they all give it a shot at some point.","index":144,"end_time":415.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":413.12,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Quick, quick sidebar on that.","index":145,"end_time":417.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":415.6,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"My favorite story of a kid stealing a credit card and spending money.","index":146,"end_time":421.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":417.44,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"My stepdaughter ordered doordash to her mom''s house at, like, midnight.","index":147,"end_time":425.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":421.28,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"She doordashed herself some McDonald''s Happy Me Meal.","index":148,"end_time":428.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":425.92,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It was $30 for a Happy Meal.","index":149,"end_time":431.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":428.82,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Doordashed at midnight.","index":150,"end_time":432.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":431.58,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"She was smart.","index":151,"end_time":433.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.02,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"She''d be like, I didn''t have.","index":152,"end_time":435.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.7,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"There''s no food here.","index":153,"end_time":436.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.46,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Mom doesn''t feed me.","index":154,"end_time":438.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.38,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You''d be like, oh, my God.","index":155,"end_time":439.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.46,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Anytime you need food while you''re there, you can use the card.","index":156,"end_time":442.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.74,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, well, yeah.","index":157,"end_time":444.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":442.62,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"That''s why I lock my phone.","index":158,"end_time":448.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":447.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So my wife can only stay on.","index":159,"end_time":451.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":449.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sorry.","index":160,"end_time":451.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":451.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My baby can only stay on the camera.","index":161,"end_time":453.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":451.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s not allowed to hit any buttons.","index":162,"end_time":455.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The bold move, giving the phone to the baby.","index":163,"end_time":459.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":457.43,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"But if you lock all the buttons, she can''t do anything.","index":164,"end_time":462.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":460.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This child in question is 12.","index":165,"end_time":464.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":462.95,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":166,"end_time":465.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":465.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s like, I''m gonna doordash myself some food.","index":167,"end_time":467.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":465.51,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":168,"end_time":468.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":467.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This baby will be one tomorrow.","index":169,"end_time":469.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":170,"end_time":470.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":470.15,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"All right, so I didn''t mean to interrupt your question, but yes, for one V buck.","index":171,"end_time":476.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.87,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Colin V Buck.","index":172,"end_time":477.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":476.99,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s gonna cost that for a form.","index":173,"end_time":479.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":477.99,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean, if you send them over.","index":174,"end_time":480.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":479.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In a batch, I mean, we should batch them.","index":175,"end_time":482.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":480.91,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":176,"end_time":483.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":482.8,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"I mean, why can''t we just.","index":177,"end_time":484,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.08,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Hang on.","index":178,"end_time":484.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Why can''t we just build 10?","index":179,"end_time":485.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.44,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Just build 10 and they''ll be ready to go like, when we need them.","index":180,"end_time":492.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":488.72,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Do you need to know what the fields will be ahead of time?","index":181,"end_time":499.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":495.04,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"No, no.","index":182,"end_time":500.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":499.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, we can just update that pretty quickly on the.","index":183,"end_time":502.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":500.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, before go live, but that way we can just have the setup and the infrastructure in place for you to edit the forms.","index":184,"end_time":509.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":185,"end_time":511.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":511.3,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Matt, what tool are you using again as a cursor?","index":186,"end_time":518.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":516.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Claude.","index":187,"end_time":519.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":518.78,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Oh, Claude code.","index":188,"end_time":520.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":519.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Claude code and Claude code and I have been arguing lately, but it just stops sometimes.","index":189,"end_time":526.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.06,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Like, and I do pay for a tier, but I don''t pay for the most expensive tier.","index":190,"end_time":530.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":527.3,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But sometimes it just like is processing and then I look and it stopped and it''s done.","index":191,"end_time":535.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.78,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And it did, but it didn''t finish the task.","index":192,"end_time":537.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":535.92,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Do you have Claude cowork or are you on PC?","index":193,"end_time":540.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":537.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"PC fucking using Bullshit.","index":194,"end_time":543.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.8,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They have some more features on the Mac that allow you to just like make settings so it keeps restarting itself if it runs into an issue.","index":195,"end_time":551.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":543.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s called the.","index":196,"end_time":552.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":551.52,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s.","index":197,"end_time":554.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":553.84,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Jesus.","index":198,"end_time":554.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":554.28,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"There''s a code out there that you can download and I want to say it''s the.","index":199,"end_time":557.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":554.76,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s the Ralph Wiggum.","index":200,"end_time":559.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.76,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Ralph Wiggum code, they call it.","index":201,"end_time":560.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559.2,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"What?","index":202,"end_time":561.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":561.04,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yes, Code that you can add to Claude and it''s called Ralph Wiggum.","index":203,"end_time":565.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.42,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And if anybody remembers that from Simpsons, it''s the.","index":204,"end_time":568.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.02,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s the guy who goes, I''m helping.","index":205,"end_time":570.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.18,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"He''d say, I''m helping.","index":206,"end_time":571.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.02,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, you know, that''s what he did.","index":207,"end_time":573.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.22,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Was that Ralph?","index":208,"end_time":574.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.94,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I think it was Ralph Wigham.","index":209,"end_time":575.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.62,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m helping.","index":210,"end_time":577.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":575.5,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So he would say.","index":211,"end_time":577.819,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.18,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So the.","index":212,"end_time":578.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.819,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s called basically what it does is it goes out there and helps and it restarts Claude to make sure it finishes your task for you.","index":213,"end_time":583.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":578.22,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":214,"end_time":584.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":584.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I built two tools over the weekend actually with.","index":215,"end_time":587.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":585.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I did Supabase as the database and then Claude code and then Lovable as the front end.","index":216,"end_time":591.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":587.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know what any of that is other than the cloud code.","index":217,"end_time":594.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":592.75,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Lovable is just like a front end development tool.","index":218,"end_time":597.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":595.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s like ChatGPT, but it does like all the design and everything and you can connect to everything directly to a database.","index":219,"end_time":604.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":598.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, Colin''s up in my game.","index":220,"end_time":608.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":607.39,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Dang.","index":221,"end_time":609.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":609.23,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Now you''re dangerous.","index":222,"end_time":611.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":610.35,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"You can do front end design too.","index":223,"end_time":613.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":612.03,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":224,"end_time":614.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":614.03,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Why are you working with these losers?","index":225,"end_time":616.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":614.67,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Colin, it''s time for you to do your own thing, brother.","index":226,"end_time":618.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.07,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''re actually, we''re building all of these things pretty aggressively right now.","index":227,"end_time":622.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you guys are going to.","index":228,"end_time":624.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":623.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Eventually we''re going to roll out a new client portal, things like that.","index":229,"end_time":627.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":624.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With all of these updates I''m saving.","index":230,"end_time":631.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":627.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m saving Lovable because that looks pretty interesting.","index":231,"end_time":633.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":631.01,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Lovable is really nice.","index":232,"end_time":634.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":633.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, very cheap too.","index":233,"end_time":637.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":634.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like we built like how many.","index":234,"end_time":641.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":639.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I bet you they don''t charge you a full Colin dollar.","index":235,"end_time":643.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.21,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Full Colin Buck could build something well.","index":236,"end_time":646.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":643.37,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You do have to mess around with it because you find, like, inefficien.","index":237,"end_time":649.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":646.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":238,"end_time":650.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":650.31,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So, like, oh, I''ll go to Claude for this change, but I''ll go to Lovable for this change, whether it''s back end, front end, or where it exists.","index":239,"end_time":656.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":650.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":240,"end_time":658.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":657.91,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Very interesting.","index":241,"end_time":659.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":658.95,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Well, I''m getting there.","index":242,"end_time":661.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":660.63,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s.","index":243,"end_time":662.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":662.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m upset.","index":244,"end_time":664.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":663.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m just a dumb business owner.","index":245,"end_time":665.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":664.11,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''m just trying to make my way downtown.","index":246,"end_time":668.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":665.59,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You''re doing the important stuff.","index":247,"end_time":670.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":669.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":248,"end_time":670.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":670.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve been talking about this a lot as a company of, like, so many businesses that we see come in that have a conversation like they want nothing to do with what''s going on with the actual business.","index":249,"end_time":680.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":670.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re not.","index":250,"end_time":680.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":680.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re working in the business, not on the business.","index":251,"end_time":682.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":680.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Business we see.","index":252,"end_time":683.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":682.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I never see that from you.","index":253,"end_time":684.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":683.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, you''re actually, like, what new tools or processes or what can we change?","index":254,"end_time":687.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":684.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which is just very refreshing.","index":255,"end_time":689.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":687.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":256,"end_time":691.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.69,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":257,"end_time":692.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":692.05,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I hate it.","index":258,"end_time":693.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":692.57,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Colin, I.","index":259,"end_time":693.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.01,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We just had this call yesterday.","index":260,"end_time":694.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.57,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I want to be.","index":261,"end_time":695.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":694.65,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I want to be, like, half in it and just around all the time, but got to make money, got to keep.","index":262,"end_time":702.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":695.21,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Keep moving.","index":263,"end_time":702.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.13,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yep.","index":264,"end_time":703.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":703.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I should have picked a different career.","index":265,"end_time":705.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.13,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Something that was easier.","index":266,"end_time":706.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.49,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Well, what was your.","index":267,"end_time":710.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":709.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What was your other option?","index":268,"end_time":711.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":710.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was a restaurant manager for years, and that sucked.","index":269,"end_time":716.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":713.57,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That does suck.","index":270,"end_time":717.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":716.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did it suck?","index":271,"end_time":718.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":717.73,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Did it suck more than marketing?","index":272,"end_time":720.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":718.93,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, it did.","index":273,"end_time":722.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.33,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It did.","index":274,"end_time":722.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":722.13,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It did suck.","index":275,"end_time":723.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":722.93,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"A lot of headaches.","index":276,"end_time":724.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":723.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nothing worse than your dishwasher.","index":277,"end_time":726.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":725.49,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Like, you''re out of spoons and your dishwasher walked out.","index":278,"end_time":729.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.01,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Or he''s high, passed out in the back, or he''s smoking weed in the back in the.","index":279,"end_time":735.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":730.29,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Walk in, and you can''t let them go because if you let them go, you got no one to wash dishes the rest of the night.","index":280,"end_time":739.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":735.39,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":281,"end_time":740.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now it''s you.","index":282,"end_time":741.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now it''s you.","index":283,"end_time":742.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.39,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yep.","index":284,"end_time":742.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":742.07,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"But now all the salads taste like weed.","index":285,"end_time":744.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":742.43,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I''m just.","index":286,"end_time":745.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.15,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"No, no.","index":287,"end_time":747.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":746.35,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I know.","index":288,"end_time":747.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":747.31,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Gotta do what you gotta do.","index":289,"end_time":749.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":748.19,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay.","index":290,"end_time":752.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":752.03,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Porn star was my other option, though.","index":291,"end_time":755.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.63,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Colin.","index":292,"end_time":756.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":755.59,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"There you go.","index":293,"end_time":757.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":756.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Only.","index":294,"end_time":759.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":758.99,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Only Dads.","index":295,"end_time":760.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":759.47,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I was gonna do Only Dads for old gay men because that''s probably about the only thing I would hopefully get.","index":296,"end_time":766.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":760.23,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I could pull.","index":297,"end_time":767.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":766.34,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You guys have a lot of money, right?","index":298,"end_time":770.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":768.94,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Probably.","index":299,"end_time":773.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":772.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":300,"end_time":775.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.58,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":301,"end_time":776.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.86,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Not a lot of options.","index":302,"end_time":777.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.18,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So, Lindsey, what is on your list?","index":303,"end_time":783.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":781.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you have any chance to take a look at the 3cx ad group looking to move?","index":304,"end_time":793.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":784.7,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It is not doing anything.","index":305,"end_time":796.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":793.35,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I''ve not looked at it today.","index":306,"end_time":797.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":796.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not doing anything.","index":307,"end_time":801.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":800.15,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So basically, I think we''re kind of looking for a recommendation on what we should do, you know, do we change the terms?","index":308,"end_time":806.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":801.67,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Do we scrap it?","index":309,"end_time":807.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":806.67,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Real quick on that.","index":310,"end_time":809.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.31,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Ryan sent me a text earlier today that we''ve been getting hammered on the phones lately for people looking for 3Cx support.","index":311,"end_time":815.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":810.23,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"The 3Cx support ad group is performing much better than seeing a lot more traffic than the looking to move ad group.","index":312,"end_time":824.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":816.72,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yes, that''s very exciting.","index":313,"end_time":830.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":828.88,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yes.","index":314,"end_time":830.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":830.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We will put together recommendations.","index":315,"end_time":832.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":830.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll send this to you.","index":316,"end_time":833.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":832.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I got items, Lindsey, if you don''t have anything else.","index":317,"end_time":863.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":861.45,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"The other thing that I had was related to Google campaigns as well.","index":318,"end_time":868.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":864.73,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Just the other ones that are not performing well.","index":319,"end_time":872.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":868.41,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"The.","index":320,"end_time":872.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":872.11,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"The price offer, automated one, we dropped the budget significantly.","index":321,"end_time":880.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":874.03,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And then also our Amazon Connect 1 is not performing.","index":322,"end_time":883.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":880.55,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So at what point do we, you know, do we reconfigure?","index":323,"end_time":888.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":883.95,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Do we scrap them?","index":324,"end_time":889.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":888.55,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Like, is there like a standard?","index":325,"end_time":891.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":889.83,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re coming up on that time right now.","index":326,"end_time":893.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":892.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":327,"end_time":894.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":893.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re seeing like volume come through, but not the quality of leads.","index":328,"end_time":898.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":894.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s where we''re like, okay, it''s time to make changes or scrap this.","index":329,"end_time":901.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":898.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Our teams, I mean, that Amazon one we''ve been running for a long time and that has done nothing.","index":330,"end_time":906.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":902.66,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, the Amazon one doesn''t have much traffic at all.","index":331,"end_time":909.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":906.82,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":332,"end_time":910.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":909.62,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So should we just kill it?","index":333,"end_time":911.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.1,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I think so.","index":334,"end_time":912.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":911.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":335,"end_time":913.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":912.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It gets killed.","index":336,"end_time":913.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":913.06,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"What I''d like to see us come up with is the process on these.","index":337,"end_time":916.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.26,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Like, we build something and let''s use RingCentral as an example.","index":338,"end_time":919.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":916.74,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"The new one we got coming out, we run it, we let it sit for four weeks, six weeks, whatever it is.","index":339,"end_time":925.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.66,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Colin, I guess we look for your recommendation and then after we evaluate at that point, make changes, and then we evaluate again at three months, and then we kill it after six months if it''s.","index":340,"end_time":935.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.91,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"If it''s not getting traffic.","index":341,"end_time":936.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.27,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So I''d like to see some sort of formalized process around how we want to do that.","index":342,"end_time":940.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.39,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, I can write that up.","index":343,"end_time":942.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":344,"end_time":942.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":942.35,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That way we''re sticking to the script on it.","index":345,"end_time":945.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":943.79,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":346,"end_time":946.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":945.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On the Google stuff, we''ve run two pmax campaigns that have not went well.","index":347,"end_time":966.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":960.52,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Should we just not do PMAX campaigns because they do tend to eat budget?","index":348,"end_time":971.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":968.28,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t think pmax is.","index":349,"end_time":973,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":971.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think with a competitive landscape, it''s proven not to be the most effective method.","index":350,"end_time":978.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":973.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So do we need to kill our PMAX campaigns then?","index":351,"end_time":981.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.9,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, I would say so.","index":352,"end_time":984.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":982.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m gonna have our team go in and do a more thorough audit of the.","index":353,"end_time":986.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":984.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The price offer campaign and then see if it''s worth rebuilding that as a regular search campaign or move to A totally different focus.","index":354,"end_time":997.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":989.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":355,"end_time":998.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":997.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll have information on that next week.","index":356,"end_time":1005.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1004.11,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yes.","index":357,"end_time":1006.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1006.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, Lindsey, what else did you have?","index":358,"end_time":1013.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1006.99,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We talked about making sure that we have journeys.","index":359,"end_time":1021.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1016.35,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So when people land on our landing page that, you know, every landing page that, you know, it addresses all of the potential search queries that people are doing and that there''s places for them to go and that we kind of funnel them there afterward.","index":360,"end_time":1035.289,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1021.87,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I was going to do kind of an internal audit on that as well, but it was definitely something that I had on the list to discuss here today.","index":361,"end_time":1042.369,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1035.289,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":362,"end_time":1043.169,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1042.849,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ve been weighing that in as I created, like, even just for example, the Ringcentral page, utilizing like one.","index":363,"end_time":1049.369,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1043.169,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The info that Matt sent over with some research that we put together, but also giving them a lot of options to click through and go to other content.","index":364,"end_time":1055.729,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1049.369,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":365,"end_time":1058.809,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1058.369,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So I do want to talk about that a little bit.","index":366,"end_time":1060.689,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1058.809,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So I think what I want to make sure we''re doing.","index":367,"end_time":1062.529,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1060.689,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And my thought on this is when we''re doing, let''s use the Ringcentral as an example.","index":368,"end_time":1067.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1063.08,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You know, they Googled something to get to us, Right?","index":369,"end_time":1070.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1067.8,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They Googled something or they did something to get to us.","index":370,"end_time":1072.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.6,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Are we answering those questions that we want people to get when they land on our page?","index":371,"end_time":1078.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So whatever they''re googling, are we somewhere on the page answering that question, whether it''s Ringcentral Sucks, RingCentral Alternatives, UCAS Alternatives.","index":372,"end_time":1086.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1078.84,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Are we directly answering those questions in the page?","index":373,"end_time":1090.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1086.84,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I want to make sure we''re doing that.","index":374,"end_time":1092.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1091.05,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yep.","index":375,"end_time":1093.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1092.65,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"The other side of that is if, like on the Ringcentral page, we need to make sure we are doing the journey as Lindsay had.","index":376,"end_time":1099.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1093.37,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But we got a ton of Ringcentral blogs now.","index":377,"end_time":1101.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1099.17,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I want to say four or five.","index":378,"end_time":1102.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1101.13,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So we should be linking those in that.","index":379,"end_time":1104.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1102.65,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"In that page somewhere.","index":380,"end_time":1108.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1107.61,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And then we also have the Ringcentral.","index":381,"end_time":1110.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1108.61,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Why do you.","index":382,"end_time":1113.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1112.33,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"What do I want to say?","index":383,"end_time":1114.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1113.61,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"What''s the one we just built the Ringcentral.","index":384,"end_time":1116.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1114.45,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I want to call it a quiz, but what should we call those Assessments?","index":385,"end_time":1120.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1116.27,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Assessments.","index":386,"end_time":1120.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1120.27,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"We also.","index":387,"end_time":1121.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1120.91,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''ve been calling them quizzes.","index":388,"end_time":1123.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1121.43,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"The RingCentral assessment, which we should be using in there also.","index":389,"end_time":1126.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1123.55,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Is that ready to deploy on there or once we finalize the form, it''s right?","index":390,"end_time":1131.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1127.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, yeah, I mean, if you guys.","index":391,"end_time":1132.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.11,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Have you guys finalized the form we talked about last week or no.","index":392,"end_time":1134.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1132.39,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what I was confirming today.","index":393,"end_time":1136.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1135.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can.","index":394,"end_time":1136.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1136.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can go ahead and finalize that.","index":395,"end_time":1138.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1136.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, I lost my train of thought, but yes.","index":396,"end_time":1143.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1141.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I also want to add a carousel at the bottom with those RingCentral blogs to automatically feed in anytime you write a new one.","index":397,"end_time":1149.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1143.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, yeah, that''s a good idea, but I''m thinking we have the blogs right in the copy, not just a rotating list of them, like somewhere in here.","index":398,"end_time":1156.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1150.28,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We just have it as a tile or something like that.","index":399,"end_time":1159.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1156.88,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"About talking more about it.","index":400,"end_time":1160.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.28,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay.","index":401,"end_time":1161.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1161.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":402,"end_time":1162.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1162.6,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I''ll go back through the content.","index":403,"end_time":1163.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1162.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Am I wrong?","index":404,"end_time":1164.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1163.8,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Am I wrong?","index":405,"end_time":1165.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1164.52,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"No, it''s just more locations for them to click through.","index":406,"end_time":1167.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1165.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t want it as an.","index":407,"end_time":1172.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1171.71,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t want stuff like that as an afterthought.","index":408,"end_time":1174.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1172.55,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I think I want it built into the pages more.","index":409,"end_time":1175.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1174.15,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, like, hey, you get.","index":410,"end_time":1178.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1175.95,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Did you get all the.","index":411,"end_time":1178.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1178.03,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t want it like, as.","index":412,"end_time":1179.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1178.75,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Did you get all the information you need?","index":413,"end_time":1180.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1179.55,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Here''s more down here.","index":414,"end_time":1181.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1180.83,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I want.","index":415,"end_time":1182.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1181.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is part of the.","index":416,"end_time":1182.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1182.03,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I want it to be part of the information, I think is probably the best way to describe it.","index":417,"end_time":1186.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1182.87,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I got you.","index":418,"end_time":1187.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1186.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if we could lead with maybe a little bit of the teaser or maybe the AI summary of it as part of that blog, too.","index":419,"end_time":1196.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1188.83,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"As part of the tile.","index":420,"end_time":1197.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1196.23,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":421,"end_time":1198.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1198.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":422,"end_time":1198.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1198.37,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s how I started it.","index":423,"end_time":1199.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1198.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I want to make sure we''re doing that going forward for all new pages.","index":424,"end_time":1206.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1203.69,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yep, absolutely.","index":425,"end_time":1208.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1207.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":426,"end_time":1208.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1208.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All following the AI approach that we talked about.","index":427,"end_time":1210.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1208.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''re going to come right behind this one with a Comcast one.","index":428,"end_time":1213.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1210.89,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay.","index":429,"end_time":1214.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1214.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Will be the next one coming right out right up behind this one.","index":430,"end_time":1217.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1215.61,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I actually almost finished the first blog on it.","index":431,"end_time":1220.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1217.89,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s got probably one more revision I got to go through it on, but it''s pretty close.","index":432,"end_time":1227.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1223.7,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t have a ton of content on Comcast yet, but by a week from now, when we talk, I''ll have three blogs up.","index":433,"end_time":1234.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1228.02,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And I already built the assessment for Comcast already.","index":434,"end_time":1240.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1235.86,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Basically, now that I have the template, it''s easy for me just to change out ring to Comcast.","index":435,"end_time":1246.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1240.98,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":436,"end_time":1247.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1247.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I guess that''s one thing we were talking through last week as well.","index":437,"end_time":1250.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1247.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if the assessments are staying relatively the same as far as just what information they''re collecting, then we can have one that just updates dynamically based on page title.","index":438,"end_time":1259.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1250.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if they''re going to ask different questions, then we would just need different forms.","index":439,"end_time":1263.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1260.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They potentially could ask different questions.","index":440,"end_time":1266.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1264.91,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay.","index":441,"end_time":1267.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1267.07,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"You know, I don''t want them so generic that they''re all the same.","index":442,"end_time":1270.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1268.91,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right.","index":443,"end_time":1271.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1270.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to make sure I customize it specifically to the users so they feel engaged by it.","index":444,"end_time":1276.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.15,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yep.","index":445,"end_time":1277.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1277.07,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Cool.","index":446,"end_time":1278.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1278.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just wanted to confirm there.","index":447,"end_time":1279.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1278.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Especially if it only cost me one Colin Buck.","index":448,"end_time":1285.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1283.05,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"One Colin V. Buck.","index":449,"end_time":1286.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1285.37,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"There you go.","index":450,"end_time":1288.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1288.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":451,"end_time":1305.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1304.89,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That was Everything I had on my list all month.","index":452,"end_time":1307.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1305.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s that said?","index":453,"end_time":1309.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1308.74,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Have you guys avoided being sick all month?","index":454,"end_time":1311.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1309.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have told you.","index":455,"end_time":1312.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1311.78,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You just mentioned it.","index":456,"end_time":1313.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.66,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Me, Me and my wife, My daughter''s been passing something back and forth for like a month.","index":457,"end_time":1318.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1314.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I never go anywhere.","index":458,"end_time":1320.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1318.98,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And I''m almost like a agoraphobe now with where I just don''t want to go out and I don''t because I don''t want to get sick because everybody''s got the flu.","index":459,"end_time":1328.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1320.1,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And yeah, like we going out to eat last night and I came back home, I had to wash my hands super hard and.","index":460,"end_time":1334.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1328.14,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Like.","index":461,"end_time":1336.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1336.33,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Where do you want to sit?","index":462,"end_time":1337.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1336.61,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I want to sit in that far corner all by myself.","index":463,"end_time":1339.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1337.21,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":464,"end_time":1339.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1339.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where no one sat all day.","index":465,"end_time":1341.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1339.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":466,"end_time":1342.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1341.69,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Matt, I gotta get a picture of you in this hat.","index":467,"end_time":1347.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1345.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Love it.","index":468,"end_time":1351.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1350.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":469,"end_time":1352.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1351.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I gotta.","index":470,"end_time":1355.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1354.49,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I got the mug too, but the mug''s at the other.","index":471,"end_time":1356.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1355.09,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Nice.","index":472,"end_time":1359.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1358.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":473,"end_time":1364.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1364.18,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"That was everything I had on my list.","index":474,"end_time":1365.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1364.54,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So you''re going to take a look through that Ringcentral campaign again or the website?","index":475,"end_time":1369.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1365.78,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yep.","index":476,"end_time":1370.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1370.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the campaign.","index":477,"end_time":1371.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1370.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think once we narrow that, once we nail that template, Colin, this should be pretty easy to continue to roll out.","index":478,"end_time":1375.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1371.22,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely.","index":479,"end_time":1377.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1375.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actually, I do have one more question.","index":480,"end_time":1378.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1377.62,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We have written probably.","index":481,"end_time":1383.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1381.94,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"How many blog topics do we have now?","index":482,"end_time":1384.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1383.34,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Probably 80.","index":483,"end_time":1385.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384.9,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"How many have we written?","index":484,"end_time":1388.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1387.72,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''m running out of content to talk about, you know, that we haven''t already talked about.","index":485,"end_time":1395.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1389.88,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And I can, I can write on the same topics again if I need to.","index":486,"end_time":1398.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1395.72,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Just do it differently.","index":487,"end_time":1400.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1399,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So my thought is, is that we''re kind of heading down this road of going after my next evolution of this is kind of like, I''m right.","index":488,"end_time":1406.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1401.24,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We''re doing these competitive pages, right.","index":489,"end_time":1408.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1406.56,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Ring Comcast, write a couple blogs on it.","index":490,"end_time":1411.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1408.6,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We link it is.","index":491,"end_time":1413.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.36,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Do we think that''s a strong way to go over basically regurgitating content, existing generic content that may have more of an appeal.","index":492,"end_time":1422.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1413.61,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Right.","index":493,"end_time":1422.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1422.49,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Like, hey, what''s Shake and Stir?","index":494,"end_time":1424.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1422.97,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Or what''s.","index":495,"end_time":1425.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1424.49,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Why is your call being marked as spam?","index":496,"end_time":1427.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1425.37,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You know, we could write on.","index":497,"end_time":1428.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1427.57,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I could write five or six blogs on that with the same content over and over again.","index":498,"end_time":1431.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1428.53,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And that probably has a higher search volume than some of this blog stuff that we''re writing.","index":499,"end_time":1436.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1431.77,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"What that''s very competitive, focused.","index":500,"end_time":1437.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1436.21,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So thought is what, where are we better going with something like that?","index":501,"end_time":1442.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1438.54,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So I don''t think it''s an all or nothing strategy.","index":502,"end_time":1444.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1442.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think you still have some of the like more term based things like that, but also the content that is much more suited towards someone that is currently a Ringcentral customer or is clearly looking for alternatives, you know, based on like, like the RingCentral page again as an example.","index":503,"end_time":1459.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1444.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know you''re talking about blogs, but having a mix of the content that we''re putting on the website allows like Google and ChatGPT to understand the breadth of expertise that you have and without boring the user as well.","index":504,"end_time":1475.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1460.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":505,"end_time":1476.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1475.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, because I guess my question is specifically, and I apologize, Colin, I might not have asked it right.","index":506,"end_time":1482.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1477.35,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Am I better off doing regurgitated content or continuing to write new content on competitors?","index":507,"end_time":1490.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1483.11,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"And what.","index":508,"end_time":1491.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1491.15,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Go ahead, I''ll let you answer that.","index":509,"end_time":1492.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1491.55,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, so I would say it''s not.","index":510,"end_time":1494.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1492.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I say with my all, not all or nothing.","index":511,"end_time":1496.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1494.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think you would still have some of the like regurgitated content.","index":512,"end_time":1499.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1496.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think you would have some new content on competitors, but you''d also have new content.","index":513,"end_time":1502.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1499.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would recommend maybe on like thought leadership or like why having a trustworthy phone system and support team in place is so vital to the health of a business.","index":514,"end_time":1512.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1502.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":515,"end_time":1515.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1514.67,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So a mix.","index":516,"end_time":1517.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1516.76,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":517,"end_time":1518.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1517.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":518,"end_time":1520.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1520.28,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Hopefully that response was much more succinct.","index":519,"end_time":1527.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1525.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s fine.","index":520,"end_time":1529.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1528.36,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I hate rewriting.","index":521,"end_time":1533.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1532.6,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I mean.","index":522,"end_time":1534.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1533.64,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Or should I just go back?","index":523,"end_time":1535.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1534.08,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"The other question is, should I just go back and take some of the blogs you''ve already written, rewrite them to be more direct as far as AI, what do I want to say?","index":524,"end_time":1545.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1535.72,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"AI Friendly.","index":525,"end_time":1547.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1546.22,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"AI Intent friendly.","index":526,"end_time":1549.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1547.66,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Because we weren''t initially writing as AI Friendly intent.","index":527,"end_time":1551.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1549.18,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":528,"end_time":1552.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1551.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if I take an existing blog, basically rewrite it, make it more AI Intent friendly, and then put a different title on it, I could do that pretty easy.","index":529,"end_time":1559.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1552.42,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":530,"end_time":1560.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1559.82,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"And I would keep that on the existing blog because you then you have the authority that the blog''s already built up over time.","index":531,"end_time":1565.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1560.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":532,"end_time":1566.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1565.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, that sounds like no fun.","index":533,"end_time":1570.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1567.58,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Maybe I''ll teach Chris how to do that.","index":534,"end_time":1572.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1570.55,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Probably build.","index":535,"end_time":1575.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1574.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like creating.","index":536,"end_time":1576.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1575.27,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t like fixing.","index":537,"end_time":1577.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1576.07,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, you could probably create a tool that does it.","index":538,"end_time":1579.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1577.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably could.","index":539,"end_time":1580.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1579.91,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Not quite ready to give control over Colin, where I don''t.","index":540,"end_time":1584.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1581.67,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t read stuff before it goes out.","index":541,"end_time":1586.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1584.43,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, well, yeah, 100.","index":542,"end_time":1589.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1586.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know a lot of people do that.","index":543,"end_time":1592.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1591.11,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"A lot of people do that.","index":544,"end_time":1593.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1592.59,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I just can''t quite do that yet.","index":545,"end_time":1595.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1593.67,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we have a lot of safeguards in place, a lot of read only permissions, things like that.","index":546,"end_time":1601.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1596.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, that''s everything I had.","index":547,"end_time":1604.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1603.7,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":548,"end_time":1606.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1606.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lindsey, anything else from your end?","index":549,"end_time":1608.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1607.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was wondering if you had a chance to take a look at the Bing ads platform and see if Ringcentral is blacking out their replacement terms.","index":550,"end_time":1620.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1609.46,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"There as well.","index":551,"end_time":1621.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1620.42,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I have not checked today, but I''ll get you that in our updates on the campaigns.","index":552,"end_time":1626.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1621.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":553,"end_time":1630.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1629.8,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":554,"end_time":1639,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1638.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, if anything else pops up, please do email me, but we''ll be in touch with a few emails this week and more updates in our next call.","index":555,"end_time":1649,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1642.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":556,"end_time":1649.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1649.57,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Thank you for your help this morning.","index":557,"end_time":1651.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1650.37,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":558,"end_time":1652.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1651.73,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":559,"end_time":1652.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1652.29,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Glad that was a quick fix.","index":560,"end_time":1654.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1652.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Me, too.","index":561,"end_time":1655.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1655.09,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":562,"end_time":1656.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1655.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And just if there''s, like, ever any code or anything you need to inject, if you have a question, just please feel free to reach out.","index":563,"end_time":1662.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1656.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":564,"end_time":1663.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1663.01,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":565,"end_time":1664.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1663.97,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":566,"end_time":1665.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1664.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":567,"end_time":1668.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1668.29,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"See you guys.","index":568,"end_time":1669.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1668.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See ya.","index":569,"end_time":1669.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1669.41,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"}],"dateString":"2026-01-27T20:00:00.000Z","host_email":"lhall@techmode.com","meeting_link":"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_ODBmZWFjMWYtMWIxYi00NmZmLTgyMDEtOWFiZWJhYWEwYzVh@thread.v2/0?context={\"Tid\":\"3801011d-e732-48ee-be2a-e499b1a29ba4\",\"Oid\":\"e804fbe9-a623-4d26-a887-992e62fb92d1\"}","participants":["cquigley@techmode.com,michael.lewis@techmode.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,lhall@techmode.com,mlook@techmode.com,rfisher@techmode.com","cquigley@techmode.com","michael.lewis@techmode.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","mlook@techmode.com","rfisher@techmode.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFVMZ6X58G44BZH75BW18RM9","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.9,"bullets":["Aligned on building and reviewing RingCentral page, with blog integration and assessment strategy.","Decided to retire underperforming Amazon Connect and PMAX campaigns due to low traffic and ROI.","Lindsay flagged 3CX ''looking to move'' ad group underperforming; Colin to issue recommendations.","Agreed to document formalized process for campaign evaluation timelines and next-step decisions.","Established new template model to streamline rollout of future competitor landing pages like Comcast."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I think once we narrow that, once we nail that template, Colin, this should be pretty easy to continue to roll out.","speaker":"Matthew Look"},{"quote":"Yeah, I can write that up.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"The 3Cx support ad group is performing much better than seeing a lot more traffic than the looking to move ad group.","speaker":"Lindsay Hall"}],"topics":["launch","delivery","performance","ads","process"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-0613","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-27T23:51:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Website Content and SEO Strategy**\n\nThe team is finalizing the **RingCentral page design and content** to improve SEO alignment and user engagement (01:39).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** integrated extensive keyword research with Matthew Look’s document to create page copy ready for design and review.\n- The page will include multiple blog posts, a carousel feature for dynamic blog display, and embedded assessments to guide user journeys.\n- Matthew emphasized embedding competitor-related queries directly in the content to capture search intent like “RingCentral Alternatives” or complaints, ensuring visitors find answers immediately.\n- Future pages, starting with a **Comcast page next week**, will follow this model, including customized assessments tailored to specific user questions rather than generic forms.\n- This approach aims to boost organic search relevance and engagement by linking blogs, assessments, and rich content within the main pages.\n\nContent evolution will combine **new competitor-focused blogs with repurposed content** enhanced for AI search intent (23:01).\n\n- Colin recommended a balanced mix of fresh competitor content, repurposed blogs optimized for AI and search engines, and thought leadership pieces on communication system importance.\n- Matthew plans to rewrite existing blogs with AI-friendly titles and formats to capitalize on their established authority.\n- Christopher Quigley supported maintaining existing blog authority rather than discarding older posts.\n- This strategy targets both competitive keywords and broader industry topics to widen reach and maintain relevance.\n\n## **Form Management and Integration**\n\nThe team resolved issues with **Gravity Forms and HubSpot email integration**, opting to send emails via HubSpot for reliability (04:05).\n\n- Colin explained that Gravity Forms will feed data into HubSpot, which then sends confirmation emails, avoiding SMTP failures.\n- This setup requires building and connecting each form in HubSpot, which costs about **one “Colin V Buck” ($100)** per form creation (06:00).\n- To optimize costs and efficiency, the team agreed to **batch build forms** ahead of demand, enabling quick updates and deployment.\n- Forms may differ in fields per assessment, so some customization will remain necessary, but shared infrastructure will speed execution.\n\nThis system balances user experience with backend reliability and reduces email delivery failures affecting lead capture.\n\n## **Advertising Campaign Performance and Optimization**\n\nSeveral **Google ad campaigns are underperforming**, prompting a review and formal process for campaign evaluation and adjustment (13:04).\n\n- The **3Cx “looking to move” ad group is inactive**, while the “3Cx support” group shows stronger traffic and engagement, per Lindsey Hall and Matthew Look.\n- The **Amazon Connect campaign has minimal traffic and no results** and will be discontinued immediately (15:10).\n- Matthew proposed a **formal campaign lifecycle:** run new campaigns for 4–6 weeks, then review and adjust based on quality and volume; re-evaluate at 3 months; kill if ineffective after 6 months.\n- Colin agreed to document this evaluation and decision process to ensure consistent campaign management.\n- **Performance Max (PMax) campaigns have not yielded good results** and will be discontinued, with an audit underway to decide whether to rebuild as standard search campaigns or pivot (16:00).\n\nThis structured approach aims to maximize marketing ROI by focusing on high-quality leads and stopping ineffective spend quickly.\n\n## **User Journey and Landing Page Optimization**\n\nLanding pages will be designed to **answer user search queries directly and guide visitors through relevant content journeys** (16:56).\n\n- Lindsey emphasized the need to audit landing pages to ensure they cover all potential search intents and provide clear paths to related content.\n- Colin is incorporating multiple options for users to click through from pages like RingCentral, including blogs and assessments.\n- Matthew wants these linked resources integrated as core content, not afterthoughts, to keep users engaged and better informed.\n- The strategy focuses on creating seamless journeys from landing pages to deeper content, improving user experience and conversion potential.\n\nThis will help capture users’ intent fully and nurture them toward conversion through targeted, layered content.\n\n## **Technology Tools and Development Initiatives**\n\nColin shared recent work building tools using **Supabase database, Claude code AI, and Lovable front-end** to support internal and client solutions (08:57).\n\n- These tools enable dynamic design and data integration, showing the company is advancing automation and user-friendly platforms.\n- Colin mentioned plans for a **new client portal rollout** incorporating these technologies to enhance client interactions and operational efficiency.\n- Matthew is exploring options to automate blog rewriting for AI optimization but prefers manual control for quality assurance.\n\nThese tech initiatives aim to scale operations, improve the client experience, and keep pace with evolving AI and web design tools.","outline":null,"keywords":["RingCentral","HubSpot integration","Google campaigns","blog layout","Gravity Forms","AI content strategy"],"overview":"- **Website SEO Strategy:** Finalizing RingCentral page to enhance SEO and user engagement through blogs and assessments.\n\n- **Content Evolution:** Combining new competitor blogs with optimized existing posts to broaden reach and maintain authority.\n\n- **Form Management:** Gravity Forms will integrate with HubSpot for reliable email confirmation, costing $100 per form built.\n\n- **Ad Campaign Review:** Underperforming Google ad campaigns will follow a structured lifecycle for evaluation and adjustment every few weeks.\n\n- **User Journey Focus:** Landing pages will guide visitors by answering queries and linking to related content for better engagement.\n\n- **Tech Initiatives:** Developing tools with Supabase and AI to improve client interactions and operational efficiency, plus a new client portal.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend RingCentral page design and copy for team review (02:09)\nBuild blog post category templates once Lindsey provides category list (04:03)\nFinalize HubSpot forms integration, handling routing for multiple Gravity Forms (08:15)\nConduct thorough audit of price offer campaign and evaluate future direction (16:22)\nCreate written process for campaign evaluations with timelines for testing, changes, and kills (15:40)\nReview and send recommendations for underperforming Google ad groups including 3Cx and Amazon Connect (13:50)\nImplement enhanced internal linking and embed blog and assessment content directly into competitor landing pages like RingCentral (19:10)\nCheck Bing ads platform for RingCentral trademark blocking and provide update (26:49)\n\n**Lindsay Hall**\nProvide list of blog categories to Colin for template building (04:03)\nSend batch of form IDs needed for HubSpot implementation to Colin (07:59)\nConduct internal audits on customer journey flows on landing pages to ensure full query coverage and funnel paths (16:56)\n\n**Matthew Look**\nContinue writing RingCentral and Comcast competitor blogs including assessments (20:14)\nPrepare content revisions focused on AI intent for existing blogs and coordinate rewriting (24:51)\nProvide batch lists of new form IDs for HubSpot integration to Colin (07:59)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"b3a7dbd0-5aed-4a6e-ac72-5af2c8b87150","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
