    '{"id":"01KFVE50V07MED9GV4XWPPKMNE","title":"KTC // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Website Development and Branding**\n\nThe website is nearly finished with **14 fully developed pages**, and branding updates are underway to simplify the company name presentation (08:24).\n\n- **Michael Kersten requested changing all instances of \"Kirsten Town Capital\" to \"KTC Search\"** on banners and logos, especially on the contact page, to create a cleaner brand identity (09:29).\n    - This includes updating email addresses and replacing logos where the full company name appears.\n    - The goal is to remove the full name for easier customer recognition and branding consistency.\n    - Colin confirmed progress is visible in HubSpot and that the website is coming together well.\n    - This branding update aligns with a streamlined market positioning strategy for easier recall.\n\n- **The team plans to finalize design elements including music and voiceover options, with follow-up due by tomorrow** per Michael’s instruction to send final materials for Kristen’s budget review (13:36).\n    - Michael emphasized prompt feedback to keep production on schedule.\n    - This ensures the website’s multimedia elements support engagement and brand tone.\n\n## **Sales Pipeline Integration and CRM Testing**\n\nThe integration of sales data into HubSpot is still incomplete, with limited deal imports observed as of the meeting (10:10).\n\n- **Michael flagged missing deals from Richie May and questioned if the team was working in a sandbox environment** instead of live production (10:10).\n    - Colin confirmed that the current activity looks like sandbox testing without active imports.\n    - Michael noted that development was expected to finish by the end of the month, so full data import should follow soon.\n    - This affects visibility into the sales pipeline and requires monitoring to ensure seamless CRM adoption.\n\n- **Colin offered to investigate the data import details further if provided with more information**, signaling readiness to support resolving integration issues promptly (10:56).\n    - Ensuring full data flow is critical for pipeline management and campaign targeting.\n\n## **Advertising Campaign Strategy and Execution**\n\nThe team developed initial ad copy with **three headline variants** targeting executive search differentiation and cost benchmarking (12:04).\n\n- **Michael and Colin discussed expanding marketing focus beyond retained search to include contingent and fractional services**, aligning budget allocation with revenue priorities (12:34).\n    - Retained searches remain the primary revenue driver; contingent and fractional are secondary targets.\n    - Colin confirmed infrastructure is ready to add new campaigns swiftly by creating related content and landing pages.\n    - This flexible setup allows quick pivoting as market segmentation priorities evolve.\n\n- **Campaign design and copywriting are underway, with the first ads to be delivered shortly for review** (13:36).\n    - Messaging emphasizes competitive advantages like faster hiring and exclusive candidate access.\n    - The approach aims to stop prospects from scrolling and increase engagement rates.\n\n## **LinkedIn Business Manager Setup and Access Control**\n\nMichael has no prior experience with LinkedIn Business Manager, so Colin and Paula will provide detailed setup instructions to allow proper ad account and page management (14:05).\n\n- **LinkedIn Business Manager will centralize company page and ad account control**, enabling secure access delegation to the marketing team (14:44).\n    - This setup avoids past issues where agencies retained client access indefinitely.\n    - Michael will create the business account and invite the agency for editing permissions.\n    - Once set up, the agency will update the LinkedIn company page with new branding and manage campaigns.\n\n- **This process is critical for maintaining client ownership and clear accountability over ad spend and page content** (15:27).\n    - Colin is holding off on major updates until full clarity on the Richie May integration is achieved.\n    - The approach reflects a shift toward client-controlled digital assets with agency collaboration.\n\n## **Content Calendar and Project Timeline**\n\nContent calendar updates are stable with ongoing collaboration between Kristen and the team, maintaining alignment on deliverables (15:45).\n\n- **The website launch is approaching completion, with full site readiness expected shortly before campaign rollout** (16:00).\n    - After launch, the team can redesign or reformat based on user feedback or market needs.\n    - Michael confirmed he will send the Richie May deck and KTC Search materials for final integration.\n    - Finalizing these materials will support cohesive messaging across sales and marketing channels.\n\n- **The combined progress points to a full-steam-ahead approach, emphasizing speed and flexibility in launching marketing efforts** (16:00).\n    - This momentum aligns with quarterly goals to increase market presence and lead generation.","outline":null,"keywords":["Website branding","HubSpot integration","LinkedIn Business Manager","Marketing campaigns","Content calendar","Executive search"],"overview":"- **Website Development:** 14 pages nearly complete; branding update transitioning to \"KTC Search\" for consistency and recognition.\n\n- **Sales Pipeline Integration:** Active CRM imports are low; need full data flow by month-end for visibility and monitoring.\n\n- **Ad Campaign Strategy:** Three headline variants created; focus expanding to contingent and fractional services for broader market reach.\n\n- **LinkedIn Business Manager Setup:** Centralization of ad accounts planned; clear access control to maintain client ownership and accountability.\n\n- **Content Calendar Progress:** Website ready before campaign launch; materials to align sales and marketing messaging across channels.","action_items":"\n**Michael Kersten**\nSend Richie May deck for integration with KTC Search materials (16:15)\nRespond to marketing team’s follow-up on music and voiceover review by next day (13:43)\nComplete LinkedIn Business Manager setup following instructions and invite marketing team for access (16:41)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nUpdate website banners and contact page to replace full company name with ''KTC Search'' and update logos and email addresses accordingly (08:24)\nContinue website development and finalize color scheme and design upon feedback (08:24)\nMonitor Richie May deal import status and investigate HubSpot sandbox/testing environment if needed (10:10)\nSend voiceover and background music options again for review (13:36)\nSend detailed LinkedIn Business Manager setup instructions to Michael Kersten and Paula Ocampo (14:05)\nPrepare marketing campaign designs based on headline variants and new segment campaigns (12:04)\nUpdate LinkedIn company page and ad account once business manager access is granted (15:20)\nCoordinate content calendar updates with Kristen and Paula, maintaining progress (15:45)\n\n**Paula Ocampo**\nAssist with sending out LinkedIn Business Manager setup instructions and support Michael with setup questions (16:44)\n\n**Kristen**\nContinue work on content calendar and coordinate updates with marketing team (15:45)\n"},"duration":17.049999237060547,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"id":2,"name":"Michael Kersten"}],"sentences":[{"text":"How''s it going?","index":0,"end_time":255.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":1,"end_time":257.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.38,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"It''s been a crazy day actually for me, so.","index":2,"end_time":260.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.74,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":3,"end_time":261.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":261.14,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"What about you?","index":4,"end_time":262.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":261.86,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Always a crazy day, Paula.","index":5,"end_time":265.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I need to get used to.","index":6,"end_time":268.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":266.58,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Hey, guys.","index":7,"end_time":447.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":446.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hey, Michael.","index":8,"end_time":448.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":9,"end_time":449.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":448.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":10,"end_time":450.249,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":449.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":11,"end_time":450.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450.249,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, good.","index":12,"end_time":451.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":451.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So, hey, couple things.","index":13,"end_time":454.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Whoops.","index":14,"end_time":455.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":454.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Touch the screen.","index":15,"end_time":457.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":456.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You disappeared.","index":16,"end_time":457.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":457.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":17,"end_time":458.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":457.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Keep.","index":18,"end_time":459.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":459.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Keep plowing down the way that we''re going.","index":19,"end_time":462.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":459.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, obviously we talked a little bit that.","index":20,"end_time":465.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I''m thinking I may.","index":21,"end_time":468.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.15,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"For purposes of.","index":22,"end_time":469.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":469.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What I want to do is keep it stand status quo because really all we''re trying to do is, is, is handle billings.","index":23,"end_time":475.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":469.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So to me, leave it to Brand.","index":24,"end_time":478.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":476.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And you know, I can from a billing standpoint.","index":25,"end_time":481.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":478.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hey, they''re, they''re my billing agent.","index":26,"end_time":483.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":481.829,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, there''s.","index":27,"end_time":484.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":483.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I can wordsmith that differently.","index":28,"end_time":486.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":485.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"The one question I did have though is on the, on the web pages, if you bring those web pages up, the one, the one where it goes across where it says Kirsten Town Capital, can we can of the, the spelling out the.","index":29,"end_time":499.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":487.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All that out and just put KTC Search.","index":30,"end_time":501.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":499.29,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It was on one of the banner ones.","index":31,"end_time":502.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":501.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I forget which page it was on.","index":32,"end_time":503.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I just noticed that.","index":33,"end_time":504.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I was actually going to show an update because we have, we have 11 or, sorry, 14 pages that have been fully developed and we''re going to go back through.","index":34,"end_time":515.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just wanted to talk more about our conversation on Friday to see like how much we want to change colors wise.","index":35,"end_time":521.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can just keep rolling as you''re going, so.","index":36,"end_time":524.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":522.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep, cool.","index":37,"end_time":525.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":524.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay.","index":38,"end_time":526.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":526.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it was something.","index":39,"end_time":527.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":526.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was a banner that said curse and talent.","index":40,"end_time":529.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":527.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it was something that was on one of the pages.","index":41,"end_time":533.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":529.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It was like going right across the top.","index":42,"end_time":535.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":533.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys may have already caught it.","index":43,"end_time":536.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":535.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It was, it was second.","index":44,"end_time":539.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":536.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I can pull up the email you sent.","index":45,"end_time":540.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":539.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m pulling it up now.","index":46,"end_time":542.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the email that you sent me on those links, it was on that.","index":47,"end_time":546.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":542.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Ah, I got it.","index":48,"end_time":569.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was on the contact page.","index":49,"end_time":570.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":50,"end_time":571.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":570.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":51,"end_time":572.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":571.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, so contact KTC Search.","index":52,"end_time":576.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, Put that in there.","index":53,"end_time":577.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":576.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":54,"end_time":577.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":577.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That way, you know, and then I''m assuming you know where we have the logos.","index":55,"end_time":582.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":578.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You''re going to change those logos.","index":56,"end_time":583.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":582.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So like right there where it says get in touch, where it says Kirsten Town.","index":57,"end_time":586.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":583.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll replace that with ktc.","index":58,"end_time":588.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":586.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":59,"end_time":588.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":588.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":60,"end_time":589.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":588.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because the key is I''d like to get my, my complete name off there, you know, so, you know, obviously it doesn''t look like it, you know, a little bit easier from that standpoint.","index":61,"end_time":597.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":589.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep, yep.","index":62,"end_time":598.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":597.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":63,"end_time":598.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":598.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll update like the email addresses and everything like that.","index":64,"end_time":600.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":598.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Too.","index":65,"end_time":601.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":600.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":66,"end_time":601.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":601.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I mean obviously you''re in your HubSpot, so you can see all the progress you''re making.","index":67,"end_time":605.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have all of these pages already built out.","index":68,"end_time":607.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":605.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":69,"end_time":608.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Things are coming together really nicely.","index":70,"end_time":609.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":71,"end_time":610.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":610.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hey, quick question while you''re in there because you may be able to see I was messing.","index":72,"end_time":613.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":610.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I have a call with them on Friday.","index":73,"end_time":614.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":613.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Can you tell over on the, on the sales thing?","index":74,"end_time":618.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":615.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Can you see, you know, I don''t, I know they were working on, you know, bringing my stuff over, but I don''t see any of the deals coming over, especially from like Richie May.","index":75,"end_time":627.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t see that they.","index":76,"end_time":628.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":627.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t know if they''re testing it in a non production environment or if it''s that.","index":77,"end_time":632.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":628.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is that it?","index":78,"end_time":632.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":632.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This might be a test.","index":79,"end_time":634.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They may have stood up a sandbox.","index":80,"end_time":638.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if their account has the same box.","index":81,"end_time":639.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s like an enterprise level.","index":82,"end_time":641.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":639.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is.","index":83,"end_time":641.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":641.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m on enterprise.","index":84,"end_time":642.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":641.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay.","index":85,"end_time":642.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":642.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So maybe they did stand up a sandbox and just didn''t invite us.","index":86,"end_time":645.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":642.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":87,"end_time":646.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":645.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then if we go to deals.","index":88,"end_time":648.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":647.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, because it''s like I don''t see, you know, it looks like they''re messing with stuff, but I don''t, you know, like the Richie May stuff.","index":89,"end_time":654.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":649.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"There should be like a bunch of different ones in there, you know.","index":90,"end_time":656.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":654.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, I gotcha.","index":91,"end_time":657.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m not, I''m not as familiar with like where they''re at and everything they''re doing.","index":92,"end_time":662.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":658.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I''m happy to dive into the details if you want to share anything and want us to check it out.","index":93,"end_time":667.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Happy to do that.","index":94,"end_time":669.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":95,"end_time":669.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":669.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":96,"end_time":670.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":669.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, but from what I can see, it doesn''t look like they''ve imported much.","index":97,"end_time":673.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, let me see, what apps did they connect?","index":98,"end_time":676.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I got a lot in here.","index":99,"end_time":680.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":100,"end_time":681.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean I don''t see them like actively doing it.","index":101,"end_time":689.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just looks like they''re testing to me.","index":102,"end_time":690.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":689.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":103,"end_time":691.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":690.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay.","index":104,"end_time":692.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":691.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":105,"end_time":698.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":697.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":106,"end_time":699.819,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":698.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What''s in here?","index":107,"end_time":701.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":701.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":108,"end_time":707.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":706.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it looks like they''re working through Automations, but it looks like this was added a while ago.","index":109,"end_time":710.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, they must be in sandbox.","index":110,"end_time":712.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":711.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I was in there the other night.","index":111,"end_time":713.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":712.83,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I was like, all right, I don''t see anything.","index":112,"end_time":714.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":713.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I mean they said that the development was supposed to be done the end of the month, so I guess we''ll wait and see.","index":113,"end_time":722.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":714.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay.","index":114,"end_time":723.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":722.83,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":115,"end_time":726.789,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":724.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, we''ll keep plowing ahead on that then.","index":116,"end_time":728.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":726.789,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":117,"end_time":729.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":728.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve also written some ads, so these are getting designed.","index":118,"end_time":732.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":730.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I always like to show some copy though.","index":119,"end_time":734.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the big thing is always the headline.","index":120,"end_time":737.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":734.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s going to stop someone from scrolling.","index":121,"end_time":738.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":737.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we came up with three variants to start with our test.","index":122,"end_time":741.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"An open executive C costs more than you think, being the headline.","index":123,"end_time":745.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":742.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then benchmarking your hiring process.","index":124,"end_time":747.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So talking really about how you''re able to get movement in these a lot faster than competitors.","index":125,"end_time":754.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":747.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":126,"end_time":756.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":754.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Now, hey, quick question just from a standpoint is I know we talked about this, but some of the stuff that I was talking to with Alex, which is F3, is I''m putting some budget numbers there where contingent was kind of primary.","index":127,"end_time":766.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":756.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m sorry, retained primary, contingent second.","index":128,"end_time":769.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":766.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And the fractional.","index":129,"end_time":770.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":769.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If we, as we start kind of figuring out, hey, where we want to market to, obviously retain is where the real money is.","index":130,"end_time":775.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":770.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But if we wanted to add another segment in there, like, hey, we''re going after fractional stuff, we can kind of build that in there too.","index":131,"end_time":783.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":775.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that way, hey, when we''re going out retake, we can help you with retain, we can help you with contingent.","index":132,"end_time":787.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":783.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We can help you with, you know, you know, fractional.","index":133,"end_time":790.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":787.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All three type services.","index":134,"end_time":792.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":790.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":135,"end_time":792.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":792.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":136,"end_time":793.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":792.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I won''t share the whole diagram, but we put together a lot of different tools into a map.","index":137,"end_time":797.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so when we want to load an extra campaign or anything, we already have all of that already set up.","index":138,"end_time":801.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":797.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can just add it in.","index":139,"end_time":802.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":801.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we just have to write the content, the landing page.","index":140,"end_time":804.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":802.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all that stuff.","index":141,"end_time":805.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":804.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":142,"end_time":805.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":805.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":143,"end_time":806.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":805.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Confidential Executive searches was another one.","index":144,"end_time":808.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then your competitors are finding the leaders that you''re not.","index":145,"end_time":812.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":146,"end_time":813.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":812.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That one I really liked.","index":147,"end_time":814.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":813.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":148,"end_time":815.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":814.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"No, that''s good.","index":149,"end_time":815.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":815.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":150,"end_time":817.289,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":816.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll get those designed and sent over.","index":151,"end_time":818.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":817.289,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wanted to check if you''ve had a chance or if Kristen''s had a chance to review the music options that we sent over as well.","index":152,"end_time":823.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":818.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, let me.","index":153,"end_time":824.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":823.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So do me a favor.","index":154,"end_time":828.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":826.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Send.","index":155,"end_time":829.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":829.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"When we''re done, just send out whoever.","index":156,"end_time":830.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":829.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If it''s you, Paul, or just kind of say, hey, I need this done.","index":157,"end_time":833.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":830.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Copy, Senator, Copy me.","index":158,"end_time":835.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":834.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then I''ll just respond back, hey, can you get back to her?","index":159,"end_time":837.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":835.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Get back to them by tomorrow.","index":160,"end_time":840.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":838.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She was working on some budget stuff, so she probably did.","index":161,"end_time":843.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":840.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":162,"end_time":843.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":843.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":163,"end_time":845.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":845.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the voiceover and the.","index":164,"end_time":846.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":845.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The background music will send that over again and then I''m not sure.","index":165,"end_time":850.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you ever set up a LinkedIn business manager?","index":166,"end_time":853.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have one that exists or like an ad account or anything?","index":167,"end_time":855.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":853.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I. I never done it before.","index":168,"end_time":858.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":856.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So if you tell me how to do it, I''m sure I can kind of do it.","index":169,"end_time":860.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":858.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So you just have to tell me how to.","index":170,"end_time":861.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":860.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What I need to do.","index":171,"end_time":862.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":861.83,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":172,"end_time":862.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":862.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":173,"end_time":863.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":862.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":174,"end_time":863.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":863.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Paula, we can.","index":175,"end_time":864.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":863.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can really copy and paste these instructions, so it''ll walk you through creating a business account.","index":176,"end_time":867.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":864.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The reason that we have our clients do that is because years ago, that wasn''t a possibility.","index":177,"end_time":871.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":868.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We would get access to their account, and then it was just up to them.","index":178,"end_time":874.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, if we entered our contract, there''s still clients, like, two years later that I would be.","index":179,"end_time":879.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":874.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have access to all their information.","index":180,"end_time":880.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":879.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We don''t like that.","index":181,"end_time":881.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":880.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why we recommend going through this process.","index":182,"end_time":883.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When we say LinkedIn business manager, what is that?","index":183,"end_time":886.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":884.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Am I adding that to my personal.","index":184,"end_time":887.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":886.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Or am I adding that to my.","index":185,"end_time":888.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":887.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So LinkedIn business manager is basically like where you say, I manage my page and I manage my ad account from here.","index":186,"end_time":895.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":889.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s pretty much all it is.","index":187,"end_time":897.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":896.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s like a Facebook business manager.","index":188,"end_time":898.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It just holds your page in your account.","index":189,"end_time":900.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":898.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":190,"end_time":901.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":900.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So you.","index":191,"end_time":901.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":901.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And you''ll send me the instructions how to set up.","index":192,"end_time":903,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":901.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is it.","index":193,"end_time":903.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":903.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is it.","index":194,"end_time":904.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":903.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is it bringing both my personal and the company one into that?","index":195,"end_time":906.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":904.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"No, it''ll just be a business page.","index":196,"end_time":908.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Business page and an ad account.","index":197,"end_time":909.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":908.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":198,"end_time":910.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":909.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":199,"end_time":910.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":910.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then we''ll give you.","index":200,"end_time":912.239,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":201,"end_time":912.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":912.239,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You just have to invite our id, and then we''ll.","index":202,"end_time":914.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":912.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll be in there.","index":203,"end_time":915.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":204,"end_time":916.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":915.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then for my LinkedIn company page, you know, you got.","index":205,"end_time":919.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":916.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys will update all that too, right?","index":206,"end_time":921.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":919.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":207,"end_time":921.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":921.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay.","index":208,"end_time":922.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":922.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":209,"end_time":922.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the KTC search stuff.","index":210,"end_time":923.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":211,"end_time":924.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":923.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So when I do this, does that give you access to go in there and update all that stuff too?","index":212,"end_time":927.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":924.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":213,"end_time":928.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when you do the business manager, you''ll be able to assign us to also be able to edit your page and your ad account, and that''s where we can make that.","index":214,"end_time":934.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":928.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was just holding off on.","index":215,"end_time":935.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":934.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On writing, like, a lot of those changes until we have the full direction from what''s happening with you and Richie Mae and how all this is coming together.","index":216,"end_time":942.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, no, go ahead and plow through the way we''re going.","index":217,"end_time":944.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":942.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":218,"end_time":945.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":944.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":219,"end_time":945.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":945.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Cool.","index":220,"end_time":945.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":945.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":221,"end_time":946.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":945.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":222,"end_time":947.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":946.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then everything else other than that was just if there''s been any updates on the content calendar.","index":223,"end_time":950.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":947.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know Kristen''s been working on this stuff as well, so I haven''t seen any changes.","index":224,"end_time":956.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":950.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll just keep that conversation evolving.","index":225,"end_time":958.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":956.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that one''s good.","index":226,"end_time":959.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":958.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":227,"end_time":960.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":959.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But, yeah, that''s pretty much it.","index":228,"end_time":961.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":960.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re.","index":229,"end_time":961.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":961.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re full steam ahead, getting close to finishing the website, and then after that, we can kind of go on launch campaigns.","index":230,"end_time":970.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":961.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can reformat redesign if we need to, you know, whatever kind of you need for this situation.","index":231,"end_time":975.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":970.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":232,"end_time":976,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":975.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then.","index":233,"end_time":976.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":976,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"On our.","index":234,"end_time":976.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":976.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"On our deck.","index":235,"end_time":977.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":976.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"On the deck.","index":236,"end_time":978.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":977.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I need to send that over to you.","index":237,"end_time":979.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":978.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys can take the RM deck, which is all my contact.","index":238,"end_time":982.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":979.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We just had the RM stuff on there.","index":239,"end_time":983.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":982.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And you can that KTC search stuff, too, correct?","index":240,"end_time":987.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":983.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":241,"end_time":987.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":987.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, if you send that over, we can get that done.","index":242,"end_time":989.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":243,"end_time":990.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":989.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":244,"end_time":991.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":990.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I think that''s pretty much everything, Paul.","index":245,"end_time":992.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":991.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there anything I''m missing?","index":246,"end_time":993.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":992.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Please keep me honest.","index":247,"end_time":994.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":993.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think that''s all awesome.","index":248,"end_time":997.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":994.9,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"All right, well, short and sweet, Michael.","index":249,"end_time":999.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":997.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like it.","index":250,"end_time":999.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":999.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Talk to you guys soon.","index":251,"end_time":1000.499,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":999.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":252,"end_time":1000.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1000.499,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":253,"end_time":1001.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1000.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You send me the instructions on that, and then I''ll make sure I get that done today.","index":254,"end_time":1004.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1001.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":255,"end_time":1004.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1004.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":256,"end_time":1005.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1004.54,"speaker_name":"Paula Ocampo"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":257,"end_time":1006.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1005.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2026-01-27T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83519004309?pwd=JvKSZR6BzSlyNxK5WTgZHYayMsLSKi.1&jst=2","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,michael@kerstentalentcapital.com,kristen@kerstenta