WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '1194e57c-a4a6-4e1e-bac3-83c4ff3c4ad7',
    '2026-01-26 18:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KFCV8D4AF5NTB9ZZ13RDED23',
    'Gallagher & Mohan // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Colin Costigan","Nathalie Mintjens","Doug"}'::text[],
    957,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83518678110?pwd=MiWMBPC8T7FkFpRVsa3mZByA9Y76FA.1',
    '{"id":"01KFCV8D4AF5NTB9ZZ13RDED23","title":"Gallagher & Mohan // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Contact List Expansion and Multi-Level Outreach Strategy**\n\nThe team expanded the target contact list to nearly **2,400 contacts**, adding about **600 new C-suite and executive-level contacts** to improve outreach breadth and quality (05:34).\n\n- **Colin Costigan explained** that automating outreach to multiple levels, including mid-tier contacts, increases overall engagement by sparking internal conversations at target companies.\n- This approach frees up sales reps’ time by automating initial touches, allowing reps to focus on qualified leads identified through these sequences.\n- The strategy leverages multiple touchpoints to create a “water cooler” effect where lower-level contacts pass interest internally toward decision makers.\n- Ongoing monitoring and adjustments will ensure the outreach targets the right contacts and adapts to response patterns for better efficiency.\n\n## **Content and Campaign Development with Adjusted Offers**\n\nThe team plans to deliver email sequences, LinkedIn messaging, and landing page copy by **Wednesday**, while reevaluating the offer strategy after reservations about the calculator tool were expressed (07:31).\n\n- Doug raised concerns about the calculator offer’s fit with brand messaging, emphasizing the need to balance attracting clients and top talent without appearing solely cost-focused.\n- Colin committed to developing alternative offers and sending them over for review, ensuring alignment with the company’s strategic messaging.\n- A content calendar focusing on organic social media and blog posts will replace podcast efforts temporarily due to internal bandwidth constraints.\n- This phased content approach maintains engagement while allowing the client team to focus on immediate priorities.\n\n## **Advertising Budget and Multi-Channel Integration**\n\nThe agreed starting monthly ad budget is between **$1,000 and $1,500**, intended to run alongside ABM efforts across multiple channels including programmatic display and retargeting (09:00).\n\n- Colin explained that paid ads will complement email and LinkedIn outreach by reinforcing messaging when contacts visit related sites like the Wall Street Journal.\n- Doug confirmed willingness to increase spend beyond current levels if the campaigns show positive ROI.\n- Ads will be managed via direct credit card connections to advertising platforms, eliminating agency fees and simplifying billing.\n- This multi-channel setup aims to maximize reach and frequency efficiently while providing clear budget control and scalability.\n\n## **LinkedIn Automation and Email Warm-Up Execution**\n\nLinkedIn connection requests and messaging will be automated through the agency’s platform, sending outreach from their environment but appearing as personal messages (13:41).\n\n- Doug will connect his LinkedIn profile to the tool as instructed, enabling automated but personalized outreach.\n- The email accounts for this campaign are already warming up to improve deliverability and open rates.\n- This automation supports scaling outreach to the expanded contact list without increasing manual workload.\n- Visibility into outreach progress will be provided via the Pulse portal, which offers real-time transparency and tracking of tasks.\n\n## **Client Portal Transparency and Collaboration Framework**\n\nThe Pulse portal will serve as a transparent collaboration hub where Doug and his team can track progress, see deliverables, and monitor outstanding items (12:36).\n\n- Colin confirmed that password resets are available every 24 hours to ensure continuous access.\n- This transparency promotes trust and faster feedback cycles by giving the client direct insight into all ongoing work.\n- The portal will include updates on email content, landing pages, LinkedIn messaging, and the evolving content calendar.\n- This setup supports efficient communication and reduces bottlenecks in the campaign execution process.\n\n## **Strategic Patience on Podcast and Content Series**\n\nDue to current workload and team availability, the podcast content series will be paused, with a focus shifting to more manageable content formats for now (11:40).\n\n- Doug indicated his team is too swamped for podcast production, preferring to revisit this format later.\n- Colin proposed creating a content calendar focused on blogs and social media posts that require less client time.\n- This approach aims to keep content flowing without overburdening the client team or sacrificing quality.\n- Future podcast efforts can resume when internal capacity and priorities better align.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM outreach","email marketing","LinkedIn automation","content calendar","paid advertising budget","marketing collaboration"],"overview":"- **Contact List Expansion:** Target contact list grew to **2,400**, adding **600 C-suite contacts** for better outreach and engagement.\n\n- **Outreach Strategy:** Automating outreach boosts engagement and frees up sales reps to focus on qualified leads.\n\n- **Content Development:** Email sequences and LinkedIn messaging due by **Wednesday**; need to adjust offers for brand alignment.\n\n- **Ad Budget:** Monthly ad budget set at **$1,000-$1,500**, integrating across channels to enhance messaging and reach.\n\n- **LinkedIn Automation:** Outreach will be automated for personalized communication; email accounts are warming up to improve deliverability.\n\n- **Client Portal Use:** The Pulse portal ensures transparency in progress tracking and enhances communication with the client team.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated contact list including 600 new C-suite contacts to client (05:34)\nDeliver finalized email and LinkedIn outreach copy plus landing page content by Wednesday (07:31)\nProvide framework and questions needed for calculator offer data by Wednesday (07:56)\nSend client authorization form for ad spend and instructions for linking credit card to advertising platforms (10:54)\nCreate and share a content calendar proposal for organic blog and social media posts by next Monday (12:04)\nSupport client login to Pulse portal and manage password reset requests as needed (12:36)\nSend instructions for connecting LinkedIn profile to outreach tool and upload contact list for automated messaging (13:30)\nShare overall marketing updates, including email warming and multi-channel strategy progress, with client (14:00)\n\n**Doug**\nReview email and LinkedIn outreach content upon delivery (07:31)\nConfirm ad budget and authorize payment setup for advertising spend (10:56)\nAttempt Pulse portal login and request password reset if access fails (12:36)\nDiscuss content calendar and podcast plans internally, especially with new team member David Willett, before making final decisions (15:06)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nReview ABM task set and email sequence requirements to ensure smooth content integration (02:57)\n"},"duration":15.949999809265137,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":2,"name":"Doug"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Those new headphones?","index":0,"end_time":15.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":14.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I''ve had them for a while.","index":1,"end_time":18.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.72,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I just never use them.","index":2,"end_time":19.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":18.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Do you guys get hit bad with snow?","index":3,"end_time":27.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yesterday it was like I don''t know how many inches but it was like from the moment I woke up at like 7.","index":4,"end_time":36.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":29.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Didn''t stop until like 10pm yeah, same here.","index":5,"end_time":40.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":37.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And ice.","index":6,"end_time":41.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":7,"end_time":41.929,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":41.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":8,"end_time":43.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I had to.","index":9,"end_time":45.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.17,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I went to church in that like took the bus and everything and they gave us all free coffee for making it.","index":10,"end_time":51.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":45.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, Our church canceled.","index":11,"end_time":53.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":52.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They went virtual.","index":12,"end_time":54.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":53.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh.","index":13,"end_time":55.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.64,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":14,"end_time":57.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":56.88,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I think we were about 13 inches last I saw.","index":15,"end_time":60.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":16,"end_time":62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And did most people around you like they''d have to drive there?","index":17,"end_time":64.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"What do you mean?","index":18,"end_time":68.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":67.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like versus taking a train or something?","index":19,"end_time":72.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"No, there''s like buses and trains and stuff that flow through the town.","index":20,"end_time":76.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I imagine most people are driving.","index":21,"end_time":79.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":77.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s very, very old.","index":22,"end_time":82.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":81.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Give a few more minutes here.","index":23,"end_time":172.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If he''s unable to join, if you can just send him an update.","index":24,"end_time":175.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":172.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everything we had in our deck.","index":25,"end_time":176.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":175.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":26,"end_time":177.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":177.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh, also for.","index":27,"end_time":182.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":181.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think you sent me a note about the set of ABM tasks for them that some things need to move around because what was it we needed like the email sequence or something?","index":28,"end_time":195.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Oh yeah.","index":29,"end_time":196,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":195.52,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"We need the content before we can really like set up a lot of the other things.","index":30,"end_time":199.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":196,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll take a look at that.","index":31,"end_time":202.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":201.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m still like familiarizing myself with these new.","index":32,"end_time":205.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":203.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":33,"end_time":206.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":206.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know I moved the training because I was in eight and a half hours back to back on Friday.","index":34,"end_time":210.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":206.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just needed some time back.","index":35,"end_time":212.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, with the new ABM setup because of all the automations and everything that we connect together, we need the content to be flowing pretty like minimal changes before we launch.","index":36,"end_time":222.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":213.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":37,"end_time":224.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":223.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hey, Doug.","index":38,"end_time":239.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":39,"end_time":240.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I can''t hear you for some reason.","index":40,"end_time":242.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":240.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about now?","index":41,"end_time":248.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":248.05,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yep, working.","index":42,"end_time":249.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":249.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":43,"end_time":250.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":250.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, good.","index":44,"end_time":251.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":251.09,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":45,"end_time":252.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":251.65,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"All right.","index":46,"end_time":253.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":252.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t remember where you''re located.","index":47,"end_time":255.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you get hit with a storm?","index":48,"end_time":257.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not really, no.","index":49,"end_time":259.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":258.75,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I''m in Atlanta.","index":50,"end_time":261.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":260.03,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":51,"end_time":262.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They still close things down.","index":52,"end_time":263.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":262.27,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But no, not.","index":53,"end_time":264.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":263.55,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"There''s nothing really happened, to be honest.","index":54,"end_time":266.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":264.59,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":55,"end_time":266.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":266.47,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":56,"end_time":267.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, that''s good.","index":57,"end_time":268.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":267.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m in Maryland.","index":58,"end_time":272.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie''s in Chicago.","index":59,"end_time":273.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I was just telling her we got about 13 inches last I checked.","index":60,"end_time":277.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, wow.","index":61,"end_time":278.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.71,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re in Maryland again.","index":62,"end_time":280.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":278.51,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Are you like Baltimore area?","index":63,"end_time":281.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":280.03,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Frederick.","index":64,"end_time":281.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m 45 minutes from Baltimore.","index":65,"end_time":283.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"45 minutes from D.C. okay.","index":66,"end_time":284.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":67,"end_time":285.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":284.9,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That''s crazy.","index":68,"end_time":287.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":286.66,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That''s.","index":69,"end_time":287.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":287.42,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":70,"end_time":288.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":288.42,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Because my friends, I have a lot of friends that are in Arlington or like Fairfax.","index":71,"end_time":293.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":288.78,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like they only got like five inches, I think.","index":72,"end_time":295.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":293.26,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":73,"end_time":296.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":74,"end_time":296.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":296.06,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That''s where Tristan and Justin are like the Richmond area and they only got like two inches and mostly ice.","index":75,"end_time":300.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s crazy.","index":76,"end_time":302.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":301.22,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Thirteen.","index":77,"end_time":302.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.34,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That''s a lot.","index":78,"end_time":303.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.62,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I guess you''re like way more inward, right?","index":79,"end_time":304.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":303.06,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re, we''re like northwest Maryland pretty much.","index":80,"end_time":308.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":305.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"West Virginia and Pennsylvania are like a third drive.","index":81,"end_time":310.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":308.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":82,"end_time":310.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":310.5,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Nice.","index":83,"end_time":311.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":311.38,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Cool.","index":84,"end_time":312.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":311.7,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":85,"end_time":313.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.3,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Where are you again, Nathalie?","index":86,"end_time":318.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":315.86,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I''m in Chicago, so I don''t think most people here noticed.","index":87,"end_time":323.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.14,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It''s just another Sunday in January in Chicago.","index":88,"end_time":326.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":323.14,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, always noticed.","index":89,"end_time":327.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":326.34,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":90,"end_time":329.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":327.78,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It''s like a huge event for us, but.","index":91,"end_time":331.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":329.9,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":92,"end_time":334.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, we''ll dive in.","index":93,"end_time":336.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":335.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so we got several updates.","index":94,"end_time":343.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ve updated the contact list based on the feedback that you sent over.","index":95,"end_time":347.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that added a few probably almost 600 new contacts into the pool from those companies with the more C suite oriented titles.","index":96,"end_time":355.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can send that over to you as well.","index":97,"end_time":357.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just have a preview here.","index":98,"end_time":358.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re at almost 2,400 contacts that we''ve identified at these companies.","index":99,"end_time":363.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so a question I had is like, does it hurt your efforts at all, like if you do go after these people that aren''t really good?","index":100,"end_time":373.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":366.64,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like, like, you know, like for example, there was lower level people, right.","index":101,"end_time":378.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":373.92,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Or like mid level even, where it''s like, it''s probably not like the best use of time for me to like even, you know, talk to them.","index":102,"end_time":386.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":379.76,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But like, maybe I''m wrong, you know, type of thing.","index":103,"end_time":388.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":386.2,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So what''s your point of view?","index":104,"end_time":389.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":388.48,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"There''s.","index":105,"end_time":390.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":389.8,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So I would say, I would say there''s two answers.","index":106,"end_time":392.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":390.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":107,"end_time":392.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":392.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So from your perspective, I 100% agree that it''s not worth your time, but because we''re able to set up these automated sequences, we actually find much better results when we''re starting conversations at multiple levels of the business because they''re having things internally meetings.","index":108,"end_time":406.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":392.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, I saw this thing from Gallagher and Mohan.","index":109,"end_time":408.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, let''s check this out.","index":110,"end_time":409.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":408.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s able to, like I always say the conversation around the water cooler analogy.","index":111,"end_time":413.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Since we''re able to automate these sequences and get in front of more people, I think it''s a good use of that instead of your actual time sending emails.","index":112,"end_time":421.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":414.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":113,"end_time":426.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":424.89,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":114,"end_time":428.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":427.85,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And if these are all like big companies, then, you know, I''m willing to like do meetings and work your way up the chain with people, I guess, because it''s like, I mean, a lot of times it''s just like when you pitch somebody, they''re like, oh no, I''m not interested.","index":115,"end_time":441.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":428.49,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like it was like, yeah, you''re not really the person I''m Trying to sell to anyways, you know.","index":116,"end_time":444.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":441.45,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":117,"end_time":444.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":444.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You get kind of get rejected, you know, and it''s like, you know, so anyways, we can give it a shot, see what happens.","index":118,"end_time":451.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":444.97,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":119,"end_time":452.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll monitor everything as we go.","index":120,"end_time":453.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And update.","index":121,"end_time":454.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are writing the actual email and LinkedIn outreach copy.","index":122,"end_time":459.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":455.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that will be delivered to you on Wednesday as well.","index":123,"end_time":462.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"David Willett on that email that gets me.","index":124,"end_time":465.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":463.21,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yep, no problem at all.","index":125,"end_time":467.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they''re also writing the copy for the landing pages for the key offers that we talked about.","index":126,"end_time":472.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the institutional retail focus and then also that calculator.","index":127,"end_time":476.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll.","index":128,"end_time":477.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":476.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the calculator one we''ll probably need to send over some questions of just like the base data that sometimes you guys are able to collect.","index":129,"end_time":482.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":477.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you started working on the calculator yet or.","index":130,"end_time":484.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.62,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"No.","index":131,"end_time":484.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re putting together the framework for it.","index":132,"end_time":486.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s what we''ll send over of like, hey, we just need to know if you can.","index":133,"end_time":488.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":486.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":134,"end_time":489.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":488.82,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Me and David talked about it and I mean we''re not like 100% sold that if it''s like a good like how we want to present it, you know, necessarily.","index":135,"end_time":499.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":489.14,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":136,"end_time":503.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.22,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"We definitely don''t want on the website.","index":137,"end_time":505.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.7,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":138,"end_time":505.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":505.3,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"We''re talking about like in general.","index":139,"end_time":508.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":505.62,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I don''t know if this would be.","index":140,"end_time":509.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":508.34,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Because it''s like, you know, half of our business is also making sure we''re attracting like the best talent, you know, so it doesn''t look good when you''re just like, oh, we''re like, this is like, you know, we''re cheaper than people in the U.S. you know what I mean?","index":141,"end_time":521.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":509.94,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like that''s not really kind of like what, you know, doesn''t really inspire people, I guess.","index":142,"end_time":526.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":521.26,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And so it''s like, so that''s like what we were talking about.","index":143,"end_time":530.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.42,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And the other thing is, I don''t know, I mean, maybe it''s good for like a like attention grab thing, but we''re not like insanely sold on it, I guess.","index":144,"end_time":539.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":530.76,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":145,"end_time":540.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well we''ll think through some more offers then and we''ll send those over to you guys to muddle through and are noodle on.","index":146,"end_time":545.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":147,"end_time":548,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":547.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then on your intake form, you guys indicated a thousand dollar monthly ad budget.","index":148,"end_time":552.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just wanted to confirm that that''s accurate.","index":149,"end_time":553.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Say it again.","index":150,"end_time":555.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":555.17,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"You.","index":151,"end_time":556.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":556.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So on the intake form that you guys filled out, you said that you have a thousand dollars for monthly ad budget on top of our agency.","index":152,"end_time":561.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":556.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that, is that accurate?","index":153,"end_time":563.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":561.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what I do currently on my own.","index":154,"end_time":565.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":563.73,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":155,"end_time":565.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":565.41,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":156,"end_time":566.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.77,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Is that like, do you guys do you guys need a budget for like, that''s like other efforts.","index":157,"end_time":572.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":566.29,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But do you want like, were you expecting a thousand for this as well or.","index":158,"end_time":575.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":572.29,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":159,"end_time":575.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we like to have paid ads as a layer on top of this.","index":160,"end_time":578.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because we''re getting multiple channels involved, we''re able to hit someone once more where they are.","index":161,"end_time":583.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":578.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":162,"end_time":584.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":583.75,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"First, so for doing like the abm, like for this list.","index":163,"end_time":587.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":584.27,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":164,"end_time":588.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":587.55,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":165,"end_time":588.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''d be advertising them to them on a few different channels as well as like programmatic display.","index":166,"end_time":592.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if they go to the website after seeing an email and then go to like Wall Street Journal, they''re still getting hit with your ad.","index":167,"end_time":597.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":592.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, and so how do.","index":168,"end_time":599.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":598.79,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I mean, is the, is a thousand dollars like the right amount?","index":169,"end_time":602.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":599.79,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"What do you, I mean I, I didn''t, I think I misunderstood the question in the forum.","index":170,"end_time":605.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":602.11,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I was.","index":171,"end_time":606.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.15,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That''s what I pay now, currently.","index":172,"end_time":607.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.59,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":173,"end_time":608.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":607.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":174,"end_time":608.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m willing to pay more.","index":175,"end_time":609.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":608.67,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like it would work, you know, obviously.","index":176,"end_time":611.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":609.95,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":177,"end_time":611.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":611.43,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like right now like with our efforts, like we almost like can''t even spend a thousand dollars.","index":178,"end_time":615.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":611.79,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I don''t know why, you know, so it''s like, like if I want, like I would, obviously I would want to.","index":179,"end_time":620.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":615.15,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"If it works, right?","index":180,"end_time":622.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":620.35,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yep.","index":181,"end_time":622.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":622.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":182,"end_time":623.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":622.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what I always recommend is starting out with like a pilot budget of between $1,000 and $1,500.","index":183,"end_time":627.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then when we start to see like, okay, this is generating results, we can pour more into here, let''s turn it off here.","index":184,"end_time":633.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":628.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''re going to constantly run like new tests that, that''s where we''ll, over the first few months we''ll be like, okay, this is where we''re getting the most return on our investment from ads.","index":185,"end_time":641.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this is where we run into like that glass ceiling.","index":186,"end_time":643.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we, even if we spend more, we''re not getting any results.","index":187,"end_time":645.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":643.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so all right, so okay, so a thousand dollars is fine then, right?","index":188,"end_time":653.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":646.13,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I mean, and how do I pay that amount to you guys?","index":189,"end_time":656.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":653.53,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So it''ll be.","index":190,"end_time":657.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll actually hook up your credit card directly to the advertising platform.","index":191,"end_time":660.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We don''t take a agency fee or anything like that.","index":192,"end_time":663.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":660.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, yeah.","index":193,"end_time":665.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":664.4,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"All right, well that''s fine.","index":194,"end_time":666.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":665.6,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I can do a thousand or fifteen hundred, just whatever makes sense, I guess.","index":195,"end_time":670.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":666.56,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":196,"end_time":671.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll also send over just an authorization form.","index":197,"end_time":674.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":198,"end_time":676.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ve also designed a few different quote cards for the show.","index":199,"end_time":682.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So a few different names in here that utilize your guys branding.","index":200,"end_time":686,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one being inside the deal, another underwriting reality.","index":201,"end_time":690.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then behind the portfolio were three initial name concepts that we came up with.","index":202,"end_time":694.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, this is for the podcast?","index":203,"end_time":697.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":696.19,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, the content series.","index":204,"end_time":699.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":205,"end_time":701.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":700.59,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I don''t know, it''s like.","index":206,"end_time":705.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":704.35,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It''s like the same thing I was saying last time.","index":207,"end_time":706.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":705.31,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like, I understand, you know, this is like.","index":208,"end_time":708.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":706.79,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It''s just.","index":209,"end_time":709.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":708.75,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I don''t know, we''re just like, so swamped, right?","index":210,"end_time":713.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":710.67,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It''s like, not like, good timing for us to, like, focus on this, to be honest.","index":211,"end_time":716.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":713.15,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I gotcha.","index":212,"end_time":717.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":716.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So is there other, Is there, like, other ways that we could, like, focus on, know, our team''s attention than, like, the podcast stuff?","index":213,"end_time":723.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":718.03,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, we can table this and we can start maybe just coming up with a content calendar instead, where it''s like, this is what we should post about organically from a blog perspective.","index":214,"end_time":732.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":724.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is what social media should be talking about, things like that.","index":215,"end_time":734.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we can come back to this when time is more available.","index":216,"end_time":737.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":734.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, yeah.","index":217,"end_time":739.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":738.23,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Cool.","index":218,"end_time":740.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.47,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"There''s some other designs in there as well.","index":219,"end_time":743.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":220,"end_time":746.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, and then did you have any questions of navigating Pulse or anything?","index":221,"end_time":750.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":746.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you get the invite?","index":222,"end_time":750.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Were you able to log in?","index":223,"end_time":752.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I didn''t.","index":224,"end_time":754.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":753.61,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I saw you send it.","index":225,"end_time":755.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":754.13,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I didn''t log in though.","index":226,"end_time":755.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":755.01,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":227,"end_time":756.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":756.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, let me know.","index":228,"end_time":757.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":756.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Whenever you try, There is a 24 hour reset on the password, so if it doesn''t let you in, just let me know and I''ll send you a new one.","index":229,"end_time":762.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s just where I see the updates of where you''re at, right?","index":230,"end_time":765.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":763.13,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s our.","index":231,"end_time":766.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":765.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s our completely transparent portal.","index":232,"end_time":768.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":766.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you see everything we''re working on, anything we''re waiting on you on, etc.","index":233,"end_time":772.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":768.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":234,"end_time":774.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":774.34,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":235,"end_time":777.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":775.3,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Any other updates from your end?","index":236,"end_time":779.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":778.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not really, no.","index":237,"end_time":784.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":783.22,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":238,"end_time":784.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":784.3,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"All right, so we have a lot of deliverables coming to you on Wednesday being like the email content landing pages and everything we''re putting together, we''ll think through also some new offers to replace the calculator idea, and then we''ll put together a content calendar, probably sharing that on Monday of next week for just a way around the content series for now.","index":239,"end_time":801.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":784.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":240,"end_time":802.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":802.52,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And what about, like, LinkedIn stuff?","index":241,"end_time":804.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":802.8,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Are you.","index":242,"end_time":804.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":804.28,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"You said that''s like part of your deliverable as well, right?","index":243,"end_time":807.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":804.76,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Correct?","index":244,"end_time":807.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":807.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the LinkedIn messages and everything.","index":245,"end_time":809.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":807.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''re already setting up the platforms that we would be connecting your profile to.","index":246,"end_time":812.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":809.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll send you instructions to log in and just hit connect.","index":247,"end_time":815.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":812.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I actually connect with the people, like physically.","index":248,"end_time":820.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":818.52,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"No, no, no, no.","index":249,"end_time":821.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On.","index":250,"end_time":822.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you just need to connect your profile to the tool and then everything else from there is automated.","index":251,"end_time":826.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":822.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":252,"end_time":827.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":826.84,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"All right, Got it.","index":253,"end_time":828.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":827.93,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":254,"end_time":829.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll upload this list, and then it''ll go through mimicking human behavior.","index":255,"end_time":834.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":829.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Send a connection request on my actual.","index":256,"end_time":836.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":834.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Browser or on your environment.","index":257,"end_time":838.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":836.33,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It''ll send it all from our environment.","index":258,"end_time":839.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":838.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":259,"end_time":840.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":840.33,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But I''ll see, like, obviously the messages.","index":260,"end_time":842.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":841.21,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And stuff when they come correct.","index":261,"end_time":843.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":842.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":262,"end_time":844.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":263,"end_time":845.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":844.97,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":264,"end_time":846.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":846.09,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And we''ve already got your emails warming up and everything.","index":265,"end_time":850.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":847.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just to kind of.","index":266,"end_time":851.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":850.17,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So for this list of 2,000.","index":267,"end_time":853.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":851.17,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Whatever.","index":268,"end_time":853.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":853.01,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":269,"end_time":853.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":853.45,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So just some, like, understanding the goal is, you know, we''re email blasting, right?","index":270,"end_time":860.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":854.32,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yep.","index":271,"end_time":860.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":860.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your LinkedIn messaging.","index":272,"end_time":864.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":860.96,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yep.","index":273,"end_time":865.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":864.64,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And we are doing SEO stuff that''s.","index":274,"end_time":868.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":865.2,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And advertising.","index":275,"end_time":869.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":868.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":276,"end_time":869.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":869.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s directly targeted to them.","index":277,"end_time":872.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":870.32,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":278,"end_time":872.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":872.24,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":279,"end_time":873.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":872.6,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":280,"end_time":875.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":874.56,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And the.","index":281,"end_time":876.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":875.76,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"The messaging, the podcasting is not really related.","index":282,"end_time":879.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":876.56,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It''s not like ABM particularly.","index":283,"end_time":881.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":879.28,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":284,"end_time":881.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":881.08,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It''s not ABM particular.","index":285,"end_time":882.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":881.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s more of a content engine that we can like.","index":286,"end_time":884.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like, you saying not having time is actually perfect.","index":287,"end_time":888.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":885.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s.","index":288,"end_time":888.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":888.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s why we kind of create these things, because if we get 30 minutes of you, a month or a week or whatever it is, that''s all you have to do.","index":289,"end_time":894.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":888.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''re able to get, like, hey, we got two white papers out of that episode.","index":290,"end_time":897.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":894.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We got five blog posts out of that episode.","index":291,"end_time":900.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s just, like, we''re able to best use your time so that we can syndicate content across different channels.","index":292,"end_time":905.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":293,"end_time":906.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":906.29,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"All right, well, let me think.","index":294,"end_time":910.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":909.49,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So, like, let''s think about it a little more.","index":295,"end_time":912.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":910.89,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I need to get David a little bit more, like, a little bit more situated, too.","index":296,"end_time":916.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":912.73,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"He''d only started, like, a couple weeks ago, so I probably want to.","index":297,"end_time":921.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":916.95,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Probably want to get his opinion, you know?","index":298,"end_time":927.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":925.79,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":299,"end_time":928.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":927.87,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So, yeah, let''s just go from.","index":300,"end_time":930.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":928.99,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Let''s go from there.","index":301,"end_time":931.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":930.43,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":302,"end_time":931.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":931.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":303,"end_time":932.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":931.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, stay warm, Doug.","index":304,"end_time":934.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I really appreciate your time.","index":305,"end_time":935.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":934.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll send over the updates that we were talking about.","index":306,"end_time":937.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":307,"end_time":938.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":937.55,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":308,"end_time":938.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":938.35,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"All right, see you.","index":309,"end_time":939.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":938.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2026-01-26T18:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83518678110?pwd=MiWMBPC8T7FkFpRVsa3mZByA9Y76FA.1","participants":["nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,dougg@gallaghermohan.com,dwillett@gallaghermohan.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","dougg@gallaghermohan.com","dwillett@gallaghermohan.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFCV8D4AF5NTB9ZZ13RDED23","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Added nearly 600 C-suite contacts, expanding total outreach pool to approximately 2,400 leads.","Doug confirmed $1,000–$1,500 budget range for ads; platform access will link directly to card.","Team will deliver email and LinkedIn messaging, landing pages, and ad copy by Wednesday.","Calculator offer likely dropped; new content offers to be proposed for Doug and David to review.","Podcast content tabled; team shifting to blog and social calendar for immediate content strategy."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We are writing the actual email and LinkedIn outreach copy. That will be delivered to you on Wednesday.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"I can do a thousand or fifteen hundred, just whatever makes sense, I guess.","speaker":"Doug"},{"quote":"So we''ve updated the contact list... almost 2,400 contacts that we''ve identified at these companies.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["abm","budget","content","delivery","ads"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-0613","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-26T00:52:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Contact List Expansion and Multi-Level Outreach Strategy**\n\nThe team expanded the target contact list to nearly **2,400 contacts**, adding about **600 new C-suite and executive-level contacts** to improve outreach breadth and quality (05:34).\n\n- **Colin Costigan explained** that automating outreach to multiple levels, including mid-tier contacts, increases overall engagement by sparking internal conversations at target companies.\n- This approach frees up sales reps’ time by automating initial touches, allowing reps to focus on qualified leads identified through these sequences.\n- The strategy leverages multiple touchpoints to create a “water cooler” effect where lower-level contacts pass interest internally toward decision makers.\n- Ongoing monitoring and adjustments will ensure the outreach targets the right contacts and adapts to response patterns for better efficiency.\n\n## **Content and Campaign Development with Adjusted Offers**\n\nThe team plans to deliver email sequences, LinkedIn messaging, and landing page copy by **Wednesday**, while reevaluating the offer strategy after reservations about the calculator tool were expressed (07:31).\n\n- Doug raised concerns about the calculator offer’s fit with brand messaging, emphasizing the need to balance attracting clients and top talent without appearing solely cost-focused.\n- Colin committed to developing alternative offers and sending them over for review, ensuring alignment with the company’s strategic messaging.\n- A content calendar focusing on organic social media and blog posts will replace podcast efforts temporarily due to internal bandwidth constraints.\n- This phased content approach maintains engagement while allowing the client team to focus on immediate priorities.\n\n## **Advertising Budget and Multi-Channel Integration**\n\nThe agreed starting monthly ad budget is between **$1,000 and $1,500**, intended to run alongside ABM efforts across multiple channels including programmatic display and retargeting (09:00).\n\n- Colin explained that paid ads will complement email and LinkedIn outreach by reinforcing messaging when contacts visit related sites like the Wall Street Journal.\n- Doug confirmed willingness to increase spend beyond current levels if the campaigns show positive ROI.\n- Ads will be managed via direct credit card connections to advertising platforms, eliminating agency fees and simplifying billing.\n- This multi-channel setup aims to maximize reach and frequency efficiently while providing clear budget control and scalability.\n\n## **LinkedIn Automation and Email Warm-Up Execution**\n\nLinkedIn connection requests and messaging will be automated through the agency’s platform, sending outreach from their environment but appearing as personal messages (13:41).\n\n- Doug will connect his LinkedIn profile to the tool as instructed, enabling automated but personalized outreach.\n- The email accounts for this campaign are already warming up to improve deliverability and open rates.\n- This automation supports scaling outreach to the expanded contact list without increasing manual workload.\n- Visibility into outreach progress will be provided via the Pulse portal, which offers real-time transparency and tracking of tasks.\n\n## **Client Portal Transparency and Collaboration Framework**\n\nThe Pulse portal will serve as a transparent collaboration hub where Doug and his team can track progress, see deliverables, and monitor outstanding items (12:36).\n\n- Colin confirmed that password resets are available every 24 hours to ensure continuous access.\n- This transparency promotes trust and faster feedback cycles by giving the client direct insight into all ongoing work.\n- The portal will include updates on email content, landing pages, LinkedIn messaging, and the evolving content calendar.\n- This setup supports efficient communication and reduces bottlenecks in the campaign execution process.\n\n## **Strategic Patience on Podcast and Content Series**\n\nDue to current workload and team availability, the podcast content series will be paused, with a focus shifting to more manageable content formats for now (11:40).\n\n- Doug indicated his team is too swamped for podcast production, preferring to revisit this format later.\n- Colin proposed creating a content calendar focused on blogs and social media posts that require less client time.\n- This approach aims to keep content flowing without overburdening the client team or sacrificing quality.\n- Future podcast efforts can resume when internal capacity and priorities better align.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM outreach","email marketing","LinkedIn automation","content calendar","paid advertising budget","marketing collaboration"],"overview":"- **Contact List Expansion:** Target contact list grew to **2,400**, adding **600 C-suite contacts** for better outreach and engagement.\n\n- **Outreach Strategy:** Automating outreach boosts engagement and frees up sales reps to focus on qualified leads.\n\n- **Content Development:** Email sequences and LinkedIn messaging due by **Wednesday**; need to adjust offers for brand alignment.\n\n- **Ad Budget:** Monthly ad budget set at **$1,000-$1,500**, integrating across channels to enhance messaging and reach.\n\n- **LinkedIn Automation:** Outreach will be automated for personalized communication; email accounts are warming up to improve deliverability.\n\n- **Client Portal Use:** The Pulse portal ensures transparency in progress tracking and enhances communication with the client team.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated contact list including 600 new C-suite contacts to client (05:34)\nDeliver finalized email and LinkedIn outreach copy plus landing page content by Wednesday (07:31)\nProvide framework and questions needed for calculator offer data by Wednesday (07:56)\nSend client authorization form for ad spend and instructions for linking credit card to advertising platforms (10:54)\nCreate and share a content calendar proposal for organic blog and social media posts by next Monday (12:04)\nSupport client login to Pulse portal and manage password reset requests as needed (12:36)\nSend instructions for connecting LinkedIn profile to outreach tool and upload contact list for automated messaging (13:30)\nShare overall marketing updates, including email warming and multi-channel strategy progress, with client (14:00)\n\n**Doug**\nReview email and LinkedIn outreach content upon delivery (07:31)\nConfirm ad budget and authorize payment setup for advertising spend (10:56)\nAttempt Pulse portal login and request password reset if access fails (12:36)\nDiscuss content calendar and podcast plans internally, especially with new team member David Willett, before making final decisions (15:06)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nReview ABM task set and email sequence requirements to ensure smooth content integration (02:57)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"fc6f6555-35aa-4b0f-8f30-16106d68231a","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
