  VALUES (
    '059db008-bde9-43e2-b5ea-2d8080194a92',
    '2026-01-26 16:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KFBXWYGDQHESGFDC5KB6S3SR',
    'Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync',
    '{"victor garcia","Colin Costigan","christinazanca","christinazanca","Guille Santana"}'::text[],
    2576,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85439302813?pwd=qMBHtkNo4lURIrnTCVFhLG0k15ZQca.1',
    '{"id":"01KFBXWYGDQHESGFDC5KB6S3SR","title":"Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Website Design and User Experience**\n\nThe website redesign focuses on balancing modern simplicity with brand cohesion to meet diverse executive and audience needs.\n\n- **Christina Zanca highlighted feedback from leadership emphasizing a cleaner balance between line drawings and stock images on brochures and the website, advising against layering both together excessively to avoid visual clutter** (06:56)  \n    - Betty preferred distinct use of either line drawings or stock photos, not both simultaneously.  \n    - The goal is to simplify the brand’s visual language for easier user focus and executive buy-in.  \n    - Future designs will incorporate more white space to reduce busy navigation and emphasize content.  \n    - This approach supports a more modern, sophisticated feel aligned with Ponce’s evolving brand identity.\n\n- **Feedback emphasized tailoring homepage content to four key audience segments: consumer (business and retail), community/foundation, investor relations, and staffing/recruiting** (09:01)  \n    - Executives want clearer representation of commercial and recruitment areas alongside community focus.  \n    - Homepage iterations will include specific content variations for general Ponce Bank, microsites, and recruitment to satisfy executive expectations.  \n    - The homepage will feature placeholders for core sections like hero banners and ads to visually represent these segments early.  \n    - This segmentation will help drive executive alignment and improve targeted messaging.\n\n- **Image selections must reflect current or futuristic themes and better local market relevance, avoiding outdated visuals that suggest stagnation** (11:10)  \n    - Executives noted overrepresentation of Hispanic imagery; diversity should include Caucasian, Bangladeshi, Indian, Asian, and Greek communities.  \n    - Historic images will be reserved for appropriate pages like \"About Us\" to maintain authenticity without undermining innovation.  \n    - Outdated ATM images risk negative perception; Ponce can provide updated photos to improve brand impression.  \n    - Incorporating these changes will better resonate with diverse local audiences and support brand inclusivity.\n\n- **Visual design adjustments include reducing repetitive blue bar elements and using them strategically to complement hero sections, with more white or light color space in subsections** (13:50)  \n    - Line drawings may be blended transparently or replaced with icons or solid color backgrounds in subsections to avoid overload.  \n    - Color palette alignment is critical: dark blue must match Ponsse’s existing brand blue, with teal and yellow accents carefully balanced to avoid confusion with competitor Jane.  \n    - These refinements aim to create a cleaner, more focused visual hierarchy supporting brand differentiation.  \n    - A limit of around four rotating hero banners is planned to keep user experience smooth without overwhelming content.\n\n## **Content Strategy and Navigation Structure**\n\nThe content organization and navigation will be redesigned to clarify product offerings and streamline user journeys for different banking services.\n\n- **Christina proposed separating personal banking, mortgages, and business banking into distinct navigation sections to avoid any division feeling secondary** (24:30)  \n    - Personal banking will include deposits and mortgages with clear calls to action.  \n    - Business banking will be highlighted equally to reflect its importance to executives and clients.  \n    - Ponce Bank Direct, offering limited products like CDs and SBA loans, will have a distinct callout or microsite to avoid confusion with full-service banking.  \n    - This approach ensures all client segments feel prioritized and find relevant information easily.\n\n- **A dedicated promotions and campaigns page will centralize all special offers and terms, reducing clutter and disclosure issues on the homepage** (27:10)  \n    - This page will serve as a landing spot for calls to action related to marketing campaigns.  \n    - The structure will replicate best practices from previous successful implementations at MCU for clarity and compliance.  \n    - Separating promotions supports easier updates and better user focus on core banking products.  \n    - This plan anticipates smoother marketing execution and regulatory alignment.\n\n- **Dynamic rate tables will be built so that updates propagate automatically site-wide, avoiding manual changes across multiple pages** (28:50)  \n    - This will allow a 4% or other rate updates to be managed in one place.  \n    - The system design follows existing structures for product-specific disclosures and digital banking sections.  \n    - Dynamic content management improves accuracy and reduces manual errors.  \n    - It enhances customer trust by ensuring current rates display consistently.\n\n- **Navigation menus will include a “super nav” to house extra buttons without crowding the interface, improving user clarity** (29:55)  \n    - Hover menus will showcase featured promotions or key products tailored to each audience segment.  \n    - Ponce Bank Direct will likely be nested under digital services to maintain brand clarity.  \n    - This layered navigation supports intuitive discovery across diverse banking products.  \n    - It aligns with user expectations for quick access to relevant info.\n\n## **Technical Integration and Data Management**\n\nThe website will integrate with HubSpot and other tools to streamline data handling, personalization, and location management.\n\n- **HubSpot is confirmed as the primary system for contact record management and location data, simplifying updates across platforms** (07:05)  \n    - HubSpot integration will allow centralized input of branch hours and locations feeding into the website.  \n    - This replaces fragmented management currently spread across multiple third-party platforms.  \n    - Leveraging HubSpot’s listing structure could improve accuracy and reduce manual workload.  \n    - Integration supports future scalability and data consistency.\n\n- **Localization efforts require building local pages that dynamically reflect accurate hours, events, and team information** (35:55)  \n    - Local content will be sourced from HubSpot or similar centralized tools to ensure consistency.  \n    - These pages will feature secure, well-designed forms with CAPTCHA to maintain data integrity.  \n    - The approach addresses the challenge of user-generated incorrect information on external sites.  \n    - It supports better customer engagement with community-specific content.\n\n- **Future phases may include embedding buyer’s intent tracking to identify companies visiting the website for sales leverage** (37:30)  \n    - This HubSpot feature tracks web visitors like Bank of America to support targeted outreach.  \n    - It requires embedding specialized code into the website.  \n    - Victor Garcia suggested this as a Q2 implementation to enhance sales intelligence.  \n    - This capability could improve lead generation and conversion rates.\n\n- **Personalization options like greeting users by name on the homepage are planned to enhance user experience** (33:28)  \n    - This builds on the investment in HubSpot’s CRM capabilities.  \n    - Location-specific images and content will improve relevance and engagement.  \n    - These features will be balanced with fallback content to maintain broad usability.  \n    - Personalization aims to deepen customer connection and loyalty.\n\n## **Project Management and Next Steps**\n\nThe team is aligned on next deliverables, timelines, and stakeholder engagement to secure executive buy-in and ensure smooth rollout.\n\n- **Christina requested a revamped homepage mockup focusing on main navigation, hero, placeholders, and footer to present to investor relations and foundation teams** (30:37)  \n    - This version will be a visual draft, not fully built, to facilitate early feedback.  \n    - A similar approach is planned for the careers section to show consistency.  \n    - The goal is to gain executive buy-in before proceeding with broader builds.  \n    - Colin and Yugi will coordinate delivery by Friday and communicate timelines.\n\n- **Additional rounds of homepage and microsite refinements are expected based on ongoing executive feedback** (17:05)  \n    - Christina plans to secure in-person walkthrough sessions with Betty and other leaders to improve understanding.  \n    - This aims to reduce disconnect and build consensus around brand direction.  \n    - Feedback cycles will focus on balancing content, design, and audience needs.  \n    - The iterative process supports a stronger final product.\n\n- **Marketing campaigns for Ponce Bank Direct are planned for spring, but the current lack of an ads account is a barrier** (41:30)  \n    - Colin is actively pursuing Google support for account recovery, emailing every three days.  \n    - Christina will begin preparing internal teams for email campaigns and social channel reconnections.  \n    - The sunset of Constant Contact is planned in favor of HubSpot-driven communications.  \n    - These steps support a coordinated go-to-market strategy aligned with the website launch.\n\n- **The team agreed to cancel the regular follow-up meeting as key topics were covered, signaling readiness to focus on next deliverables** (42:25)  \n    - This reflects confidence in current progress and clarity on immediate priorities.  \n    - The team will synchronize internally and provide updates as needed.  \n    - This decision streamlines communication and frees resources for implementation.  \n    - It underscores efficient project management practices.","outline":null,"keywords":["Ponce Bank","Website Design","HubSpot Integration","Brochure Feedback","Buyer’s Intent","Local Market Imagery"],"overview":"- **Website Redesign Focus:** Prioritize modern simplicity and brand cohesion, balancing line drawings and stock images for clarity.\n\n- **Audience Segmentation:** Tailor homepage content for four main segments: consumer, community, investor relations, and recruiting to improve messaging.\n\n- **Visual Updates Needed:** Use current visuals, enhance local relevance, and diversify representation to better resonate with audiences.\n\n- **Content Organization Improvement:** Create distinct navigation for personal and business banking to clarify services and enhance user experience.\n\n- **HubSpot Integration:** Centralize data management for branch locations, ensuring accurate and consistent customer information across platforms.\n\n- **Next Steps Agreed:** Revamp homepage mockup for executive feedback, refine microsites, and prepare marketing campaigns for a coordinated rollout.","action_items":"\n**Christina Zanca**\nProvide additional brochure and sales sheet feedback post-team review this week (06:56)\nCoordinate internal alignment to gain executive buy-in on homepage design iterations (40:20)\nIdentify teams to involve for upcoming email campaigns and social channel reconnections (41:45)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nConfirm receipt and loading of contact records in HubSpot (07:05)\nDeliver a revamped Ponce Bank homepage mockup including main nav, hero placeholders, and footer for investor relations and foundation review (31:39)\nSync and incorporate feedback into all designed pages, including preparing updated brochure and website assets for Friday or later date (40:26)\nContinue communications and follow-up with Google user support for ads account activation (41:13)\nSend updates on test contact loading and HubSpot integration status (41:13)\n\n**Victor Garcia**\nIntroduce buyer’s intent feature discussion for potential Q2 phase launch, explaining data tracking benefits to sales team (37:36)\n"},"duration":42.93000030517578,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"victor garcia"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"christinazanca"},{"id":3,"name":"christinazanca"},{"id":4,"name":"Guille Santana"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Good morning.","index":0,"end_time":209.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.8,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":1,"end_time":210.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":210.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Colin.","index":2,"end_time":214.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":213.92,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Where are you located again?","index":3,"end_time":215.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.36,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Maryland.","index":4,"end_time":216.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":215.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, so y'' all got.","index":5,"end_time":218.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.12,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Y'' all got what we got?","index":6,"end_time":219.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.12,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, we.","index":7,"end_time":220.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":219.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we''re at, like, 13 inches.","index":8,"end_time":221.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it sounds about right for us as well.","index":9,"end_time":226.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.12,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":10,"end_time":227.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.2,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Meanwhile, Guiller''s enjoying beautiful hot weather.","index":11,"end_time":233.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.28,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":12,"end_time":234.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":233.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"In lovely Mexico, Right?","index":13,"end_time":236.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.38,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":14,"end_time":239.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":236.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That was.","index":15,"end_time":240.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"It''s okay, though.","index":16,"end_time":242.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":242.06,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"You guys don''t have the luxury of wearing beautiful heavy coats.","index":17,"end_time":245.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":242.9,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Right, Right.","index":18,"end_time":248.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":246.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":19,"end_time":249.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":249.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sometimes I wish we had, like, snow days here.","index":20,"end_time":252.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":249.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Come to New York, spend a weekend in New York.","index":21,"end_time":256.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":253.5,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Now.","index":22,"end_time":256.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.06,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I have some friends there.","index":23,"end_time":259.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":257.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They went on vacation and they''re not having a good time.","index":24,"end_time":263.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":259.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I have two things.","index":25,"end_time":266.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.99,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I, I wish I could just.","index":26,"end_time":268.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.43,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I, I love my seasons.","index":27,"end_time":270.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.99,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I love seasons because my wife wants to move to Florida.","index":28,"end_time":274.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":270.43,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I think Florida is another country.","index":29,"end_time":276.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.99,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I don''t think it shouldn''t exist as a part of the United States, but they don''t have seasons.","index":30,"end_time":282.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.99,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"It''s just really, really hot and then mildly.","index":31,"end_time":287.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.91,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Okay.","index":32,"end_time":288.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":287.45,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"I like variety.","index":33,"end_time":291.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.01,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yep.","index":34,"end_time":294.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":294.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yep.","index":35,"end_time":294.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":294.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s funny.","index":36,"end_time":299.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":298.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It.","index":37,"end_time":311.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":311.67,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Let me see if Christine is actually going to be joining us.","index":38,"end_time":356.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.48,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"There she is.","index":39,"end_time":364.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.77,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":40,"end_time":368.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":368.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":41,"end_time":371.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you?","index":42,"end_time":372.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":371.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Trying to stay warm.","index":43,"end_time":374.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, God.","index":44,"end_time":376.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":375.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Are you still sick or are you feeling a little better?","index":45,"end_time":378.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":376.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I, I, I don''t know if I got myself sick again playing out there with my daughter, but.","index":46,"end_time":382.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":378.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, geez.","index":47,"end_time":383.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":383.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":48,"end_time":384.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":383.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":49,"end_time":384.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":384.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, yeah, it''s like 13 inches of snow here.","index":50,"end_time":386.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":384.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was just telling Victor.","index":51,"end_time":387.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, man.","index":52,"end_time":388.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":387.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":53,"end_time":388.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":388.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, we got quite a few inches as well.","index":54,"end_time":390.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":388.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And now I have the kids home with me today, and they''re like, wait.","index":55,"end_time":393.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":390.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Are we going outside?","index":56,"end_time":394.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":393.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I just want to lose my mind.","index":57,"end_time":396.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":394.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But, yeah, it''s all good.","index":58,"end_time":398.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":396.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":59,"end_time":401.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":400.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think today''s focus is website feedback.","index":60,"end_time":403.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":401.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Am I right or is this our regular meeting?","index":61,"end_time":405.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":403.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I know I asked for a website.","index":62,"end_time":407.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":405.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Feedback meeting, so let me know tomorrow.","index":63,"end_time":409.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.14,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"But we don''t have anything.","index":64,"end_time":412.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.82,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"We could do that today as well.","index":65,"end_time":414.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.3,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":66,"end_time":415.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":414.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Most of the stuff for HubSpot, in my opinion, they''re already handling.","index":67,"end_time":419.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":416.02,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"The only thing that I want to confirm is just to make sure that you guys receive that email with contact records.","index":68,"end_time":423.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":419.58,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"Yeah, they''re being loaded in.","index":69,"end_time":426.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":425.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re good to go then.","index":70,"end_time":427.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":426.94,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"On.","index":71,"end_time":428.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":427.9,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"On the HubSpot side.","index":72,"end_time":429.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428.18,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"All right, so then maybe what we do.","index":73,"end_time":432.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":430.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Let me just give you a quick background, and in the, in the midst of that, if you guys can pull up the website, you know, samples.","index":74,"end_time":440.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":433.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I''m meeting with the team this week to go over the brochures and the sales sheets, so I should have feedback on those overall.","index":75,"end_time":448.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":442.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Betty loved the them.","index":76,"end_time":450,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":448.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The, The Layouts, the direction.","index":77,"end_time":451.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":450,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"She just had a little bit of an issue kind of wrapping her head around the balance of, and, and kind.","index":78,"end_time":459.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":451.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Of the segue between the, the line.","index":79,"end_time":463.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":459.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Drawings in the background with the stock photography overlaid.","index":80,"end_time":468.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":463.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so she likes the one that has like the squiggle where it has the, the image of like stock image and then a clear like separation between.","index":81,"end_time":481.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The, the line drawing and that is.","index":82,"end_time":484.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":481.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m talking about the brochure piece.","index":83,"end_time":487.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":484.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like if you can go back to the brochure and look at that, I think there''s opportunity for, when we design to have these work together, but not necessarily like on top of each other.","index":84,"end_time":504.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":488.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think it''s, it''s becoming like a little bit too much and like image overkill.","index":85,"end_time":510.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":504.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":86,"end_time":510.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":510.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so when she thinks about like modern simplicity, it''s like if we''re using a line drawing, like let''s use a line drawing.","index":87,"end_time":520.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":511.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If we''re using a stock image, it''s okay to use a stock image.","index":88,"end_time":524.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":520.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like we don''t have to as the brand evolves.","index":89,"end_time":527.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":524.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Used both of those treatments simultaneously.","index":90,"end_time":530.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe sometimes it makes sense to do it, but I think that we are using them simultaneously too much.","index":91,"end_time":536.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":530.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think that that was the only feedback that she got.","index":92,"end_time":539.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":537.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, hold on.","index":93,"end_time":540.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":539.54,"speaker_name":"victor garcia"},{"text":"So now we can bring the website up and like I said, I''ll give you more feedback on the brochures and the placemats.","index":94,"end_time":547.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":541.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I, I think it''s only going to be more content than you know, than, than designs.","index":95,"end_time":554.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":547.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think that we''re good in that place.","index":96,"end_time":555.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":554.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So a couple of things that I.","index":97,"end_time":561.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Want you guys to think about right as you''re, as you''re designing.","index":98,"end_time":564.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":561.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"One, we are going to have the three distinct or maybe four distinct kind of positioning because we have the audiences on the consumer side we have and consumer is broken out into like business, consumer and, and retail.","index":99,"end_time":586.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":566.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then we have on the community side.","index":100,"end_time":589.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":587.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":101,"end_time":589.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":589.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And that kind of encompasses foundation.","index":102,"end_time":592.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":590.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We have audiences for investor relations.","index":103,"end_time":595.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":593.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s the investor relations side obviously.","index":104,"end_time":599.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":597.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then we have audiences for staffing and recruiting.","index":105,"end_time":603.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":599.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So as you think about developing kind.","index":106,"end_time":608.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":604.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Of the, the future digital experience for.","index":107,"end_time":610.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":608.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Ponsse, you have to think about those AUD and kind of which brand treatments are going to make sense for that.","index":108,"end_time":617.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":610.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":109,"end_time":618.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":617.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So what''s happening with the homepage is that, and I knew this was going to happen and I kind of caveated that with Betty.","index":110,"end_time":625.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Executives were looking at it like, well, how is it going to be translated for high profile commercial.","index":111,"end_time":632.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":626.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What about employees?","index":112,"end_time":634.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":633.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, it''s leading too far community.","index":113,"end_time":639.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":635.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like we''re getting a Lot of those things.","index":114,"end_time":641.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":639.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so I think what we can do is I''ll give you.","index":115,"end_time":647.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":642.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And.","index":116,"end_time":647.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":647.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And we can just focus on the.","index":117,"end_time":649.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":647.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The version that you shared me in the beginning.","index":118,"end_time":651.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":649.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We can get into some of the.","index":119,"end_time":653.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_tim